name: Room in Cool Deco Apartment in Brunswick East
summary: A large air conditioned room with queen spring mattress bed in a vintage apartment. Located right outside is a tram to the city just 19 minutes away. This area is known for its arts culture, live music, cafes and international food.
space: The apartment is Deco/Edwardian in style and has polished floorboards and ornate ceilings and wooden blinds. Your room is large sized, has polished floorboards, a Queen sized spring mattress bed and vintage furniture. The rest of the flat also vintage style with 1940's style tiled bathroom with a shower bath, a groovy little kitchen and a deco style lounge room with vintage furniture and bric a brac. The flat is located next to two major public transport routes. Tram 96 is just 30 metres away and takes you south to the city centre in 15-20 minutes or all the way to St Kilda beach in 45 minutes. Bus stops take you east to Bundoora and west to Pacoevale. The Lygon Street tram line that goes past Melbourne University is 10 minutes walk west and Sydney Road and its great thrift stores, middle eastern foods and a fashion district is within 20 minutes walk. Taxi to/from Airport takes 25-30mins and 50-$60. Traffic sounds are normal for a room next to a main street but minimised by double wind

neighborhood_overview: This hip area is a crossroads between two great cultural strips of inner Northern Melbourne.  Located in East Brunswick, between High St, Northcote and Lygon St Brunswick you have the choice of some of Melbourne's best budget dining and cool bars. Restaurants range from cheap eateries to quality Lebanese and Turkish with Indian, Greek, Italian and Thai places. Around the corner Ceres Environmental Centre is set on reclaimed parkland next to Merri creek and it's convenient bike paths. Ceres has a daily organic foods market and two cafes with outdoor and indoor dining. They also have a bike shed where you can buy a second hand bike cheap - or take your own to work on. There are three coffee places within 50metres, and the Lomond Hotel Pub right across the road has good live music and there's also a pizza place downstairs.
notes: Due to Airbnb policies I don’t accept bookings made for other people. If it is not you actually staying then please do not book.
transit: Easy transport options - the tram is right outside.
access: Wifi. Bathroom and kitchen is shared but I mostly shower at the swimming pool and use the downstairs toilet as much as I can.
interaction: I'm home mostly but sometimes I may be working when you arrive so there will be directions for you to enter if I am not there.
house_rules: Theres a yoga studio downstairs so if you see shoes out then please keep noise to a minimum :)
host_about: As an artist working in animation and video I am involved in many community related projects. I manage a Yoga studio at this address, downstairs from the flat. I really enjoy Yoga, good food, good company and getting out into the sunshine whenever I can. Melbourne is a great city of arts and music - there's always something on and my flat is in a great location between Brunswick and Northcote, two suburbs with many arts warehouses and venues. Please be aware that the apartment is old yet has a funky vibe - think Berlin - it is not for those who want spick and span modern hotel style accommodation.

Number of guests staying limited to maximum number allowed in property and as confirmed and paid for in airbnb. Where bedding options offered, such as king beds or king single beds, you must request your preference at time of booking. Where extra bedding offered, no extra bedding provided if number of guests staying is property standard occupancy, unless extra bedding is requested and paid for by you in airbnb at time of booking. Bedding preferences / extra bedding can not be guaranteed. SELF CHECK IN FROM 3PM / SELF CHECK-OUT TO 10AM Following information available in AIRBNB APP after 48  hours of booking: - PROPERTY ADDRESS and MAP - SELF CHECK-IN/OUT
host_about:
Thanks for reading our profile. 

We've been hosting since 2009 and love It!

And when time permits, we also love travelling!

We've been partnering with property owners since 2009, when we established a2c, our complete turnkey short stay property management and co-hosting service.

If you're a property owner and interested in tapping into our considerable experience and expertise, then feel free to get in touch to discuss our property management and airbnb co-hosting services, and we'll be happy to assist!

We pride ourselves in offering an exceptional collection of unique, highly rated, hand selected homes, in the best inner city Melbourne locations, super clean and beautifully furnished, with airbnb guests in mind.

Exceeding guest expectations is what we’re about.

As hosts, we look forward to welcoming you, and making your experience unforgettable.

As guests, we'll always be respectful of both you and your home, and look forward to sharing the experience!

Best,
The a2c Team

name: CLOSE TO CITY & MELBOURNE AIRPORT
summary: Easy to travel from and to the Airport; quiet and safe neighbourhood; a spacious and sunny room; backyard for sun baking; a friendly host who are easy going and super friendly! I would like to make your journey more comfortable!
space: My place is great for guest from overseas, interstate or want to live in northern suburbs. If you like live in CBD, this one is not for you, if you are looking for someplace that is between airport and city, have free places to park your car, and like a spacious and quite place for some privacy, or not in rush and happy to travel 30 minutes on the train to city(like us local people do) , it is the perfect place for you. Recently, we have upgraded lighting to LED ceiling lights with adjustable lighting in the bedrooms, we have bought new queen size bed to make the guest room more comfortable.   The guest bedrooms provided here for your comfort is in a two bedroom unit with 100sqm backyard(my green garden). This bedroom is airy and bright with big windows. Your room has a queen size bed and a build in wardrobe, good mattress, good cotton bedding and linen, and room is often decorated with fresh roses from my garden. Bathroom and kitchen are kept in 70's style with colourful tiles .  All

neighborhood_overview: The neighbours are quiet and friendly,  please don't park the car on my driveway because one of our neighbours is doing shifting work as a nurse. There are plenty of space for parking in the guest parking bay and along the street for free.
notes: My mum and Daa's hearing is a bit weak, so please feel free to raise your voice to talk to her. She loves it!
transit: 8-10 minutes walk to local train station, and half hour train ride you will be in city CBD.  Melbourne is a big city, if you don't live in CBD, then train or bus will be the main public transportation.  You can borrow our spare MYKI card to get around for around $8 a day unlimited travel on public transport. If you drive, it is about 15-20 minutes trip from and to Airport, and 30 minutes  (13kms)trip to City.
access: You have access all facilities in the house, I open my home to you! The price is for accommodation and facilities, I do provide tea, coffee and milk to make coffees,  also dish washing liquid and washing machine liquid just to make your travel easier. If you like to have home cooked Chinese meals like fried rice or dumplings, or use of telephone, I am happy to provide with extra charges. As you can understand, they are not included in the price quoted here.
interaction: The amazing thing about being the host is the privilege to be part of some strangers life for a short period of time :-)  I don't live in the house with you, but only 2kms away and more than happy to help if anything you need assistance.
house_rules: I m here to host, you are here to enjoy! Please enjoy the place and treat it as your own home.
host_about: We all travellers on this planet, if my place can provide you a peaceful sleep at night during your trip, then the pleasure is entirely mine!

name: Tranquil Javanese-Style Apartment in Oakleigh East
summary: Study the exquisite detail of the antique Javanese garden wall, or meditate beside the calming fishpond. BBQ on the huge covered deck, also a perfect place for catching some morning rays. Or settle back with a book from the well-stocked shelves.
space: Welcome to Melbourne! The Studio A fully self contained studio apartment within the grounds of a spacious suburban home block, this is a delightful and tranquil setting. Rental includes:  use of the undercover decking with bar-b-que, gas heater or portable air-con and surround  sound music/DVD system looking out to a lovely rear garden with pond and Antique hand carved teak Javanese walled storage shed. Also on the deck is a clothes dryer for the winter months where drying washing is a difficulty. The apartment itself offers reverse cycle climate control, Flat screen HD LCD TV, DVD Player, full insulation, modern shower and toilet facility, washing machine, its own kitchen and dining nook along with all one needs for a short stay in the wonderful SE suburbs of Melbourne. Wireless Internet connection is available for your use. The raised bedroom area has an adequate wardrobe and medium/firm double bed with high quality bedding and dual control electric blanket. If you are thinking of having visitors while you stay for a BBQ or just relaxing on the enclosed deck watching TV or listening to the Stereo - It's all there for your enjoyment
interaction: The apartment is situated at the rear of the private house block of land. Access is via the driveway. I live within the main house and you are welcome to entertain family and friends of your choosing within the large interconnected rear deck area. Your stay can be as private as you wish. Your space is yours to enjoy and any interaction with myself is entirely your choice.
house_rules: This is a private and peaceful opportunity that I am offering to share with you. When you come to stay please be respectful of all that is offered and treat it within the bounds of normal social decency. Leave as you find and If there is anything that is, within reason, an issue,  please raise it immediately so I can hopefully rectify the matter. It is my strong desire that you will enjoy your stay, recommend the apartment to friends or hopefully come again .
host_about: Being a 'Baby Boomer' has given me a life full of amazing experiences and this posting has proved itself as yet another adventure. I am well travelled, liberally minded, have a wonderful partner, young in heart and mind, in fine health, enjoy friendly company, a grandfather to 3 lovely boys & 2 wonderful girls , and enjoy my work managing a hollow chocolate moulding factory.

name: Queen Room in Beautiful House
summary: Light filled private room with Queen bed tastefully decorated with desk, lamps and roll down shutters - to keep you cool in summer and dark for sleep.  Situated right at the back of the house and down the passage way the room is quiet and private.
space: Luxury spacious accommodation at an affordable price which is friendly, clean, safe and secure. This stunning property is located in the heart of Frankston on the Mornington Peninsula. Close to beaches, wineries, shops, hospitals and universities. Public transport at the end of the street (approx 1 hr to Melbourne CBD) freeway direct to the city is 2 mins away. Grocery shops, post office and community coffee shops all within 5 mins walk. The Private room is tastefully furnished with a queen size bed, desk, lamps and built in robes.  The house is huge with 3 toilets, 2 bathrooms and a beautiful warm amazing living area - ducted heating for winter and airconditioning for summer. All linen,towels,Internet access and off street parking provided. Would suit professionals, visitors to the area or anyone requiring "quality" short term accommodation.  . name: Très Charming in Fabulous Richmond
summary: As Melbourne's longest-running host, I pride myself on value, communication and comfort. I go out of my way to make sure each booking is seamless. Quality linen, beautiful furniture and in an excellent location. This apartment has charm, style and everything you'd need for a fantastic stay, whether it's for business, leisure or a romantic getaway. This cosy little flat has hosted 600+ people from all over the world and absolutely loved it!
space: 100% of proceeds from this Airbnb listing go towards the running of the charity that I founded in 2013. So you can feel like a hero and stay at Melbourne's original Airbnb at the same time! With the CBD just 3km away (either a short tram trip, bike ride or lovely half-hour walk), Richmond is the best place to experience Melbourne. The apartment is surrounded by cafes, restaurant and shopping strips (Bridge Road, Swan Street, Victoria Street), shops, boutiques, bars and pubs. Full of natural light, in a very well-maintained building, the apartment is filled with classic antique and vintage pieces.  The guest room is bright and well-furnished, and guests are provided with towels and locally-made organic soaps. We have lots of local guide books, booklets and maps. There's kitchen cupboard space for guests who want to do some of their own cooking, and you're welcome to our impressive array of condiments. If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to ask.

neighborhood_overview: Bridge Road (once famous for discount shopping, now known more for cafes and restaurants) is literally at the doorstep, then Victoria Street ('Little Saigon' - the best Vietnamese and Chinese cuisine outside of Asia) is just a few blocks away, as is Swan Street (the grungier side of Richmond with great pubs, cool bars, live gigs and sports fans from the MCG). The three strips are parallel - needless to say we have loads of great places to recommend - check out the Guidebook in the profile. Supermarkets, convenience stores, delis, chemists, specialty produce shops, liquor stores are scattered all throughout the vicinity. Opposite the famous Melbourne Cricket Ground is AAMI Park, the Melbourne Tennis Centre and Olympic Park - hosting almost every sport you can imagine between them.
notes: Good Apps to download are:  * TramTracker  * Zomato  (and obviously G**gle Maps if you haven't already!)
transit: There are two tram lines right outside the apartment on Bridge Road, both of which take you directly into the city. Extremely conveniently, the #48 tram will take you to/from the Melbourne Airport shuttle (SkyBus) and the #75 to Etihad stadium. On a sunny day, I prefer to stroll into the city - virtually a straight line down Bridge Road, past the iconic Melbourne Cricket Ground, through the beautiful Fitzroy Gardens (home to Captain Cook's Cottage and the gorgeous Conservatory). It takes about 30-40 mins but is an excellent way to see Melbourne. The tram to St Kilda (which goes along the entirety of renowned shopper's delight Chapel Street) stops a 5-minute walk from our door, and the very cool Fitzroy and Collingwood neighbourhoods are just the other side of Victoria Street - a few kms away. That's where you'll find an abundance of galleries, cafes, artists haunts and the amazing Abbotsford Convent (yoga, vegetarian social experimental restaurant, markets, outdoor cinema, beautiful ga
access: - courtyard - unlimited wifi - tea/coffee/sugar/milk/Vegemite etc - kitchen and laundry facilities (Global kitchen knives, Analon cookware) - hairdryer
interaction: I will be contactable immediately (via phone or email) if need be, but the space is very self-explanatory. I have a local contact if I'm out of the country for any urgent issues (but with over 600 guests and no problems, I like my odds!).
house_rules: The place isn't really child-friendly, so children - as much as we love them - aren't able to stay. The hot water system is smaller than that of a house, as it's an apartment. Be aware that if you have a full bore water pressure shower, the hot water will probably only last 10 minutes, which should be more than enough. Water restrictions have been very strict in Melbourne over the past decade but I would hope that my kind of guests are conscientious of water wastage regardless! All we ask is that you respect our home, as you would expect of visitors in your own home. Easy. Also; if you're going to eat whilst in the apartment, please don't do it in the bedroom (especially on the bed). There's a dining table that's perfect for eating at!
host_about:
I'm 33, open-minded, friendly and reliable. I took my time acquiring a double degree in International Business/Japanese and am now kept pretty busy directing a charity that I founded in 2013. I have lived in lots of different cities around the world and experienced a host of very different living arrangements (pun always intended), so I was pretty well accustomed to this gig before Airbnb even existed.

I like to run, travel, appreciate art, shop, wine, dine, learn Spanish (my wife is Mexican) and love a good board game. I get my kicks from real-life auctions, discovering exotic fruits and vegetables at my weekend farmers market, and meeting interesting people.

name: Central City Warehouse Apartment
summary: The absolute centre of Melbourne, this converted, open-plan warehouse is full of natural light and loads of character. Easy walking distance to all points in the city as well as Southbank, Docklands, Carlton and Fitzroy. One of a kind laneway experience and Rankins Lane is becoming one of the most interesting laneways with pop-ups and hidden businesses in the upper levels. Parties, events and gatherings of any kind are not permitted.
space: One-of-a-kind warehouse conversion in an unbeatable city location for shoppers, foodies and culture lovers. CAR PARKING - This is the centre of the city so only short term metered street parking or commercial car parks are available within the block from Bourke Square Parking and The Strand Car Park. However, I have a private car park on Elizabeth Street three blocks away that I can make available for rent if required for stays of longer than two nights. This needs to be pre-arranged and suits those driving to the city but not wanting to drive every day during their stay. And it's only $30 per night. See a video of this apartment on the Sydney Weekender website when it was featured by AirBnB. Search for AirBnB and Melbourne and it should come up. My apartment is located seconds from the official centre of Melbourne, yet it's in a quiet lane with excellent natural light. It's big, over 100sqm of space. neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in the centre of Melbourne, not just the CBD but the actual middle of everything. Plus it is in a laneway, one of Melbourne's most beloved features with two excellent cafes, one at each end.
notes: The spa function of the bath tub does not work.
transit: Yes, minutes to trains, trams and buses but most places are an easy walk including Fitzroy, the Queen Victoria Market, MCG, Docklands and the convention centre. There is no train service between the airport and the city but the Skybus leaves every 10 minutes and stops just 15 minutes walk away. Skybus offers a shuttle service to city hotels so if you don't feel like the walk tell them you're staying at City Garden Hotel on Little Bourke St which is just 50 metres from the apartment. Skybus tickets can be purchased online in advance which I recommend to avoid queuing. It's sad watching the bus leave while you're waiting to buy a ticket.
access: Guests have full access to the apartment but are requested to avoid the upper level of the rooftop where the bee hives are kept.
interaction: Interaction at their initiation.
house_rules: Whatever gets taken up to the roof must be brought down. Special care needs to be taken to ensure that nothing is left that can block the drains. Do not open the door behind the ladder. No smoking.
host_about:
Melbourne girl, business owner, publisher, traveller, wannabe gardener and dog owner (but not).

I make guides to bar and restaurants in a deck of cards format under my brand Luckie Guides - @Luckieinc on (Hidden by Airbnb) and my guests are always given a set of guides.

Current mission: Pursuing a luxe minimalist approach to life. The pursuit of great life experiences over acquisition of stuff. Digitising photos, music, movies, documents and getting rid of stuff. 

As a guest I'm super low maintenance. I'll be happy with a the wifi password and a place to sleep. And chances are I'll have a big list of underground places to visit before I even arrive.

name: Stay in lovely bayside Elwood!
summary: Relax in a colourful, older style character filled apartment in a leafy, bayside suburb that has great access to the city/CBD.
space: Close to bayside beaches, public transport and cafes, the apartment is a two-bedroom ground-floor flat built in the early 1900s, in the leafy Melbourne bayside suburb of Elwood.  It has unusually high ceilings, large windows and natural wooden floorboards. The lounge and bedrooms have plenty of light whatever the season.  The kitchen is modern. It features a drawer dishwasher, new stove, slim silver fridge, wooden floor and yellow and blue walls. It is well-equipped with a lot of quality cooking utensils and quirky crockery and cooking in it is fun. The apartment has a high-speed internet connection which guests can use for free - please consider subsequent guests however and don't download heavily. I have no TV, by choice. Lots of music though, with a stereo in the lounge and a lovely retro-posh radio in kitchen. And quite a few books and games (monopoly, scrabble, backgammon etc), not to mention books (especially art books).  The flat is light-filled and airy with relaxing, colourful

neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is a highlight! Elwood is the green, quieter, graceful partner of St Kilda (St Kilda is bars and pubs such as the famous Esplanade Hotel and the Prince of Wales hotel, Luna Park, Salt Sea Baths, Fairy Penguins at the end of the St Kilda Pier, restaurants and cafes, street life, backpackers), Balaclava (grocery shopping, community life, cafes, restaurants, library, Jewish community), Ripponlea (quaint shops and train station, orthodox Jewish community), …….Elwood is characterised by its green leafy streets, close to bay, close to funky shopping areas, multicultural (European mainly), parks, close to St Kilda. It is getting increasingly rich but there are also many apartment dwellers who rent which keeps the neighbourhood interesting. Close to multiple public transport options. My favourite parts of Elwood are walking around the tree lined streets of eclectic architecture, the stroll down to Elwood beach and the community life of Carlisle St in Balaclava.
notes: I have been really impressed by Airbnb guests - always had lovely, interesting and respectful guests. My philosophy is that generosity begets generosity. Please leave the apartment just as you found it.
transit: Tram, train, bus and cycle paths are all on hand. The  numbers 67 and 3 tram are at your doorstep, the 246 bus is a little further. The Sandringham train line has two nearby train stations within 7-10 minute walk - Ripponlea and Balaclava. I generally cycle into the city if its good weather - it's just one road along Brighton Road which becomes St Kilda road with a bike path straight into the city. Parking is on the street and free - so you can leave your car there and head off on foot or other means. It's a safe area - I have never had any trouble with leaving my car in the street. The flat is a 30- 45 min drive ( traffic dependent) from the airport. A taxi will cost $50 - 65 depending again on traffic. Best option in terms of arriving is the Sky Bus (about $18) to the city or St Kilda directly (though check the times as it doesn't run after 7pm). If you have little luggage, a Sandringham train to Ripponlea station then a 10 min walk to the flat...Public transport travel in Melbourne
access: The whole apartment will be yours. One bedroom is only used for Airbnb. The other bedroom is mine and will have my personal things in it so if you are more than one person or a couple you need to feel comfortable with that.  Regarding the kitchen - please help yourself to dry foodstuffs (I have lots of spices and herbs) and anything in the fridge. Please note that I don't buy food especially for guests (milk, bread etc) as I try to keep the fee low and work load down and also generally folks now are so particular with what they eat and I don't like to see food go to waste.  Nearby supermarkets  - the closest (7 min) is 168 Tennyson Street. Larger supermarkets are on Carlisle Street in Balaclava (Coles and a small Safeway) and Safeway on Acland St, St Kilda. They are all a 10 - 15 minute walk away. There are a lot of Farmer's Markets in the area - all on a Saturday. (Hidden by Airbnb) The Elwood Farmers Market, the Peanut Farm Market and the St Kilda Primary School Market. The closest p
interaction: You will be interacting online.
house_rules: Please strip the beds of linen and place in the washing machine, with towels, before you leave and put them in the washing machine and put it on. This way you will know if you have left anything precious of yours at the bottom of the bed and it will help the cleaner as they can hang out the washing as soon as they get there. If you can also put kitchen linen in that would be great. If anything is broken please let me know. Thank you! Guests who are respectful of a space, open and friendly and who look after other's things are great guests! No smoking in the apartment, porch or garden. Absolutely no parties. I’m close with my neighbors and they keep an eye on the flat for me.
host_about: Easy going, considerate house guest and host. I like art, social justice, happiness, architecture, film, design, ideas, cooking, laughing, being in nature, passion, travel, people, solitude, beauty...

neighborhood_overview: A stay at our hip apartment will mean you can enjoy some of Melbourne’s best restaurants, bars, cafes, shopping, and night life, all at your doorstep! With easy access to major venues such as the MCG, Hisense, AAMI Arena and Rod Laver Arena – home of the Australian Open – and the hip shopping and restaurants of Bridge Road and Swan Street. Leave the apartment, head north and in minutes you’ll find yourself in Bridge Road, home to brand name fashion outlets, cafes and restaurants. A trip into the CBD is just one stop away by train, or a short tram ride. Head south and you’ll be in Swan Street. Home to many pubs and clubs, supermarkets, restaurants and hip independent stores. This apartment is close to everything Melbourne has to offer. The place to stay on your next Melbourne visit! Our apartment is also only minutes away from Epworth Hospital.
notes: 1 set of keys. No luggage storage before/after stay. Ground floor apartment. Permissible sized hot water tank that requires time to reheat water between use, especially between showers. Number of guests staying limited to maximum number allowed in property and as confirmed and paid for in airbnb. Where bedding options offered, such as king beds or king single beds, you must request your preference at time of booking. Where extra bedding offered, no extra bedding provided if number of guests staying is property standard occupancy, unless extra bedding is requested and paid for by you in airbnb at time of booking. Bedding preferences / extra bedding can not be guaranteed. SELF CHECK IN FROM 3PM / SELF CHECK-OUT TO 10AM Following information available in AIRBNB APP after 48  hours of booking: - PROPERTY ADDRESS and MAP - SELF CHECK-IN/OUT
host_about:
Thanks for reading our profile. 

We've been hosting since 2009 and love It!

And when time permits, we also love travelling!

We've been partnering with property owners since 2009, when we established a2c, our complete turnkey short stay property management and co-hosting service.

If you're a property owner and interested in tapping into our considerable experience and expertise, then feel free to get in touch to discuss our property management and airbnb co-hosting services, and we'll be happy to assist!

We pride ourselves in offering an exceptional collection of unique, highly rated, hand selected homes, in the best inner city Melbourne locations, super clean and beautifully furnished, with airbnb guests in mind.

Exceeding guest expectations is what we’re about.

As hosts, we look forward to welcoming you, and making your experience unforgettable.

As guests, we'll always be respectful of both you and your home, and look forward to sharing the experience!

Best,
The a2c Team

name: Large Bayside suburban house
summary: Ideal location for a family - close to the beach, great local community, only 20 minutes to the City.
space: This is a modern family home comprising of 4 bedrooms (main bedroom with ensuite and king bed, second bedroom with queen bed, third bedroom with two bunk-beds, and fourth bedroom with single bed). There is an ensuite bathroom, another full bathroom upstairs (with bath and shower), and a guest toilet downstairs.  There is an open plan kitchen/dining/family room with full heigh windows to the lush back yard.  There is also a large office, large outdoor deck and garden, and play room upstairs.  The house is 15 mins walk from the beach and 20 mins walk to the train station which can take you into the CBD/downtown and anywhere else in Melbourne. The neighbourhood is quiet and family friendly.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood of Clifton Hill is very friendly and welcoming.  We have a very high owner occupied neighborhood which fortunately creates a great sense of community and pride in our properties. For those who travel with their doggies you will be pleased to hear Clifton Hill has the greatest number of doggies in any suburb of Australia.  Thus we are very doggie friendly and restaurants, coffee shops, bars would welcome doggies. We are well and truly spoilt for parks....all around this area are parks and in fact one can walk, cycle, run etc for hours and feel as though one is in the bush.  We have the best of both worlds, a city retreat with a rural environment. One can wander along the river and enjoy a local farmers market most saturdays either at the Abbotsford (converted to a community based environment) Campus or the Childrens Farm... a real farm with a delightful cafe. Smith St, Fitzroy has wonderful second outlets as well as boutique shopping.  Many supermarkets are close by and
notes: The apartment is situated in a friendly residential street.
transit: If you dont have a car there is excellent public transport close by.  Trains, Trams and buses are all within five minutes of the apartment.  Trains are often express to the city and take 8 mins...5 mins to the MCG/Tennis centre.  There is a good bus system that goes to Melbourne University and some of the major Melbourne Hospitals. There are two drop off points for cars that can be rented by the hour, day, week or month(s). Taxi are easily available. Bicycles can be rented close by.... the whole area is surrounded by bicycle tracks.
access: Guests have access to the private courtyard garden.  In fact when you enter the premises via the park, you come through a side gate that takes you into a small delightful sunny courtyard garden (for your use) .  Your apartment opens onto this delightful space.
interaction: I am very happy to assist with any special requirements you may have in Melbourne.  You are welcome to knock on my door or send me a sms. I can recommend wonderful eateries, coffee shops, dog groomers, can provide dog minding and dog walking if requred;  I am also mindful of privacy.  As the apartment is totally self contained with its own private entry you have a home away from home but I am more than happy to provide any local information you may require.
house_rules: Shoes Off policy, come inside the apartment and remove shoes No Smoking No Parties allowed Dogs not allowed in bedroom or to sleep on furniture Friendly house trained dogs only Quiet and respectful to the dwelling
host_about:
Hi my name is Wendy. I enjoy the opportunity of being a host and for guests to have a wonderful experience of both staying at my apartment but also getting to know the area of Clifton Hill, a truly unique part of Melbourne.
I own a doggie who is very friendly, athletic and welcomes other doggies.  However you do have your own private area so if you don't want your doggie to be in close proximity to mine that is not an issue.
I enjoy playing bridge weekly, going to the theatre and the opera...movie going is one of my relaxations as is cycling and walking.
I have travelled extensively and also lived in Europe.  Meeting others is a wonderful experience.
Please be in contact with me about my listing and if you have any questions or would like me to make a booking for any of Melbourne's special ocassions please ask . I look forward to welcoming and hearing from you.

notes: The breakfast consists of fruit, yoghurt, cereal, bread for toast, juice, tea or coffee and condiments.  One mountain bike available for guests to use free of charge. Visitors during your stay - only by prior arrangement, including any additional overnight guests. Smoking only outside. No eating in the bedroom. Not suitable for children
transit: If driving, safe free parking is available outside the house on the street. The train station is only two minutes to my house. For the active guests, I have a mountain bike available to get around.
access: Guests may use the BBQ anytime you wish to cook,  Own TV and Lounge area. Also great out door space for eating or relaxing, especially in summer. If guests use kitchen,  own provisions required, as well as clean up and put dishes in the dishwasher. Laundry,  one wash per person per week. Hair dryer in your bathroom. Electric blanket in the winter.
interaction: I will do my best to ensure you have a memorable stay in Melbourne and make the most of our time here. I love meeting and interacting with my guests,happy to share a glass of wine while advising and discussing things to see and do in Melbourne and Victoria. The amount of interaction will depend upon the requirements of each individual guest and their required privacy. As I live in the house,  I will be present off and on during you stay and always there to assist, but happy to leave you to your own space and privacy, you also have available your own lounge and TV area to use, as I have my own lounge and office upstairs.  I have hosted young and not quite so young guests and enjoy interacting with all cultures and age groups.
house_rules: For privacy, guests will make their own bed.  Fresh towels are provided every 3 days. Fresh sheets once a week.  Use of washing machine available, one wash per guest per week.  Guests are free to use the kitchen and utensils, buy own provisions, clean up, with dishwasher for your ease.  Space available in the fridge for your food.
host_about:
I am originally from beautiful New Zealand; Melbourne has been home for the past 25 years.

I love good food, wine, and a passion for traveling, experiencing different cultures and meeting new and interesting people from around the globe. This stems from 30 years working in travel, hospitality and various airlines. I am privileged to have traveled to many corners of the globe, including, Africa, USA, Canada, Europe, UK, the Pacific, NZ, Australia, South America and Asia.

My Interests include cycling, sailing, swimming, horse riding, physical well 
being, cooking, meeting people, good conversation over a wine.
Consider myself to be friendly, social, sense of humor, independent, adaptable, well organised and tidy.
Love exchanging travel stories, ideas and meeting people of different cultures. My purpose for traveling is to experience varying cultures, hopefully improve my tolerance, knowledge and grow as an individual from the experience and fortunate to have volunteered in Brazil and South Africa 

As a Host and guest, I appreciate what I would like to get out of using and hosting with Air BnB.

I will be very happy to sit down over a glass of wine to provide advise on what to see and do while in Melbourne , Australia and of course beautiful New Zealand! 
If guests want minimal interaction I am happy to leave them to their own devises and independence or interact as much as required.

Yesterday is history, today is a gift, tomorrow may never come - so enjoy each moment :)

neighborhood_overview: One of Melbourne's smallest urban areas, Fitzroy, is a real treasure of old and new, working class and gentrification, historic preservation and modern architecture.  Right next to the city with both the Fitzroy and Carlton gardens in between, it's never boring but very relaxed.  If on the odd occasion it's noisy there are ear plugs in your bedside tables. Diversity, cafes, boutiques, galleries, pubs, parks, restaurants, cocktail bars, music, street art = good vibes.
notes: It's a good idea to check Melbourne's weather report before you arrive, we really can have "all seasons in 1 day" so it's wise to bring something warm even for those summer nights.  I recommend the app 'Weatherzone'. Help yourself to the umbrellas at the bottom of the stairs!
transit: There is so much to offer in Fitzroy you could spend most of your time getting around on foot.  I've left a local guide and map in your room and marked a square around the main Fitzroy streets as a start. The 86 or 112 trams go straight into the city in about 10 minutes, they run so regularly you don't even need a timetable. Hire a bike from one of the blue Melbourne Bike Share stations, the closest to us is opposite the wonderful Smith & Deli at 111 Moor Street, a 4 minute walk away. Taxi or Uber Or if you have a car my Visitor's Parking Permit might be available - first in first served!
access: Level 1 - front door access and laundry (also my rooms and other guest room) Level 2 - shared dining room, lounge, kitchen & 2 large furnished balconies Level 3 - your own bedroom, bathroom, wee balcony & study
interaction: This is a very independent set up.  My rooms and another guest room is on Level 1.  We are all usually out and about enjoying Melbourne so it can be rare we run into each other but I'm always contactable on my phone.
house_rules: - Please call out 'h!' or 'bye' when you use the front door, it's nice to know who's around.  If you're uncomfortable doing this, please don't book! - Please ensure the front door is always locked and gently used - The house is just for myself, my personal guests and my Airbnb guests - It's ok to use the kitchen but not ok to bring home Cage Eggs - The records, the alcohol and the kitchen cabinets with rubber bands on them are just for my personal use - No dickheads - Please respect the check-in and check-out times, thank you :)
host_about:
Hi there.  I'm originally from New Zealand but moved to Melbourne 19 years ago. 
Like most people who arrive in this wonderful city we think we are going to move on, but as soon as we get here ... well, there are reasons no-one ever wants to leave!  I was lucky enough to find this great house in the best part of Fitzroy so here I still am.   I have a habit of collecting things hence all the vintage love around the house.  Over the last decade+ I've shared my home with hundreds people from all around the world.  Things I can't live without?  Friends, freedom, Fitzroy...  If you think my home sounds like your kind of pad I'd love to hear from you and know what brings you to Melbourne.

space: This modern, architect-designed townhouse In the heart of Fitzroy is unusual for the area not only for the spacious layout in this 19th century suburb, but also because it is filled with light and in a cul-de-sac away from the main roads.   The house is safe and secure, and has an alarm. Downstairs are two bedrooms, a study, and the bathroom. The house is ideal for a family, or up to two couples - the main bedroom has a queen bed and the second bedroom has a double bed. Each bedroom has a large built-in wardrobe. The study looks out over a small, green private courtyard.  Upstairs is the main living space - a huge open plan area with the kitchen, dining suite, lounge, and patio. Like to entertain? The kitchen is has everything, featuring lots of bench space. neighborhood_overview: Fitzroy is the oldest suburb in Melbourne and a great example of why Melbourne is regularly called the world's most livable city.  Fitzroy has very diverse residents; shops; bars, cafes and restaurants; all services; and interesting streetscapes. There are beautiful parks and gardens nearby, plus museums and galleries. It's very walkable and bike friendly. Most buildings are low rise, one or two stories, even though its only ten minutes walk to the centre of the city. In the Guidebook I have listed a few on my favourite local places - though I'm sure you'll find your own just by wandering around. Sometimes these inner city neighbourhoods can be noisy, but the townhouse is in a street with very little through traffic. During the day there is some activity because the house borders an office and commercial precinct.
notes: There is a printer and a scanner which you can use, subject to a fair use policy. Please see the Guidebook for more details after you make your booking.
transit: Public transport is excellent - three tram routes within a few minutes walk, and a CBD train station ten minutes walk to take you anywhere in the city. There are two Myki cards (the local public transport smart card) for guest use (these need to be recharged in a local shop). There is no on site parking, but there is unrestricted street parking in front of the house. The main car rental offices are 20 minutes walk or 10 minutes taxi ride in the central city.   From the airport, if you are not coming by taxi, the Skybus takes you to Southern Cross Station in the city where you can transfer onto one of the three tram routes, which are one minute walk from the station.
access: "Tamerlane" is all yours! You will have all the essentials - wifi, coffee and tea, condiments, shampoo, soap and conditioner in the bathroom, laundry and dishwashing detergents, umbrellas. There is a Nespresso coffee maker, with two Nespresso stores nearby in the city for extra supplies.
interaction: I will always be available via the AirBnB site to answer questions or resolve any issues during your stay.
house_rules: Respect the house and your residential neighbours.  - Please leave the house as you find it. - No parties, loud noise, or gatherings of non-residents.  - No loud noise after 10.00 pm or before 8.00 am.  - No smoking or pets. - No shoes in the house - enjoy the comfort of socks or bare feet!  - Please clean up after yourself in the kitchen and bathroom.  - Please water the upstairs and downstairs gardens. Thanks  ...
host_about: I've lived in Melbourne all my life - well, almost. I'm semi-retired and frequently go travelling. Since I've had such great experiences with AirBnB, I thought it was only natural that I list my home for visitors to Melbourne.

name: Blissful Beachside Port Melbourne Warehouse
summary: Your own stylish, spacious bedroom and bathroom - plus shared use of the whole house - in a large, lofty, one-of-a-kind town home carved out of a 150-year-old landmark factory building. Ideally located in trendy Port Melbourne, with easy parking right out front. Just half a block from the beach - 3 blocks to ferry & cruise departures or the local tram stop - and 10 easy minutes by tram to the heart of Melbourne.

neighborhood_overview: Port Melbourne is one of Melbourne's most sought-after inner enclaves - a salty-aired, breezy, resort-like bayside neighbourhood - yet just 10 minutes by tram from the centre of the city.  Formerly a rough-edged wharfie zone, today Port is a delightful mix of high and low, old and new, teeming with quirky cafes, every flavour of restaurant or pub and shops of all kinds. Plus the beach, with its kilometres of bike and walking paths meandering along the waterfront, is just a few steps from my front door.  But what makes my 'hood' a truly special place to stay...  Well, if you like a real neighbourhood, not just a location, you'll love Port. It's a friendly, bustling place where Vince the barista extraordinaire  learns what coffee you like and has it ready for you before you ask - folks say hi as you run (or stroll) along the beach - and neighbours drop by for a natter. Come stay and see why my neighbours and I wouldn't live anywhere else!
notes: The whole house, suitable for 4-5 guests, may occasionally be available for the right guests at the right time. Please contact me if you're interested.
transit: Couldn't be easier! The tram and 10-minute access to the city is just a few blocks away, with guest metro passes available at the tram stop. Plus rent-a-bikes just out the front door. And easy walking to neighbourhood and bayside delights.
access: Access as much of my home as you like. Share the lounge, the kitchen, the courtyard with me if you like to hang out. Or stick to your own private room and bath if that's what you prefer. Expansive common area grounds, gym and pool are also yours to enjoy.
interaction: In my place, it's really up to you.  I've had quiet guests with their own plans who prefer to keep to themselves. And gregarious ones who jump in and live the local life with me and my congenial neighbours. All are welcome, always on your own terms.
house_rules: One pet (dog only) possibly allowed - but you must contact me to discuss first. (Depends on how they're likely to get on  with resident top dog Boof!) No smoking inside please.   Other than that, I'd ask only that you keep shared areas tidy and be as respectful of my home as I would of yours.
host_about:
I'm a once-upon-a-time New Yorker, transplanted to Australia almost 30 years ago for a one-year assignment, and never looked back. 

I now work from home running my own marketing consulting and creative services business. And my place is a frequent stopping off point for friends from around the globe - or for neighbours just dropping by on the way home from the tram. 

If you stay with me, you'll find an easy-going home away from home here. I'll show you where everything is, you can help yourself any time, and feel welcome to join in for a drink or a chat. Or if you prefer to stay to yourself, that's cool too.

And - if you let me stay in your home, you can be sure I'll treat it with the same care I hope for from guests in my own house.

name: ❤ Safe, Cosy Oasis 10 km from CBD ❤
summary: Warm, relaxed home away from home!  If you want the comfort and privacy and conveniences of a true family home…PLUS friendly relaxed hosts AND the confidence a 100+ positive reviews offer, then you should definitely check us  out :-)
space: You will be sleeping in a comfortable double bed, complete with an electric blanket to keep you warm on cold Melbourne nights, (should you need it). The room on offer can host a couple or single and we can offer a cot if you have a little one. (no extra cost). There is ample storage both for clothing and suitcases to be tucked away in the built in robes and chest of drawers. Fast WIFI will make accessing the world and future plans easy for you. There is a comfortable desk to use your computer. Your room has its own small fridge. For drinks and snacks, but you are also welcome to access the fridge and pantry in the kitchen to store food. There is a tv with dvd player in your room and we have many dvd's you can borrow for your viewing pleasure. Toiletries are provided to ensure you have everything you need to be comfortable on your immediate arrival. Newport is a safe,family friendly suburb in the inner west of Melbourne. We are close to the beach and close to the city with easily access

neighborhood_overview: So folks, you should know, Newport is not a bustling hub of nightlife, shopping and entertainment. It is a middle class, safe area with lots of young families. It's a real experience of normal life in Melbourne.  Newport is considered inner city. It has a regular train service to the city centre that takes 20 minutes to get you to Flinders St. Station. Newport Railway station is only a kilometre from our home or a 10 minute walk. There are a few really good cafes' restaurants and pubs near us. They may not be readily visible to a traveller so be sure to ask for recommendations from us or a local.  Mason street where the train station is located, has a butcher, fruit and vegetable shop, pharmacy, bakery, cafe, IGA Supermarket, hairdressers, atm, and cafe's. So food is readily accessible close to home. There are great parks, walking trails and bike paths to explore. I highly recommend Newport Lakes (which is 5 minutes from our home), where you can feel like you are in the country and not
notes: We are happy to have long term guests, but we like to get to know you first before committing. So please feel free to chat to us about extending your stay if this is something you would like to do. If you are travelling to us via train. Please let us know and we will endeavour to collect you from Newport Station. It is only a 10 min walk from there to our home but with luggage it can be inconvenient.
transit: Train, bus, bike or car are all good modes of transport in the inner-west. Our street has free unlimited street parking if you are travelling by car. There is also a taxi rank located at the train station and bus interchange in Newport.
access: Whilst staying with us you will have access to: Fast wifi Laundry facilities for those staying longer than a minimum stay.  No dryer access A separate refrigerator for your food and space in the pantry to store other food. Kitchen facilities for cooking simple  meals.  DO NOT COOK FOODS THAT REQUIRE A LOT OF FRYING AND SPICES. OUR KITCHEN IS NOT DESIGNED FOR ASIAN/INDIAN STYLE FOOD PREPARATION Please note that between 6 − 7 pm the kitchen will be pretty busy cooking the family meal, so where possible try to prepare food outside of this time. We have a collection of DVD's you are welcome to use and a large selection of books you can borrow.
interaction: We understand every guest is different. Some people like to have interaction and others a quiet place to base themselves to meet busy schedules. So we understand and will be led by you and always respect your privacy. But if you want a chat or need advice or assistance with anything we are available.
house_rules: ABSOLUTELY NO SMOKING INSIDE OUR PROPERTY. You are welcome to use the kitchen, but no cooking after 9.30 pm and please ensure you clean up properly after yourself.  Please note that between 6 − 7 pm the kitchen will be pretty busy cooking the family meal, so where possible try to prepare food outside of this time. In the interest of hygiene we ask that you use the dishwasher to ensure proper cleaning of utensils and cups, plates etc. please turn it on when full and take a turn emptying it. Large items like saucepans etc will need to be hand washed, dried and replaced in the cupboard.  The coffee machine is a barista quaility one and NOT for general use, (even by me :-)!  ) But if you are around in the morning when Jim has fired it up he will happily make you an awesome coffee - (espresso, cafe latte )with the best locally sourced coffee beans.  If you are a long term guest (more than a week) you are responsible for maintaining the washing of the towels and bed linen you have been provi
host_about:
Hey future guests and friends,

Thanks for taking the time to read our profile. 

We are a regular Aussie family with a home that many tell us has a relaxed and welcoming vibe. Which is GREAT because that’s how we want you to feel when you stay with us. 
You need to know that our home is not a sterile hotel, or a grungy hostel or even a display home. There is the normal detritus of modern family life with children. But that aside you can be assured your environment will be clean, your linens fresh and your room cleaned and dusted before you arrive. There can be a lot of laughter, love (the occasional tantrum) in our home, and you are welcome to share in that, or to have privacy and limited interaction if that is your preference. We will be led by you. ☺

Above all we just want you to be comfortable!

We love keeping fit. Enjoying time with friends. A good red wine or a craft beer AND of course travelling!!

We have been having airbnb guests for 5 years now. It has been truly rewarding and we have met remarkable people from every continent, many we are still friends or in contact with. 

We look forward to meeting you too ☺.

name: City's edge Penthouse - private bath, views!
summary: No cleaning fees. Private room ideal for solo travellers. Queen size bed, TV, fast WiFi, Netflix and a private bathroom in a central, quiet, secure top floor apartment.  Ducted A/C & heating throughout.  Tram stop and IGA supermarket 40 metres from the door.
space: Welcome to historic South Melbourne! Safe comfortable accommodation in a large, top floor 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment with secure entry. It is just 2 km (1.2 miles) from the city centre, 2.5 km from St  Kilda, 1.5 km from South Melbourne beach, and walking distance through parkland to the MCG and Rod Laver Arena.   Your Room There is an exceptionally comfortable queen size bed, your very own private bathroom and separate toilet.  All bed linen and towels are supplied, including beach towels for the pool or beach. There's also a hairdryer, bathrobes, snuggly rugs and chiropractic pillows.  You will have stunning panoramic views over South Melbourne, Port Phillip Bay and Albert Park from every room. You can watch the ferry leave for Tasmania at sunset, or see hot air balloons at sunrise. How to Get Here Take Skybus from the airport to Southern Cross Station, then a short uber or tram ride to mine. MYKI cards are supplied for public transport, just top up as you go. Where To Go?   The

neighborhood_overview: There are ten restaurants within a 3 minute walk. Clarendon Street is a 5 minute walk and has something for everyone - beautiful wide streets and footpaths, cobblestone lanes, restaurants, cafes and bars, eclectic shopping, a great market.  It's much more local and friendly, and still within walking or tram distance of the city.
notes: NO cleaning fees. Early (8am-1pm) check in,  or late (11am-4pm) pm) check out incurs an extra charge of $20. Directions for arrival will be sent following booking confirmation.  More detailed information is also available on arrival, along with Myki PT cards and WIFI password.
transit: Catch a #58 tram 50 metre away to take you straight to Melbourne Convention Centre,  Southbank and Crown Casino, the Aquarium, the city centre, then on to Queen Victoria Market and even Melbourne Zoo.  Hop off at the river for a waterside walk to Exhibition Centre, South Wharf.  Here there is plenty of shopping and restaurants. The domain interchange tram stop is just two minutes away, where you can catch trams to almost anywhere in inner Melbourne.  It's just a ten minute ride to almost everything - for the city, Federation Square, Southbank and major sporting venues, take any tram northbound.  For St Kilda it's #16, Chapel Street #6, Toorak Road #58 south bound. For drivers, it's two minutes to Citylink, twenty to the airport.   Street parking is free overnight and on weekends.
access: Amenities  For breakfast, you're welcome to help yourself to tea/coffee, cereal and toast. For those who like to cook, you have full use of the kitchen, or there are plenty of restaurants, cafes and pubs close by for those who don't!    A supermarket and bottle shop is a handy 50 metres away.   There's a mini barbecue on the balcony too. A laundry with large washer, dryer and laundry products is available to freshen up those travel clothes. Fast WiFi is included and available through the whole apartment.  A 42" flatscreen TV is in your room. Other bonuses are a heated pool, tennis court (racquets available) and a gym. And just in case it rains (in Melbourne??) there are plenty of new and old movies, books, Kindle and audio books for your phone/ipad.
interaction: Guests are free to utilise the whole apartment, except of course my bedroom and ensuite.   You can call, email or message me if you need. I am home most week nights, watching a favourite TV series or a movie. You're welcome to join me on the couch for a glass of wine or a cuppa.
house_rules: Shoes off inside please. No eating meals in the bedroom. Early checkins or late checkouts are negotiable for a fee. Use the clothes dryer, don't hang wet clothes on bedroom furniture.  Please respect my home by keeping it clean and using the amenities sensibly.   Turn off lights and fans when not in use. Please be careful not to let suitcases scratch the walls. Save water and chipped crockery by putting dishes in the dishwasher, not hand washing dishes. I do have to work during the week, so quiet homecomings if you are late on week nights. Smokers are welcome to use the balcony.  If it's really cold out there, we have blankets. :)
host_about:
Airbnb host and  user since 2011.  
You will love  Melbourne and staying in  my relaxed eclectic apartment.
I've Airbnb'd in London, Paris, New York,  Seminyak, Barcelona,  Seattle, Venice, Ho Chi Min and more, so I understand both sides of Airbnb.
 I've had a few adventures and glitches on the road too, and of course the best part, meeting and staying with many different people.

name: 2 bedrooms-ideal for friends/family
summary: Very comfortable modern, house in quiet, leafy environment with easy access to local shops and all public transport-bus,tram,train and access to freeways for country driving.
space: Lovely townhouse offering two rooms; One with a queen bed in spacious room with plenty of wardrobes; the other room has a double bed and also has plenty of wardrobe space. Both share one large bathroom and all are situated on the first floor. Ideal for family group or friends travelling together. Quality towels, linen, soaps. Hair dryer provided. If you only want one room that is fine: I won't put someone else in the other. I have the second floor with separate ensuite to guests.  The suburb of Prahran is located south east of the city (45 minutes walk - 10 minutes by train) in a prime position to experience Melbourne and all it has to offer. Just a two minute walk to the railway station, and trams and buses at each end of the street. Just a couple of minutes walk to the famous and vibrant district for shopping, restaurants, cafes, bars, pubs, boutiques of Greville and Chapel Streets. neighborhood_overview: Walking distance to Bridge Road and Swan Street, where you’ll find great restaurants, bars, cafes, supermarkets, shopping and night life. Walk to 1000 Blessings, a fab organic cafe and enjoy great coffee and food. Enjoy the Weekend Farmers’ Market,bursting with fresh produce and loads of atmosphere. Richmond Recreation Centre, with gym and 50 metre indoor pool and a large park with BBQ areas, playground and oval are all just around the corner. Hop on a tram and in minutes you’ll be in the heart of Melbourne city or in trendy Chapel Street South Yarra with its endless shopping options. There’s easy access to Melbourne’s major venues – the MCG, Hisense and AAMI Arenas and Rod Laver Arena – home of the Australian Open. This apartment is close to all Melbourne has to offer and is famous for. Definitely the place to stay! Also only minutes away from Epworth Hospital and The Melbourne Clinic.
notes: 1 set of keys. No luggage storage before/after stay. Second floor apartment without lift access. No air conditioning. Heaters/fans only. Permissible sized hot water tank that requires time to reheat water between use, especially between showers. NO PARKING OR PARKING PERMIT AVAILABLE. THANK YOU! Thanks for taking the time to read our Listing. We really appreciate it! Let us know you have by mentioning 'Read the Listing!' in your first message to us. The a2c Team
transit: Our apartment is located within walking distance of all the major attractions, and for travelling further afield, trams are a short stroll away, so getting around is a breeze!
access: Guests have exclusive and private access to the entire apartment. Check-in details provided once booking is confirmed.
interaction: We don't always get to meet all our guests in person, however we're available if you need us! Simply get in touch and we'll be happy to help out with any questions or assistance you may need before or during your stay.
house_rules: Please take a moment now to read our House Rules. COMMUNICATION All communication is via airbnb messaging only. Ensure you have AIRBNB APP and mobile connectivity, so we can easily communicate. GUEST BOOKING, GUEST NUMBER, GUESTS STAYING AND BEDDING For personal travel, you as guest booking must be one of guests staying for entire stay. Number of guests staying limited to maximum number allowed in property and as confirmed and paid for in airbnb. Where bedding options offered, such as king beds or king single beds, you must request your preference at time of booking. Where extra bedding offered, no extra bedding provided if number of guests staying is property standard occupancy, unless extra bedding is requested and paid for by you in airbnb at time of booking. Bedding preferences / extra bedding can not be guaranteed. SELF CHECK IN FROM 3PM / SELF CHECK-OUT TO 10AM Following information available in AIRBNB APP after 48  hours of booking: - PROPERTY ADDRESS and MAP - SELF CHECK-IN/OUT
host_about:
Thanks for reading our profile. 

We've been hosting since 2009 and love It!

And when time permits, we also love travelling!

We've been partnering with property owners since 2009, when we established a2c, our complete turnkey short stay property management and co-hosting service.

If you're a property owner and interested in tapping into our considerable experience and expertise, then feel free to get in touch to discuss our property management and airbnb co-hosting services, and we'll be happy to assist!

We pride ourselves in offering an exceptional collection of unique, highly rated, hand selected homes, in the best inner city Melbourne locations, super clean and beautifully furnished, with airbnb guests in mind.

Exceeding guest expectations is what we’re about.

As hosts, we look forward to welcoming you, and making your experience unforgettable.

As guests, we'll always be respectful of both you and your home, and look forward to sharing the experience!

Best,
The a2c Team

name: Sunny 1950s Apartment, St Kilda East  Longer stays
summary: Greyfriars is an iconic apartment block with a beautiful central garden, a car park and our sunny 1950s renovated one bedroom flat. Green views from living and bedroom, a cute separate kitchen and a retro bathroom.  Walk to shops, tram to city. Your pied-a-terre in vibrant Melbourne.
space: Retro one bedroom apartment for two in East St Kilda.  A beautiful garden, your own car space and trams to St Kilda and the city from this treed residential neighbourhood.  The apartment has a well equipped kitchen with a cafe table and chairs. The renovated original bathroom has a shower over the bath, new toilet and hand basin, thick towels, soap and shampoo.   A good sized bedroom houses a comfortable queen bed.  Quality linen is supplied with a selection of cotton or woollen blankets or a doona. The bedside tables are vintage marble and brass. The 1950s glam lamps are a useful frivolity.  A built in wardrobe, a cheval mirror, lady's chair, a chest of drawers and a towel rack complete the room.  The living room has a large marble topped dining table with four bentwood chairs.  There is a leather sofa, side table, a bookshelf with books about Melbourne and Australia amongst others, and a television.  There is a reading chair and a floor lamp near the wide windows. A vintage sideboard

neighborhood_overview: Greyfriars is an iconic 1950s apartment block built near the top of East St Kilda hill.  Stately mansions like Labassa and Grimwade House are a stones throw away.  The area is green and residential but a walk, a tram or a short drive away, and you are in all the action of Balaclava, Ripponlea and Elsternwick. Stroll down Orrong Road to Glover Station, an eatery in Glen Eira Road or to Ripponlea Village to visit the Firebrand Bakery or for a fabulous brunch.  Walk down the Balaclava Road hill to eclectic Balaclava with its cafes, restaurants, bars, bakeries and shops.  And tram back up the hill if you are feeling lazy. The St Kilda Esplanade, Luna Park and Ackland Street are a short tram ride away on the no 16 or 3A trams. Enjoy the tram a little longer and you are in Melbourne's CBD on either the no 16, 3 or 3A.  (The no 3 takes you to the City via a different route to Ackland Street and St Kilda Beach) Alternatively you can take the train from Balaclava Station to the city or the MCG.
notes: NA
transit: The tram is just outside the apartment gardens.  Enjoy the rides! The 220 bus travels regularly up and down Orrong Road to the city and beyond via Malvern Road, South Yarra crossing Chapel Street to the Prahran Market. And we will leave a Myki card for you with a few dollars worth of transport. Just load it up at a newsagents to travel more on trams, buses and trains around Melbourne. Greenmeadows Gardens is around the corner and is a popular, leafy park for families and those just wanting to sit and read or walk their dogs.  Of course, Greyfriars has a lovely garden to relax in too. Markets on weekends like the famous St Kilda Esplanade Sunday Market, St Kilda Farmers Market, and the Hank Marvin Markets in Alma Park which are a weekend event with food trucks, produce and craft stalls. South Melbourne, Prahran and the famous Queen Victoria Market in the city are all great places to buy fresh produce on weekends and to explore during the week too.
access: The apartment is all yours and this includes the lovely garden with fresh herbs for picking, a communal laundry with washers and driers, large rubbish bins.  The car park and garden are all accessible for your time here.  There is free, safe bicycle storage in a large communal space with a keycode entry. There is also plenty of free street parking just outside.
interaction: The apartment is all yours. We will meet you on arrival and show you around. And we’re only an email or phone call away if you need us.  The other apartment dwellers are helpful and friendly.
house_rules: We hope that you enjoy your time in our apartment and we are sure that you will treat it with respect. The apartment block is not a party block so noise including loud music after 10pm is to be avoided.  Only one or two people are allowed to stay and you are expected to treat Greyfriars with respect, of course. There is a large communal laundry with coin in the slot washers and driers that can be accessed most of the time.  Please see the information sheet.
host_about:
We live on a broad acre cropping, sheep and alpaca farm on the Wimmera plains. We enjoy the space, people and environment and the ability to grow our own produce. 

Our beach house on the Great Ocean Road is a complementary contrast to life on the farm. 

Satis Beach House is comfortable, quirky and just around the corner from a beautiful surf beach, estuary and cliff top walks along the coastline of south eastern Australia.  Excellent cafes, restaurants, a bookshop, galleries and a pub add to the coastal mix at Aireys Inlet.

Greyfriars is an iconic 1950s apartment block with a lovely central garden in St Kilda East, Melbourne. It’s our city ‘pied à terre’ and we love it! 

We invite guests of Satis Beach House and others to stay at Greyfriars, our cute one bedroom apartment and live like a local in this fascinating suburb for a stay of three plus weeks.

Contact Fiona for bookings or check us out here and @satisbeachhouse

summary: The Garden Bungalow was this year fully booked by former guests from mid January until the 12th May, 2018 .  I apologise to my lovely regulars who have been unable to book with me.  Now everything back to normal and we are open for business again.  Henry and I await your company!
space: The Garden Bungalow with the Possums is fully self contained and en suite. Separate weatherboard bungalow in my lovely garden.  Totally private, own access with parking on the quiet road; fresh flowers or fresh fruit and fresh sheets. The garden bungalow has a new queen sized bed and a bed settee and a easy chair.. There is Wifi internet access for my guests at no extra charge. There is a flat screen TV. Next to the main room is a simple but functional small kitchen which has a hob,  fridge, kettle and toaster and a microwave oven. If you are thinking of staying here, please note, there are no city views, city is 45 minutes away on the train or drive in 20.  No bay views, but you can walk there in 10 minutes and best of all there is a map linking this listing so you can see exactly where you could be laying down your head.

If you need to be staying in Emerald,  Ivanhoe, Carnegie or Essendon then my place is not for you.  These lovely bungalows are in my beautiful garden where the birds sing in a street in Parkdale on the bay where the friendly locals are and the best coffee in town.

summary: Welcome to Little George, a light-filled 3 level home in vibrant Fitzroy filled with comfy furnishings and vintage touches. space: Hi there, This listing is for one bedroom on the ground floor of my large 3 level home just off the wonderful Gertrude Street. (I have 2 rooms available - the other listing is 'Stunning Fitzroy own level+ensuite' listing #72576). ***Please not I only have 1 parking permit so please check it is available before booking, it usually is but it's definitely worth checking*** This is an excellent spot for guests in Melbourne for a short time who want that 'local feeling'.  Or for those lucky folk who are moving to Melbourne (nice choice!) it's a great landing pad while you look for something permanent. Located in between action-packed Brunswick and Smith Streets, this is a fantastic, diverse area full of great cafes, restaurants, wonderful local pubs, art galleries, parks, live music venues, diverse architecture and the Melbourne Museum.  The beloved #86 tram (our 'tramily') and #12 are just at the end of the road giving easy access to other parts of this wonderfully liveable city. The house
description: Welcome to Little George, a light-filled 3 level home in vibrant Fitzroy filled with comfy furnishings and vintage touches.   With Fitzroy's almost 100 cafes, restaurants, live music venues, cocktail bars and pubs you have chosen a wonderful area to stay in.  This is an award winning Kerstin Thompson house and has been my home for over 17 years.  I love living here and I hope you'll enjoy visiting - it's nice to have you! (I have 2 rooms available - the other listing is 'Stunning Fitzroy own level+ensuite' listing #72576). ***Please not I only have 1 parking permit so please check it is available before booking, it usually is but it's definitely worth checking*** This is an excellent spot for guests in Melbourne for a short time who want that 'local feeling'. neighborhood_overview: One of Melbourne's smallest urban areas, Fitzroy, is a real treasure of old and new, working class and gentrification, historic preservation and modern architecture.  Right next to the city with both the Fitzroy and Carlton gardens in between, it's never boring but very relaxed.  If on the odd occasion it's noisy there are ear plugs in your bedside tables. Diversity, cafes, boutiques, galleries, pubs, parks, restaurants, cocktail bars, music, street art = good vibes.
notes: Please note the bed (an extremely comfortable queen) is against the wall on one side. It's a good idea to check Melbourne's weather report before you arrive, we really can have "all seasons in 1 day" so it's wise to bring something warm even for those summer nights.  I recommend the app 'Weatherzone'.  Help yourself to the umbrellas at the bottom of the stairs! Optus reception is sometimes not great in this room but other networks are good.
transit: There is so much to offer in Fitzroy you could spend most of your time getting around on foot.  I've left a map in your room and marked a square around the main Fitzroy streets as a start. The 86 or 112 trams go straight into the city in about 10 minutes, they run so regularly you don't even need a timetable. Hire a bike from one of the blue Melbourne Bike Share stations, the closest to us is opposite the wonderful Smith & Deli at 111 Moor Street, a 4 minute walk away. Taxi or Uber or ladies, use Sheebah, it's a great company to support! Or if you have a car my Visitor's Parking Permit might be available - first in first served.
access: Level 1 - your room, your own powder room/toilet, laundry, share full bathroom, front door access Level 2 - shared dining room, lounge, kitchen & 2 large balconies (Level 3 is the other guest's private area of bedroom, bathroom, wee balcony & study)
interaction: This is a very independent set up.  Apart from our rooms on level 1 there is another guest room on level 3.   As we are all usually out and about enjoying Melbourne it can be rare we run into each other but I'm always contactable on my phone if I'm not at home.  If I haven't responded for more than an hour I'm probably in the cinema, my favourite place.
house_rules: - Please call out 'h!' or 'bye' when you use the front door, it's nice to know who's around.  If you're uncomfortable doing this, please don't book! - Please ensure the front door is always locked and gently used - The house is just for myself, my personal guests and my Airbnb guests - It's ok to use the kitchen but not ok to bring home Cage Eggs - The records, the alcohol and the kitchen cabinets with rubber bands on them are just for my personal use - No dickheads - Please respect the check-in and check-out times, thank you :)
host_about:
Hi there.  I'm originally from New Zealand but moved to Melbourne 19 years ago. 
Like most people who arrive in this wonderful city we think we are going to move on, but as soon as we get here ... well, there are reasons no-one ever wants to leave!  I was lucky enough to find this great house in the best part of Fitzroy so here I still am.   I have a habit of collecting things hence all the vintage love around the house.  Over the last decade+ I've shared my home with hundreds people from all around the world.  Things I can't live without?  Friends, freedom, Fitzroy...  If you think my home sounds like your kind of pad I'd love to hear from you and know what brings you to Melbourne.

name: Stone's Throw Studio, Belgrave
summary: Our beautiful 1 bedroom studio is suitable for 2 people as it has 1 double bed only. It has a garden setting with a private entrance & patio, large bathroom with clawfoot bath, separate shower and separate toilet. Located on a private street, yet walking distance to Puffing Billy, shops, bars, restaurants and train station. If you have a larger group we have a cottage as well. Please see our other listing Stone's Throw Cottage. Linen, towels and continental breakfast included. Free WIFI
space: Your one bedroom studio gives you complete  privacy. Private patio, entrance, full bathroom and separate toilet. Located in Belgrave, Dandenong Ranges. Suitable for 2 people maximum. Walking distance to Puffing Billy and Belgrave station. One hour by train or car from Melbourne's Southern Cross station.  Break free of the busy city for a few days and visit this relaxing peaceful area.  Once here, the main attraction is Puffing Billy Steam Train which chugs along several times a day through fern gullies and massive mountain ash trees. Lots of walks through the forest where in the early hours you could spot a lyrebird, echidna or wombat. We have a Trees Adventure Park nearby for those that like to brave ziplining! You will be minutes from Belgrave village and a short drive or bus trip to Sassafras and Olinda. All have unique shops and top restaurants.  This room is part of our main house and is completely private, with it's own entrance and patio.  The bathroom has a clawfoot bath, separ

neighborhood_overview: We live in a very lush area here in the Dandenong Ranges. Native birds are part of the setting and they'll visit your patio most days. Puffing Billy, Trees Adventure Park and  Grant's Picnic ground are walking distance ... but maybe take a 5 minute drive there. Short drives also to Burnham Piggery, Kallista, Sassafras and Olinda. Lots of amazing hikes and drives through mountain ash and fern forests.
notes: Small fridge, microwave, electric frying pan, kettle, toaster, hairdryer, toiletries and WIFI. Although we have ducted heating that will reach your room, you also have a split system A/C so you can control the temperature in winter or summer. Electric blanket included also.
transit: We are very lucky at our location. At the Belgrave train station there are many buses that will take you anywhere you'd like to go. And it's 1 hour by train into the city of Melbourne.
access: You're welcome to stroll around the garden. Enjoy any fruit in season. Our outside laundry is the only place that's shared and we have free WIFI at the propety.
interaction: Very happy to interact or to leave you in complete privacy.
house_rules: Strictly no smoking. Sorry but this room isn't suitable for children/babies or pets. The room is for 2 people only.
host_about:
I love Melbourne!! And happily run a B&B now after being in the fashion industry for years. Love meeting people from all over the world and hearing about their lives and travels. Personal travel can be difficult sometimes but we manage to get away a couple of times a year. I lived in the US for 23 yrs so I travel there a lot to visit friends and family.
Love being an AIRBNB host. Itry to keep my cottage and private suite in tip top condition with all the little necessities that I can think of to make your stay comfortable. I've lived in the area here in the Dandenong Ranges for 14 years and have a very extensive knowledge of what you should experience while here. There are lots of wonderful things to do and some fabulous restaurants too. I'll help you in any way I can. So come visit Belgrave.

name: Healesville Yarra Valley Cottage
summary: The cottage is a small self contained cabin on a picturesque property. It is simple, comfortable, clean and private. This space is perfect for people  looking for a quiet stay in a rural location with access to all the Yarra Valley offers.
space: Comfy private self contained cabin set on 3 hectare rural property. A short 5 min drive from the picturesque town of Healesville, renowned for its wildlife sanctuary, bush walks, food and wine and burgeoning arts scene. The location provides easy access to town, but in a rural and picturesque setting The cabin is one bed/sitting room with ensuite bathroom and a really nice deck looking out over a vast expanse of lawn. It has a comfy double bed with electric blanket,and there is tea and snack making facilities, mobile phone coverage, ipod dock, and CD player.We are happy to loan from our CD collection during your stay. The room isn't huge, but it is cosy and comfortable, with a  floor to ceiling window next to the bed so that you can lie in bed and look out to the mountains. Most times you will get to see mobs of kangaroos grazing on the lawn. It is situated far enough away from the house for privacy without feeling abandoned. If you're up for the walk into town it is a 30 min walk, or
