neighborhood_overview: This is a lovely leafy and quiet location. We are far enough away from town to be peaceful and secluded, while still close enough to easily access the cafes, restaurants  and tourist spots.
notes: There are kangaroos and other wildlife on the property. We would appreciate taking care, and taking off shoes inside cabin to avoid soiling carpet.
transit: There is a bus at the corner that travels into the town however service is limited. My best advice is to have a car or bike.
access: Guests are welcome to wander through the garden. The cabin has a nice deck to enjoy a glass of wine and sit in the sun.
interaction: Interaction with guests is usually kept to greeting and settling them in on arrival. We tend to come and go and allow guests to enjoy their privacy.
house_rules: This accommodation is most suitable for singles or couples. Please take off shoes inside. Wildlife lives on our property, their "evidence" can get on your shoes! Definitely no smoking inside. Parking is available on a shady concrete space under our large elm tree. Please do not park on our lovely green lawns, there is a large septic system under them which is compromised by cars or heavy equipment. Continental Breakfast provided for 2 night or more bookings.  There are no cooking facilities in the cabin. Sorry, we're presuming you've come up here for a break from all that. As a working family we aren't always available for check in before 5pm during the week,especially at short notice. However, if 24 hours notice is given we can usually make suitable arrangements. We have kept the price of Mount Lebanon Cottage low because it is a simple uncluttered space that we clean ourselves. In return we expect guests to leave the space as clean as they found it, including washing, drying dishes,
host_about:
Karen & Michael live on a 4 acre property with two grown sons, their Australian Terrier and a range of assorted wildlife, including a mob of kangaroos, marauding wombat and the occasional echidna. 
They have a strong connection to community, and love living in this part of the world. 
Karen loves to read, paint, and create things, as well as playing in a ukele band with 4 friends. Michael loves football,music, and with his background in horticulture is in charge of the garden at the property. which consists of open space as well as a vegetable garden and range of fruit trees.
They have both travelled extensively, but travelling has been on hold for a few years now. They love meeting new people

notes: Property has street parking available. The townhouse is a no smoking space but there is a small outdoor balcony or yard area on which you can smoke. This is three storey townhouse, elderly and young children may not be suitable. -Please do not tamper with the Smoke Alarm. If anything beeps, including the smoke alarm please contact us.  -Please clean after yourself when leaving, including taking out all the trash, wash the dishes and put the bedding in order. Although we do have a house keeper, all your help would be greatly appreciated.  -No party and smoking inside at all times. -Please be kind enough to keep the power bills down so we can pass the savings onto our guests.  -Call-outs after 7:00pm may incur a fee of $50+ any additional associated costs.  -If keys are lost, there will be a replacement cost/locksmith call out fee of upwards of $300.00. transit: Local cafés, Aldi Supermarket, Chemist warehouse, and shops just around the corner within walking distance. Northland shopping centre is within 10 minutes driving distance. Go to La Trobe University around 20 minutes by bus. 20 minutes walk to Austin Hospital. Relax and unwind at Fairfield Park Boathouse, which is 5km away. 11km from Melbourne CBD, you can get there by car, bus or train.
access: Guests have access to the entire townhouse & yard but NOT the garage. There is free street parking at the front or the back of the house, Ivanhoe is a very safe suburb.
interaction: Available to ensure an easy check in and for any assistance required. A compendium is available in the property to ensure you have all information at your fingertips.

neighborhood_overview: Within a 5 minute walk you’ll discover the delights of the Tennyson Street Shopping Village.  Cafes, bars, restaurants, bakery, hairdresser, supermarket, wine shop and even a quaint little village church! Also close by you will find Ormond Road Village. Lots of cafes and restaurants. Try Dandelion Vietnamese Eatery. For great coffee Combi Cafe. Elwood beach is a short walk away and vibrant St Kilda is close by. Hop on a tram and enjoy a trip into the city via St Kilda Road. This passes the Botanic Gardens, The Arts Centre and fashionable Southbank river precinct, with its many bars and restaurants. This top floor views apartment is close to everything Melbourne has to offer. Definitely the place to stay.
notes: 1 set of keys. No luggage storage before/after stay. Second floor apartment without lift access. No air conditioning. Heaters/fans only. Permissible sized hot water tank that requires time to reheat water between use, especially between showers. NO PARKING OR PARKING PERMIT AVAILABLE. THANK YOU! Thanks for taking the time to read our Listing. We really appreciate it! Let us know you have by mentioning 'Read the Listing!' in your first message to us. The a2c Team
transit: Our apartment is located within walking distance of Tennyson Street Village, and for travelling further afield, tram and bus stops are a short stroll away, so getting around is a breeze!
access: Guests have exclusive and private access to the entire apartment. Check-in details provided once booking is confirmed.
interaction: We don't always get to meet all our guests in person, however we're available if you need us! Simply get in touch and we'll be happy to help out with any questions or assistance you may need before or during your stay.
house_rules: Please take a moment now to read our House Rules. COMMUNICATION All communication is via airbnb messaging only. Ensure you have AIRBNB APP and mobile connectivity, so we can easily communicate. GUEST BOOKING, GUEST NUMBER, GUESTS STAYING AND BEDDING For personal travel, you as guest booking must be one of guests staying for entire stay. Number of guests staying limited to maximum number allowed in property and as confirmed and paid for in airbnb. Where bedding options offered, such as king beds or king single beds, you must request your preference at time of booking. Where extra bedding offered, no extra bedding provided if number of guests staying is property standard occupancy, unless extra bedding is requested and paid for by you in airbnb at time of booking. Bedding preferences / extra bedding can not be guaranteed. SELF CHECK IN FROM 3PM / SELF CHECK-OUT TO 10AM Following information available in AIRBNB APP after 48  hours of booking: - PROPERTY ADDRESS and MAP - SELF CHECK-IN/OUT
host_about:
Thanks for reading our profile. 

We've been hosting since 2009 and love It!

And when time permits, we also love travelling!

We've been partnering with property owners since 2009, when we established a2c, our complete turnkey short stay property management and co-hosting service.

If you're a property owner and interested in tapping into our considerable experience and expertise, then feel free to get in touch to discuss our property management and airbnb co-hosting services, and we'll be happy to assist!

We pride ourselves in offering an exceptional collection of unique, highly rated, hand selected homes, in the best inner city Melbourne locations, super clean and beautifully furnished, with airbnb guests in mind.

Exceeding guest expectations is what we’re about.

As hosts, we look forward to welcoming you, and making your experience unforgettable.

As guests, we'll always be respectful of both you and your home, and look forward to sharing the experience!

Best,
The a2c Team

name: Beautiful Northcote home with heart -close to city
summary: Our 3 bedroom 1940's renovated home is light, open and full of charm. The large garden and nearby creek create an urban oasis only 20 minutes from the city by public transport (a short walk to train station and tram stop). Just minutes from CERES organic markets / farm and the restaurants and shops of High St. A safe and quiet neighbourhood. Room is perfect for solo traveller and hosts can help as much or as little as needed.
space: Our home is close to lively shopping strips, quiet creek walks and public transport. The guest bedroom room is spacious, peaceful and light with floorboards, queen bed, wardrobe, chest of drawers and large windows looking onto a native garden. You will have plenty of privacy as the room is down its own end of the house. You will have the bathroom / toilet to yourself aside from the  short time we shower there - the rest of the time we use a second toilet and sink at the other end of the house.  House is tidy and clean, pet free and non smoking.  Your hosts are keen on yoga and you are welcome to loan yoga mats etc and do your yoga practice on the deck or in your room (plenty of space). Includes: Wireless internet access, fresh linen including towel & face-washer, electric kettle & tea making facilities in room, off street parking if required and hair dryer and ironing facilities on request. Renovated kitchen and bathroom.

Also a lovely cycle to the city if you have access to a bike.
notes: Prefer guests aged 30+ with planned work or activity itinerary. If same day booking check in will need to be after 6pm.
transit: 7-10 minute walk to tram 11 and tram 96. 12-14 minute walk to Croxton train station. Express train gets to city in 20 mins. Trams will get you to the city in 25  - 30 minutes. We can loan you a MetCard (you will need to top it up with credit at local milk bar or charging station).
access: Guest will have access to broadband internet with good download (no movie download). We love Melbourne (it's full of diversity, art and entertainment) and have plenty of ideas for recommended destinations and activities.

neighborhood_overview: Our house is perfectly located for you to enjoy and explore abundant restaurants, cute bars, and shopping. Easy walking distance (15 minutes) to a range of cafes, pubs and restaurants, the cinema and the fresh food market, open 5 days a week. The nearest wine bar and local fish and chips are just 2 minutes walk away! Auburn Village, a short stroll away down one of the finest residential strips in Melbourne, is an untouched strip dotted with boutiques and cafes for the sophisticated and friendly clientele that will keep you coming back. A perfect spot to spend a weekend brunching, riverside walking or hitting the shops.  Also in easy walking distance is Camberwell shopping centre with numerous eateries, cafes and bars and a great range of shops and boutiques, as well as several other lovely local shopping areas - Glenferrie Road in Hawthorn and Maling Road in Canterbury. Here you can find pretty much anything you may want and there is plenty to choose from in terms of restaurants and ca
notes: This is an old house and a treasured home, lovingly maintained; the layout has changed many times in it's history. The guest bedroom room is at the top of a flight of stairs, which go no where else, whilst the guest bathroom is at the bottom of the stairs. Great spot to stay for all the major events and attractions in Melbourne - easy transport to the F1 Grand Prix, Australian Open Tennis, Spring Racing Carnival, cricket or AFL at the MCG. Business travellers welcomed, all facilities available (WiFi, printer, scanning etc).  Note to Prospective Guests: • Hosts like us want to know who our guests are. Post an accurate profile photo of yourself (not dog or cat) and write a bit about yourself and what the purpose of your trip is. • VERIFY YOUR ID. Airbnb is going to require you to do this eventually, so do it while you aren't pressed for time. This shows you value trust in our community. (See https://www.airbnb.com/help/question/450 for more information about Verified ID.)
transit: To travel on Public Transport you will need a Myki Card, visit the PTV government website to find out details about visitor value pack passes. Myki cards can be bought from a number of outlets, including any 7/Eleven store or at the SkyBus terminal at Melbourne Airport or Southern Cross Railway Station. Walk or tram to shops, bars & restaurants in Camberwell (Burke Road), Auburn Village, Canterbury (Maling Road). Camberwell station is a gentle 15 minutes walk from the house; train travel time to the CBD (city) is 15 minutes.  Tram stops are 5 minutes walk from the house. Tram 72 which runs from Melbourne University to Camberwell, trams commence in Swanston Street near Faraday Street (University of Melbourne) and run via Swanston Street (City), St Kilda Road (Domain Interchange), Commercial Road, Malvern Road and Burke Road to terminate near Cotham Road (Kew). Coming from the city get off at tram stop number 67 and walk 5 minutes to the house. Public transport from the airport to the ho

We don't make check in/check out times but when there are guests back to back we expect people to be out of the bedroom by 10.00 am. latest, so we can clean and get ready for the next guests. You are welcome to leave your luggage safely here, by arrangement.
host_about:
I was born in the UK but moved to Melbourne with my family in the late 90's and now call this home. Since then i have been a full time mother and housewife leaving behind a successful career in marketing and design. I love to cook and am amazing housekeeper (like scary efficiency!!) so you'll be guaranteed a clean, well kept place to stay as my guest.

The most important things in my life are my family, my friends, good food, good company, good wine - what more could I need?

Jump on the free City Circle tram if you’re a newb, which will trundle you past sights like the Melbourne Aquarium, Old Melbourne Gaol and Parliament House – and of course you’ll want to jump out and explore the coffee, boutiques and street art of the laneways and old arcades. When you're spent and hungry try to find Izakaya Den, Cookie, Cumulus Inc, MoVida or one of the many iconic Melbourne hangouts. So do the time-honoured thing: meet someone under the Flinders Street Station clocks and explore.

space: Classic colonial home on Caulfield Park hill. Between park, train station, trams and popular Glenferrie shopping and resteraunt strip. 15 minutes from city centre. Both rooms consists of a very comfortable queen / double bed and you have everything you need for a nice and relaxing stay in Melbourne. summary: Warm and inviting inter-war (between the world wars) cottage in Melbourne's green wedge.  Minutes from transport to the city, airport, LaTrobe Uni Bundoora, RMIT Bundoora. summary: Welcome to the award winning architecturally designed apartment in a historic heritage building located on Melbourne's iconic Flinders Lane.
space: The spacious, creative and light filled apartment has two small bedrooms, one bathroom with bath and modern kitchen. It features lots of tactile ply joinery with lots of plant life. The apartment will suit couples, singles and also small families.  The apartment has been featured in many books and magazines including Kinfolk Home, The Design Files, The Saturday Papers, Inside Out and Belle to name a few. It features high ceilings, large northerly facing arched windows on all sides of the apartment and a balcony with views over the Arts Centre. It is filled with natural light and sunshine. name: Parkland apartment on edge of CBD
summary: Light filled and quirky in a quiet parkland neighbourhood. The apartment is on two levels with a mezzanine floor and high windows on both upper level rooms. The two bathrooms are connected by a shared toilet.  The living room has a large north facing window looking onto the courtyard garden
space: This stylish "A" framed contemporary apartment of the late 70's is one of 16 apartments (8 on either side of a central driveway) comprising two levels and a courtyard garden. The upstairs level has two bedrooms (one is a mezzanine open to the living room) and two bathrooms sharing one central toilet. The main bedroom has a comfortable king sized bed. The second mezzanine bedroom has a fold out single couch/bed.   Downstairs is an open plan kitchen/dining/sitting room with floor to ceiling double glazed, north facing windows opening onto an attractive Japanese styled, courtyard garden. The kitchen has AEG appliances and the second bathroom has a washing machine and dryer. Off street parking available for one car. Parkville is an historic inner Melbourne suburb adjoining the central business district north of the city and home to the gracious campus of The University of Melbourne and the Melbourne Cemetery. As it's name implies this suburb abounds in beautiful open parklands. Apartment "

We are 10 minutes walk to both North Melbourne Station and Melbourne Central station, 7 minutes walk from Flagstaff station and about 15 minutes walk from Southern Cross Station (the main station for intercity trains and also the arrival/departure point for the Melbourne Airport SkyBus). North Melbourne is rapidly becoming one of inner Melbourne's most sought after suburbs and is full of fantastic cafes and restaurants.  It is also home to some wonderful little bars. We are 400 meters away from the renowned Queen Victoria Markets, truly one of the worlds great food markets.

name: Inner city apartment with amazing views
summary: Spacious apartment, in leafy Parkville. Inner city location, across the road from Royal Park golf course. One block from Princes Park with its 3.14 km running track. Enjoy your own sunny room and private bathroom, access to large living area, kitchen & laundry. Short walk to tram and train.
space: Located in a quiet, central part of inner Melbourne, this sun-filled apartment is the perfect place to explore everything the city has to offer. Set in a contemporary building, I would love to share this large apartment with you. Located in a quiet area, it is a short tram ride to the central city district. It is surrounded by parklands (Royal Park and Princes Park). The apartment features floor to ceiling windows, providing sensational views of Melbourne. Bedroom  Your room has floor-to-ceiling windows. It is a cheery and bright room. It has its own private balcony.  It comes with a large bathroom for your exclusive use. Wardrobe space is available. neighborhood_overview: Parkville is a quiet and tranquil oasis, 4 kms from the Melbourne Central Business District CBD). Renowned for its world class university and hospitals, what people also discover are its beautiful parklands, its fantastic collection of Victorian homes, its fantastic access to public transport (train and tram) which can take you in and out of the city quickly, and its proximity to other bustling areas such as Brunswick, the new cool and funky area of inner Melbourne., and Carlton, the italian centre with its pizzerias, stylish clothes stores, cinema and bookstores.
notes: This is a quiet building in a tranquil parkland setting. Its difficult to imagine you are in a big city!
transit: The apartment is perfectly located for you to enjoy and explore the abundant restaurants, bars, pubs, art galleries, bookshops, theatre, musical venues and shopping. For those of you who enjoy walking,  the CBD, Zoo, Victoria Market and Carlton can be reached on foot, otherwise the Route 19 tram is just around the corner. This Route runs along Elizabeth Street into the city or can take you into the heart of Brunswick.  Trams are frequent and our stop is number 17.  The Upfield train line is also close by (Royal Park station). This takes you directly to Southern Cross station to link to the airport skybus or to attractions such as Puffing Billy (Belgrave line link).  Making your way around Melbourne arent difficult when you stay here.
access: I fit in with guests' needs as best I can.  Security The building is fully secure. Access is by swiper. Swiper replacement, if lost, is $50.
interaction: I can help out as much or as little as you need.
house_rules: No Smoking.  No additional guests unless cleared beforehand. Guests need to be respectful of others - not throwing objects from the balconies or making excessive noise so as to cause a nuisance.
host_about:
Retired professional. Enjoy theatre, music, reading, cycling, walking AND travelling - anywhere off the beaten track. 
I travel light and really enjoy staying with people, rather than impersonal hotels. I want to experience the day-to-day life of where I go, learn tips from the locals on what to do, where to go ... and generally, blend in and live like a local. 
As a host, I am friendly, open and very much enjoy getting to know people, who they are, what they do and sharing life's experiences. 
Fluent in italian, happy to provide italian conversation for those of you interested in brushing up on your language skills!!!!

name: Treehouse apartment in Fitzroy
summary: Spacious, light filled one bedroom apartment in the heart of Fitzroy. The apartment is in a prime location with amazing cafes, restaurants, shops and transport options on your doorstep. Yet it's also very peaceful and quiet and surrounded by trees.
space: Ideal for a single person or couple, the apartment is very light, clean and spacious with a lovely atmosphere.  It is often compared to a tree-house as it is surrounded by greenery, flowers and birds.  As you near the entrance stairs you are surrounded by bamboo, the front door is overlooked by a huge fig tree (bare in winter and full in summer) and the balcony and living room are shaded by an amazing and huge lemon scented gum tree whose smell wafts inside with the breeze. Built in the 1950’s the space is clean, and the design classic. It has thick parquetry floorboards and large windows.  The furnishings are stylish and uncluttered.  The space is quiet and private and on entering you will notice that it has a great energy about it.  In the bedroom, there is a very comfortable, high quality queen size bed. Fresh towels and bed linen are provided. There is hanging space in the bedroom closet and ample storage for bags.  There is a single mattress available for a third person if necessa

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in the heart of Fitzroy - one of the most iconic, vibrant, hip and central neighbourhoods in Melbourne. Fitzroy is known for the best shops, restaurants, bars, galleries, music, graffiti, street life and people watching.  Truthfully, there is too much going on to begin to list it all! Walk to Brunswick St, Gertrude St, Smith St, Lygon St and the Melbourne CBD.  The apartment is located opposite Carlton Gardens, Exhibition Buildings and the Melbourne Museum. It is close to Melbourne University, RMIT and St Vincent’s Hospital.  All important services are within short walking distance.  There are two supermarkets, many cafes, banks, pharmacies, bakeries, restaurants, parks, a cinema, music venues and more.
notes: If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Let me know if you'd like an early check in or late check out as it may be possible.
transit: Walk to Brunswick St, Gertrude St, Smith St, Lygon St and the Melbourne CBD  (less than 1km or 10-15 mins). I have guests tell me that they didn't end up taking any transport as there is so much to explore on foot. The trams 86, 96 and 112 are all within a five minute walk. Parliament Train Station is a ten minute walk (or 3 minute tram ride) and can take you anywhere in Melbourne.  There are many bike paths in the area. If you feel like hiring a bike and discovering Melbourne as a local, The Humble Vintage is just around the corner.  Sports enthusiasts can easily access the Melbourne Cricket Ground (MCG), Melbourne Tennis Centre and Etihad Stadium on public transport.
access: The apartment has wireless Internet access.  There are all sorts of books and brochures about things to do in Melbourne.  The shared laundry has a washing machine and dryer.  There is an off street parking space for one car.  Once the reservation is confirmed I’ll send through the check in details.  Check in is at 3pm and check out at 11am.  Late arrivals are fine as I can leave the keys waiting for you in a lock box.  If you need to drop your bags off earlier, just let me know when you make the reservation as it is often possible to arrange this.
interaction: The apartment is your own quiet and private retreat right in the heart of Melbourne.  I am overseas at the moment so I won’t be there to meet and greet you when you arrive.  I have a Property Manager who is available if there is an emergency so I will provide her details once the reservation is booked.  Of course I am also available on email or text message if you have questions at any time. On arrival you will also find comprehensive information about the apartment and things to do in the area.
house_rules: No smoking or pets.  Building is relatively quiet so please respect the neighbours and keep the noise down at night. The laundry is shared between four apartments. Access is generally easy but if it's busy there is a laundrette at the end of the street. About a two minute walk.
host_about: Lover of art, dance, music, love, laughter, water and the magic and mystery of life.  I listed my much-loved apartment on airbnb in November 2011 as I took off on a three month dancing trip to the San Francisco Bay Area.  It’s now eight years of sharing my beautiful home with people from all over the world.  I love being part of the airbnb community.  It’s a very sweet, connecting experience.  Happy travels!

neighborhood_overview: A quiet street in leafy Albert Park midway between Melbourne CBD and St Kilda.   A 300 metre walk from the start of a strip of more than 20 restaurants and pubs.  The room is safe, convenient and spacious and air conditioned.  The house is just 3 km from the centre of the city yet  has no through traffic.  All located within 600m: - Beach - Albert Park shops - Cafes, including the Albert Park Deli, Combi Espresso coffee & Hausfrau - Restaurants, including the famed Misuzu's & Lina's Bistro a Vin - Bars, including the Albert Park Hotel & Santiago Tapas - Albert Park grand prix circuit - Melbourne Sports and Aquatic Centre MSAC - 5 minutes on the 12  tram to St Kilda Nearby facilities for sporting activities and the arts include: - Fabulous running tracks at the Tan, along the beach and also around Albert Part and the new Athletics Centre - Public Hire Tennis Courts (en tous cas) available at Fawkner Park. and (hard  court) at the Rod Laver Arena - Public Golf Courses (Albert Park 1.5km)
notes: Early check-in and late check out may be possible - please ask in plenty of time. Leaving bags early (after 0800) is ok. Leaving bags late (until 2200 on your check out day) is ok and a late shower may be possible.
transit: The beach, Albert Park Golf Course and South Melbourne market are within 10 minutes walk.  There are three different tram routes within 500 metres [Routes #1, #12 and #96] - all go to the city when north bound.  The #12 and #96 go to St Kilda when southbound. The #1 goes to South Melbourne beach when south bound. There is also a bus two streets away that travels from Port Melbourne to Elsternwick rail station.
access: Getting from the airport:  Public transport consists of the Skybus from the airport (T1, T2 and T3) to the city (or less regularly to St Kilda from T4) and then a tram (but you must buy a MYKI card $5 and then load the card) before you board the tram. Taxis cost between $65 and $80 plus tolls.   Ask for details of a limo driver who will meet you at customs, carry your luggage and bring you to the door for a fixed around $85 to $90.   A number of guests have used him and then booked him when they leave too.
interaction: Interaction is at the guests' discretion.   Most catching up occurs on checking in and just before dinner time.   As I mostly work from home I am never far away.  I have prepared some walks that will introduce you to Melbourne and its little secrets - to take you to Melbourne as Melburnians use and see Melbourne. I have also prepared a driving guide for those who wish to visit the Great Ocean Road and Otways (my favourite cycling destination) - what we highlight the sights the paid tours miss.   You can rent a car and all major car rental companies (Avis, Hertz, Thrifty and Budget) are within 1500 metres.   For most enjoyment of the Great Ocean Road plan a 2-3 day trip and if you take 3 days you can return clockwise via the fabulous Grampians instead of retracing your steps. Usually my day starts much earlier than the guests as I am out on the bike from as early as 0530 and guests usually end their day much later than mine
house_rules: Apply common courtesy and common sense.   No food or drink in the bedroom and clean up after yourself - promptly.    Common courtesy and common sense includes the following: •Turn off the air conditioner & lock up when you go out.  •Always place the key back in the key safe immediately after use to ensure it is there if you lock yourself out.  •Clean up any mess you make & never leave food scraps around.  •Do not take food or drink to the bedroom (water excepted). •Please ask before inviting guests back.
host_about:
Relaxed but keen on staying fit and healthy. Work in the legal field. Love good food.  Enjoy exploring other places. 

Enjoy cycling. Regularly make the one hour drive to cycle along the Great Ocean Road.  Ridden in many Euro countries, the USA and Japan in the last couple of years.

neighborhood_overview: Before all the hipsters moved in (just joking! We love hipsters!) Thornbury has historically been home to many Greek-Australians and Italian-Australians, so there are a plethora of great deli's and food stores. Now they sit comfortably alongside hip cafes, bars, health food stores and music venues, mostly along High St, which is just a few minutes walk.  The flat is walking distance to these great sights and attractions: CERES Community Environment Park - a Community park and garden with a nursery, organic market, cafe and mini farm plots Merri Creek bike and walking path - takes you on a scenic route to the city without needing to ride / walk on the road Wesley Anne bar, eatery and live music venue  Psarakos fruit & vege market - cheap fruit, veges, meat and fish only 10 minutes walk away Thornbury Theatre - live music venue Northcote Social Club - a great pub with good meals and a place to see some of Melbourne's finest bands
notes: NA
transit: Croxton Train Station (on the Epping line, also called the South Morang line) is 300m East and will take you to the CBD (Flinders Street Station) in 19 mins. For footy fans, you can get to the famous MCG in 14 minutes by train! Tram stop (Route 112) is 300m west, taking you directly to Brunswick St (Fitzroy) in 12 mins, Melbourne CBD in 22 mins and St Kilda in 50 minutes.  Tram stop (Route 86) is 500m east, taking you down High St (Northcote) in 5 mins, then to Smith St (Collingwood) in 15 minutes and into the CBD in 25 mins. Off street parking is available for one car.
access: Guests will have access to the entire apartment exclusively for their own use. They also can access a shared space at the back of the block where there are a number of shared clotheslines. They can also use the shared laundry on the ground floor, which has coin-operated clothes drier and washing machine. NB. The apartment is equipped with its own washing machine.
interaction: I like to leave my guests to enjoy their stay in Melbourne without interfering too much.  I'll be in touch in the days leading up to your arrival to confirm what time you'll check-in. Late night check-ins are no problem. I'm available 24/7 on my mobile and email if there are any problems. I will then stay in touch via the odd text message or phone call to make sure everything is going smoothly.
house_rules: Complying with the following House Rules is a requirement for permission to enter and occupy the Property.  4.1 General requirements a) Guest and Visitors must comply with all House Rules and instructions from the Host during their stay; and b) Guests must notify the Host of any disputes or complaints from neighbours as soon as is practicable. 4.2 Noise and Residential amenity a) Guests and Visitors must not create noise which may disturb neighbours, especially between 9pm - 8am and during arrival and departure at any time throughout the occupancy; b) Offensive noise is prohibited and may result in termination of your stay, loss of rental paid and extra charges for security and other expenses which may be deducted from your deposit;  c) Guests and Visitors must not engage in anti-social behaviour and must minimise their impact upon neighbours and local community. 4.3 Visitors a) As the apartment is not large, and is in close proximity to neighbours, no more than two Visitors are permit
host_about:
Shaun is a social worker and a musician and Lanie works in communications. We're from Melbourne, Australia.

We love Melbourne for all it's good things (coffee, shopping, cultural diversity and live music) and all it's one bad thing (unpredictable weather).

We rent out our 2-bedroom flat in Melbourne and love to let our guests in on the little secrets that turn them from a tourist into a traveller.

Things we can't live without: sunshine, books, family, fish'n'chips on the beach in summer.

neighborhood_overview: North Melbourne is an inner suburb of Melbourne, Australia, 2 km north-west of Melbourne's Central Business District. Its local government area is the City of Melbourne. North Melbourne is bounded by the CityLink freeway to the west, Victoria Street to the south, O'Connell and Peel Streets to the east and Flemington Road to the north. Formerly known as Hotham, it was essentially a working class area, with some middle class pockets and was one of the first towns in Victoria to be granted Municipal status. Today it continues to undergo gentrification, noted for its Victorian architecture, cosmopolitan demographic, commercial and older industrial areas.

Hi there, I'm Chloé! :)
A friendly and very accommodating host, happy to share with you my very neat & eclectic styled home; my local knowledge on great places to go, explore & visit will be all yours. Also I'll endeavour to help with directions so you can navigate around Melbourne's city with ease. :)

I enjoy meeting new & interesting people from all over the world.
I love chocolate! I love to display flowers at home and think pets are adorable- (hopefully you like cats?) I'm a mother of a two fur babies: Bella, 7y.o black & white tuxedo girl who is playful, curious and loves to welcome new guests! Then there's Tinka, a shy little old tabby rescued from the street life; she is shy, calm & affectionate in small doses. Happy to chat with guests about the area, life n such but generally do my own thing.

Enjoy the many restaurants in Melbourne- there are some good ones, and some great ones! I love my local area, here we have everything just a short stroll away.
Other then that, you'll find both a comfortable place to stay & a very friendly host. Look forward to meeting you! ;)

host_about:
I have very special interests in Life and Life matters. I love to cook, travel, hear your life experiences & stories and connect with people from our hearts. I love being the helper for people's shining. Recently I've come back from a near death experience riding the rapids of the mighty Zambezi at Victoria Falls - with a renewed sense of purpose and feeling inspired.

Having had conventional medical and alternative, complementary medicine practice of 30 +yrs and more than 35,000 hours consultation experience, I am putting my message in a book and a program called "What our Bodies Ache For - uncovering repressed longings hidden in body symptoms, anxiety, depression and chronic illness"
I would like to dispel the myths of current medical thinking and inspire our systems to work on the cause rather than just the symptoms. Preventative medicine is not just about screening physical bodies but need to address underlying dis-ease ( lack of ease) in our emotions, mind and spirit).

I have a  luscious Retreat set up called ANGELUS in Mount Dandenong Melbourne, a 23 acre property for stress management and residential workshops from where you can have transformative experiences, make new friends, embrace new ways of being and return home with more of your Essence.

Therapies for a more focussed physical rejuvenation, revitailisation utilising the best practices in wholistic, complementary and functional medicine are accessed from the clinic in Burwood Melbourne. Details can be got from (Website hidden by Airbnb) 
My message? - "Live, Learn, Love, Grow"

neighborhood_overview: So folks, you should know, Newport is not a bustling hub of nightlife, shopping and entertainment. It is a middle class, safe area with lots of young families. It’s a real experience of normal life in Melbourne.  Newport is considered inner city. It has a regular train service to the city centre that takes 20 minutes to get you to Flinders St. Station. Newport Railway station is only a kilometre from our home or a 10 minute walk. There are a few really good cafes' restaurants and pubs near us. They may not be readily visible to a traveller so be sure to ask for recommendations from us or a local.  Mason street where the train station is located, has a butcher, fruit and vegetable shop, pharmacy, bakery, cafe, IGA Supermarket, hairdressers, atm, and cafe's. So food is readily accessible close to home. There are great parks, walking trails and bike paths to explore. I highly recommend Newport Lakes (which is 5 minutes from our home), where you can feel like you are in the country and not
notes: NA
transit: Train, bus, bike or car are all good modes of transport in the inner-west. Our street has free unlimited street parking if you are travelling by car. There is also a taxi rank located at the train station and bus interchange in Newport. You could live well enough here without owning a car. The frequent buses meander through the streets connecting Newport train station with Yarraville via Altona North & Kingsville/Spotswood. That enables you to get to schools, strip shops, doctors, dentists & Altona Gate Shopping Centre for all your basic needs.  For entertainment, etc., you can easily get to Yarraville for the Sun Cinema, cafes, and shops, etc; or visit Williamstown for a wide variety of eateries, cafes, pubs, market, etc. If you want to get to the beach, the train from Newport station to the beach is only a 5 minutes trip to Williamstown Beach station, or if you prefer pools then the Leisure Centre is on the bus route along Mason St.  For cyclists, the bike path along the foreshore is
access: Whilst staying with us you will have access to: Fast wifi. Laundry facilities are available if staying longer than the minimum 2 nights. A separate refrigerator for your food and space in the pantry to store other food. Kitchen facilities for cooking simple  meals. DO NOT COOK FOODS THAT REQUIRE A LOT OF FRYING AND SPICES. OUR KITCHEN IS NOT DESIGNED FOR ASIAN/INDIAN STYLE FOOD PREPARATION  Please note that between 6 − 7 pm the kitchen will be pretty busy cooking the family meal, so where possible try to prepare food outside of this time.

So we understand and will be led by you and always respect your privacy. But if you want a chat or need advice or assistance with anything we are available.
house_rules: You are welcome to use the kitchen but no cooking after 9.30pm. Please note you are responsible for cleaning up after yourself, and replacing any breakages. In The Interest Of Hygiene, We Ask That You Use The Dishwasher To Ensure Proper Cleaning Of Utensils And Cups, Plates Etc. Large items like saucepans etc will need to be hand washed.  Long term guests are asked to assist with unpacking the dishwasher also. The coffee machine is a barista quaility one and NOT for general use, (even by me   ) But if you are around in the am when Jim has fired it up he will happily make you one. If you are a long term guest (more than a week) you are responsible for maintaining the washing of the towels and bed linen you have been provided for in your room. On your departure your do not need to do anything in regard to washing linen etc. We also ask that you do not eat or drink on your bed, or use oils or body lotions that may stain the linen and make it look unpleasant for future users. If soiled  li
host_about:
Hey future guests and friends,

Thanks for taking the time to read our profile. 

We are a regular Aussie family with a home that many tell us has a relaxed and welcoming vibe. Which is GREAT because that’s how we want you to feel when you stay with us. 
You need to know that our home is not a sterile hotel, or a grungy hostel or even a display home. There is the normal detritus of modern family life with children. But that aside you can be assured your environment will be clean, your linens fresh and your room cleaned and dusted before you arrive. There can be a lot of laughter, love (the occasional tantrum) in our home, and you are welcome to share in that, or to have privacy and limited interaction if that is your preference. We will be led by you. ☺

Above all we just want you to be comfortable!

We love keeping fit. Enjoying time with friends. A good red wine or a craft beer AND of course travelling!!

We have been having airbnb guests for 5 years now. It has been truly rewarding and we have met remarkable people from every continent, many we are still friends or in contact with. 

We look forward to meeting you too ☺.

summary: You enter from a quiet heritage laneway, with bluestone stables and architectural remnants from the mid 1800's  through our workshop to the studio. It is three storeys and includes two bathrooms,  three bedrooms, living/kitchen, laundry, verandah and views over the rooftops. Two or three minutes walk to Brunswick, Smith or Gertrude streets. Close to all Fitzroy has to offer, yet peaceful at night.
space: Our studio is down a quiet back lane in Fitzroy. we have 1 x Double, 1 x Queen plus 1 x Single beds. We can provide a cot suitable for 0 to about 3, or a cot or kid's single bed if you are a family of six. *You enter on the ground level through our workshop. When you enter through your doorway you will find a laundry with washing machine and a separate bathroom with shower and toilet. Also a small bedroom with a single bed. *On the middle level there is a fully equipped kitchen with dishwasher, microwave, fan-forced oven, and all you need to cook...that's if you can resist the many fabulous cafes in the surrounding streets!The living area has comfy couch and opens onto a verandah to take the air and dry the washing. Still on this level a bedroom with queen size bed. We can put a child's cot or a small bed in this common space. *On the top level there's a double bed and en-suite bathroom with bath and views over the rooftops. neighborhood_overview: Fitzroy has been called "the centre of the universe" for good reasons! An exciting area with a focus on the visual and performing arts, food, fashion and independant retail. It takes about fifteen minutes to walk to the city and is close to the major hospitals and universities, Melbourne Museum and the Exhibition Building. Twenty minute walk to the Victoria Market, or a tram ride. Thirty minutes to Collingwood Children's Farm and artist's/farmer's markets. Much has been said of Brunswick St, running down the middle of Fitzroy and it's unique atmosphere and galleries, venues, bars and cafes. Gertrude St was the first block outside the city to be sub-divided and has many bluestone buildings from the 1850/60's that now house quirky be-spoke designer makers and "stand alone" retailers ...from men's hats at SMART, Alec to organic bread at Fatto a Mano. Gertrude St Projection Festival transforms the street in winter annually. Smith St epitomizes the incredible blend of cultures that call Fit
notes: You should be aware the house is over three levels, open plan and there are stairs. It is made of bluestone and recycled materials, was once an old stable, so quirky and atmospheric...not your average dwelling!
transit: A tram on every corner! The Smith/Gertrude Sts tram, the number 86 takes you down Bourke St into town. The Brunswick St tram, number 11, takes you down Collins St into town and to Docklands. The Nicholson St tram, number 96 takes you all the way to St. Kilda. Two minutes walk to Victoria Parade trams and buses.  Five minute walk to Johnston St buses. If you are driving we have on street parking,so it is sometimes difficult to find a spot. Better to use the many forms of public transport around us. A cab to the airport takes between 30 minutes to an hour, depending on the traffic. Or catch a tram into the city and the airport bus from there. To get to Southern Cross Station (Spencer st station) take the Smith/Gertrude St tram number 86.
access: You will have the whole house to yourselves and your entrance is separate from ours. The backyard has a table and chairs so you can enjoy the garden. We can arrange car off street from time to time, by arrangement. This car space is not always available so feel free to ask.
interaction: We are close by and available to answer any questions you may have. It is a private self contained space and we will probably not see each other unless we meet in the garden....great spot to chat under the grapevine as the sun goes down.
house_rules: *We have school age residents so the backyard is only for daytime use as we go to bed early. *Likewise this is not a place for parties, sorry. *Smoking outside or on the verandah. *rubbish and recycling needs to be in the relevant bins on tuesday nights. *you must wash your own dishes and keep the space clean.
host_about: We design and make things, objects and wearable and have lived in Fitzroy for many years and seen it blossom and grow. We are surrounded by galleries, performance spaces, providores of food, markets and interesting stand alone makers. Wouldn't live anywhere else!

name: Fitzroyalty - stylish and central
summary: In the heart of Fitzroy, immerse yourself in the Melbournian lifestyle. A stone's throw from everything that Melbourne has to offer.
space: This top floor apartment is in a brilliant location, 80m to Brunswick Street and the Carlton Gardens and everything on your doorstep (pubs, bars, shops, cafés, supermarket, gardens – you name it). This light and modern, fully renovated apartment has city views, and a stylish living area to relax in.  Although you will be in the heart of it all, my place is a warm, comfy and quiet refuge. It is not unusual to spot rainbow lorikeets on my balcony, while sitting on the sofa!

neighborhood_overview: I love Fitzroy because is is walking distance to the city, and is the best place to dwell when you are in Melbourne. Amazing brunch/lunch and dinner options are all on your doorstep. As are galleries, fashion boutiques, music venues, bars and local Aussie pubs.  Plenty of parks and public transport too. My place is a short walk to: - Brunswick Street (80m) - Gertrude Street (500m) - Smith Street (850m) - Royal Exhibition Buildings (250m) - Melbourne Museum (250m) - Carlton Gardens (150m) - St Vincent's Hospital (700m) - Melbourne City (950m) - Lygon Street Restaurants (950m)  - Theatres (Princess Theatre & Her Magesty's Theatre) (1km) - Melbourne Cricket Ground: MCG (1km)   There is also a small supermarket and bottle shop at the end of my street (approx 100m).
notes: NA
transit: Everything is quick and easy to get to from my place! You can WALK to the city in about ten minutes (through the Carlton Gardens).  Alternatively you can jump on #86  and #112 TRAMS at the end of my street (approx 1 minute walk). If you need the TRAIN, Parliament Station is a quick 10 minute walk from my place. I have maps to give you to make this easy, it is all very simple and convenient.
access: You will have access to the whole apartment including: Large bedroom  - city view - new queen size bed with luxury sheets and quilts - waffle robe and slippers - build in robe with coat hangers and drawers - iron and board  - tissues - soft lighting and good light blocking curtains Fully equipped kitchen  - Nespresso coffee provided - tea and milk provided - cooking basics such as oil, salt and pepper, and some sauces - breakfast cereal also provided Living area - city view - Smart TV with Netflix and Stan (and DVD player) - WIFI  - stereo with connection for iPod. - large comfy sofa Balcony - city view - luscious green balcony  - two comfy rattan cane chairs to enjoy a glass of wine at sunset - hammock available Bathroom - thick and soft towels  - soap, shampoo and conditioner provided - hairdryer - lovely hot shower Parking - parking available (please advise in advance)
interaction: My phone is always on for any questions that you may have.  If you need an early check in or late check out I may be able to accommodate this, please let me know.
house_rules: - please be respectful of my neighbours - please respect and care for my belongings - no smoking
host_about: I I love travelling and try to go on at least one big adventure a year.  When I do I love staying with Airbnb and meeting new people along the way.

host_about:
I have very special interests in Life and Life matters. I love to cook, travel, hear your life experiences & stories and connect with people from our hearts. I love being the helper for people's shining. Recently I've come back from a near death experience riding the rapids of the mighty Zambezi at Victoria Falls - with a renewed sense of purpose and feeling inspired.

Having had conventional medical and alternative, complementary medicine practice of 30 +yrs and more than 35,000 hours consultation experience, I am putting my message in a book and a program called "What our Bodies Ache For - uncovering repressed longings hidden in body symptoms, anxiety, depression and chronic illness"
I would like to dispel the myths of current medical thinking and inspire our systems to work on the cause rather than just the symptoms. Preventative medicine is not just about screening physical bodies but need to address underlying dis-ease ( lack of ease) in our emotions, mind and spirit).

I have a  luscious Retreat set up called ANGELUS in Mount Dandenong Melbourne, a 23 acre property for stress management and residential workshops from where you can have transformative experiences, make new friends, embrace new ways of being and return home with more of your Essence.

Therapies for a more focussed physical rejuvenation, revitailisation utilising the best practices in wholistic, complementary and functional medicine are accessed from the clinic in Burwood Melbourne. Details can be got from (Website hidden by Airbnb) 
My message? - "Live, Learn, Love, Grow"

neighborhood_overview: Boredom should not be an issue as there is a 18 hole golf course, several gyms and an aquatic center within 2 km from the house, not to mention a scenic bike track.
notes: The house is in a safe and secure neighborhood, but for added ease of mind we have security cameras covering the front of the house and the side. All rooms have lockable doors and guests get a set of keys peer room.
transit: The bus leaves out the front of our house and the local train station in down the road, we also provide bikes free of charge so guests can take them to the station or even into the city. If arriving or leaving by plane, train or any other method of transport, we also offer a pick up/drop off service for $40 AUD whenever possible, a taxi from the airport could be close to double.
access: Guests have access to everything in the house and as seen in our pictures except our bedroom and our cars :-) So Kitchen, BBQ, Spa, Gym etc. is at at your disposal.
interaction: We live at the property and love to socialize, but as the house is huge all guests will have an option of privacy if they wish. There is a living room for each bedroom so space is never a problem. We have lots of suggestions for things to do and places to see, we have even made several tours for you to follow, all collected in our house information book, this also includes the most price competitive options for travel and car rentals etc. With experience of working in hotels Ryan and Rhiannon also have prepared a welcome pack you will find in your room with lots of information and maps that will be useful during your stay. We even have self serve room menu with drinks and snacks if you run out of you own!
house_rules: We would appreciate it if people booking, please make sure your profile has a picture of you  :-)  As the house is full of artwork and custom made furniture we only accept young children if full accountability is taken for any damages, we hope you can understand. We do not allow pets unless specifically requested and agreed to beforehand.  We do not allow smoking inside the house, but do have an area for you outside. If you loose the house keys we may charge for replacement of locks. We offer pick up and drop offs to airport or city if available for only $40 AUD, but please plan ahead. If you damage or break something you have to compensate or replace it if possible. We do not want you to feel as a guest staying with us, but as a friend that lives with us, make yourself at home. Only thing you can do wrong is not ask a question if you have one. We look forward to meeting you and sharing our home and city with you. Kind regards Ryan & Rhiannon
host_about:
Ryan and Rhiannon are your hosts
Ryan is a fashion designer and trained tailor, working from home.
Rhiannon also works in fashion as an account manager.
We both love movies, socializing with friends and enjoying everything Melbourne and life has to offer.
We recently completed out dream home and a large part of out dream was to be able to share it with others, keeping a fresh perspective on you surroundings is important, so you never forget to keep discovering. There is no better way of doing that than with friends from all over the world.
Ryan has lived 17 years in Norway and only came back to Australia when he was going to University.
Since then he has gained experience as a concierge, bartender etc. so between Ryan and Rhiannon you could not wish for better hosts.

name: Queen BR + Private Bathroom in Huge CBD Apartment
summary: Truly unique inner-city oasis only one block from Swanston Street, with a comfortable, friendly, older-style  household environment. This is a queen-bed room with a private bathroom in a large 1980s warehouse conversion, with a private garden courtyard and direct street access.   Specialising in medium and longer stays for academics,  students and relocations: we can help you find your find your feet in Melbourne, including assistance and references for finding longer term rental accommodation.
space: This is a queen bedroom in a 240 sq.m two-storey warehouse conversion that even has it's own backyard.  This room, which also has a large private bathroom, is well sized and fully furnished, including a study desk and built in wardrobe.    Guests have access to the whole house and all facilities - including a full kitchen, separate laundry, large rear courtyard, large living and dining areas.  WiFi is included although not unlimited.  There are  hundreds of books to read and DVDs to watch - but you'll be far too busy - as the house is only minutes walk from Melbourne's best restaurants, bars, galleries, gardens and shopping; including China Town, Victoria Market, Emporium and Melbourne Central. Please note that this is a 30 year old conversion in a 150+ year old building so not everything is 'shiny and new'; it is however very large and comfortable and very friendly.  Cheaper rates for weekly and monthly rental are available, and should apply automatically through the booking form. Rig

neighborhood_overview: The East or "Paris" End of the City is the sophisticated side of the inner city, home to some of Melbourne's best shopping, great bars and restaurants, as well as jazz clubs, theatres, parks and gardens - and some hidden city-living gems - like my house.  We are walking distance to RMIT and Melbourne Universities and one block from Melbourne Central underground station.  The neighbourhood itself is a bit of a hidden gem, with large townhouses converted from historic warehouses and factories, tucked down every laneway.
notes: I work in the CBD and can arrange checkin during much of the day, however checkin must be arranged in advance, as I am not automatically available. Like many Australian houses, we have off-peak storage hot water - this means hot water is generous - but not unlimited.   Please remember: whilst this is a comparatively quiet and peaceful neighbourhood,  Melbourne is a 24hr city, which means people, vehicles and bustle, particularly on the weekends.
transit: Trams, trains and buses are all within a block, including the free tourist City Circle Tram.  The house is within the CBD "Free Tram Zone" and Mykis are also available for guests use.  On street and garage parking is available at a number of nearby locations.  Airport bus shuttle drops offs and pickups can be made to a number of nearby hotels. Walking distance or short tram ride to all major inner-city attractions, including: RMIT, Melbourne Uni, MCG, Rod Laver (Tennis Centre),  Etihad Stadium, Southbank and Casino, Aquarium, Flinders St Station, Southern Cross Station, Botanic Gardens, Fitzroy and Carlton Gardens (Museum and Exhibition Building), NGV, Brunswick & Gertrude Streets Fitzroy, Lygon Street, China Town.
access: Guests have access to the whole house and all facilities.
interaction: I am usually home at night and am always contactable if you need me.
house_rules: Room is a maximum of two people by booking - no unbooked guests or overnight visitors are allowed.  ALWAYS lock the front door, including when you are in the house. Please turn off the lights and heating when you leave the house. Please respect the neighbours when you are coming and going. There is no smoking in the house, but you are welcome to smoke out on the back terrace. I have a dog - he likes everybody and will happily take you for a walk around the park if that takes your fancy - otherwise you may comfortably ignore him, other than not leaving the front door open. The apartment is set on Richmond Hill very close to Bridge Road and Swan Street shops and cafes. Walking distance to the Tennis Centre, the MCG and a quick tram ride into the heart of the City. The living area has a super comfy couch, flat screen TV with Netflix and amazing sound.  The is a large teak dining table for six right next to the fully equipped kitchen. Private balcony with breakfast bar and plenty of plants. Heaps of storage, European style laundry and washer dryer.  The six metre high windows on the first level in the main living area include an automatic blind for shade in the mornings and an amazing view in the afternoon and evenings. You can watch the moon pass by from the couch! The master bedroom on the second level has a king bed, TV, heaps of storage and private ensuite. The views of the city at night are fantastic. name: Cosy nest in vibrant eclectic area
summary: This is a space to enjoy, a place to come and read a little, dream a little, reflect a little. It is light, quirky, and quiet, only a stones through of the Yarra  river/bush, the Abbotsford Convent Arts Precinct, markets, galleries, music,  bars, restaurants and shops. It has all the convenience of being in the middle of things, but at the same time you can go home and shut the door on it all. This is my home with the trappings of home;  books, space to draw, paint, play and cook.
space: Designed by its architect owner, a property as restorative as this is rare, in Melbourne’s densifying inner city. This one-of-a-kind residence regenerates and nourishes with its design, while enjoying the neighbouring vitality of Little Vietnam and the bourgeoning Johnston and Hoddle strip.    With Gertrude and Smith streets a wander away, guests can experience some of Melbourne’s most celebrated bar’s and eateries. The Everleigh, Culter & Co, Saint Crispin, Huxtaburger, Po Boy Quarter, Forester’s Pub & Dining, Anada and the Builders Arms, to name but a few.   The proximity to the Yarra River, with its many biking & walking trials, the Abbotsford Convent precinct and Studley Park Boat House - Abbotsford has become one of Melbourne’s most highly sort after suburbs to reside in.  Over three levels, this unique property boasts a ground floor studio, opening onto a lushgarden; first floor deck, living and dining and a mezzanine second floor, hanger bedroom. With underfloor heating and all

neighborhood_overview: I love Abbotsford for its mix of local characters. There is no describable demographic but a wide range of ages, ethnicities and socio economic backgrounds. You can walk to all kinds of different places be it Asian supermarkets or craftsmen making furniture. There is also a great range of eateries from Asian to boutique beer and designer icecream all within walking distance. Then you can  go home and relax in your own little nest, in this quiet backstreet/lane.
notes: NA
transit: Train, tram, and bus are all within walking distance. This is a very bike friendly area with both off road and on road bike tracks at the front door. There is a bike shop around the corner who has been known to hire out a bike or two. Parking is not available in Little Charles street but off street parking can be arranged if needed.
access: Guests have the run of this 2.5 story house and garden. There is a gas kiln outside which can be used by arrangement.
interaction: Guests have full privacy. I like to meet guests on arrival where possible so they can ask any questions and then you are on your own.
house_rules: Please look after the house and it will look after you. Water the garden occassionally, put the rubbish out once a week on Monday night and you need to bring the bin (garbage cans) in off the street or the council will fine me. The house only caters for two people who share a bed!
host_about: An observer I love wild, natural places, and fast cities. I love to travel and am currently working quite often in country areas, which allows me to make my house available to others. I read alot and there are lots of books, novels, art books, magazines etc... I also like to cook so the kitchen is reasonably well equipped. I live close to the city near the river and there are lots of places to walk both along the river (bush) or different urbanscapes ( Collingwood, Fitzroy and the city).

Relax in the Powlett Reserve or on Darling Square.    Smile a friendly greeting at the people you pass, grab a morning coffee from the George Street cafe, enjoy an afternoon vino in the Fitzroy Gardens.  Shopping at the discount designer outlets
notes: (1) We try to avoid gaps in our calendar. Sufficient broadband is provided for normal usage (email, surfing, youtube, (Hidden by Airbnb) etc) but data-intensive use may result in the internet speed being shaped. Use of illegal peer-to-peer or torrent download services is specifically prohibited.

Born in Melbourne, grew up in Melbourne, and this great city is home.  My work in management consulting and executive education takes me around Australia, to Asia, the Middle East and Europe.

Happy to answer your questions about Melbourne or my properties 

;-)

notes: The house is in a safe and secure neighborhood, but for added ease of mind we have security cameras covering the front of the house and the side. All rooms have lockable doors and guests get a set of keys peer room.
transit: The bus leaves out the front of our house and the local train station in down the road, we also provide bikes free of charge so guests can take them to the station or even into the city. If arriving or leaving by plane, train or any other method of transport, we also offer a pick up/drop off service for $40 AUD whenever possible, a taxi from the airport could be close to double.
access: Guests have access to everything in the house and as seen in our pictures except our bedroom and our cars :-) So Kitchen, BBQ, Spa, Gym etc. is at at your disposal.
interaction: We live at the property and love to socialize, but as the house is huge all guests will have an option of privacy if they wish. There is a living room for each bedroom so space is never a problem. We have lots of suggestions for things to do and places to see, we have even made several tours for you to follow, all collected in our house information book, this also includes the most price competitive options for travel and car rentals etc. With experience of working in hotels Ryan and Rhiannon also have prepared a welcome pack you will find in your room with lots of information and maps that will be useful during your stay. We even have self serve room menu with drinks and snacks if you run out of you own!
house_rules: We would appreciate it if people booking, please make sure your profile has a picture of you  :-)  As the house is full of artwork and custom made furniture we only accept young children if full accountability is taken for any damages, we hope you can understand. We do not allow pets unless specifically requested and agreed to beforehand.  We do not allow smoking inside the house, but do have an area for you outside. If you loose the house keys we may charge for replacement of locks. We offer pick up and drop offs to airport or city if available for only $40 AUD, but please plan ahead. If you damage or break something you have to compensate or replace it if possible. We do not want you to feel as a guest staying with us, but as a friend that lives with us, make yourself at home. Only thing you can do wrong is not ask a question if you have one. We look forward to meeting you and sharing our home and city with you. Kind regards Ryan & Rhiannon
host_about:
Ryan and Rhiannon are your hosts
Ryan is a fashion designer and trained tailor, working from home.
Rhiannon also works in fashion as an account manager.
We both love movies, socializing with friends and enjoying everything Melbourne and life has to offer.
We recently completed out dream home and a large part of out dream was to be able to share it with others, keeping a fresh perspective on you surroundings is important, so you never forget to keep discovering. There is no better way of doing that than with friends from all over the world.
Ryan has lived 17 years in Norway and only came back to Australia when he was going to University.
Since then he has gained experience as a concierge, bartender etc. so between Ryan and Rhiannon you could not wish for better hosts.

host_about:
I naturally gravitate towards people who are open-hearted, generous of spirit and self aware. Most of the people I am surrounded by are making a positive difference in the world or are on a spiritual or personal growth journey of some kind. 

I love my work and work for myself. I am a Film Producer, working on a global film collaboration project. We are producing a psycho-spiritual film to inspire the audience to discover what it takes to live your life everyday  in love and joy.

I value heart felt, emotionally intimate connections with friends and associates. I enjoy people. I love going out listening to music, theatre and dancing. I am fit, eat heathily, don't work too hard these days and appreciate being outdoors in nature.

On my bookshelves you will find mostly find books on psychology, spirituality, health, business & money.

The best holiday I had was being in Cuba for one month with a women from Calgary who I had met the year before in Thailand. Our trip to Cuba cemented a lifelong friendship. I love the music and dance in Cuba and the simplicity of life. I also love being in Paris. I will always remember my first day in Paris because I was awestruck by the beauty all around me plus I always feel romantic when I am in Paris. Needless to say, romantic comedy is one of my favourite film genres.

I used to be an adrenaline junkie but I am so pleased to say that gone are the days of busyness, gone are the days of being addicted to activity and stress and gone are the days of covering up feelings of not being good enough with over achievement. Phew!! That's a relief. 

Today, my life is peaceful, joyful and mostly serene and whilst there are some limits, I have managed to achieve a certain amount of freedom about how I spend each day. 

One of my philisophies on life is, "People do the best they can in any given moment. And whilst at times that best may not feel so great, it is that person's best in that moment."

I am also mindful that we only have 168 hours in each week and that doesn't seem like many hours to me so I make sure that I live my life in joy as much as I possibly can.

summary: Our one bed apartment is ideal for singles or couples. It is perfect for those wanting an inner city experience but not in the CBD. We find lots of people choose the destination because of proximity to relatives or friends and also the variety of very good cafes & pubs.
space: Comfortable secure flat in interesting converted Historic Brickworks in Brunswick. Close to Sydney Road, lots of pubs, bars, cafes and restaurants, plenty of public transport in every direction and on the correct side of the city for the airport. notes: Internet is available and provides unlimited access though NBN. The password can be found on a Telstra fridge magnet. Myki cards; use as required and top up at any 7/11 or Post Office for the guests who follow. Guests travelling with a car may note that there is limited street parking on Pottery Court,although this is free unlimited as is the parking in the surrounding streets. However the carpark facing Pottery Court is for the residents of the Kiln Apartments and if parking there you should take care NOT to park in the designated marked areas.
transit: It is easy to get to any area of Melbourne by public transport or as is more usual, by car. Lots of bike tracks if you know where to look and public bike hire is available . Check your Melbourne website.
access: Guests have full access to everything in the flat. We do not live there and nothing is off limits.
interaction: We have email communication from first inquiry. Either myself or a member of our family have telephone contact upon quests arrival in Melbourne and we arrange to meet personally at the apartment with the keys. We are very happy to hear at any time from our guests.
house_rules: Please water plants if there has been no rain. You can pick the figs if it is summer and they are fruiting! At end of stay please leave clean and tidy.  Please check that both electric heaters are switched off before leaving. When placing rubbish in the communal bins please make sure you use the bins at the rear so as not to overload the front ones. Of course we trust that if you are smoker you will not smoke inside the apartment. N.B. Our Check In and Check Out times can be flexible depending on guest change over so please ask us. We do discourage Check In after 8.30pm except for inevitable emergencies. If you will be needing the extra bedding please let us know prior to your arrival so it can be made ready. MYKI cards are provided for use; please top up if necessary at Post Office or 7/11 store for benefit of following guests. KEYS....... We do not normally provide two sets of keys as we like to retain a security key in case of problems. However if it is vital that you require a seco
host_about: I have been hosting on Airbnb since 2011. Now that my husband Ian has retired he has joined with me in the fun of meeting guests from all throughout Australia and around the world. We live in Brunswick as we have family in the suburb and we love to tell everyone visiting Melbourne what a great place Brunswick is. It is blessed with plenty of public transport which makes it easy for travellers to enjoy the CBD, the beaches and all the premier sporting venues that Melbourne excel at. The MCG for cricket and AFL football , Melbourne Tennis Centre for the Australian Open, Flemington Racecourse, home of the Melbourne Cup. These world class venues are a short PTV ride away. Brunswick also offers  great local amenities such as parks, swimming pool, library, bicycle tracks. We enjoy all these with our family, not to mention the food.... Spoilt for choice. Plus bars, pubs and nightclubs............ Maybe not always for us!

neighborhood_overview: Kooyong is an exclusive suburb adjacent to Malvern, Hawthorn, and Toorak. We are only 7km from the city centre.  This is a quiet and safe residential neighbourhood. Kooyong Village is blessed with many cafes and is frequented by locals doing their shopping and enjoying their coffee! Our home backs on to Kooyong Park and the Yarra Trail bicycle and pedestrian path, which is one of the most scenic cycling routes in Melbourne. It is a gentle 30 minute ride into the city from our place on a dedicated track.
notes: Let me know what your special interests are as I keep up-to-date with the arts scene and what's happening in and around Melbourne.
transit: Kooyong Train Station (Glen Waverley Line) is 500m from our house, at the end of our street. This provides convenient access to the city centre which is only 10 minutes by train.   We are also well serviced by two tram routes: the 16 tram is also on the corner of our street and winds its way to the city via St Kilda, and the 58 tram is a little further away, but provides a more direct route to the city via the Chapel Street shopping precinct and the Royal Botanical Gardens. We are conveniently located at the Toorak Road exit of Citylink which is only a 25 minute drive from the airport (off peak).
access: The Pool House has its own private, separate entry so guests can be completely independent. Guests have access to the garden pool and spa. Most of the time they will have this area to themselves.
interaction: The Pool House has it's own private, separate entry so guests can be completely independent.  Most of the time guests will have the garden and pool area to themselves. We enjoy chatting with our guests and pointing them in the direction of interesting local spots and eateries, but we are also respectful of guests' privacy should they prefer it. I personally meet and greet guests upon their arrival and I am always contactable during their stay.
house_rules: For the comfort of other guests, smoking is allowed outside only. No loud music to be played after 11pm. Please ensure that heating or cooling is turned off before leaving the Pool House. No more than two visitors at a time.
host_about:
We are privileged to live in a lovely part of Melbourne. We have one young adult son left at home, and one small friendly indoor dog that does not enter the guest area of the garden. 

I am self employed and work mostly from home, which is ideal for having guests come and stay.

I love walking, cycling, cooking, reading, theatre, live music and travel and I try to keep up-to-date with what is happening in and around Melbourne, so I am able to recommend restaurants, activities and festivals. I am particularly fond of quirky events around town and I am always up for a new experience!

When we travel we forgo the homogeneous chain hotels and stay in anything from camper vans to B&Bs to boutique hotels--accommodation that reflects a bit of the culture around us. I particularly love destinations that offer an insight into a completely different way of life.

I look forward to welcoming you to our part of the world and giving you some great tips on Melbourne.

summary: Bright, easy and comfortable to live in and so close to the train, tram, supermarket, shops, restaurants.
space: Welcome to Melbourne! This is a really comfortable flat to live in. It has a great kitchen with a dishwasher, a very large open plan living/dining room space plus study nook. The master bedroom is large and has a huge walk in wardrobe which will be half emptied so you can use it. The second bedroom has 2 single beds in the form of a 'captain's bunk bed' and large BIR with a window onto the balcony. There is a large bathroom with separate shower and bath. Also a separate toilet and european laundry cupboard with washing machine, dryer and sink. Large square sized balcony with BBQ and lounging chairs, with a view of the city off to one side. The flat is on the first floor and a 2min walk to Newmarket station which gets you into the heart of Melbourne in under 10 minutes. 2minute walk to the tram too. host_about:
Hi!
I was born and raised in Australia and lived 5 years in Europe. 
My husband and I met while working in Europe. Funnily enough we were 2 Australians who were working for a small dance  company in Switzerland in Vevey. Eventually.. we fell in love got married and moved back to Australia, we still continued to work in Europe from Australia... but then Herbie came along last year. Our son was born in may 2011, he's just great. We are now still maintaining a little of our performing lifestyle by touring a show to canada.. but these days we are strongly based in Melbourne.

name: Split Level City Centre Apartment + free parking
summary: This light, bright, quiet apartment is right in the centre of Melbourne. It is spacious and has three double bedrooms so comfortably sleeps six people. Just a few minutes walk will bring you to all the special places such as CBD,  Federation Square, the Botanic Gardens and sporting venues like the MCG and Rod Laver Arena.The apartment is on the third floor of this low rise building and is reached by stairs.
space: This is a modern light filled apartment on the 3rd (top) storey of the building and it is reached by stairs. It has the benefit of air conditioning on both levels. It is only a short walk to the CBD and around the corner from the Royal Botanic Gardens and parklands. There are galleries, concert halls and theatres close by. A short walk across the parkland will bring you to the MCG, the Tennis Centre and other sporting venues on Swan St. There is plenty of public transport -  trams and buses on St Kilda Road; more trams on Clarendon St and Sturt St. Flinders St station is a ten minute walk from the apartment and you can catch a train from there to anywhere in Melbourne. South Melbourne Market and Clarendon St is the local shopping centre. When you first arrive and need a few supplies there is the IGA supermarket across the street, a two minute walk. name: Grand Old Victorian Hawthorn Home
summary: A beautiful classic 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom Victorian home with big rooms and high ceilings in a sought after suburb only 8kms from the CBD. Situated on a quiet, leafy street, yet just a few minutes walk from cafes, shopping, trams and express trains.
space: We've been renting out our home to visitors and locals since 2008 and everyone who has stayed has always loved the place from the minute they walk through the door. It's an ideal corporate rental for executives on assignment or families relocating to Melbourne or just coming for a few weeks to visit friends. Situated on a quiet, leafy street it is just a few minutes walk from Camberwell cafes, restaurants and top quality shopping. Camberwell station is only a few minutes walk with fast trains providing easy access to the CBD and eastern suburbs, including most major businesses, universtities and hospitals. Suits both executives and families who like light filled, spacious living with easy access to all that Melbourne has to offer.
