The main bedroom has a queen size bed, wardrobes, chest of drawers and ensuite with a shower over the bath. Second bedroom has a queen size bed and wardrobes. neighborhood_overview: South Melbourne has that wonderful blend of historical significance, modernity and village atmosphere all with a location that is second to none. Between the city, the beach, Albert Park Lake, the Botanical Gardens and of course with the heart of the suburb the wonderful South Melbourne market. For the little one's there are parks galore, swans to feed and trams to ride. I discovered South Melbourne ten years ago - and i am still discovering "new" charms....all the time.
notes: Everything and anything you would ever need to shop, eat and drink is in walking distance Highlights are: o South Melbourne Market (open all weekend) corner of Cecil and Coventry St (basically turn right out the door, walk to the lights (clarendon st), turn right, walk 3 blocks to Coventry and turn left (its at the end) o Coventry St itself is filled with awesome shops and even better cafes (take your pick they are all superb o Pubs (plenty of good ones including the water rat over the road, honey bar up on the clarendon st corner, golden gate and the George on Coventry st) o Resto’s o Excellent Greek at spitiko on Park st (just cross over clarendon and keep walking -  if you hit cecil st you have gone to far) o Excellent small plate style food on clarendon half way along to Coventry st at Hercules Morse o Excellent pub dining at Lamaro’s on cecil (bit more upmarket) o Great seafood at the south Melbourne market Claypots on the corner of cecil and York – very atmospheric o Really good
transit: Ok super convenient public transport. Firstly the airport trip is around 25 minutes in a cab which until Melbourne airport link arrives is the best transport option for a group. Secondly there is a tram stop outside the front door for the number 1 tram - takes around 6 minutes into Federation square. A few hundred meters walk you will be able to pick up the 112 which takes you to the Casino and Convetion centre (5 minutes) and then up Collins St. There is one parking spot in the drive directly in front of the Loft - free parking  worth its weight in gold in inner city Melbourne these days
access: Guests have the entire Loft to themselves. Laundry facilities are shared but available at all times. Single car spot available directly in front of the Loft in the driveway to the property (off-street) "which is a rarity in this part of Melbourne. The garage next to the Loft is a car park for the graphic design studio next door to the Loft.
interaction: I love meeting Guests and sharing local knowledge of living in South Melbourne for the last ten years and watching the suburb continue to evolve into a very special Melbourne "village"
house_rules: Simply to be friendly and respectful of the space. However stuff happens and i don't sweat the small stuff - i simply want my guests to feel as though they have a home away from home
host_about:
Right now I consider myself a very lucky person. For my work I get to both help people in need (working in International Development) and to travel to many interesting and wonderful places around the world. I like to eat street food and drink in local bars and avoid wherever I can, the bland (you could be anywhere) 4 and 5 star hotel experience. Food, wine, running (not all at the same time mind you) are all interests as well as any local festival that might be within coo-ee!!

As a guest I am friendly and unimposing having travelled so much in developing countries my expectation is that the experience is "what it is" and a "positive" attitude will mean you make the most out of it. As a host well, shortly, following a renovation I will have a cool new apartment in "the worlds most liveable city" Melbourne on the air so am very excited about this and giving all the lowdown on my great city!!

neighborhood_overview: Just a hop, skip and jump from the CBD, Richmond is a vibrant and thriving neighbourhood with all the benefits of inner-city living. If you're wanting to get amongst the action, Richmond's the place to be. Everywhere you look Richmond oozes character; from its narrow laneways covered in magnificent street art to its trendy microbreweries and hidden foodie delights. Richmond showcases an eclectic mixture of fascinating architecture which pays homage to the neighbourhood's working class heritage, with converted warehouses contrasted with gorgeous Victorian buildings and ultra-contemporary designs.

Use the PTV (Public Transport Victoria) App to help you get around Melbourne. It's free and easy to use.

You have access to a large upstairs  deck, private balcony and private en suit bathroom.  It is a medium sized room with a super comfortable, queen sized bed with a latex mattress, feather pillows and crisp white cotton bed linen with either a duvet and/or blankets. The room has a private en suit bathroom. It is fairly small but it is modern, fully functional and with plenty of hot water. There is a small fridge in the room and tea and coffee making facilities.  The room has two french doors which open onto a private balcony where you can sit overlooking the street. You also have access to the large upstairs private deck with comfortable outdoor furniture. neighborhood_overview: See my description but I am close to everything in Central Melbourne. Close to CBD,  universities, hospitals, Queen Victoria market, supermarkets, restaurants, shopping malls, boutique shopping strips, art galleries, theaters, music venues, pubs  and wine bars, Melbourne zoo, Melbourne aquarium, parks and gardens, sporting venues, car hire, public transport, tour operators and much more.  Most are walking distance or short public transport ride.
notes: NA
transit: I am 5 minutes from the two major public transport routes to the entire city of Melbourne.  I am 2kl from Southern Cross station which is the country link railway station.
access: Private room. Large upstairs deck. Private balcony. Kitchen and meals area.
interaction: As much or as little as the guests like. I live here but work during the day. I am usually here at breakfast time and most evenings and sometimes during the day. I am self employed so sometimes work from home. I converse easily with guests but also do not mind if guests keep to themselves. The entrance  to the house and the guest room is separate from my part so guests can be completely private if they wish. I am not offended if people keep to themselves.  Sometimes I am very busy with work and can't get caught up in long conversations, or relax, but this is rare.
house_rules: Smoking is ok but only on the outside deck or balcony please.  You are welcome to have visitors but just let me know in advance. And please no overnight stays unless they are paying guests.  Alcohol consumption is OK but please, nothing to excess and no inconsiderate behavior. I have to work in the morning!
host_about:
My name is Lucy and I'm a middle aged professional who works in Melbourne's CBD. I have a house which occasionally I share with my 22 year old daughter, Ellie. 
My daughter and I have traveled a lot and stayed in airbnb's in a number of countries. We found it a great way to find affordable, comfortable accommodation while meeting great people. We hope you will enjoy our place as well. We would love the opportunity to introduce you to our vibrant city. We both love travel, art, books, photography, good food, wine, lively discussions and friends.

summary: A romantic art deco tree top apartment minutes from a trendy cafe and restaurant strip has an art house feel of spaciousness and light. So gorgeous film crews have hired it for films, photographic sessions and art house films.
space: Welcome to this Romantic Art Deco Garden Delight!  This beautiful 2 bedroom apartment is all yours, and includes 2 large bedrooms and a grand bathroom.  This apartment has two bay windows, a large eat-in kitchen, sunny, leafy Juliet balcony overlooking the courtyard garden for bright breakfasts and there is also a formal dining area in the lounge for your enjoyment. name: Quiet Studio Next to Train Station
summary: Private self contained ground floor studio apartment located in downtown Rosanna.  It is a one minute walk to the train station, but quiet, because we are nestled deep in the shopping strip, with vibrant cafes and eateries.  The room has a private ensuite toilet, but you share the upstairs shower.
space: Private cozy self contained ground floor studio apartment located in downtown Rosanna.  Great access, as it is a one minute walk to Rosanna train station and the Rosanna shopping strip.   If you don't feel like going out, you have a kitchenette, a 42 inch plasma TV, and fast internet. The apartment is quite new and very cozy, in a heritage building, formerly tenanting a cobbler and then a conveyancer. The room has a private ensuite toilet, but you share the upstairs shower.  It is very quiet most of the day, as it is set back from the main street.

neighborhood_overview: Apartment located in downtown Rosanna, a one minute walk to the train station and the Rosanna shopping strip.  We are right next door to vibrant cafes and eateries, including Greek, Italian, Thai, Chinese, Vietnamese restaurants, and even an gourmet burger joint.  Two minutes away, we have Rosanna Parklands, a 15 hectare park with creek, playground, and even a tree house.  If you want to explore further afield, you can use our bicycles.
notes: NA
transit: Probably the best access to public transport of any Airbnb in Melbourne. The train to the city stops just outside the door, and also, there are buses for east west travel, for example, an 8 minute trip to Northland shopping centre. Transport from the airport is easy;  take the Melbourne airport bus (Skybus) from outside the airport terminal to Southern Cross train station in downtown Melbourne, and then cross over to the Eltham/Hurstbridge metro train line.  Get off the train at Rosanna station, and you are there.  Alternatively, it is about $50 by taxi. There is parking nearby, and Melbourne city is a 29 minute direct train ride, with at least 4 trains per hour.  We are 2km from Austin/Mercy Hospital and 4km to La Trobe University.
access: Kitchen, laundry facilities, shower
interaction: My roommate and I live on the floors above the flat, and we are are very friendly;  we are from Canada and Singapore, and together, we can communicate in French, Spanish, English, Mandarin, Cantonese, Hokkien, Teochew, Malay, and Indonesian. We work and study at La Trobe University during the day, but are happy to visit when we are home.

host_about:
Founded in 2006, the Boutique Stays Accommodation Group is an accredited tourism business providing quality houses and apartments to singles, couples and families in Melbourne. Distinguished by a commitment to high property standards, impeccable presentation and personalised customer care provided by a team located in the bayside suburb of Port Melbourne. 

A bespoke collection of 60 homes in Melbourne’s most iconic and popular neighbourhoods are handpicked to make guests feel at home with peace of mind that a dedicated, professional customer service team are ready to support each and every guest seven days per week.  A range of one, two, three and four bedroom homes are available in a choice of twenty suburbs in Melbourne for guests visiting family and friends, holiday makers travelling with or without pets and business travellers.

The Boutique Stays Accommodation Group has welcomed over 4,000 guests and 150 pets into our homes in the past year and look forward to welcoming you for your first or return visit.

name: Budget-friendly double room
summary: Great northside location. Bedroom with double bed, high ceilings in older character-filled home. Free wifi. Very close to public transport & nearest supermarket. Good coffee just a few blocks away. Two friendly miniature dachshunds. Great budget option if you are tired of hostel accommodation. Please note we do not provide additional storage: the room is set up for one or a couple of tourists/travellers, with 1 suitcase or two. If you have a carload of stuff please book elsewhere.
space: PRICE OF ROOM CURRENTLY REDUCED AS I AM USING IT FOR STORAGE FOR MY FASHION LABEL AND WILL REQUIRE SOME (LIMITED) ACCESS DURING YOUR STAY. Our home is a long, narrow, older-style house, it was built in 1920, with double brick plastered walls and high ceilings. Close to three trams, a supermarket, train station and bus stop. Your guest room contains a comfortable queen-sized double bed, with free wifi  included.  PLEASE NOTE that we only offer the *one* guest room in our home, available to one booking at a time, so you will not be staying in a house with any other guests! We get this particular inquiry often, I'm assuming it happens a bit out there in Airbnb land, so hopefully this makes if very clear. You will be sharing our home with us as we go about our normal lives.  This does mean exactly that: we very much enjoy having laid-back guests in our home, but we will continue to go about life as normal while you are here. This is not a 5-star hotel, it is our home. We are not super-tidy

neighborhood_overview: An eclectic and vibrant area in Melbourne’s inner north, Brunswick & Coburg bustle with a diverse cross section of interesting street cafes and restaurants flaunting a spectrum of global flavours. Easy walking distance to bars, cafes, inexpensive restaurants, shops & post office (the house is within easy walking distance of both Lygon Street and Sydney Road). The area has plenty of cafes and bars, lots of artists and musicians live in the area and there is an active live local music scene. Historically it was a poor working class/migrant area which has recently become gentrified. There are lots of front yards still with lemon trees and fig trees growing to reflect this history. There is a great article in Broadsheet Melbourne (a local online paper) describing some of the excellent places you can eat out in Brunswick for under $10 if you feel like googling!
notes: EARLY ACCESS: please don't show up earlier than your check-in time. Your room will not be ready, and you will not be permitted to check-in early. Sometimes I must admit to being very absorbed in my work which can mean I stay up very late working in the home office, however I am very quiet when I do this! It can also mean that sometimes if I am absorbed in planning a photoshoot or some such thing, the house is not tidied for a couple of days. If neither of these things would bother you then I am sure you will enjoy staying with us.
transit: Trams: #8 and #1 tram are both a very easy 2-3min stroll away - both trams will take you in to the city. #19 tram is also an easy walk. Trains: the Upfield train line is approx 900 metres away on the west of Sydney Road. Buses: the 510 which travels between Essendon & Ivanhoe via Brunswick, Northcote &Thornbury goes right past the door, the nearest bus stop is a two minute walk.
access: Guests have access to most rooms in the house, including the shared bathroom, laundry, toilet & kitchen. Every room in the house, in fact, except for my home office, and our bedroom. You are welcome to make yourselves at home! During the warmer months we enjoy dining and relaxing on the back deck, enjoying the sun. You are most welcome to do the same.
interaction: It is up to you how much interaction you have with us. Some guests like to retreat to the privacy of their room, or spend all their time out and about exploring Melbourne. Other guests like to spend time chatting around the kitchen table with us. Either is welcome, however please keep in mind that as I work from home, a lot of the time I do need to actually get work done rather than socialise.
house_rules: No smoking indoors. No extra pets, please (two dogs and some fish is quite enough). If you use the kitchen, please clean up after yourself. You are welcome to use the washing machine but please do ask first. The bathroom is a shared facility - please leave it in the same state you found it. Please remember to close & lock your window and the front door when going out. Our security depends on you! Please show consideration with regards to noise eg loud talking/music/tv/slamming doors/etc early in the morning (before 8am) and late at night (after 10pm). Please don't turn on the central heating without asking first. If you wish to eat in your room, feel free to do so, but please clean up after yourselves. Leaving food & crumbs on shelves and grease in the bed is not the way for a preferred guest to behave, and encourages pests.
host_about: Hey there! I'm a creative, fun-loving, travel-loving, cocktail-drinking, chocolate-eating person. My husband Mick and I love to travel. And when we are not travelling ourselves, we love hosting other travellers in our home. We are pretty independent people, and are happy to leave you alone if you are too - but also very happy to share our expertise if there's anything you would like to know. I'm very often at home, and always available to share all our tips & tricks for getting the very best out of your visit to Melbourne.

neighborhood_overview: Although 100metres from thriving Fitzroy Street, Nelson Street is remarkably quiet in a residential Street. Supermarket, dry cleaning, laundry, 24 hour convenience store, bottle shop all within just a few minute walk.  If you like walking or running, Albert Park Lake is 200 meters away, or you can walk or run along the foreshore to Port Melbourne in one direction, or the St Kilda promenade in the other. If you have kids, the Famous Luna Park is only a short stroll away, as is Acland Street with it's bustling street life and some of Melbourne's best cafes, restaurants and pastry shops. If you love animals, St Kilda has its own Penguin Colony which appears at dusk each night, alongside the St Kilda Pier. St Kilda is a remarkable place. It is situated on one of the most picturesque points of the Bay a short distance from the city, has safe sandy beaches St Kilda is home to a number of elegant gardens and reserves. There are the 6½ hectare heritage-listed Botanical Gardens just east of Bar

The Melbourne Bike Share system is a 3 minute walk from the apartment and it's great for riding around the bay or the lake and surrounding areas. name: Stylish Fitzroy Apartment with Cool Brick Arches
summary: Experience the best of Fitzroy’s most stylish food, wine, and coffee spots from an architect-designed apartment on the edge of the city. The modern kitchen in spotted gum, painted brick walls, and quirky ornaments create a unique, contemporary look.
space: This beautiful Fitzroy studio apartment seeks guests who enjoy cafes, galleries, picturesque gardens and short walks to the centre of Melbourne.  Located in the fabulous Gertrude Street precinct, this elegantly renovated apartment is perfect for an individual or couple who are seeking to stay in a great location.  We generally host longer-term stays, which is why the nightly rate is much lower than similar apartments in the area. If you are seeing this listing for a short-term visit, congrats! You have found a small spot between bookings. :) The apartment includes free wifi, air-con, reverse cycle heating and ceiling fans. It has a full kitchen including microwave, oven, dishwasher and stovetop espresso machine. Enjoy city views from your comfortable queen sized bed, or tumble out to Gertrude, Brunswick, Smith Street or the CBD which are all at your doorstep.
description: Experience the best of Fitzroy’s most stylish food, wine, and coffee spots from an architect-designed apartment on the edge of the city. The modern kitchen in spotted gum, painted brick walls, and quirky ornaments create a unique, contemporary look.
neighborhood_overview: Fitzroy is Melbourne's hippest neighbourhood, and an easy walk to the centre of the city. It boasts cafes, nightlife, and fashion, record, and book stores. The apartment is a few hundred metres from the beautiful Fitzroy and Treasury Gardens.
notes: NA
transit: The apartment is an easy walk to the centre of town. There are many different trams that run from the CBD through Fitzroy, or walk 20 minutes to the subway.
access: NA

The apartment is recently renovated, so everything is in good working order. host_about: We love life in Melbourne and we’re happy to share it with visitors. We’re both northsiders. This means a life of coffee, laneways, beautiful parks and interesting people.

summary: Stay with a local host instead of a hotel.  You will share a WHOLE HOUSE, with your own private bedroom and fully equipped bathroom.  All  the modern conveniences are here. Friendly, knowledgeable host can provide sightseeing advice & local tips.
space: Welcome to Melbourne! Modern town house, your own private bedroom and bathroom, close to many restaurants, bars, cafes and tourist attractions.  It doesn't get much better than this in our lovely and elegant city!! You definitely won't need a car if you stay here.  Also close to Grand Prix circuit.  Vroom Vroom in March!! neighborhood_overview: My home is a peaceful oasis in a bustling and vibrant area. Close by is our famous St Kilda beach, Albert Park Lake, 4 km to central Melbourne (shopping and sightseeing, bars and restaurants) and 5 minutes walk from a busy bayside strip of shops and restaurants on your way to the pier and beach (for Kite surfing lessons, watching the penguins come in at dusk or swimming).    There is also a world class aquatic centre close by and excellent public transport, parks, hire bikes and supermarket within 400 metres. This area is the best in Melbourne and you will love your stay here.
notes: If you are allergic to cats, this isn't for you.  I have one beautiful, long haired cat and the house is vacuumed daily but.......
transit: There are three tram routes (96, 12 and 16) within 300 metres of the house, so getting around on public transport is easy and convenient.  A public transport card (MYKI card) costs $7 to buy initially, then only $7.30 for the daily fare.  If you are hiring a car, you will be given a parking permit for on street parking outside my home.
access: You will have access to the whole house including: living areas, kitchen, laundry, study, computer, WiFi, cable television, balcony overlooking garden, garden, your own room and own bathroom.  Only area out of limits is owner's bedroom.
interaction: Depending on other social and work commitments, it is nice to interact with guests and share a glass of wine or cup of tea.  I am well equipped with knowledge about my local area and sightseeing day trips and happy to provide ideas and advice to make your stay more enjoyable. I love meeting and hosting fellow travellers.
house_rules: NO SMOKING INSIDE NO ILLICIT DRUG USE Clear and Simple House Rules:  Ensure house is secure at all times.  This means locking up properly (including safety shutters) when you leave the house. Keep shared living areas tidy and as you find them No access to owner's bedroom suite area. Arrivals before 9 pm please. No guests other than those booked - this is a private residence. Prefer shoes off upstairs....  wooden floors can disturb people resting or sleeping downstairs. Smoking is not allowed inside the house but there is a covered balcony with table and chairs available for smoking outside. Be kind to the pets.
host_about:
I run a successful consulting firm which keeps me fairly busy during the day Monday to Friday but I still find time to travel overseas every year for at least one month.  I can easily host a single traveller or a travelling couple in my lovely house located in a magical area close to the beach, the park and the centre of our city of Melbourne.

The location is within 400 metres of the famous St Kilda Beach and just as close to the Albert Park Lake reserve where the Grand Prix is held in March each year.

I am in my early 50's, ride a motorbike for fun, love skiing in Europe and am accustomed to having friends and guests stay over and am happy to provide you with ideas for your Melbourne stay over.  

The only reason I occasionally host guests from airbnb is because it provides an opportunity to meet interesting people from around the world.  Therefore, I will look at your profile, to see how you have described yourself and any partner you might be travelling with, to make my decision.  Airbnb stays are very different from staying in a hotel.............. and you need to understand this as a prospective guest.

My experiences with airbnb have been fantastic and I have met people I will know for the rest of my life.  Interesting, happy, engaging, respectful and cat friendly people who have understood how to share the house and amenities.

If you have received a request from me to rent your house, please realise that as a host myself, I will look after your house as if it is my own.

summary: Soak up the natural light from the beautiful steel arched windows of this apartment located at the top of the historic Majorca Building. Set in the heart of the cafe precinct, the flat is bright, spacious, and has a fully equipped kitchen.
space: A minutes walk to Flinders Street Station, Federation Square, Tram to St. Kilda Beach, Arts Centre, National Gallery, Collins Street fashion houses and the Yarra River. Boasting arched windows this well appointed, spacious apartment with jarrah floors and high ceilings overlooks Degraves Street and Flinders Lane. A Juliet balcony adjoins the bedroom with ensuite. The kitchen is fully equipped with cooking utensils and a dishwasher. An entrance hallway leads to an open plan kitchen, dining and living area. Includes separate laundry with both washer and dryer. The apartment is an ideal place to stay to enjoy the activities available during the International Comedy Festival, Melbourne Arts Festival, Summer Music Festival, Midsummer Festival, Formula One Grand Prix, Moomba, Australian Open, Royal Melbourne Show, Spring Racing Carnival and of course the AFL Grand Final.

space: Medley Hall is a residential college of The University of Melbourne.  What this means is that during the University academic year, our rooms are occupied by students.  In the break times (Dec to mid Feb) our rooms are vacant and from $80 per night can live in one of these rooms and located perfectly and accessible by foot to all of Melbourne's favorite spots. Just around one corner is the bistro life of Carlton and The Melbourne Museum and the the University of Melbourne, and around the other are the Exhibition Gardens, the Central Business District, Chinatown, theatres and night life etc. The recent renovations and major building works at Medley Hall includes a lift to help shift between the fully renovated three levels of bedrooms (some doubles), a tv lounge room adjoined to a fully functional kitchen allowing you to cook your own food if you wish, and a modern and beautiful three story high glass atrium. There is no airconditioning in the rooms but there is heating.  The bathrooms are cleaned daily but cannot guarantee the state of these after other guest's use.  We try to maintain the place so our guest feel like this is a home away from home.
transit: Transportation is located a short walk away.  You will find trams and trains and buses that will take you all over Melbourne.
access: Access to all areas unless otherwise notified.  Sometimes we have wedding ceremonies in the mansion part of the buildings.  Guests will be notified if this is the case.
interaction: Medley Hall office is open Mon to Fri 9.30am to 6pm.  After this time we have staff who live on the premises and can be contacted for any emergencies or issues like lock outs or for advice.
house_rules: 18 single rooms per floor.   Each floor has 5 bathrooms (one of which is wheelchair accessible) Each floor has a kitchenette with microwave, kettle, toaster, fridge and dishwasher, Coin operated washing machines and dryers. No smoking on the immediate parameters of the premises or inside. Check in available from 10am Check out at 10am TV lounge and kitchen with complete cooking facilities available.   Tennis table available. All rooms are single bedrooms. Rooms available from Dec to Feb and July only. In the interests of safety, all bedroom and all outside doors must be kept locked.  Medley Hall takes all care but no responsibility for personal possessions. Departure time is 10.00am but arrangements may be made to store your luggage until later in the day.
host_about: This is a residential student college.  We have 55 rooms available to be rented out to guests during the mid year break and the end of year when the students depart.  We are located a short stroll away from the city and the bustling cafe life of famous Lygon Street.  The rate of accommodation is for a single room, equipped with bedding and towel.  There are 5 showers/toilets on each floor and a kitchenette too.  It is clean, fresh and modern simple accommodation surrounded by a beautiful mansion which is heritage listed and close to everything important to visitors to Melbourne.  Happy to provide you with more information.  Just email me.

space: Quiet, 1 bedroom, 1 bathroom apartment with amazing 12th floor views, right in the heart of downtown Melbourne. In building parking, Gym, Sauna, Pool and access to an indoor/outdoor entertaining area. Opposite Melbourne's iconic Southern Cross station, Etihad Stadium, a tram stop and taxi rank, this place really is ideal for the traveler looking to be 'right where the action is'. Those coming straight from the airport can simply jump on the Melbourne Airport Skybus service (about $15AUD) - the bus stops directly in front of the apartment building! Walking distance from Melbourne's Crown Casino, Southbank,  award-winning restaurants, bars and clubs. If shopping is more your thing, this apartment sits opposite a D.F.O (Direct Factory Outlet) and is a ten minute walk from Bourke Street mall, Melbourne Central Shopping District and many boutique fashion stores.  There is even a push bike rental station within a 1 minute walk of the building, for those who live a more active lifestyle!

neighborhood_overview: Right near the famous Royal Botanic Gardens, active people will delight in the motivation provided by thousands of Melbournians lapping 'The Tan' every day. Or you can stroll through the gardens as you make your way on foot to the city centre of Melbourne. This is the perfect place to base yourself while you explore everything Melbourne has to offer. Close to the Melbourne Cricket Ground and many sporting stadiums. There are also many shops, cafes, restaurants bars and clubs nearby.
notes: No smoking. I prefer no shoes inside but that is up to you.
transit: The location couldn't be more much more central really, and in truth, I rarely use my car when going out for leisure as I much prefer to walk. Your feet will get you into the city in 25min, to Chapel St in 15min, or 10min to Richmond Station( the most central station in the Eastern suburbs)/Swan St cafes. Lawson Grove cafe is 5min away as are the excellent restaurants on Domain Rd.  There is also plenty of public transport: The 246 bus stops right outside the door, trams run into the city from Swan Street and Domain Rd and trains run all over Melbourne from nearby Richmond Station.

name: Edna Walling Cottage (Heritage-listed)
summary: Edna Walling Cottage is a boutique self-contained eritage-listed cottage with accommodation for 2 adults. Set on 3 acres, this 1936 cottage was originally built as a full-sized dolls' house and is located amidst Edna Walling's "greatest achievement," Mawarra, described by Edna herself as "a symphony in steps and beautiful trees."
space: The cottage features a lounge, TV, and kitchen, along with a bathroom and upstairs Queen-sized bedroom. There are also laundry and washing machine available for your convenience. It is also close to a selection of restaurants and cafes and is metres from Sherbrooke Forest. Wineries and berry farms are also nearby.  Whether you are coming to the Dandenong Ranges for a night or a week, you will receive a warm welcome at Edna Walling Cottage, the perfect spot for a break from the hassles of city life. Pets are welcome to the grounds but must sleep outside! There is a dry alcove and heated bedding for your pet can be supplied upon request.

neighborhood_overview: Sherbrooke is located in a rain forest with towering eucalypts, tree ferns and exotic birds and wildlife. Just a short walk away are other heritage-listed public-access gardens. The village of Kallista is a beautiful 15 minute walk past gracious  neighbouring properties. Kallista has excellent cafes with superbn Melbourne baristas and tea-rooms nprovidi ngn Devonshire teas as good asn any in Devon itself.
notes: Occasionally, guests will be staying there instead of the owners.
transit: There is an occasional bus service at the front door and a regular bus at Kallista, a short walk down the hill. Train services at Belgrave meet the bus and service the city.
access: The cottage is found through security gates, down the driveway to Mawarra Manor. Cottage parking is adjacent to the cottage. You have exclusive use of the cottage and unlimited access to the entire 3 acres of heritage-listed Edna Walling garden. You may come across lyrebirds, the owners or guests statying at Mawarra Manor.
interaction: The owners live at Mawarra Manor on  the same property.
house_rules: Please leave the house and grounds in the same condition as you found them.

summary: Great WiFi. Modern & very clean bedroom (Wall mounted 40" Sony LCD TV with active Netflix via AppleTV), dedicated guest bathroom in the heart of Port Melbourne offering an array of shopping, relaxation and dining experiences, within 200m of the beachfront & 600m walk to the 109 tram (Stop 129) at StationPier (Spirit of Tasmania access point). space: North facing bedroom on the top floor in a modern (Building completed July 2013) two bedroom apartment in Port Melbourne. Located one block back from the popular & beautiful Port Melbourne beach, your bedroom opens directly onto the balcony & faces North offering glimpses of the city & Docklands skylines. You will enjoy a luxurious dedicated guest bathroom & shower (Contains infrequently used but SHARED Euro laundry). The apartment is very well furnished.  Access to the front loader washing machine & condenser clothes dryer is included. Excellent Wi-Fi access is provided as well as a fully equipped kitchen, with gas stove, microwave oven, convection oven, dishwasher & fridge freezer should you choose to use it. I also provide clean towels and freshly laundered bed linen on arrival (Bed linen, including DOUBLE pillow coverings, as well as towels are washed weekly for longer term guests).

neighborhood_overview: Port Melbourne has become one of Melbourne's favourite suburbs and for good reason! This leisurely, sun drenched precinct offers an array of some of the finest entertainment, shopping, relaxation and dining out experiences that Melbourne has to offer. Just ten minutes southwest of Melbourne CBD by light rail (Route 109 terminus is approx 600m walk & serviced every 8 minutes) and walking distance to the famous Bay Street, Port Melbourne Pier (Spirit of Tasmania departure point) with foreshore cafes, restaurants and shops. Two major freeways run adjacent to Port Melbourne, The Westgate Freeway (To Avalon airport, The Surfcoast & Great Ocean Road) and Citylink which provides 'express' access to Tullamarine airport.
notes: The bed is fitted with an electric blanket for an extra pleasant & comfortable sleep in the cooler months (Generally April through to August).
transit: The 109 tram is an easy 600m walk away & provides an easy link into Melbourne's public transport system, especially Southern Cross Station & the CBD.  You will need to purchase a "Myki" card to use the system.  These are available at most train stations as well as 7-11 stores across Melbourne. A bus stop is located approx 200m away on Bay St & requires the same "Myki" card for use.
access: The beach is a 200m walk South & the water is visible from street level at building entrance. The building has a rooftop deck/common area offering 360 degree views of the CBD, Docklands & the Melbourne 'Star' as well as Port Phillip Bay. All are quite spectacular at night & great for unique photographic opportunities. Port Melbourne's  main retail shopping strip, Bay St is a mere 200m walk away to the East & offers an increasingly diverse range of food, café, clothing & entertainment options.
interaction: I'm always up for a chat & am interested in my guest's experiences.  I'm happy to provide opinion & advice about local knowledge if sought : )
house_rules: The room is for the individual/couple that booked it, no friends or 'randoms'. Strictly NO SMOKING in apartment or on the balcony.  If you are a smoker, please take it to the rooftop on level 6 or to the footpath at street level.  Your compliance with this requirement is greatly appreciated. I am providing quality bed & linen in a dedicated bedroom, please DO NOT sleep anywhere else in the apartment. The leather couch in the common area is NOT for sleeping on at guest discretion (Bed linen can be easily removed & cleaned, leather couches cannot be easily cleaned). Guests are welcome to use the kitchen for meals, please place used/dirty dishes in the dishwasher for cleaning when finished. Overhead pantry cupboard on the LEFT of the rangehood as well as the lower shelving of the fridge is dedicated for guest use. Please be respectful of the space, treat everything as if it was your own & leave the space as you found it i.e. Clean & tidy. Please ensure you lock the apartment when you leav
host_about: As a trusted SUPERHOST, I like my guests to feel 'at home' & I've enjoyed meeting people from around Australia & around the world!  I'm quite enjoying my Airbnb experience (Since 2012) & I look forward to meeting you and introducing you to Port Melbourne & Australia! : )

neighborhood_overview: This neighbourhood is very quiet whilst being very close to the city, beach, shops, cafes and restaurants.
notes: There is a farmers market 3rd Sunday of every month at Gasworks a few minutes walk. South Melbourne Market is open Wed, Fri, Sat and Sun offers incredible selection of ingredients to cook with and meals from around the globe - approx 20 minutes walk.
transit: Close to number 1 and 109 tram.
access: Guests have access to communal pool, gym and BBQ area.
interaction: On arrival I can spend time with you to show around the apartment and amenities. I will also provide a local map and leaflets to update you about events taking place during your stay and tips for local restaurants and shops. As I live close by I'm also on hand to help out with questions during your stay.  I've often been called on for extras required such as travel adapters, umbrellas and even a scooter! If there's an essential item you may need let me know as I may be able to help.
house_rules: While this is a great place to enjoy the best of Melbourne it is not a party place. The body corporate is very strict on late night parties and noise and fines are issued if security has to be called out. It is a family friendly place and we are looking for considerate people/family who will be respectful of the apartment, neighbours, facilities, and body corporate rules. The kitchen is stocked with basic ingredients so please help yourself to these things and leave behind useful ingredients for others to share too. Please be honest if anything is broken during your stay. Replacing broken items may mean that your bond will not be used. No smoking or pets are allowed. On departure please start the washing machine with a load of washing and leave all other linen and towels in the bath.
host_about: I'm English but have been living in Melbourne for over 15 years.  Having travelled to numerous cities around the world I consider Melbourne the best city to be in the world.

name: Warehouse Apartment in heart of Richmond!
summary: Set back from the hustle and bustle of Bridge Road, this 2 bedroom apartment is located within a former chocolate factory presents light-filled interiors and convenient location a superb combination for inspirational inner city living.
space: Fabulous private location in the heart of Richmond. Bright open plan lounge and dining areas step out to a balcony bathed in sunlight via its elevated setting.  With a link to its industrial past, the chic fit-out to the kitchen / meals zone has it featuring stainless steel bench appliances, a dishwasher and island bench.  The two double bedrooms both have floor to ceiling built in robes. The central bathroom is bright and modern, master bedroom with ensuite. With an abundance of style and character, and just a hop, skip and a jump to Richmond's renowned array of shops, cafes and delectable cuisine, it includes a secure car space, electric heating and secure intercom entry, plus a beautiful bluestone communal courtyard as the cherry on the cake.

neighborhood_overview: Spotswood is ideally located within a walk or short drive to the beach, cafes, restaurants and the Sun Theatre (in Yarraville). It is also home to Science Works  a world renowned interactive science museum in Melbourne, Australia. It is a venue of Museum Victoria which administers the cultural and scientific collections of the State of Victoria Historical Williamstown is a short 5 - 7 minute drive where guests can enjoy a variety of restaurants and cafes,  a swimming beach and botanical gardens. Or perhaps you may wish to enjoy the farmers markets and craft markets that are held regularly along the foreshore.

host_about:
Hello - my name is Anthony and I live in Brunswick, Melbourne.

I am a musician and engineer and interested in finding solutions to climate change.

In my music work, I love singing, playing bass and performing. I do everything from performing at weddings, to parties, to busking (which I love).

I enjoy traveling  and exploring cities of the world, whether in Australia or overseas (Europe especially beguiling - London, Paris, Berlin). 

I am into sustainability, pretty relaxed and easygoing, don't smoke, and enjoy meeting up with friends for coffee and films  :)

Also, I have many interests, and tend to go out a lot of the time, rather than being house-bound.

AirBnB says to include a Life Motto ..... well, I like this one..... "Find something you love doing and you'll never work a day in your life"

Best Regards
Anthony

name: Sunny Room for solo travellers
summary: This is a cosy room with a very comfortable bed. Perfect place to kick back and relax after a busy day.
space: This is a small private room with a super comfortable bed, wardrobe, desk and chest of drawers, with wifi internet access. Perfect for the solo traveller, you could have a couple in this room if your were not spending a lot of time in there and just needed a comfy place to sleep... We are in a zone 1 suburb of Melbourne which means we are only 20 minutes away by train from the Melbourne CBD. It is a 10 minute walk to the Newport train station.  Around the location of the train station you will find a myriad of cafes and shops and other useful business to ensure you have everything you need at your convenience. There is even a supermarket open until midnight walking distance from our home. A short five minute walk from our house is Newport Lakes Reserve; an old quarry turned into a park with a large lake and an abundance of wildlife, a beautiful place to walk or run or even watch the sunset. You can loose yourself in the serenity of the lake and wildlife and forget you are even in subur

neighborhood_overview: So folks, you should know, Newport is not a bustling hub of nightlife, shopping and entertainment. It is a middle class, safe area with lots of young families. It’s a real experience of normal life in Melbourne.  Newport is considered inner city. It has a regular train service to the city centre that takes 20 minutes to get you to Flinders St. Station. Newport Railway station is only a kilometre from our home or a 10 minute walk. There are a few really good cafes' restaurants and pubs near us. They may not be readily visible to a traveller so be sure to ask for recommendations from us or a local.  Mason street where the train station is located, has a butcher, fruit and vegetable shop, pharmacy, bakery, cafe, IGA Supermarket, hairdressers, atm, and cafe's. So food is readily accessible close to home. There are great parks, walking trails and bike paths to explore. I highly recommend Newport Lakes (which is 5 minutes from our home), where you can feel like you are in the country and not
notes: We are more than happy to have longer term guests, but like to get to know our guests first before making this commitment. So please feel free to discuss this option with us when you arrive.
transit: You could live well enough here without owning a car. The frequent buses meander through the streets connecting Newport train station with Yarraville via Altona North & Kingsville/Spotswood. That enables you to get to schools, strip shops, doctors, dentists & Altona Gate Shopping Centre for all your basic needs.  For entertainment, etc., you can easily get to Yarraville for the Sun Cinema, cafes, and shops, etc; or visit Williamstown for a wide variety of eateries, cafes, pubs, market, etc. If you want to get to the beach, the train from Newport station to the beach is only a 5 minutes trip to Williamstown Beach station, or if you prefer pools then the Leisure Centre is on the bus route along Mason St. For cyclists, the bike path along the foreshore is a really nice ride - you have Williamstown & beyond to the east and Altona beach to the west.  As Newport & Williamstown are on a sort of mini-peninsula, we don't get the through-traffic congestion that a lot of other suburbs get. Commut
access: Whilst staying with us you will have access to: Fast wifi Washing machine is available if you are staying longer than  the minimum 2 night stay - NB: clothes dryer NOT available. There is a big outdoor washing line and small indoor drying racks in your room. A separate refrigerator for your food and space in the pantry to store other food. Kitchen facilities for cooking SIMPLE  meals. Oils, and condiments for cooking may be available on request. IMPORTANT: OUR KITCHEN CAN NOT CATER FOR REQUIREMENTS OF SOME PARTICULAR CULTURAL FOODS THAT REQUIRE A LOT OF FRYING AND STRONG SPICES, AS THIS CREATES AN ENVIRONMENT THAT IS NOT CONDUCIVE TO THE COMFORT OF OTHER GUESTS AND OUR FAMILY. Please note that between 6 − 7 pm the kitchen will be pretty busy cooking the family meal, so where possible try to prepare food outside of this time.
interaction: We understand every guest is different. Some people like to have interaction and others a quiet place to base themselves to meet busy schedules. So we understand and will be led by you and always respect your privacy. But if you want a chat or need advice or assistance with anything we are available.
house_rules: PLEASE NO SMOKING ON THE PROPERTY. You are welcome to use the kitchen for SIMPLE meals.  IN THE INTEREST OF THE COMFORT OF OTHER GUESTS AND OUR FAMILY WE ASK THAT YOU DO NOT COOK FOODS THAT REQUIRE A LOT OF FRYING AND SPICES. OUR KITCHEN IS NOT DESIGNED FOR ASIAN/INDIAN STYLE FOOD PREPARATION But please do not cook after 9.30 pm. Quiet time after 10pm IN THE INTEREST OF HYGIENE WE ASK THAT YOU USE THE DISHWASHER TO ENSURE PROPER CLEANING OF UTENSILS AND CUPS, PLATES ETC.  Large items like saucepans etc will need to be hand washed dried and put away. Not left on the dishrack next to the sink. It would be great if you could assist in emptying the dishwasher on occasion. Especially if you are a long term guest. The coffee machine is a barista quaility one and NOT for general use, (even by me  ) But if you are around in the am when Jim has fired it up he will happily make you one If you are a long term guest (more than a week) you are responsible for maintaining the washing of the towels a
host_about:
Hey future guests and friends,

Thanks for taking the time to read our profile. 

We are a regular Aussie family with a home that many tell us has a relaxed and welcoming vibe. Which is GREAT because that’s how we want you to feel when you stay with us. 
You need to know that our home is not a sterile hotel, or a grungy hostel or even a display home. There is the normal detritus of modern family life with children. But that aside you can be assured your environment will be clean, your linens fresh and your room cleaned and dusted before you arrive. There can be a lot of laughter, love (the occasional tantrum) in our home, and you are welcome to share in that, or to have privacy and limited interaction if that is your preference. We will be led by you. ☺

Above all we just want you to be comfortable!

We love keeping fit. Enjoying time with friends. A good red wine or a craft beer AND of course travelling!!

We have been having airbnb guests for 5 years now. It has been truly rewarding and we have met remarkable people from every continent, many we are still friends or in contact with. 

We look forward to meeting you too ☺.

name: Artist Warehouse Apartment Fitzroy
summary: If you like Art, Food, Design and Fashion you haven found the place, Located in the heart of Fitzroy in between Brunswick St and Smith St in what was formally a chocolate factory now a stylish Warehouse conversion, filled with my art and others.
space: me and my girlefriend are renting out the second bedroom in my renovated warehouse apartment, the medium sized room is fully furnished has built in robes, queen sized bed, lounge, books, and large warehouse style windows and polished floors.  The flat rotates around the themes of art, literature, good food and sustainability with a big open space with a large kitchen and dining room looking out onto a well stocked vertical garden so if you love to cook, read, relax and enjoy art this place is for you.     Ideal for guests in Melbourne for a short time who want to live like a local in vibrant Fitzroy and who are interested in staying in lovely bright, Art filled apartment and want something much more then a hotel.

interaction: As a artist i am some times really busy and other times a bit more relaxed and am able to chat, hangout have a martini. I’m always happy to answer any questions you have about things to see and do, there is always a few art openings going on each night in Melbourne.
house_rules: No smoking, No pets, No big Parties apart from civilized dinner party’s. Tidy up the kitchen after your self and respect the space. and be as sustainable as posable while staying ( turn of lights when not in the room and use the recycling bin)       Relax and enjoy your self!
host_about:
I am full time Artist, Writer, Designer, philosophy loving, well traveled, open-minded and sociable. 
I have currently returned to Melbourne after living in Paris and am now starting up a business aimed at helping the creative industry become more sustainable. 
I have lived in france, UK, germany, china, japan, vietnam as well as travailing to numerus other places around the world.

I have a broad range of interest from art, fashion, architecture, design, philosophy, sustainability, news and current affairs and food!  

I studied sculpture and spacial practises at the Victorian college of the Arts and have goon on to exhibit here in Australia and overseas you can see more of my art and writing on  my website (Website hidden by Airbnb) 

On returning to melbourne I renovated my warehouse apartment instilling all my loves of food, sustainability, art, and socializing  at the core of the design.
When it is not being rented out on AirBnB I run a residency program called the philosophical rose (Website hidden by Airbnb) 

I am easy going and love a good glass of wine, food and good conversation.

neighborhood_overview: Wide streets, local gardens, village-atmosphere with easy access to fabulous cafes and shops make Fitzroy one of the most interesting locations in Melbourne. Walking is the way to best explore the diverse, friendly neighbourhood.
notes: I have a very placid 8yo Fox Terrier named 'Peggy'. She is with me most of the time.
transit: Public transport is just 100 metres from the property. A parking permit is available for you to use if you have a car. Please advise in advance to ensure availability. Option 1: From the Southern Cross station catch tram no.11 from Collins St. and alight at Hanover Street stop on Brunswick St. Walk for 30 metres then turn left into King William Street. No 68 is on your left.   Option 2: Take tram no.96 from Bourke Street (slightly closer to Southern Cross Station) and alight at Melbourne Museum on Nicholson Street. Walk across the road to King William Street which is about 25 metres north of the tram stop. Stay on the right side, walk for 100 metres and you're at no 68 King William Street.
access: Guests  welcome to use the central lounge area, kitchen and outside spaces - ultimately, your privacy is always respected.
interaction: I always aim to meet guests on arrival and at a time that suits them as I usually work from home. There will be times guests will have the entire house to themselves as I tend to travel.
house_rules: Your own set of keys will be provided for the duration of your stay. Check-in is after 4.00 pm and Check-out is 11.00am. A strict no-candle rule applies. Smoking permitted outside only. No additional guests without prior negotiation.
host_about: Fitzroy is a hip inner-city locale: diverse, vibrant and very close to the CBD (15 min walk). Your room comes with its own private bathroom. I'm a media professional and have lived in Melbourne for over 20 years. My hosting style is welcoming and fun but you'll have as much privacy as you need. ‘Peggy’ is my quiet and calm fox terrier. What I’m liking right now: cinema, yoga, travel and art.

notes: one condition with booking this place is the vertical garden needs your love and watering, daily in summer but very simple to do with the watering can.

You will need to give the vertical garden a daily water while you stay.  No smoking (even on the undercover balcony), No pets,  Tidy up the kitchen after your self and respect the space. and be as sustainable as posable while staying ( turn of lights when not in the room and use the recycling bin under the sink)       Relax and enjoy your self!
host_about:
I am full time Artist, Writer, Designer, philosophy loving, well traveled, open-minded and sociable. 
I have currently returned to Melbourne after living in Paris and am now starting up a business aimed at helping the creative industry become more sustainable. 
I have lived in france, UK, germany, china, japan, vietnam as well as travailing to numerus other places around the world.

I have a broad range of interest from art, fashion, architecture, design, philosophy, sustainability, news and current affairs and food!  

I studied sculpture and spacial practises at the Victorian college of the Arts and have goon on to exhibit here in Australia and overseas you can see more of my art and writing on  my website (Website hidden by Airbnb) 

On returning to melbourne I renovated my warehouse apartment instilling all my loves of food, sustainability, art, and socializing  at the core of the design.
When it is not being rented out on AirBnB I run a residency program called the philosophical rose (Website hidden by Airbnb) 

I am easy going and love a good glass of wine, food and good conversation.

name: Sofabed in Yarraville - nice sub
summary: NA
space: I have a sofabed in my house in Yarraville.  Formerly a working-class suburb, in recent years Yarraville has experienced rapid gentrification due to its proximity to the Melbourne city centre. Yarraville lies immediately north of the West Gate Bridge, and immediately west of its namesake, the Yarra River. Anderson and Ballarat Streets, in the heart of the Yarraville Village, are lined with refurbished 19th century buildings and dotted with quaint neighbourhood cafés, restaurants and boutique shops. This village atmosphere is anchored by the restored Sun Theatre and the adjacent Sun bookshop. Notable examples of Edwardian and Victorian architecture can be found in Yarraville. The Yarraville Village is home to many award-winning restaurants and cafes. A reflection of Melbourne’s multicultural nature, Yarraville offers an array of world cuisine styles including Greek, Italian, Modern Asian, Indian, Cambodian, Thai, Chinese and Modern Australian.

neighborhood_overview: Residential suburban area. Dandenong centre is 5 minutes by bus (20 minutes walk) - offering very multicultural shopping, cafes and restaurants and entertainment facilities. Swimming pool & gym nearby.  Close to beautiful Dandenong Ranges for weekend hiking.
notes: There is an accessible (disability-friendly) bedroom. Shared bathroom facilities are also accessible / disability friendly.
transit: 6 minutes by bus to train station. Central Melbourne 45 minutes by train. Buses run from 6am to 9pm. Trains run until midnight.
access: Lockable sole occupant bedroom, Bathroom (shared with up to 6 others), Laundry with washer & outdoor  clothesline, shared Kitchen with basic appliances - open 7am to 10pm (each person has storage space & own cutlery/crockery), garden area.
interaction: Owner is present in house on weekends and outside of business hours. House members are independent and there is little social interaction, although the atmosphere is friendly.
house_rules: Guests are to keep common areas clean and tidy at all times. Guests are to respect other guests, keeping a quiet and peaceful space (from 7am to 10pm). No pets, no smoking, no drugs. No overnight guests unless prior arrangements have been made.   Cooking not to be left unattended, for the safety of other guests.
host_about: I love life! Everyday is a new experience! I love to help others and enjoy laughing and watching others have a good time! I am a very honest person who will bust his butt to to achieve goals in life! I am very into nature and will pull over on the side of the road to move a turtle so it doesn't get run over. I like all kinds of weather (except when it is over 80 degrees) I don't like watching people get hurt and I will defend people that can't defend themselves! I don't like people who lie or are high and mighty! People who purposely hurt others are scum and should be put away forever! But for the most part I am a content person who believes that we should all stop and enjoy life when ever we can because we are only here a short time and letting life slip by without enjoying it is a waste! I could go on and on but you get the idea of how I am!

name: Charming 1930s Flat East St Kilda
summary: A very sunny light-filled charming 1930's flat in East St Kilda. Just 5 minutes walk to the fantastic Balaclava shops (cafes, delis, restaurants & more) + tram stop and train station very close by. In 10 minutes you can be in the city.
space: Old style (1930s) one bedroom flat in East St Kilda / Balaclava area, just metres from busy shopping and cafe strip Carlise St.  Carlise st has great cafes (Batch is very close by) as well as bakeries (famous Jewish bakehouse Glicks around the corner), fresh vegie shops and clothes shops all nearby. The apartment is located very close (5 mins) to tram stop and train stations (10 mins train ride to city) and 10 mins walk to St Kilda beach and Acland st (Luna Park). Downtown St Kilda (Acland st area) is very cosmopolitan and busy especially in the summer.  The flat is light filled with polished wood floors and garden views, and is ideal for a couple but also is fine for 2 friends (with one on the sofa bed in the lounge). The flat is not big enough for more that 2 adults but a couple with a small child would also be comfortable. Located on the first floor, the apartment looks out on a beautiful garden setting. Garden is full of flowers and well maintained. Inclusions * Sheets & Towels * F

neighborhood_overview: Balaclava / East St Kilda is a fantastic neighbourhood, the Carlisle st shops have everything - delis, fruit + veg, great bakeries, supermarkets, banks etc. plus great takeaways (lots of sushi!), cafes & restaurants. St Kilda beach is 10 mins walk away.
notes: WIFI is available throughout the flat 24 hours. There is also no TV!
transit: The nearest tram stop is just 30 metres from the flat and train station (Balaclava) is a 5 minute walk away.
access: Whole flat is for rent including WIFI throughout, full kitchen, bathroom + communal laundry out the back of the building.
interaction: I will not be in Melbourne when guests are staying.
house_rules: Smoking is OK on the back porch (but definitely not inside). There is a compost bin (out in the garden) which you can use for vegie scraps. Washing machine and dryer are communal and located at back of flat.
host_about:
I am a well-travelled multilingual Australian who has now been back in Melbourne for four years after spending ten years in Europe (mostly Spain). I run an online magazine / digital hub about yoga and spirituality (The Global Yogi) which is worldwide so I travel quite a bit for that. I do lots of yoga, am a writer and also a musician.

OK life motto: Lean into your fears and your uncertainties, do it anyway and don't be afraid to fly! :)

Come and stay in my retro (1930s) one bedroom flat in East St Kilda! I look forward to hearing from you soon!

name: Beautiful relaxing 3 bdr home & garden
summary: Come and experience this beautiful home combines the peace and tranquility of a safe suburb minutes from the excitement of Marvelous Melbourne and the historic seaside town of Williamstown. You can take a train from the nearby station, a short walk from the house. Three train lines service the area or why not cruise across the bay in a ferry to get to the city sights? You have direct access to the motorway taking you to the wonders of Victoria's wild coastline and world famous surf beaches.
space: Welcome to this beautiful, peaceful home which combines French and Moroccan influences to create a magical space within minutes of Melbourne's city centre. About The House The house flows naturally from the moment you step within from the 'old world' feel of the sitting room, stepped in history with an antique writing desk and magnificent brazillian mahogany bookcase stacked with a wide collection of books for your quiet reading pleasure. It overlooks the front verandah and garden, which is full of native trees. This second large, light-filled living space is located at the back of the house and overlooks the garden. Beautiful French doors opens out onto a delightful terrace and undercover alfresco dinning area with a large Mexican outdoor fireplace. There is a stainless steel barbeque for you to enjoy the outddoor setting and lifestyle. The kitchen is well equipped with european appliances and decorated in rich moroccan colours. neighborhood_overview: Friendly neighbours, a real community.  There is a native park within walking distrance, offering an array of birds. There is also a marine park and bird santuary within walking distance from the house.  Like a country town with all the advantages of city living A beach close by So quick and easy to get to the city
notes: NA
transit: Trains and buses are close by. Newport is a premium station, so all trains stop there.There are three lines which come through Newport station. There are also buses close by. Trains run all night Friday and Saturday night. Uber is also a great option.
access: You access the entire house. There is a verandah at both the front and back of the hosue so you can sit out in the garden to enjoy. Please note there is an independent studio in the garden which you can also rent if you have more than six in your group. It is fully self-contained with a bathroom and kichenette. It can host two guests, with a double bed, sitting area tv and stereo.
interaction: I am available via email and telephone during your stay and my son Dustin is available in person and via phone if you have anything you need. We are both there to answer any questions you may have to ensure that your stay is as enjoyable as possible. We both have a wealth of knowledge about Melbourne and surrounds that you can draw on.
house_rules: No smoking inside the house. Turn lights off inside and in the garden when you go out. Try to keep showers to 3 minutes to conserve water. Water the plants and vegetable patch once a day, during summer Feed the cat morning and night Be respectful of the house and have a great stay!
host_about: Hi, we are a family who loves to travel. We have a French background and speak French. We love living in Melbourne as it combines so many cultures in such an interesting and exciting way - in food and wine, lifestyle and fashion. We also love the sea and enjoy  living close to the beach and having both the rich history of  Williamstown at our doorstep, combined with living in one of the world's best cities -Melbourne.

neighborhood_overview: St Kilda is a complex and interesting neighborhood with a rich history and plenty to see and experience. The local food, art, architecture and all wonderfully diverse and original. And of course the beach is only a stones throw away, as is the historic kiosk and pier and the famous Sea (website hidden) Kilda is home to some of Melbourne's best shopping and favourite restaurants, bars and cafes, including: The George, Cicciolina, Tolarno's, Lau's Family Kitchen, Chinta, Circa @ The Prince, Mirka – Tolarno , Cafe and bar Di Stasio, Newmarket Hotel, Mr Wolf and Dr Jekyll, Phamish, iLforniao, Woodfrog bakery. There are notable boutiques too offering original designs and an array of vintage, recycled clothes, home ware stores and bookshops are also located in St.Kilda. Kite-Surfing on the bay and rollerblading, new skate park, Albert Park Lake and Melbourne Sports and Aquatic Centre are all close-by.
notes: Amazing beach/water and city views of the Melbourne sky line.

When I taste new flavors I grow
When I follow my intuition I loose myself
When I sense I recall
All these unique experiences are unforgettable
And when I return it’s not my ego that is big
It’s my memory”
'Be Authentic'

name: Old distillery quiet and central
summary: A whole floor in a fascinating old distillery & malting complex - a calm oasis within an old industrial area now home to art galleries, fashion houses and creative startups. Minutes from vibrant Gertrude & Smith Sts and a lovely walk through parks to the CBD.
space: Our apartment is part of a fascinating old red brick brewery complex built in 1862 - when Melbourne was 25 years old! It's an amazing oasis in the middle of an old industrial/brewery area now mainly occupied by architects, art galleries, graphic studios and fashion outlets. Although only minutes from vibrant Smith, Gertrude and Brunswick Sts the area is surprisingly peaceful. Your space has its own private door onto one of Collingwood's funky graffiti covered lanes which features a new cafe, artist run gallery and neon artworks glowing night. It would suit a couple or two single people.

neighborhood_overview: Vibrant Smith, Gertrude and Brunswick Steets offer funky shopping, art, food and fashion and are just a short walk away. There are also many interesting cafes and shops to explore in the Collingwood industrial back streets, e.g. the Lemon, Middle and Orange cafe just outside your back door. Melbourne CBD is a lovely 10 min tram ride, or a 20 minute stroll through the magnificent Fitzroy and Treasury gardens or along Gertrude St past the Carlton gardens/Exhibition Building/Melbourne Museum. The MCG and Tennis Stadiums are an easy walk and beyond that the Botanical Gardens and National Gallery. There are many hospitals (St Vincents, Freemasons, Epworth, Eye & Ear) and universities (Melbourne Uni, RMIT, ACU) nearby. An interesting walk through beautiful East Melbourne takes you to the Bridge Rd fashion outlets. The Vietnamese quarter is close by along Victoria Pde.  Amazingly, the bushland of Yarra bend national park is less than 20 minutes walk, a  further stroll along the river to the C
notes: We are happy to run a load of washing for you. There's an iron & small ironing board in the room - just ask to borrow a full sized one if required.
transit: It's very easy to get here. Southern Cross Station (and the Airport Express Bus Terminal) are a 20 min direct tram plus 5 min walk. We are easily accessed by car from the Eastern or Monash Freeways. We may be able to provide a visitor's parking permit for 24 hour street parking but please check with us before booking.  Public transport is minutes away with a choice of two trams to the city via Gertrude St or Victoria St, loads of buses and North Richmond train station. Direct trams to St Kilda, St Kilda Beach, Port Melbourne & Docklands. We can lend you Myki cards for your stay. A supermarket, bottle shop and all manner of fascinating shops, pubs, cafes and restaurants are all within easy walking distance.
access: You have use of the whole ground floor consisting of gallery, bedroom/study/kitchenette & bathroom. The bedroom contains a super comfortable queen bed, WiFi, TV and small sitting area overlooking a leafy internal light well. An air conditioner for winter heating/summer cooling as well as fans & electric blanket. A separate office opens off the bedroom with a good work desk, a eclectic collection of books, (old) iPad and (older) iMac you are very welcome to use. This extra room would suit independent guests and would be very useful if you need somewhere to work. There's a single bed on a mezzanine level in the office accessed via a ladder. While there's no door between the rooms the beds are well out of sight. You have a small refrigerator, kettle, microwave, toaster, tea/coffee & breakfast cereals, milk, spreads etc. The bathroom is at the other end of the gallery and is for your use only. You are welcome to use our kitchen upstairs to prepare meals and may like to have breakfast in th
interaction: Mercedes and I are always happy to give local advice and help you make the most of your visit. We often enjoy sharing stories with guests but of course you can come and go just as you please - either by the front door or the door in your room. We won't bother you however if you have a query, or feel in need of a chat, we'd be delighted to oblige. We are generally around.
house_rules: Our living room upstairs is open to the gallery so we ask you to be quiet in this area when we're at home.  Please keep the upstairs kitchen and gallery clean after use as these are shared areas.  No smoking inside the building but you can in the courtyard or back lane.  You a very welcome to explore our rather eclectic book collection - just put books back where you find them. Please let us know beforehand if you intend to bring other people into our home.  Thanks!!!
host_about:
Mercedes has a background in social work/counselling, teaching, farming & fashion and follows passions in art and craft, gardening, home renovation and volunteer activities. Paul had a university career in science, education, software development and information system and is occupied on a range of woodwork, jewellery, home renovation & app development projects. We've both travelled quite widely over the years and have grand plans for the future. 

Airbnb was a revelation to us - discovered through Paul's daughter, an active host in Fairfield and frequent traveller. Now multiple family members have become active and enthusiastic hosts and travellers. We love living in this great part of Melbourne with its history, architecture, galleries, cafés and dynamic cultural mix and feel privileged to be able to share our passion with others. We'll be only too pleased to help you make the most of your stay in Melbourne.

Walk to 1000 Blessings, a fab little cafe for great coffee and a tasty treat. The Weekend Farmers’ Market, bursting with fresh produce and loads of atmosphere. Richmond Recreation Centre, with gym and 50 metre indoor pool and a large park with BBQ areas, playground and oval, are all just around the corner. Hop on a tram and in minutes you’ll be in the heart of Melbourne city or in trendy Chapel Street South Yarra with its endless fashion stores and cafes. There’s easy access to Melbourne’s major venues – the MCG, Hisense and AAMI Arenas and Rod Laver Arena – home of the Australian Open. This apartment is close to everything Melbourne has to offer. Definitely the place to stay! Also only minutes away from Epworth Hospital and The Melbourne Clinic.

house_rules: Please take a moment now to read our House Rules. COMMUNICATION All communication is via airbnb messaging only. Ensure you have AIRBNB APP and mobile connectivity, so we can easily communicate. GUEST BOOKING, GUEST NUMBER, GUESTS STAYING AND BEDDING For personal travel, you as guest booking must be one of guests staying for entire stay. Number of guests staying limited to maximum number allowed in property and as confirmed and paid for in airbnb. Where bedding options offered, such as king beds or king single beds, you must request your preference at time of booking. Where extra bedding offered, no extra bedding provided if number of guests staying is property standard occupancy, unless extra bedding is requested and paid for by you in airbnb at time of booking. Bedding preferences / extra bedding can not be guaranteed. SELF CHECK IN FROM 3PM / SELF CHECK-OUT TO 10AM Following information available in AIRBNB APP after 48  hours of booking: - PROPERTY ADDRESS and MAP - SELF CHECK-IN/OUT
host_about:
Thanks for reading our profile. 

We've been hosting since 2009 and love It!

And when time permits, we also love travelling!

We've been partnering with property owners since 2009, when we established a2c, our complete turnkey short stay property management and co-hosting service.

If you're a property owner and interested in tapping into our considerable experience and expertise, then feel free to get in touch to discuss our property management and airbnb co-hosting services, and we'll be happy to assist!

We pride ourselves in offering an exceptional collection of unique, highly rated, hand selected homes, in the best inner city Melbourne locations, super clean and beautifully furnished, with airbnb guests in mind.

Exceeding guest expectations is what we’re about.

As hosts, we look forward to welcoming you, and making your experience unforgettable.

As guests, we'll always be respectful of both you and your home, and look forward to sharing the experience!

Best,
The a2c Team

neighborhood_overview: Altona is a quiet seaside village with a beach that gets very busy if the weather is very, very hot. It is also favorite place for kite boarding and the sight of many colourful kites flying in the air as the boarders skim over the sea surface is beautiful. As well Williamstown, the first port in Melbourne with many colonial and Victorian buildings is just 10 minutes drive away. It is a mecca for fine dining, snazzy shopping and great restaurants as well as many fine yacht clubs.
notes: Altona is a good starting point for trips down the Great Ocean Road and into other areas in the hinterland of Victoria such as the old gold rush towns. As well you can not only go into the city by train you can also catch the ferry from Williamstown to Melbourne. If people want it I provide a tour around the local area so guests can orientate themselves to what is available where plus good places to wander along a beach or sit quietly in a cafe. I also provide bikes to enable guests to ride along the very attractive beachside paths which stretch all the way from Altona to Williamstown. There is a craft brewery in nearby Newport as well as a Science Museum. No stays longer than 1 month. No dogs allowed.
transit: Seaside Cottage is 5 minutes walk from the nearest railway station and there are buses which travel to largest local shopping mall. As well there is a ferry service to Melbourne from Williamstown. Altona is also has easy access to all major highways in Melnbourne so depending on what time of day you are travelling, it is easy to get around.
access: You have your own double room, with it's own sitting area with 2 comfy rocking chairs and tea and coffee facilities. There's plenty of room  for storing luggage and clothing. The rest of the house is shared: a kitchen with all facilities, an area for dining, sitting, TV and interaction between guests. A shared bathroom with all facilities and toiletries supplied. there is also a very attractive outside courtyard with shelter from the sun if needed
interaction: I am available to provide help and assistance with everything needed to make your stay comfortable, relaxed and rewarding. Plenty of information on both local, Melbourne and Victoria wide tourist attractions plus all information on public transport and how to book tours. However some guests really want a quiet rest away from interraction with others as much as possible and I support that in every way I can.

host_about:
I am a committed healthy eater and exerciser, reader, political wonk, love being out near, or living in, nature, delighting in my friends and family, most especially my 3 glorious grandchildren. Travel to see them regularly in New York City.
What I can't do without: my friends, living by the sea, my kindle, my ipad and the comfort of my little cottage.

I not only travel regularly to New York to see my 3 grandchildren I also write a daily blog about New York ( my way of keeping in touch with their lives) and maintain a (Hidden by Airbnb) apge promoting my site and I offer curated individual itineraries for people travelling to New York. It makes such a diference when someone tells where to go to get the best coffee, the best meals and the best shopping.

I like my guests to really feel at home and relaxed in my cottage. I'm more than happy to tell people about the surrounding area and the delights of the broader Melbourne metropolis and also great trips to scenic places outside of Melbourne. I also give people a guided tour of Altona and Williamstown so they can appreciate the pleasure of these 2 seaside villages if that is something they would enjoy. That said, I'm more than happy to keep out of my guests way and let them just relax if that is their need.

I walk to Brunetti's in Carlton for breakfast & a coffee then stroll leisurely to the Victoria Markets for my fresh groceries. If hot, the Baths are 5 mins away too. The Melbourne international comedy festival is a great attraction between March and April. The perfect stay for Comedians.
