neighborhood_overview: Seddon is a great place and growing by the minute but is still quiet and retains its village like atmosphere. There's great cafes and fantastic coffee,a gourmet supermarket,wine shop and a variety of restaurants from African (my favourite!) to Malaysian and Italian,and all within walking distance to the property. Just down the road is Footscray,a predominately Vietnamese community with a bit of African too,so wonderful food choices everywhere,including the Footscray Market with its fresh fruit and veg,meat and seafood. Seddon also has an eclectic mix of shops ranging from gifts shops like Sedonia to vintage shops like my very own "Once More With Feeling" at the front of the property on Charles St. So you must drop in and say hi when you stay! Its a great friendly neighbourhood that you will fall in love with and not far from the city either or major attractions like Flemington Racecourse and Etihad stadium. Leave your car and take public transport or an Uber, it's that easy.
notes: We have great public transport in Melbourne which is easily accessible from the house so leave the car at home and take public transport or take an Uber, everything you need is not far away.
transit: Just a short walk from the property is Seddon train station,and a ten minute journey to the city. Across the road from the property is a bus that will take you down to Footscray, the Footscray market and also Footscray station. And also nearby is Middle Footscray station again a short trip to the city or to nearby suburbs. If you have a car there is free parking outside the front door. Also easily accessible from Seddon are such attractions like Scienceworks in Spotswood, Melbourne Zoo, Werribee Zoo and Werribee Mansion, Etihad stadium for the footy and concerts and Flemington Racecourse.
access: guests will have full access to the house and all it contains.
interaction: i will meet and greet guests on arrival and be contactable during the stay if needs be. i also live close by the property.
house_rules: No smoking inside the building. Please leave the house as you found it.  Enjoy yourselves.
host_about: hi my name is jo and I run my own small business, a Vintage clothing boutique called Once More,with Feeling. The shop is actually at the front of the AirBnb so drop in and say hi when you come to stay. I'm also involved in Theatre and have performed many times at a wonderful Melbourne institution called La Mama. I love music and feel so lucky to live in Melbourne where we have a great live music scene. Sometimes i sing and play guitar and I love both country and western music,I also sing in the Melbourne Mass Gospel choir. My partner is Ray,who is a builder and is responsible for the wonderful renovation at Seddon and who sometimes builds sets for the theatre too. We love to travel and after using airbnb will probably never stay at a hotel again we love it so much. we hope you love it too and will love visiting the west of Melbourne, a wonderfully multicultural place so close to the city and with everything you could imagine.

We used to rent out to guests occassinally when we were travelling or working away however have since moved just north of the city to a larger apartment (room for a baby...) so do Airbnb full time now at Lonsdale St. This apartment was our home for 5 years- it is very convenient, with all the comforts that you need. neighborhood_overview: You are at the heart of Melbourne - and can enjoy whichever side of the city you want. Everything is at your doorstep.
notes: We have boycotted the iron and ironing board! We provide a garment steamer which is very fast and easy to use. There is no TV, and there never will be, that's just how we roll. Can provide baby items if requested with some notice (portacot + highchair). Any other special requests... just ask, and I'll do my best.
transit: Our front entrance is on Lonsdale st, and the back entrance is Little Bourke st (China Town). We are SO central, we are within the free tram zone in the city. We are also within the city loop of trains so you can walk to Melbourne Central or Parliament station. There are also buses on our doorstep.. and the Skybus free shuttle can drop you to the hotel next door for airport transfers. Couldn't get any more accessible. Parking is a hassle, we recommend not having a car but if you are stuck send me a message and let me know and I'll do my best to give you tips.
access: Guests have full privacy in this one bedroom apartment with a spacious bedroom, lounge area, small balcony, bathroom and well equipped kitchen. The lounge room is minimal with a couch and city view - that means no TV but fast/free wifi and a city full of food and fun should keep you entertained. Close to the apartment is a shared laundry and on the rooftop is a shared pool.
interaction: I am always available by phone and can come by if you have any problems that need me to be there in person for.  You will get details of a friend of mine who kindly does the key hand overs for me - he lives and works incredibly close to the apartment so will meet you at your convenience on arrival. We can also arrange for him to take care of your bags if we are unable to accommodate an early check in or late check out. Info for keys will come in your itinerary and I'll be in touch vie private message too.
house_rules: If you are travelling with a toddler or child, they are more than welcome, but ultimately you will be responsible for their safety in the apartment. We consider it a safe place, and have had many youngsters stay before, but of course you know your child and what is potentially hazardous for them, so please be aware of their surroundings and what mischief they may get up to!  Please respect our neighbours - no loud noise from 9pm preferrably, strictly no loud noise after 10pm. No smoking inside. No smokey cooking inside . There are sensitive smoke detectors in the hallway which attract a $3,000 from the Melbourne Fire Brigade as they are automatically alerted if the smoke alarms are set off (we have experienced this!). This has never happened to a guest before, but we let you know as a precaution.
host_about:
Hello! 

I am Miranda, and live with my partner Chris. We live in the heart of Melbourne City in our own apartment which we have spent a lot of time renovating. We live with our placid little black Cavoodle dog Charlie .
 
We love living in Melbourne, especially enjoying its great parks and cafes. Chris is an architect/ industrial designer and I am a model, as well as a recently qualified primary school teacher.

We've been together 9 years, and in that time have travelled to a lot of places throughout Asia and Europe. When we travel it's always relaxed. We love discovering new things - not necessarily the typical tourist attractions. We look forward to exploring the Americas and more of Europe when time permits :) 

We hope you like staying at our place!

neighborhood_overview: What's South Yarra like? Who wouldn't love staying in the center of Melbourne's best shopping, best restaurants, best nightlife, and entertainment. From here you can walk to some of Melbourne's finest spots, the Yarra River, the Botanical Gardens, Fed Square, the city, Southbank and more. Dine on street, people watch, enjoy fashion, glamour, and style all day, every day, all year round. Shopping’s the name of the game in South Yarra, where Chapel Street reigns supreme. The fashion strip contains all manner of high-end designer boutiques, chain-stores, hipster hang-outs, cinemas, and gift shops. There’s also a seemingly unlimited array of cafes and restaurants to help revive weary shoppers by day, and bars and clubs to keep the buzz going at night. Naturally then, South Yarra attracts the young, hip and fashion conscious, at least on its main strip and the streets immediately surrounding. The residents are a mix of young professionals, families and empty nesters – all attracted to this

summary: Located in the heart of beachside suburb Elwood, our place is a short walk to the beach, lots of yummy cafés, bike tracks & funky St. Kilda. Close to all public transport, it's a perfect  retreat & a great base to discover Melbourne's highlights.
space: Welcome to " Your Home Away from Home". Located in the fantastic leafy suburb of Elwood, next to St. Kilda, by the bay. This location is just perfect for you to explore Melbourne. It's a 5 minute walk to the beach, 10 minutes to stylish St Kilda and up the street from local funky cafes in cosmopolitan Elwood. During your stay, our home has everything you need for comfort, security, luxury and relaxation.  Your "Home Away from Home" features:  ~ All mod cons ~ Ducted heating/air conditioning ~ A large lounge and courtyard ~ A great kitchen and dining area ~ A separate laundry ~ Your own Private bathroom.  Your room features: ~ A comfortable queen bed with clean sheets and towels ~ Modern wardrobes ~ WIFI connection.  ~ You have use of downstairs powder room as well as your own personal toilet and shower.  You also have full use of all kitchen facilities, the laundry and the audio visual equipment.  We are only too happy to make your stay here with us as comfortable and pleasant as possi

neighborhood_overview: I have lived in Elwood for 15 years and never want to leave. It's leafy, quiet and has lots of great cafés and restaurants where I can get my local organic groceries and chai lattes. It's heaven in spring and summer! I can jump on my bike and ride along the canal to the shops or to the beach in a flash! For breakfast, lunch, coffee or dinners there is an endless supply of various delicacies a 15 minute walk away. A walk down the beach along the foreshore is not only soothing to the soul but a must at sunset. I have even seen dolphins in the bay during a morning walk. You'll love it and never want to leave either!!!
notes: NA
transit: This is a great area for public transport access. Out the front of the house we have a bus that goes directly into the city via St Kilda. At the end of the street (at the Turtle Cafe) you can also get the airport shuttle. There is a train station 10 minutes walk away and a tram on the way there too. In another direction, also 10 minutes walk away you will get to St Kilda, from where there is another tram directly into the city. If you want a taxi to or from the city it will cost you about $25 and take about 20-40 minutes depending on time of day and traffic.
access: You have access to the whole house and we provide you with your own Fridge for your convenience.  You are free to come and go as you like, however if you come home late at night we request that you be quiet and respectful of those who may be sleeping. We are happy for you to use all the common living areas as you choose. You can prepare meals in the kitchen when you need and use the laundry as required.  All we ask is that you clean up after yourself and keep things as you found them.
interaction: As this is our home, we will most likely be here all the time. We are more than happy to leave you in peace or chat over a cuppa or a smoothie! During the day we will most likely be at work and home in the evenings.

All we ask is that you clean up after yourself and keep things as you found them.
host_about: Hi I'm Marta and am a Naturopath, Homoeopath, Women's educator and Art of Feminine Presence teacher, with my own successful natural health clinic "Shine Health Wellbeing Centre". I love my work and I practice what I preach (as much as possible :P). I'm about creating a world that's happier, more enlightened and healthier for those who live in it. Running a busy clinic, I work Tuesdays to Saturdays and am usually home by about 7.30-8.00, however I have many hobbies and am usually out and about in the evenings. I practice yoga regularly, dance Salsa, Bachata and Zouk, so if you need to know where to go out and have fun dancing or where the closest yoga class is, I can point you in the right direction. I love traveling and have been to most of the (Website hidden by Airbnb) next major one will be South America!

We're a diverse mix of young professionals, ranging from teachers and academics to entrepreneurs and lawyers, along with a toddler, a baby and a cheeky little dog. We all get along extremely well and love meeting new people while one of our housemates is away.

host_about: I'm a late-30s Australian who's easy going, tidy and respectful of other people and their spaces. I've lived in a large, old house in East Melbourne for over 15 years so I'm familiar with shared living arrangements. I especially enjoy living with people from overseas, even if only briefly, as I find they bring a cultural diversity to the house and offer a different perspective on life. That been said, I absolutely love Australia and think Melbourne is the best city in the world, from my subjective perspective. Some of my interests are philosophy, history, science, technology and economics, while I also love movies and music along with swimming and snowboarding. I have a small family and work in software development.

name: Apartment - Heart of Melbourne
summary: Sunny mornings and quiet. Tea and coffee supplied as well as bathroom soaps etc. Tv in bedroom and lounge and free wifi. Plenty of books, games and DVDs to keep entertained. Private space with only 6 other apartments on the floor. Access to the indoor pool, gym, steam room and rooftop BBQ areas via secure swab. On site manager in the entry foyer Monday to Friday.
space: Welcome to Melbourne CBD The Apartment A brand new 1 bedroom apartment is located next to the very best of fun and work venues in Melbourne: downtown or city centre, the national art gallery, the botanical garden and southbank on the famous Yarra River with its restaurants & boutique shops, minutes walk to Flinders Street station and Federation Square, a tram ride to Southern Cross Station which is linked to the international airport skybus. Trams and trains, buses and bike paths all leading to the city Centre and the casino. Moreover, even better than all these, is a slow leisurely walk anywhere that you fancy in search of fun and games or meetings with business clients. Or just sit by the sidewalk and watch the world go by. Explore the Area and it's Surroundings The apartment itself has a lovely roof garden and an indoor basement pool,gym and steam room. It has a separate bedroom with ensuite bath/shower/toilet. The balcony gives you a wonderful essence

name: Big, cute and handy, St Kilda East
summary: Large apartment with one bedroom with queen-sized double bed, second room set up as a study, no bed. Living room has a big, comfy sofa, can easily accommodate third person with extra beding avail. There's a balcony, well-equipped kitchen, study, TV with Apple TV, shower, washing machine/dryer. Cute and cosy, it's not super-glam, but it has soul and it's in a great location.
space: Hi guys, I have a cute, good-sized  apartment on a quiet, leafy street in East St Kilda that's minutes walk from lively shopping/bar/cafe/restaurant strips in the Windsor end of Chapel Street and village-like Carlisle Street.  It's a half hour leisurely walk down to St Kilda beach, with a gorgeous park and great gym/pool one block away on our street, plus a local corner shop with coffee. We have a balcony for the summer sun too, and close to trams buses and trains into the city centre. Ist bedroom - double bed, built-in wardrobe. 2nd Bedroom - set up as study with desk. Bathroom - great big shower is fab, washing machine/dryer, rubbish bath though so if you are a soaking person, not ideal! Separate toilet. Living room - big and spacious, with library and dining table - feel free to read my books (no bending covers!). Apartment has free wifi. Great big sofas in here so could accom one more if required (not foldout beds tho) Coffee table. Balcony sits off this room with a perching bench.

Hi! I’m Mel from Melbourne, Australia, and I live with my partner, Fabrizio, from Bologna, Italy. 

We try to travel and explore the world, as much as possible. We love experiencing different cultures and enjoying great food!
We prefer to experience the local culture, rather than stopping only a couple of days in a place, and heading on to the next location. Meeting the locals is what makes the experience all the more worthwhile! Airbnb is great for this :)

We have had many people stay with us over the last couple of years, and have really enjoyed each and every experience. 

What is important about Airbnb is the relationship and communication between the host and the guest. So far we’ve had some great experiences, and hope this continues.

neighborhood_overview: St Kilda is a remarkable place. It is situated on one of the most picturesque points of the Bay a short distance from the city, has safe sandy beaches, and yet for decades was shunned by Melbournites because it was the haunt of prostitutes and druggies. It wasn't always like that. Back in the first half of the century, St Kilda was one of the most fashionable suburbs of Melbourne with grand homes and grand people. Today, it is enjoying a resurgence. Places to visit in St Kilda include: Acland Street: one of Melbourne's Food Precincts and is also a long-time favourite of Melbournians and tourists alike because of its famous cakes shops. It is now the number one stop for backpackers because of the busy cafes and close proximity to St Kilda's beaches. Upper Esplanade: has fantastic views of the Bay with the newly restored and refurbished St Kilda Baths and Royal Yacht Squadron in the foreground. The landmark Esplanade Hotel is a venue for music gigs. On Sundays, a craft market is held on

neighborhood_overview: Brunswick is a vibrant, multicultural area with various cuisines on offer, especially on Sydney road with many cultures to explore; from Italian Deli’s to Middle Eastern bakeries. Enjoy the culture of Sparta Place, a quaint and quirky laneway just off Sydney road. Have a coffee at the popular Brunswick East Project Café or indulge at George Calombaris famous restaurant ‘Hellenic Republic’. There is plenty to do for the whole family!  Lygon Street also has delicious food, wonderful service and beautiful park-lands and really comes alive in the evening. The section of Lygon Street ‘East Brunswick’ has really come to life. With well-known eateries such was Quattro Cento Gradi, world famous for their Margherita Pizza! Brunswick is very central and accessible by tram to Melbourne's major attractions; the CBD, Museums, Carlton and The Zoo.
notes: PARTIES AND FUNCTIONS ARE STRICTLY PROHIBITED
transit: From the apartments you have access to some of Melbourne's finest restaurants, cafes, shops, pubs and live bands. Trams are 400m away which takes you directly into the CBD.
access: The entire apartment will be for your private use during your stay. Included in the pricing for all our apartments is fresh, clean, quality linen and towels. Parking is also included free of charge. There is all day parking outside the complex for extra vehicles.   We now offer FREE WIFI The kitchen has all the utensils you need to have a comfortable stay. There is a full kitchen, including oven, dishwasher, fridge/freezer and microwave. This apartment has a washing machine and dryer in the bathroom. The bathroom has a hairdryer and a small amount of toiletries. The apartment is equipped with an iron and an ironing board.  A porta cot and high chair are also available for hire. Please let us know if you have young children so we can supply you with a small basket of toys for their use. This always helps keep them entertained and our guests have appreciated this very much.

notes: NUMBER OF GUESTS When you book, please be clear how many guests will be staying. name: Self contained Garden View Studio
summary: My lovely Garden studio was fully booked for a whole year and is now back in action and ready to welcome you.
space: Large sun filled self contained former art studio with pleasant garden views and a nice vantage point from which to watch and feed the native birds.  Total privacy to come and go as you please through the side access gate. Please see my other listing for entry, location in the garden and the OUTSIDE toilet and bathroom which is solely for the use of the occupants of The Studio.  The toilet and bathroom are approximately 14 paces away from the studio.  The Studio is the brick building opposite the Black Garden Bungalow with Possums......the Possums often scamper over the studio roof too to give you bumps in the night.  Both Ring Tailed and Brush Tailed Possums come here. It has a LCD flat screen TV.  A good supply of books and maps of the area. There is a bar fridge and a two ring hob top for your use.  There is also a rice cooker and a slow cooker and a microwave oven.  Those are the only cooking facilities..     There is a laundrette in the village but you are welcome to use the washe

neighborhood_overview: Parkdale is a lovely little community on Port Philip Bay.  The walk to the beach takes approximately 10 minutes at a slow pace....slightly longer on the way back as it is a gentle uphill walk.  The village has many cafe's and restaurants where you can get anything from a curry to a Peruvian Pancake, sushi and the most delicious Latte` in the world at the Station Stop Café.
notes: Henry and Barbara live here.  Barbara feeds Henry and if you feed Henry he will be your friend for life.....and every time you open the door, he will be there waiting for you.....and he knows about the back door!  So please don't feed him....  He will love you just as much if you just smile at him and give him a pat. Yes he will eat pickled onions and yes they can kill him......loves chocolate and that can kill him too.  Please don't!  Henry's health is very important to him....and me
transit: The studio is within a 5 minute walk of the mainline train station, the Frankston Line which takes you direct to the city and beyond to Southern Cross Station.  Right outside the station is a bus stop.  The buses will take you to a bus station at Southlands.  From there you can go wherever your heart desires.
access: Guest have access through the main double black gates.  The back garden has private outdoor seating located by the back door of the studio.  The black table and chairs in the centre of the garden you are welcome to use too.....and the seating area under cover by the main house.  You are welcome to smoke anywhere outside with due consideration to other guests who may also be booked in.
interaction: I am quite well up on what's on in my area and will be happy to help you find exciting and unusual places to visit.
house_rules: Please keep the access gates shut to keep my dog Henry in and safe. Please also be aware that water is in short supply and costs a fortune so please be kind and have quick power showers.  Same with electricity.  Switch heating and lights off overnight and when you go out.
host_about:
My name is Barbara and I migrated from Hampshire, Old England in 2004 and settled here, in Parkdale, on Port Philip Bay and love it.

If you are thinking of staying here, please note, there are no city views, city is 45 minutes away on the train or drive in 20.  No bay views, but you can walk there in 10 minutes and best of all there is a map linking this listing so you can see exactly where you could be laying down your head.

If you need to be staying in Emerald,  Ivanhoe, Carnegie or Essendon then my place is not for you.  These lovely bungalows are in my beautiful garden where the birds sing in a street in Parkdale on the bay where the friendly locals are and the best coffee in town.

host_about:
Ideal for gay or straight singles or couples and parents needing a separate stay when visiting the grandkids! 

Overnight stays or longer term guests hosted by long time Melbournian guys happy to share some insight to this great city and make your stay a memorable one!

Self-contained, private-entrance accommodation with your own bathroom and kitchenette.
Your room features reverse cycled quiet air conditioning, HD-TV, CD, NETFLIX and a sunny verandah to sit and enjoy the view of the trees-lined street. 
Wi Fi available on request & public transport card & map. 

Just a short train ride to Melbourne CBD and tourist attractions and a short walk to The Sun (Art Deco) Theatre and restaurants, cafes, pubs and bars. Our home is well within distance of our city's famous food & wine culture, local markets, great beaches and airport transfers. 

Mountain bikes available to hire to explore the many of Melbourne's tracks & trails.  
 
The Milk Bar has its own private entrance separate to our residence which is an old Victorian weatherboard home full of character situated in a tree lined private cul-de-sac close to everything Melbourne has to offer the traveller. 

Long-stay guests please inquire. Some meals available on request.

summary: This is a private home of two stories and a traditional B & B. The guest area is upstairs, it has four bedrooms with six beds. The lovely lounge dining room is large, 10 meters x 6 meters with quality furniture and artwork. This traditional Bed and Breakfast is only 250 meters walk to Olinda Village, gardens & forests. You are booking four private rooms & four bathrooms. Please accept my hospitality & service which is part of my business.
space: This is a lovely big area the size of a large house. This will suit singles, couples or small groups. I live on the premises with two little doggies downstairs and I am very quiet.  I am a qualified masseur with a dedicated massage room downstairs, please ask about a massage while you are here. Please, no excessive noise after 11 pm at night or no excessive drinking or parties. Please remember you are a guest in a private home, you are booking a room in a bed and Breakfast not renting real estate. neighborhood_overview: Olinda is a township on top of the Dandenong Ranges. It is a temperate rainforest with lots of tall trees, birds and beautiful gardens tourist shops and cafes and restaurants. It is about 50 km from the center of Melbourne and about 5 degrees colder the whole year.  You will love Olinda's quaint little shops and touristy township - just a minute's walk from my place. Also, forests and public gardens, public transport are just a short walk away too.
notes: Please observe house rules of no parties or events. Please supervise your children, please be respectful of the furniture, me and the neighbours, please understand you are a guest in my home. Please be aware of Global warming and Greenhouse emissions by wearing appropriate clothing for the weather conditions. Clothing is simply recycling body heat ;-) There are 17 steps in the staircase. You can use my kitchen upon request. I would love to assist you in finding the right restaurant or attractions or anything else you might require.
transit: Public transport is available from the city by train and then bus. The bus stop is only 100 metres from my B & B
access: You have your own lounge room and I have mine. Bedrooms and bathrooms have locks. I do not go into your private room. I will have to come upstairs once or twice to clean up and set the breakfast table and serve you a delicious hot breakfast. Therefore, the guest lounge room should be considered as a common space. This is the traditional B & B. You are welcome to wander around the one-acre garden.
interaction: Please let me know if there is anything I can do for you! for example, any special dietary requirements for breakfast, a surprise bottle of champagne for your loved one. etc.
house_rules: Hi, by booking this space, I want you to accept and be aware that this is a traditional B & B. I live here with my two little dogs. I serve you, I clean up after you, breakfast is served and brought up to your dining table upstairs. Alcohol is O.K. but please, no drunken, antisocial behaviour. Please keep the noise down after 11pm, no parties please. Being friendly and approachable is good. Visitors are welcome if you would kindly ask permission first.
host_about: I am hospitable, friendly and approachable. I live downstairs and the guest bedrooms and living room are upstairs. I like football, garden, photography, travel, psychology, spiritual & self-development books, natural foods, music and stage shows. My life motto is to be happy and at peace with people and nature.

Spend your morning stocking up at the emblematic South Melbourne Market or jump straight on a tram to the Melbourne CBD, just minutes away. Middle Park Beach is two kilometres down Albert Road to the West, and the Botanic Gardens are just 500 metres to the East. The neighbourhood has it all!

There is a washing machine in the ensuite bathroom and a split-system air conditioner in the main living area. The building has an undercover visitor carpark in addition to the dedicated park that comes with the apartment.

I've had some fantastic feedback, but always try to improve the experience, so if you have any queries or specific requests, don't ever hesitate to ask.

neighborhood_overview: A stay at our hip apartment will mean you will enjoy some of Melbourne’s finest restaurants, bars, cafes, shopping  and night life, all at your doorstep! With easy access to venues such as the MCG, Hisense and AAMI Arenas and Rod Laver Arena – home of the Australian Open – and hip shopping and restaurant precincts of Bridge Road and Swan Street, this apartment is close to everything Melbourne  is famous for. Leave the apartment, head north and in minutes you’ll find yourself in Bridge Road, home to brand name fashion outlets cafes, and restaurants. A trip into the CBD is just one stop away by train, or a short tram ride. Head south and you’ll be in Swan Street. Home to many eateries, pubs and clubs, supermarkets, and independent boutiques. This is the place to stay on your next Melbourne visit! Our apartment is also only minutes away from Epworth Hospital.
notes: 1 set of keys. No luggage storage before/after stay. Ground floor apartment. Permissible sized hot water tank that requires time to reheat water between use, especially between showers. Let us know you have by mentioning 'Read the Listing!' in your first message to us. The a2c Team

Where bedding options offered, such as king beds or king single beds, you must request your preference at time of booking. Where extra bedding offered, no extra bedding provided if number of guests staying is property standard occupancy, unless extra bedding is requested and paid for by you in airbnb at time of booking. Bedding preferences / extra bedding can not be guaranteed. host_about:
Thanks for reading our profile. 

We've been hosting since 2009 and love It!

And when time permits, we also love travelling!

We've been partnering with property owners since 2009, when we established a2c, our complete turnkey short stay property management and co-hosting service.

If you're a property owner and interested in tapping into our considerable experience and expertise, then feel free to get in touch to discuss our property management and airbnb co-hosting services, and we'll be happy to assist!

We pride ourselves in offering an exceptional collection of unique, highly rated, hand selected homes, in the best inner city Melbourne locations, super clean and beautifully furnished, with airbnb guests in mind.

Exceeding guest expectations is what we’re about.

As hosts, we look forward to welcoming you, and making your experience unforgettable.

As guests, we'll always be respectful of both you and your home, and look forward to sharing the experience!

Best,
The a2c Team

space: Beautiful home - Melbourne We have a lovely, light home in Fairfield, Melbourne, located in  the northern suburbs, right next door to Northcote and North Fitzroy, with some amazing cafes and great restaurants.  The house has a huge open kitchen, dining and lounge area with big open windows bringing in lots of light and sunshine. There are 3 bedrooms (with king, queen and single beds), with one bathroom. It is a 20 minute train ride to Melbourne centre, 30 minutes by bicycle.

name: Spacious double room. 15 min to CBD.
summary: Public transport at front door.   Convenient to anywhere in Melbourne.   Walking distance to eateries and supermarkets. Free off street parking.
space: Our house is located in the eastern suburb of Templestowe Lower.  This is a suburb for quality schools.  It is 30 km from Melbourne Airport.   It has a very convenient location to anywhere in Melbourne. CBD is only 15 minutes drive via the Eastern Freeway,  The house is in walking distance to Macedon shopping centre and restaurants.  The popular Westfield shopping centre is 5 minutes drive away. Box Hill Central is 10 minutes down Manningham Road. From there you can hop on the train to anywhere in the train network. notes: There are a number of ways you can get to my house from the airport. 1. by taxi, that will costs around AUD$80-$100. 2, by Airbus.   Airbus cost AU$20 one way to Southern Cross Station.  Then you will need to catch a train to Box Hill Station. Then change to bus 903 (Altona direction). Get off at Madeleine St stop.  My house is across the road.  The train + bus can be travel on the same Myki ticket, the trip will cost you AU$4.40. (Myki Zone 1 fare) 3. The cheapest way is to take Bus 901 at Terminal 4, get off at Pine Shopping Centre. At the same place, change to Bus 908 to get off at Corner of High St & Manningham Road. Walk 5 mins to my house at number 287 Manningham Road, This trip cost AUD$3.00 only. (Myki Zone 2 fare)
transit: Easy public transport.   Bus stop at door.  Bus route goes to CBD (Flinders Station), Box Hill, Heidelberg train stations.

interaction: This is a double room that sleeps 2 people.  If you have more than 2  staying with you.  Please let me know so I can add a folding bed or mattress for the additional person.
house_rules: No smoking inside or outside. Shoes off on carpets. No eating or drinking in bedroom. Turn off lights and heater when not in use. Clean up after cooking and dining. Guests are not allowed to invite non-renters into the house. No parties or events.

name: St Kilda Beach Acland St Studio
summary: My beautiful little 27 sqm studio is the ideal place to stay whilst visiting Melbourne. Light and filled with beautiful objects, breakfast, snacks, a bottle of wine upon arrival and fully kitted out with linen, towels and self catering kitchen utensils. One block from the beach, close to great restaurants and bars. It is beautifully decorated, with a super comfortable Italian Clei bed and big windows, so lots of natural light. Walk and tram everywhere. It is so easy from this ideal location.
space: This beautiful small bright freshly decorated studio is situated in the heart of the St Kilda area – I have heavily discounted the months of May june, July and August for monthly lets. Step outside and you have the best coffee in Melbourne directly across the road at Il Fornaio, the most lauded Chinese restaurant in Lau’s Family Kitchen, cheap and cheerful Trippy Taco. Aurora Day Spa for the total princess experience in the most beautiful surroundings is across the street in the prince of Wales complex.  Further along Acland and around the corner in Fitzroy st, you have great bars and restaurants of every type imaginable, live music venues and all night convenience shops. There is also the fabulous Theatre works for exciting live theatre.  A vibrant and culturally diverse suburb, St Kilda has something for everyone. neighborhood_overview: The studio is one block from famous StKilda beach with its iconic pier and marina. You can swim in the hot salty sea baths after a yoga or gym session then walk along the esplanade to acland st for cake in one of the European cake shops or perhaps a glass of wine and the best modern Italian food south of the river at my favourite restaurant Cicciolina.
notes: There is a set rate for the whole months of May, June, July and August which amounts to a discount of nearly 25% off the usual prices. I would love to have someone in there over the winter months so please contact me with any enquiries.
transit: We have a parking permit for acland st so you can park outside the studio but also drive right down the other end to do all your shopping right in the heart of acland st with no need to find paid parking. The best parking permit in st kilda!! : )). We are also a few steps from 3 of the best city bound tram routes with superstops for ease of access for those of us with slightly creaky knees... : )).    I supply two myki cards for you to use for the duration of your stay.
access: Please help yourself to the food and drinks supplied for your convenience. The books are there to be read but please finish them before you go and leave them there for me.  All of the other items are there for your use and pleasure however they are my treasured belongings and I would ask that you treat them as you would your own, with love and care.  There is a communal coin laundry on your floor to the right of our door and another on the floor above with a dryer. In the entrance on left as you enter the building there are two communal toilets for the use of guests and tradesmen however I would note that they would be an emergency only option as I am not in charge of their maintenance :  ))) And just a reminder to please please turn off all the lights, fan and especially the air conditioner when you go out as it only takes a few minutes to cool down the flat and the electricity is very costly.
interaction: I or my son will always be available for any help or advice you may need, so please do not hesitate to call us on the number provided. : ))
house_rules: Minimum reservation of 3 nights  It is a pet free and smoke free apartment We have decorated the apartment to make you comfortable and give the place some soul with some of my own favourite things and trust that you will respect them.  ***Ladies please don't use the towels to remove makeup. Fresh linen and towels are supplied. There are laundry facilities on the property and a Laundrette around the corner. For stays longer than 10 days a complete new set will be supplied on the 10th day. Should you require them to be changed more often there will be a $30.00 charge for each complete change. For all reservations there is a $40.00 cleaning fee. For any authorized late check outs there is no fee.  *** If there is an unauthorized late check out by the guest there is a fee of $20.00 per hour of extra stay in the apartment,         ************************************************************ Please be respectful of our neighbours, as much as they would love to party they have work at all hou
host_about: I'm outgoing and hospitable. I love to surround myself with great friends and beautiful things. I have travelled and lived in London for 10 years so understand how important it is to feel comfortable and secure upon arriving at a new destination. I grew up in St Kilda and go out every other night so am eminently qualified and very happy to help you out with suggestions, directions and anything else you may need to really enjoy your stay.

Check the calendar, and feel free to reach out with your requirements.  We'll advise the best rate possible. name: Comfortable home in quiet suburb
summary: NA
space: Comfortable secure family home in popular suburb of Melbourne. Close to Keilor Road, lots of cafes and restaurants, public transport close by and on the correct side of the city for the airport. Tram stop is 200 metre walk and train station is a 10 minute walk with a 30 minute ride to the CBD.  There is a terrific park across the road with sports fields; so plenty of green space for your morning jog or evening stroll. We are also members of our tennis club with courts only 100 metres away if you want to have a game of tennis!  The house is cosy, modern and very comfortable for two. There are four adults living here - myself and my husband and our two adult daughters.  We have ducted heating for Melbourne winters and evaporative cooling available for summer. The bedroom has a queen bed and we have comfortable bedding for the couch if required. We can also make available a double airbed. The kitchen is fully appointed for when you want to cook for yourself AND there is a coffee machine.

name: New York style Loft in Melbourne
summary: Sensational open space to live in, in Richmond, with a view to die for. High ceilings and open space. Beautiful huge windows and gourmet kitchen.
space: AT A GLANCE: Open plan living, dining, gourmet kitchen in LOFT space 1 Queen Bed, great mattress on slats - pillow selection.  Bathroom with Euro laundry  Heating/air conditioning  Check-in from 1.00pm/check-out by 10.00am or later by arrangement. Only 2 people can stay - if they sleep together! This wonderful old building has many apartments - all different as each owner has made their own interior. This apartment is on the third floor looking north and west. It is a Studio Loft apartment with huge ceilings and the original steel windows, renovated with love and care in New York style Loft living.  The Queen size bed is in the Loft area, there is a separate bathroom with shower and bath, with Euro laundry behind cupboard. neighborhood_overview: Walking access to Swan Street and all the restaurants and quirky stores, as well as Supermarket for supplies.  Public transport at your doorstep. Sporting and entertainment arenas in walking distance. Botanic Gardens across the Punt Road corner.
notes: We do need a good review or reference of some sort - and if you have not used Airbnb before please can you provide some sort of contact ref?  A description of you too is helpful too - as well as your verified contact details that Airbnb do. And before you ask - sorry NO Weddings, Film Crews or Photo Shoots.
transit: - Richmond Train Station (to and from EVERYWHERE) just behind building,  - MCG, AAMI Stadium and Tennis Centre in walking distance,  - Yarra River and Botanic Gardens in walking distance,  - Bridge Road shopping and Epworth Hospital in walking distance (can see it from the apartment!) - Trams to city on Swan Street - Swan Street shops and loads of amazing restaurants in walking distance
access: I provide 2 mykis for public transport, they can be topped up at Richmond train station. I also have a visitors parking permit for street parking, upon request.
interaction: I'll take you through the entry and exit details, show you round the apartment and leave you to it. Otherwise I will leave key in safe place for you and leave you long notes! I have maps and notes available to you in the sideboard drawer for further reference. And I am always at the end of the phone for any questions. Gladly.
house_rules: No smoking and respect for other residents in the building is paramount. Noise late at night is not allowed. As a much loved space we ask you care for everything in the apartment too! Love babies and children but unfortunately we cannot accept them staying too.  You will find the apartment very clean and very comfortable. All we ask is that you leave it in the similar condition. Some of our belongings are in the apartment as it is my home when I am there. I expect that my belongings will not be interfered, moved or otherwise rearranged. Feel free to read books in the bookshelves, but again take care of them. On your departure please take all personal items including toiletries and perishable goods. You can leave in a bag outside the apartment door. Please respect my neighbours by keeping late night noise to a minimum. Strictly NO parties and NO more than 2 people staying in the apartment. And again, strictly no smoking. If you smoke best not book at all. PLEASE NOTE THAT WE WILL NOT AC
host_about: My husband Pete and I renovated this amazing space and use it when we are in town. We live away from the city and I have my art studio in the other house. People who have places in the building love the position, the spaces and unique history of the area and this unique building and environment.

A green and tranquil oasis in Fitzroy, one of the most popular shopping and dining areas of Melbourne, and only minutes from the city centre. *  prized location on city edge accommodating 6 adults *  surrounded by the best eating and shopping strips *  stylish open plan living room with air-conditoning and heating *  fully equipped kitchen  *  2 large bedrooms each with a luxurious pillow top queen bed and individually air-conditoned and heated. *  each bedroom can easily accommodate an extra single or double bed that are hotel standard and extremely comfortable for an adult. Excessive noise in the immediate area of the accommodation including the street, garden and balconies will also not be tolerated. Violation of this rule will lead to your rental being terminated with no refund of fees.  We hope you can understand the reasons for this.  The survival of short term rentals as a viable accommodation option is dependent on visitors respecting the people living in the neighbouring properties.

The local food, art, architecture and all wonderfully diverse and original. And of course the beach is only a stones throw away, as is the historic kiosk and pier and the famous Sea baths St Kilda is home to some of Melbourne's best shopping and favourite restaurants, bars and cafes, including: The George, Cicciolina, Tolarno's, Lau's Family Kitchen, Chinta, Circa @ The Prince, Mirka – Tolarno , Cafe and bar Di Stasio, Newmarket Hotel, Mr Wolf and Dr Jekyll, Phamish, iLforniao, Woodfrog bakery. The apartment provides a quiet and spacious oasis, for both fun and relaxation. It is truly worth every penny to experience this amazing property in this first class location. Come and see for yourself.

Melbourne’s compact grid and network of trains, trams and buses means you won’t need wheels; to ride on any metropolitan public transport pick up a Myki card ((URL HIDDEN) at accredited newsagents or train stations, which you can then top up at stops, stations or select retailers, including 7-Eleven stores. house_rules: Commonsense . .Consider & respect others at all times. Apartment to be left in a Clean and Tidy as found, all rubbish removed to bin area in Electrical/Bin Cupboard in Hallway opposite Apartment, all dishes washed and  returned to Cupboards. *Smoking allowed outside on Balcony only...
host_about:
I love living by the Ocean, Walking, Running, Bike Riding & Snow Skiing . .Beautiful Food, Wine & Music in any shape or form. The Apartments we have I enjoy sharing with others.  I have endeavoured to style and present them in a tasteful, comfortable, professional way. I am a fussy Traveller and like Clean, Uncluttered, Funky, Classy Accommodation.
My favourite Travel Destinations in Australia are Melbourne CBD, Lorne Victoria, Byron Bay & Merimbula NSW, Noosa Qld & Sydney CBD Rocks area, Bunker Bay & all the beaches and wineries in WA. I love the Napa Valley in California and the Drive down Big Sur Highway to LA. Soho in New York
I love to Snow Ski in Japan, Whistler, Snowbird, Revelstoke, & all through California.. 
I am passionate about the 'Pay It Forward' principal of caring about others!
“When I travel I make it a journey
When I go to different places I experience them
When I meet new people I learn
When I taste new flavors I grow
When I follow my intuition I loose myself
When I sense I recall
All these unique experiences are unforgettable
And when I return it’s not my ego that is big

neighborhood_overview: Melbourne is a charming city, with amazing culture, restaurants, theatres and natural beauty. You're in the heart of the city and all this and more is at your fingertips.  I highly recommended the tourist information service downstairs at Federation Square. *Theatre* The apartment is located right in the centre of the Theatre District. Feel like seeing a show while you are here? Check out HalfTix on Swanston street at the Melbourne Town Hall on Swanston Street. They sell theatre tickets at around half price to fill seats for shows that evening. *Shopping* Keen shoppers take note! One block down Lonsdale Street is the newly opened Emporium, with many recently arrived global retailers such as UniQlo. From there you can walk across the sky bridges to David Jones and Myers, and then onto even more shopping at Bourke Street Mall. *The best markets in Melbourne* The most famous market in Melbourne is indisputably the Queen Victoria Market (known affectionately by locals as Queen Vic or Vic M
notes: The apartment is perfect for two people. Guests are responsible for any damage to the apartment which may exceed the bond. This includes losing the keys. Its important not to cause disturbance to my lovely neighbors. So no loud noise late at night whilst residents are trying to sleep. :-) When you check out -  please place used linen and towels on the bathroom floor or on top of the washing machine, and please leave the apartment as you found it when checking in. Please remember to turn off the TV + Heater when you are not there. Mistakes happen, so don't panic if something breaks! But please do let me know ASAP so I can fix it. There is a washing machine and dryer inside the studio apartment, which you are free to use.  Washing powder is provided and is located inside the vanity unit in your bathroom. If you run out of washing powder, please let me know so I can get some more for you. IMPORTANT! PLEASE READ CAREFULLY: No parking on property - Parking in the CBD is a tricky one. Best t
transit: If you plan to hire a car please note parking in Melbourne is super expensive (Expect to pay upwards of $60 per day during the weekdays) so my suggestion is to leave the car at home or rent a car if you need it from the rental agents on Franklin/A'Beckett Street (a short tram ride from my apartment). Check out this website for car hire options :   (Website hidden by Airbnb)  All forms of public transport at your fingertips. Trains, trams, buses and taxis.  Trams are also only one block away including the free City Circle Tram. Melbourne Central and Parliament stations are also a 5 minute walk away. You're in the heart of the city! How to get to the apartment : * You catch a Skybus from the airport into Southern Cross station in the city, then catch a tram up to corner of Russell and Bourke St, * Then Get off the tram and then walk north along Russell Street till you get to Lonsdale Street * Turn East into Lonsdale St then walk halfway up Lonsdale St till you arrive at Lonsdale Heights
access: The whole studio apartment, as well as the Heated Rooftop pool, Netflix, KODI Box, Tea, Coffee, WIFI, kitchenette, Laundry, High Definition TV and amazing rooftop views. Your own private oasis!
interaction: You have the entire studio apartment to yourself, I live a few minutes away, so I am never too far if you need anything, have any questions or need assistance.  I respect your privacy so will never bother you during your stay unless you contact me.
house_rules: ACCOMMODATION This Studio accommodates a maximum of 2 people only.  CHECKIN is from 3 pm to 8pm.  Please let me know exactly what time you'll arrive.  CHECKOUT is by 10 am.  Please leave all used towels in the shower, and leave the apartment as tidy as you arrived.  COOKING Please ensure the windows are OPEN, and the snake is under the entrance door (to block air flow) when you are cooking and using the hotplate.  Excess and unreasonable smoke will activate the fire alarms.  If the fire alarms activate, then the fire brigade will attend - this will incur a $1500 penalty - PAYABLE BY YOU. FIXTURES/FITTINGS Most of the appliances inside the apartment are only a few months old (I replace things pretty quickly!) so please treat everything in the apartment with tender loving care.  I want your stay to be excellent, and I also want my next guests to have the same wonderful experience. If you notice anything broken, please let me know ASAP and I'll get it replaced.  WALLS Please do not stick
host_about:
Hi I'm John.

During the week I work in my recording studio and am busy writing and producing music, as well as remixing and producing other artists. I also direct videoclips.
If you're interested in synthpop/electronic music then do a search for "Parralox".

As such, I usually travel overseas at least 3 times a year. Travel is one of the best things in the world (long haul flights, not so much!)

On the weekends I work as a registered Nurse (Permanent Night Shifts!) at a major Melbourne City Hospital.

I also dabble in property investment and my current property portfolio is 7 properties so far. You'll find some of them listed here on AirBNB from time to time!

I'm a MAJOR Science Fiction fan. Favourite authors are Larry Niven, Arthur C Clarke and Frank Herbert. Favourite directors are David Lynch & Stanley Kubrick.

I'm very passionate about Animal Rights. Animal cruelty is my biggest hate. I donate monthly to The Lost Dogs Home.
I have a dog called Jack that I treat like absolute gold. You’ll get to meet him when I check you in!
 With so much suffering on this planet I figure that if I can give one animal a perfect life then I'm doing something good.

Filled with an eclectic collection of keepsakes from my world travels, it's a perfect place to call home whilst in Melbourne. My two storey home features 1 bed, 1.5 bath, laundry, kitchen, 2 living areas, great backyard and lovely front courtyard - truly a quiet oasis in the midst of vibrant St Kilda! Perfectly located within a short walking distance to the famous St Kilda beach, cafes, restaurants and bars.

neighborhood_overview: St Kilda is an inner city bayside suburb, and is one of the most interesting and popular tourist destinations in Melbourne, and a must for all those wanting to experience a creative, vibrant multi-cultural area where the young, and young at heart enjoy an idyllic "bohemian" lifestyle by the bay. St Kilda is also home to a lively and diverse live music scene, with many venues within walking distance. Some of the many local attractions are: Luna Park, Palais Theatre, St Kilda Botanical Gardens, St Kilda Sea Baths, St Kilda Marina, Acland St. cafes and cakeshops, Fitzroy St. restaurants and bars, Sunday Market on the Esplanade, Summer Thursday Night Market, St Kilda Festival in February, and the Midsumma Gay Pride festival, etc.. My home is also within walking distance (20-30 mins walk ) to the Albert Park Formula One Grand Prix held in March.
notes: Usually I am at home to socialise and assist my guests, however I will be away from mid june until mid september, therefore you will have the place to yourself. To help you make the most of your time in Melbourne, I have a collection of tourist information and maps etc located in the bedroom.  Have a wonderful stay! PS: Please respect my home, and my neighbours
transit: Very well connected to public transport - buses, trams, and trains are all close by.
access: I really want my guests to feel at home here. Guests will have access to the whole property during duration of stay (except my bedroom, and the garage - these will remain locked).
interaction: My team is best contact via Airbnb to answer any questions you may have during your stay.
house_rules: - It is important to realise that this is my home, not a serviced hotel, therefore considerate and respectful behaviour is a priority.  - This is my home, please treat it as if it were yours, as well! - Please respect the neighbours, and do not make significant noise or play loud music after 10pm. - If guests lock themselves out of the property OR they do not place keys in the lockbox at checkout, an $80 fee will apply. If a guest loses a set of keys during their stay, a $300 fee will apply.
host_about: I am a "young-at-heart" middle-aged woman from Melbourne Australia. I live in the vibrant inner-city bayside suburb of St kilda in Melbourne. I am a professional photographer, and love graphic design and architecture.  I have lived and worked in Italy and Hong Kong, and I am a seasoned traveller, with a preference for warm destinations, where I can swim and snorkel. I have a keen interest in all other cultures. I am a respectful and responsible guest and host.

It is filled with an abundance of natural light, and windows that open to allow the breeze to flow throughout. Double doors open to a small private balcony providing  a view of the street scape and garden square below.  The apartment is very comfortable and secure, comprising  of a spacious open plan living area with a large comfy lounge for relaxing and dining setting  to enjoy breakfast in the sun. It has all the conveniences of: TV, Stero System, DVD Player, Heating/Cooling and access to Wifi internet and fresh linen & towels are provided. Born in Melbourne, grew up in Melbourne, and this great city is home.  My work in management consulting and executive education takes me around Australia, to Asia, the Middle East and Europe.  

I've been an airbnb host since beginning of 2012 (yup... since before airbnb was a global phenomenon) and have a range of properties on offer.  You'll find they're all fabulously located, spotlessly clean and super-comfortable and convenient.  I travel enough to know what makes for a great home-away-from-home... and that's what I promise to deliver for you.

Happy to answer your questions about Melbourne or my properties 

;-)

name: Bright Gertrude St Studio Apartment
summary: NA
space: Gertude Street studio apartment offers the convenience of a brilliant location, nestled on the city fringe and in the heart of iconic Fitzroy. The apartment provides the comforts of home away from home, with comfortable queen sized bed, large bathroom with two person shower, self contained kitchen in a bright light filled airy space. Need more space, or are your desired dates unavailable, check out my other listing https://www.airbnb.com.au/rooms/2182285 Fresh linen is provided and the kitchen provides the basic essentials you need to prepare your own meals. There are multiple grocers located minutes away by foot which are open late. There a supermarket close to the corner of Brunswick and Johnston street. The apartment features reverse cycle Air-conditioning ensuring comfort in every one of Melbourne's seasons. Take the amount of time you've allotted to hang out on Gertrude Street, and double it. Getting to grips with this microcosm of the best bits of Fitzroy is equal parts time cons

name: A cocoon in the heart of St Kilda
summary: Quiet, comfortable, spacious room in stylish but relaxed apartment, close to restaurants, bars, cafe life and the beaches of St Kilda and easy city access via public transport.
space: Harper's is a private room, tucked away at the rear of a contemporary apartment block right in the heart of St Kilda.  THE APARTMENT The apartment has two bedrooms, a fully equipped kitchen, an open plan living and dining room, a single bathroom with large shower and a sunny courtyard that leads to a communal garden. The bedroom is spacious and stylish.  AREA  The apartment is super quiet despite being in the middle of all the buzz around. I don't provide breakfast but the cafe downstairs is great.  The St Kilda tram station is just a short walk away and has regular trams into the CBD or other areas of Melbourne. There is tourist information and many other shops within walking distance.  It's just a short walk or a 5 minute walk to cafes, the beach and everything St Kilda has to offer.  YOUR HOST I am a single creative professional woman. I am away quite a bit but when I am home I share with my very friendly labradoodle George.

notes: NA
transit: The Tram which takes you straight to the city is only a few steps away from the apartment.
access: Guests are welcome to share my home as if it was their own. The kitchen is fully equipped and you are welcome to use it.
interaction: I am always happy to meet and have a chat with guests and tell them anything they need to know about the area. If you prefer to keep to yourself that is fine. The room is spacious and private and has a TV/DVD player.
house_rules: The apartment is a no-smoking area but I don't mind if you smoke in the courtyard. The body corporate doesn't allow smoking in the communal garden.
host_about: I am a single, creative professional woman. I work part time as an interior decorator and my other work is as a screenwriter. I go away down the coast for week-ends quite regularly and take my dog George with me. There are plenty of places to eat within walking distance of my home so I am often out of an evening visiting friends, catching a movie or having a bite to eat close by. When I am at home I like to cook and watch a good TV series (HBO, AMC, Homeland, Mad Men etc) or news and documentaries. I am very social but I also like quiet nights at home. I enjoy meeting people from other places and cultures and sharing my home with them.

name: Carr's Cottage Ringwood North
summary: We love living in this beautiful, peaceful, tree filled environment.  We also appreciate the proximity to facilities if and when we need them.  We visit Warrandyte Village on a regular basis and often take walks along the banks of the Yarra River.
space: Description This very private fully furnished, self contained cottage offers accommodation for up to 2 adults.  The Cottage has a separate well equipped kitchen and bathroom with glass sliding doors off the lounge/bedroom area leading to a secluded deck with outdoor furniture, barbecue and magnificent views.  The Cottage is very centrally located - an ideal spot from which to explore the Yarra Valley, Dandenongs, Warrandyte, the Mornington Penninsular and is only 30 minutes drive from Melbourne City.  A bus service runs past the top of the street which connects to the Train Station from where trains will take you to either Belgrave (Puffing Billy Steam Train and the Dandenong Ranges) or Lilydale (Yarra Valley) in one direction and Melbourne City in the other (approximate 40 minute train ride). Private transport of course makes these popular destinations even closer.  Yarra Valley Winery Day Tours also operate from the Ringwood train station or pickup can be arranged directly from the C

neighborhood_overview: The property is situated on the side of a hill and overlooks a valley of trees.  It is a very peaceful environment with much bird life.  However, it is close to all amenities including shops, movie theatres, restaurants, cafes etc.  There is a very pleasant bush walk just minutes walk from the cottage and more extensive walks nearby.
notes: NA
transit: Off street parking is available at the property for 1 vehicle.  The nearest bus stop is at the top of the street.  The bus will take you to the Ringwood Railway Station in approximately 7 minutes.  The train to the city takes around 40 minutes.  To drive into the city down the M3 Freeway takes approximately 25 minutes during Off Peak periods
access: Access to the cottage is down the side of the main house. You will be welcome to access the garden and lawn area surrounding the cottage.  You are welcome to use the laundry in the house when either of us is at home.
interaction: More often than not either my husband or I are at home in the big house on week days.  We are always very happy to assist you if you have any queries, however the cottage is very private and separate from the house - your privacy is guaranteed.
house_rules: The pathway down to the cottage is on a gradient with three wide steps at the base of the pathway. Although there is a handrail, access may not be suitable for some with a walking disability.
host_about: I am now five years into my retirement and am thoroughly enjoying  it. I have much more time to do the things I love most - spending time with family, gardening, reading, undertaking various projects, welcoming a wide variety of local and international guests to the property. Most of all I love taking holidays with my husband.

name: Riverside Hideaway - Private bathroom + WiFi
summary: Nestled in the trees by the Yarra river, my home is 7 kms Nth of Melbourne a short walk from Fairfield Station, cafes, restaurants & parklands. Your comfortable room has a garden view & queen bed, with private bathroom & entrance. A basic breakfast is available - cereals, toast, coffee & tea.
space: My home is over 100 years old, 7 kms north of Melbourne CBD in the leafy suburb of Fairfield. It is 5 mins walk from the Yarra river & beautiful Fairfield boathouse, & about 8 mins walk from Fairfield Railway Station (800 m) , with good access to buses & you will find trams not too far away.  Within walking distance are many great cafes & only 2 Train stops away you will find Northcote high st with it's abundance of funky bars and eateries. Your newly built room has a view onto the garden with 1 Queen bed and private bathroom, and a private entrance if you wish to use it. The bathroom has a rain showerhead, bath and toilet and contains some toiletries which you can use. I appreciate how important a good nights sleep is so I have taken this into account in your room with blackout curtains, a pillow top mattress, different bedcoverings for warmth & a variety of pillow choices.  I own a very affectionate dog so you would most likely get some cuddles from him and I have some friendly chick

neighborhood_overview: The shops are within walking distance right near the station & there are many cafes & eating choices there. There is lots of wildlife in the area so you are likely to see possums, lots of birds & perhaps even one of the blue tongue lizards that live under the house. Because of the natural bush land so close by there are many bike paths & walking tracks.
notes: Your pets are very welcome to stay with you for a small extra cost- cats $5 per day & dogs $10 per day. My home is not suitable for young children.
transit: The house is an easy 8 mins walk from Fairfield Railway Station (800 m), with good access to buses routes & trams are not too far away.  The train line takes you to - Westgarth - High St Northcote, the Westgarth historic cinema, many funky bars and an abundance of amazing cafes & restaurants Victoria Park - Abbortsford convent & childrens farm Richmond - great shopping, factory outlets Jolimont - The MCG, Melbourne tennis Centre, AAMI park soccer stadium, Hisense area next door to Melbourne Park, Olympic Park Stadium & Rod Laver arena and of course to the city.
access: There is free Wifi available & guests can use the kitchen & sitting area, and you are welcome to cook meals here too (please see the note below regarding extra charge).  My kitchen is brand new so I would ask you to take great care when using it.  As many guests choose not to use the kitchen my basic price reflects this, so rather than charge a higher price, the room price is without use of the kitchen. Each booking is priced on breakfast kitchen use only. The kitchen is beautiful and spacious and very suitable for communal cooking so if you would like to make other meals on a regular basis you are very welcome to do so. I will provide refrigerator & cupboard space for your food and there will be a daily extra charge of $5 per night added, this includes use of oil, salt & pepper and condiments. I provide basic breakfast goodies - coffee, tea, toast & cereals but would expect you to provide any other meals for yourself.  If your stay is over 2 weeks I would also expect you to buy oil, s
interaction: I am happy to join you for meals from time to time but also will respect your need for privacy.  It is your holiday and I would ensure that you have a relaxed time. I treasure my tranquility during working hours so please keep all noise down. I need my rest so I'm not usually up for general conversation, especially in the morning & the evening.  Please respect this, and remember this is my sanctuary & home, not a hotel.
house_rules: *During business hours if I have clients come for beauty or relaxation treatments I would expect guests to stay at the back area of the house and to be fairly quiet.  *Because I work from home and need a tranquil, relaxed environment my home is not suitable for young children. I also expect a high degree of tidiness & cleanliness. *My home is my sanctuary and I expect guests to be very respectful of the space - it is NOT a hotel so please keep this in mind during your stay *Noise must be kept to a minimum so if you are making noise e.g. taking on the phone please do so in your room and avoid putting on your speaker phone *I treasure and need my rest particularly in the evening, and am not usually available for conversation or company during this time *Smoking is allowed but only outside please. *Visitors are welcome but ONLY by prior arrangment please.
host_about:
I'm an outgoing, friendly & warm person and I enjoy providing hospitality. 
Airbnb is a great way to do that and is instrumental in helping me finish off my home renovations.  My goal is to provide an exceptional level of accommodation for people at a reasonable price, and I am constantly working to improve the rooms, house and garden to make everything look & feel beautiful. 

Some personal things -

I love going out & go to live music events regularly ... I also play music so have a great network of musical friends.
I also enjoy going to outdoor music parties and you will often find me out in the bush with my caravan filling my days with laughter, dancing & hugs.
In the past I have hosted many travellers through the couch surfing & helpx groups offering free accommodation and have met people from all over the world making many new friends.
I have travelled to many countries myself and spent 5 years living & working in London with Europe at my door, & I really enjoyed the little weekend jaunts as it was so close & easy.
I like to live life to the full & try to bring some happiness to the world around me. Embracing the differences of others & celebrating diversity is a big part of that. 
Above all; kindness & love rule my life ... and a smile from the heart is a gift we can all share.

*I run my house primarily on my own with limited income and sometimes things don't work properly which can happen with older homes. This won't affect the quality of your stay of course but is worth noting*
*Solo male guests - Airbnb now only reveals a profile picture when a booking is confirmed. As this presents a personal safety issue (my home is my sanctuary after all), I will require access to a picture of your face elsewhere prior to confirmation and I may ask a few extra questions about your stay*

I look forward to welcoming you into my home :-)

name: Roof room
summary: Small room at roof level with your own entry, own bathroom, no kitchen, outdoor roof space with great views for relaxing. Price is low because although bathroom has good plumbing and plenty of hot water the walls and tiles are in terrible shape, paint peeling off pending major renovations.
space: Your room is at roof level. You have your own bathroom on the roof level, reached via the (indoor) landing. The lift reaches to level 6, and one flight of stairs gains the roof.   We also have an airbnb on level 6, so don't go in there by mistake, your rooms are up the stairs. You are in the centre of the City, close to Flinders Street Railway station, trams, theatres, restaurants, Federation Square, National Gallery. When the weather is good, you can sit outside on the roof and enjoy a great view out of the City towards the river and gardens. The room is small but cosy.  The bed is double (not queen) with a good mattress. In winter we provide a heater, and as the room is small, it heats quickly.  There is thick carpet on the floor, windows that you can open and a skylight that you can open, with a blind.  There is no airconditioning, just a fan.  In a major heatwave it will get hot. In "ordinary" Melbourne heat the concrete is well insulated and stays cool. Our laundry is also on roof

neighborhood_overview: Boredom should not be an issue as there is a 18 hole golf course, several gyms and an aquatic center within 2 km from the house, not to mention a scenic bike track.
notes: The house is in a safe and secure neighborhood, but for added ease of mind we have security cameras covering the front of the house and the side. All rooms have lockable doors and guests get a set of keys peer room.
transit: The bus leaves out the front of our house and the local train station in down the road, we also provide bikes free of charge so guests can take them to the station or even into the city. If arriving or leaving by plane, train or any other method of transport, we also offer a pick up/drop off service for $40 AUD whenever possible, a taxi from the airport could be close to double.
access: Guests have access to everything in the house and as seen in our pictures except our bedroom and our cars :-) So Kitchen, BBQ, Spa, Gym etc. is at at your disposal.
interaction: We live at the property and love to socialize, but as the house is huge all guests will have an option of privacy if they wish. There is a living room for each bedroom so space is never a problem. We have lots of suggestions for things to do and places to see, we have even made several tours for you to follow, all collected in our house information book, this also includes the most price competitive options for travel and car rentals etc. With experience of working in hotels Ryan and Rhiannon also have prepared a welcome pack you will find in your room with lots of information and maps that will be useful during your stay. We even have self serve room menu with drinks and snacks if you run out of you own!
house_rules: We would appreciate it if people booking, please make sure your profile has a picture of you  :-)  As the house is full of artwork and custom made furniture we only accept young children if full accountability is taken for any damages, we hope you can understand. We do not allow pets unless specifically requested and agreed to beforehand.  We do not allow smoking inside the house, but do have an area for you outside. If you loose the house keys we may charge for replacement of locks. We offer pick up and drop offs to airport or city if available for only $40 AUD, but please plan ahead. If you damage or break something you have to compensate or replace it if possible. We do not want you to feel as a guest staying with us, but as a friend that lives with us, make yourself at home. Only thing you can do wrong is not ask a question if you have one. We look forward to meeting you and sharing our home and city with you. Kind regards Ryan & Rhiannon
host_about:
Ryan and Rhiannon are your hosts
Ryan is a fashion designer and trained tailor, working from home.
Rhiannon also works in fashion as an account manager.
We both love movies, socializing with friends and enjoying everything Melbourne and life has to offer.
We recently completed out dream home and a large part of out dream was to be able to share it with others, keeping a fresh perspective on you surroundings is important, so you never forget to keep discovering. There is no better way of doing that than with friends from all over the world.
Ryan has lived 17 years in Norway and only came back to Australia when he was going to University.
Since then he has gained experience as a concierge, bartender etc. so between Ryan and Rhiannon you could not wish for better hosts.

name: GRAND PRIX PERFECT
summary: No better place to stay for the Grand Prix weekend! We have a beautiful apartment, great neighbours and the location could not be better. We're knowledgeable locals who would love to help you get the most out of your stay in lovely Melbourne!
space: Spacious 2 Bedroom, 2 Bathroom modern apartment with breathtaking beachfront views from every room in the house. Fully furnished, this apartment is perfect for a cosmopolitan beachside getaway. Features fully equipped kitchen (including cafe-quality coffee machine), bar, balcony and dining room right on the waterfront, 2 bathrooms and a separate laundry with washer/dryer. Only 600 m from GATE 1 of the Albert Park Grand Prix circuit and Middle Park shopping precinct, 1.5km from bustling and lively St Kilda and right on the 112 tram line that will take you straight into the city centre - this apartment is perfect for ultimate Grand Prix weekend. Minimum 4 night stay but flexible for more if needed. First time listing the apartment but guaranteed not to disappoint.

neighborhood_overview: Middle Park is  one of the best suburbs in Melbourne, with so much diversity to offer. Wide leafy streets, lovely houses and very family oriented. Magnificent Albert Park lake is a very short stroll, and then the beautiful beach at your front door. Armstrong St shops is also a 5 minute walk, with restaurants, cafes and a supermarket. There's a nice local pub as well, the Middle Park Hotel with great food on offer in the dining room. St Kilda is a 20 minute walk, which is the funky, arty and "it" place to be in Melbourne. It also absolutely buzzes in Summer.
notes: Waking up to this view every day is a joy that we are excited that others may share this too! We also have access to discounted water sports and tours around Melbourne and Australia if desired.
transit: There are 2 tram lines within a 5 minute walk (the 96 and 112) which both go into the CBD. We  have Myki cards for guests so you won't have to buy them when you get here, just borrow our and load them with credit! We also have access to discounted fares with Uber, if private cars are more your style :)
access: Guests will have full access to the apartment, nothing off limits. Apartment is rented as a whole, so you will never be sharing with anyone else.
interaction: Introductory only. I am a tourism provider in Melbourne so am excited to give you the run down of our amazing city and point you in the right direction of what to do and see while here. Am always just a phone call away.
house_rules: We ask that you are respectful of our neighbours, and keep noise to a minimum. We have lovely polished floor boards so we ask ladies (or men as well!) to remove any stiletto heels before entering.
host_about:
Hi it's Will & Dave! We're in our early 30's and listing our much-loved apartment for the first time... We love the water - we make sure we swim out the front at least once a day (even in winter!).

We're very laid back, and looking forward to meeting our guests (but promise to leave you alone during your stay!). We'll also be available to help you out with anything you need to make your stay enjoyable, including advice on how to best enjoy our wonderful city!

We look forward to hearing from you...

Will and Dave

Relax in the Powlett Reserve or on Darling Square.    Smile a friendly greeting at the people you pass, grab a morning coffee from the George Street cafe, enjoy an afternoon vino in the Fitzroy Gardens.  Shopping at the discount designer outlets

This means we can't always accept short bookings more than a few weeks in advance unless they follow-on from an existing booking or fill an otherwise vacant block.  Check the calendar, and feel free to reach out with your requirements.  We'll advise the best rate possible.  (2) Electricity, gas, water and internet broadband are included in the rate BUT SUBJECT TO FAIR USE by the guest. Electricity usage in excess of 14.5 kWh per day will incur an extra charge at the rate of AUD0.26 per kWh. Sufficient broadband is provided for normal usage (email, surfing, youtube, (Hidden by Airbnb) etc) but data-intensive use may result in the internet speed being shaped.
