summary: Airbnb guests can relax in this casually stylish apartment and enjoy the beach panorama. The apartment is light, colourful, uncluttered and situated on the third floor of a prestigious apartment building. The neighbourhood will welcome you. St Kilda has it all.
space: My third floor apartment is on famous St Kilda beach facing the St Kilda pier, the marina and Port Phillip Bay.  You can sit on the balcony and watch the kite surfers or simply watch the magnificent panorama.  The guest bedroom has a double bed with top quality bedding - double electric blanket for winter with a cosy quilt and alpaca rugs.  For summer -  a cotton blanket, quality sheets and pillows. The room has ample cupboard space, bedside lamps, book shelves with storage and hanging space, décor in fresh greens and blues, television and more than enough books and magazines to read. From the bedroom window there is a skyline view of the city. My apartment is second last along the walkway so the room is private, quiet and very safe and comfortable. Guests have their own fully stocked bathroom with Turkish or traditional bath towels, hand towels and bathmat, shower gel, hand cream and body lotion. neighborhood_overview: I love my neighbourhood because it has a wonderful, lively, colourful atmosphere.  There is always plenty of activity, a great array of cafes, bars and restaurants.   The music is amazing. The Palais theatre nearby schedules performers from all over the world. It is worthwhile to see who is on when you are almost across the road. You won't be disappointed. A concert at the Palais is incredible. The nearby Memo Music Hall is also unmissable. Both walking distance, both venues you won't forget. A stroll along the pier to see the penguins who nest among the rocks is a must.  Best time to see them is at dusk.  While you are there have a drink or a snack at the kiosk.  Breakfast is excellent at Il Fornaio, Phamish and the Cowderoy Street Milk Bar. Clothing, souvenirs and food shopping is also great fun at the South Melbourne Market which is a favourite venue for Melburnians and visitors.
notes: If travellers wish to know personal recommendations regarding sightseeing I am most happy to help them. I can also recommend Airbnb accommodation at the Great Ocean Road.  This magnificent region is far better enjoyed with an overnight stop. It is an enormous distance to travel in one day and not recommended. A journey to the glorious wine region of the Mornington Peninsula can be enhanced with an overnight stay in recommended Airbnb accommodation. For visitors with specific travel queries I will do my best to assist as I have had extensive travel experience both domestic and international.
transit: No. 12 Tram is a minute's walk away. The stop is in the street behind my apartment.  It runs frequently to the city.
access: Guests have access to car park space for one car.
interaction: I interact with my guests in a friendly manner but I am very aware of their desire for privacy. International visitors are often jet lagged when they arrive at my apartment so I am very respectful of their tiredness and disorientation.  International flights arrive in the early morning so guests are most welcome to check in when they leave the airport. I
house_rules: NOTICE!  Smokers are asked to smoke outside the apartment. Any utensils or kitchen equipment to be handled with care, washed and put away after use.  Guests are asked to comply with the rules of the apartment building i.e. rules of general behaviour and decorum regarding noise and use of pool.
host_about:
I am from Melbourne Australia.  

Am very fit and have travelled extensively all over the world. Music is important to me. I live in a very attractive, relaxed, friendly apartment community. I enjoy good conversation about local and international affairs and am a keen film goer. Enjoy a good book. Sing with  gospel/blues choir.
My apartment has a swimming pool and tennis court and glorious views of famous St Kilda beach.

If guests wish to visit the many varied and beautiful regions only a short distance from Melbourne,  I can recommend  sightseeing through personal contacts.

Am looking forward to welcoming Airbnb travellers and sharing my beautiful apartment and the energy of interesting St Kilda with them.

name: Ravishing Richmond, Beautiful Bowen
summary: On request I will consider 2 day stays. My place is right next to the city.Trams 48&75 stop at Epworth Hospital - 6 min walk to my place. From the Airport you catch the Skybus to Southern Cross Station, & then the South Morang Train (stopping all stations) to West Richmond Station (6 min to my place). You will be surprised how quite my place is and is also very comfortable. It is a multi cultural suburb resulting in many & varied restaurants and lots of places of interest to entertain you.
space: Hi I'm Bella, My gorgeous cottage in Richmond has been  my home for the last 18 years.  It has a great 2nd bedroom to accommodate a fellow traveler. The king single bed is great for the extra length required for tall people! It's just a hop, skip & jump away from.... BRIDGE RD & VICTORIA ST RICHMOND - with its numerous cafes, bars, pubs,  & restaurants, so there's no need to go far! But if you decide to, the city is a short walk away or just hop on a tram on Bridge Rd, just up the road and you're there in no time. It's only a couple of short tram rides away from the Grand Prix or you could walk through Olympic Park & The Botanic Gardens to get there. South Yarra is a short tram ride away in one direction and Collingwood & Fitzroy is close by in the other direction, but Richmond is so central you can walk to almost all the entertainment venues like the MCG, Rod Laver Arena, and even the Royal Botanic Gardens where you can see live performances all the way through the summer months. This

neighborhood_overview: Richmond is a multi cultural suburb very close to the City. Therefore all the events occurring in Melbourne, especially at the MCG are within walking distance.  It is an easy and enjoyable walk to/from the city (about 35 minutes).   Melbourne is also a city full of places to go - gardens, museums, galleries, shows & of course many events. However, you cannot pass the restaurants in and eateries in Richmond! They are great - providing lots of different cuisine at all different prices.  With all this activity it is wonderful to return to my place, which is a quiet spot and also very comfortable.
notes: I want you to feel relaxed and enjoy your stay!  Above all, treat my home like your home, being mindful makes everyone happy:)  No smoking in the house  No visitors allowed to stay overnight.  I ask my guests to observe quiet time after midnight. As water is a precious commodity in Australia, I would ask guest to limit showers to 20 minutes at the most.
transit: Public Transport from my place is very easy.   The South Morang Train (stopping all stations) is a 6 minute walk from my place.  Very useful if you are travelling to/from the airport - catch the Skybus which takes you to the city -  Southern Cross Station, and then catch the South Morang Train (stopping all stations) to  the West Richmond Station, which is about a 6 minute walk from my place.   Otherwise, you can catch the No 75 tram which takes you down Flinders Street Melbourne or you catch the No 48 tram which takes you down Collins St Melbourne.  The return stop is at the Epworth Hospital - stop number 15 (1st stop after Punt Rd). Walking from my place to the Epworth Hospital tram stop takes about 5 minutes. There is also a bus on Punt Road travelling North/South.  Bus stops are at the corners of Punt Road with Bridge Road and also Freeman St - (just close to the West Richmond Station).
access: If arriving during the week access to my place will need to be after 5.30pm if arrangement for entry has not been organised.   However I have a security box at the front door, and if you wish to enter when I'm at work, I will provide you with the code which contains keys to the front doors.  On all other days I can normally greet you on your arrival, but appreciate your assistance in providing an estimated time
interaction: I really want your stay to be relaxing and enjoyable.  Some people like to talk and others don't - either way I am happy.
house_rules: My aim is to provide a safe & healthy environment to all guests and therefore am protecting my place by restricting guests who live in countries the world health organisation has identified as being high risk regarding the coronovirus 19. As water is a precious commodity in Australia, I ask guests to minimize showers to 20 minutes.  Smoking is allowed outside, but not in the house. Please lock both front doors when leaving the house
host_about:
Hey, I’m Bella!  I love living in Richmond, love its vibe, its shops, cafés & clubs and it’s walking distance to everything!….Melbourne City, entertainment venues, its magical gardens, even Fabulous Fitzroy!    I'm a cat lover and share my home with my adorable cat, Gracie :) So drop me a line if my place sounds right for you! Love to hear from you and discover what brings you here so far.
I also provide wireless access using ADSL2 wireless.

neighborhood_overview: St Kilda is a famous tourist destination for its many cafes, bars and street life. The popular beach is close by (10 minute walk) and the tram stop to catch the tram into Melbourne CBD is about 30mtrs from my apartment.
notes: This is not a hotel or serviced apartment. It is my home. I live and work from here and move out when guests book the whole apartment. host_about: I am a single, creative professional woman. I work part time as an interior decorator and my other work is as a screenwriter. There are plenty of places to eat within walking distance of my home so I am often out of an evening visiting friends, catching a movie or having a bite to eat close by. When I am at home I like to cook and watch a good TV series (HBO, AMC, Homeland, Mad Men etc) or news and documentaries. I am very social but I also like quiet nights at home. I enjoy meeting people from other places and cultures and sharing my home with them.

name: Kanturk Country Retreat hideaway
summary: Set on 3ha of garden and native bushland with a three-hole, country-style golf course, tennis court, solar-heated salt chlorinated swimming pool, bush walks, croquet and bbq facilities. Ideal for romantic getaways or gatherings with family and friends for special events.  While it sleeps 19 people, the base price is for 12 people - 2 in The Pool House, 2 in The Sixth Hole and 8 in Kookaburra Cottage. Additional guests are charge $95 per person.
space: The cottages:  Kookaburra Cottage is a contemporary-style cottage with an open-plan kitchen-living area, with full kitchen facilities including dishwasher, coffee plunger and orange press. The bathroom facilities include two showers and toilets and a laundry. It has a king-sized bed in one bedroom, a queen in the second, a built-in bunk in the third and a dormitory that sleeps six in the fourth (one on a trundle bed). All linen and bath towels, tea and coffee provisions, home made pure olive oil and coconut oil soap and home made cookies are provided for your secluded retreat.  TV, DVD and CD/radio provided. The Sixth Hole is a one-bedroom log cabin with a large open plan kitchen/living area featuring a large stone fireplace. The bedroom features a queen-sized bed and there is a double sofa bed in the lounge.  Sally makes olive oil and coconut oil soap, shampoo and body scrubs, deodorant and toothpaste on the premises. If you would like to see her range of products, just ask. They can

neighborhood_overview: Enjoy the natural setting (wallabys and koalas used to live in this area but now are rarely seen) abundant birdlife occasionally sugar gliders in the area of Langwarrin South, just 45 minutes from  Melbourne CBD, five minutes to shopping centres of Somerville, Langwarrin and Pearcedale and 15 minutes to the seaside thriving metropolis of Frankston. Langwarrin South is at the gateway to the beautiful Mornington Peninsula with its stunning beaches, world-class golf courses, wineries and restaurants.  Fishing and boating activities abound at nearby Tooradin, Warneet, Yaringa Boat Harbour and Hastings all about 15 minutes away. And the Langwarrin Flora and Fauna Reserve, Cruden Farm- the home of the late philanthropist Dame Elisabeth Murdoch- Mulberry Hill the former home of the late artist Sir Daryl Lindsay and Lady Joan Lindsay author of 'Picnic at Hanging Rock', and  the award winning Pearcedale Moonlit Sanctuary is five minutes away.
notes: While Kanturk Country Retreat sleeps 19 people, the base price to book the three cottages assumes there are 8 people booked in - two in The Pool House, two in The Sixth Hole and 4 in Kookaburra Cottage. Additional guests are charge $95 per person. Bookings to just one cottage are charged accordingly. Due respect must be shown to the guests in the other cottages. Private property The house inside the driveway circle is our home and is private property. The rest of the property is for you to enjoy. Let us know what you are particularly interested in so we can ensure it is ready for use when you arrive.  Welcoming party Our little dogs Marley, Hendrix and Lulu will join the welcoming party on arrival. They are very friendly little dogs - toy poodles and a Maltese terrier. Please let us know if you don't like dogs and we will keep them inside. The golf course, tennis court and swimming pool are shared facilities for the use of all guests. Day guests We are legally responsible for anyone wh
transit: Trains run regularly from Melbourne to Frankston. Every 20 minutes in peak hours and approximately hourly until midnight.  Buses run from Frankston to Pearcedale (the 776 buses) which stops at both ends of West Road. However we will usually try and pick you up from Frankston station if we can. This is by prior arrangement obviously. Taxis also operate from Frankston.
access: It is set in country gardens on a property of three hectares with native bush walks, bbq facilities, tennis court, solar-heated swimming pool and country-style golf course. The property is ideal for club getaways, family gatherings, birthday celebrations, book clubs - the possibilities are endless. Or just enjoy the bird watching. We live on the property in a separate house. The area inside the circle of the driveway is private property.
interaction: We interact with guests as is required. We like to greet guests to show them around if they wish, provide anything they may need like golf clubs, or tennis racquets and balls, and answer any questions. Other than that, we like to leave things to the guests. We may be involved in property maintenance and gardening if necessary, but generally when guests arrive our work ends. If you are making too much noise, we may ask you to turn it down a little.
house_rules: Due respect must be paid to other residents on the property and our neighbours. The property is for the use of the booked in guests only. This means that no visitors may enter the property without prior approval of management.  There is no smoking in the cottages but ash trays are provided on the picnic tables.  One bed is the sofa in the lounge room of the Sixth Hole that may be used as a double bed. While the property is not fenced on one side, pets are OK by prior arrangement so long as they stay outside the cottages and under the effective control of their owners. Golf can only be played on the golf course. If you are a novice, we can provide plastic golf balls to practice your stroke on. This may be done in front of the cottage. Please don't alter the pool umbrellas unless you know how they work. If in doubt just ask and we are happy to help. There are three cottages on the property. Due respect must be shown to the guests in the other cottages.  Our little poodle dogs Hendrix and
host_about: I am a writer and journalist and mother of four young adults. Gary my husband (also a journalist) look after the property, and manage the cottages between a busy life of visiting friends in Melbourne, seeing films and gardening. We love our property and hope you will enjoy it as much as we do.

name: The Stables, Island of Richmond
summary: Superbly located hotel style accommodation in a quiet courtyard with independent access.
space: The Stables is a single bedroom unit, akin to a hotel room, which is  separated from the main residence by the yard.     Built in 1900, The Stables were lovingly and sympathetically renovated in 2010.  They retain their original red brick floors and timber doors, but now feature a beautiful modern ensuite.    Location is everything, and you would be hard pressed to get closer to the MCG.  All of the attractions of the city are just a pleasant stroll through the beautiful parkland.  This is an excellent location if you are going to concerts or sporting events at Rod Laver Arena or AAMI Stadium.   Located centrally between Bridge Rd and Swan St, which are home to fantastic cafes, restaurants, and shopping. Trams, trains, and buses are all nearby. name: Melbourne Funky Flinders Lane ❤️of the CBD
summary: Funky Flinders Lane! Low Rise Heritage Listed Building in the heart of Melbourne CBD. The best location, and a Melbourne premier Lane-Way with classy cafes, bars & restaurants. You will think you are in Europe.  Fully equipped. Close to everything and in the FREE TRAM ZONE. Live like a local in Melbourne.
space: Our apartment is great for short term rentals of either two nights to four weeks. Nestled in a Heritage Listed Boutique Building (circa 1911), a vestige of the Melbourne “rag trade" area. in the beautiful Flinders Lane. It's a quirky homely environment with lots of character and not a hotel. If you like personality combined with comfort then we think we have it just right. The apartment is fully furnished with Queen size bed, and sofa, fully appointed kitchen, refrigerator and freezer, washing machine, dryer, hair dryer, flat screen television, unlimited wifi. HIGH-SPEED Internet NO DOWNLOAD OR UPLOAD LIMIT. There is a sofa bed for a friend sharing the apartment with yourself. So you don't have to bunk together (always a bonus!) Located in the best spot in Melbourne, entrance is in the gorgeous Bligh Place, one of the most beautiful lanes in Melbourne for cafes and restaurants. In fact a showpiece lane for the City of Melbourne, where cafes, restaurants and residents coexist in harmony

name: Heart of the CBD
summary: NA
space: Spacious apartment fully equipped for the short to medium stay.  Located at the top end of Chinatown in an area surrounded by some great restaurants and close to all of the main theaters. A short walk in most directions will take you into the gardens or the major shopping areas. The apartment is a one bedroom layout but at 85m2, is set up to offer a second private sleeping area and modern kitchen, dining and lounge areas.   High ceilings and large opening windows overlook a quite lane.  Situated in the heritage classified "Gordon Place" in a quiet corner of the building, guests can use the common areas which include many private seating ares inside and a swimming pool. There is a small cafe at the front of the building and plenty of places nearby to buy your food and supplies. You are situated very close to a number of Melbourne's best and/or favourite restaurants. The apartment is located just a short walk from Parliament railway station or the Bourke St tram networks.

notes: Located in the heart of Melbourne. Close to Melbourne Central,Emporium and Melboune Universary,local cafes and restaurants.
transit: CBD now has free tram travel in zone 1. Which covers the main city area. Parliament station is just around the corner for train use. And cabs pass the front door regularly.
access: The apartment is in a three storey heritage listed building with two cafes in the atrium through which the building is entered. Both have their own charm and make very good coffee and delicious home made pastries.  There are common areas through out the building giving you a feel of space where ever you go. The bbq area is out side in the pool courtyard and is wonderful in the warmer months. The charm of this building is the age and architecture. A lift is available to the apartment or you can use the stairs which make for quick access in and out of the building.
interaction: NA
house_rules: We ask that you treat the place as you would your own. No gatherings of more than 6 people in apartment. Respect the rights of the other occupants of the building.
host_about: We are from Cape Woolamai on the south coast of Australia.  We like to eat great food, interact with local folk, experience the culture of places and look at the buildings that comprise a great city.  We have adult children so we can now go to the places we like and submerge ourselves.  We love music and lots of walking around taking in our surrounds.

name: Colourful Art Deco Apartment with Street Views
summary: Stretch out in this spacious, light-drenched Art Deco apartment filled with original art. Watch the morning rush below through the city view windows in a space featuring pops of colour, a blend of rustic and chic furnishings, and an open living area.
space: Located in historic, tree lined Queen Street Honey Apartments are the perfect choice to spread out and make your self at home. The advantage of this home is everything Melbourne has to offer is just out your front door. The location is fantastic as you are right in the heart of the central business district with Melbourne's famous laneways less than a block away and the city's amazing shopping, dining and cultural options all so very close. You won't need a car here – everything is an easy walk or tram ride.   Got a big group? Honey Apartment One and Two have the added unique feature that they are located right next to each other in the same building. This is a perfect option if you want to accommodate up to nine people. To book both apartments - https://www.airbnb.com.au/rooms/18708092 Honey Apartments are a contemporary update on the building's art deco past with a full kitchen, laundry and they both have two bedrooms. The beds are all REAL BEDS (no fold out couches or air mattresses
description: Stretch out in this spacious, light-drenched Art Deco apartment filled with original art. Watch the morning rush below through the city view windows in a space featuring pops of colour, a blend of rustic and chic furnishings, and an open living area.
neighborhood_overview: Find adventures within 500 metres. Hungry? Japanese, Middle East fusion, Italian, Thai, and many more are all nearby. Thirsty? Enjoy beer and pinball at Bartronica, head to Robot for a Japanese vibe, or Saluministi for stunning coffee and cannoli.
notes: Kid Friendly Honey Apartments are single level dwelling located on the 3rd floor, accessible via 2 lifts. Portacot and highchair are available on request at no extra charge and all beds are easily accessible for children of all ages. There is a bath in the bathroom and a dinning room table to serve family dinners. There is no outside area but a kid’s playground is only 2 blocks away and the Aquarium is located just around the corner. There is no parking provided with the accommodation but there are several commercial car parks less than 200 metres away.
transit: The location is perfect with all the following attractions a very short walk or tram ride away… WALKING • National Gallery of Victoria • Victorian Arts Centre • Queen Victoria market • St Pauls Cathedral • Block Arcade • Forum Theatre • Yarra River • Southbank • Crown Casino • Aquarium • ANZ Gothic bank • China Town • Collins Street • Parliament House • Bourke Street Mall • Flinders Street station • Federation Square • Southern Cross Station Direct tram ride or more than 15-minute walk • MCG  • Tennis Centre • Etihad Stadium • Botanical Garden’s NB Trams, trains, taxi rank, and busses are less than a block away
access: You will have the entire apartment to yourself.
interaction: I meet and greet all guests on arrival to hand over the keys, introduce you to my apartment and answer any questions you may wish to ask from how does the washing machine work to advise on my favourite restaurants. I am always accessible via phone, email or sms if you have any questions during your stay.
house_rules: BOOKING TERMS AND CONDITIONS TARIFFS  Please note that the extra person fee applies to all occupants including children and infants. NB – As Airbnb doesn’t include infants in the occupancy count, you will be charged the extra amount as an additional fee which will be requested after booking. TELEPHONES  It is not possible to have the phone connected during your stay.  FUNCTIONS  Our accommodation is for residential purposes only. Functions or parties are strictly prohibited! name: Bedroom with Ensuite at Ivanhoe
summary: Situated in quiet and prestigious area of Ivanhoe, the bedroom has a Queen size bed, ceiling fan and modern en suite bathroom.  Quality linen and towels used and Wifi is available.  You are welcome to use the Lounge Room to relax in.  Please be considerate with perfumes and aftershave as I have allergies.
space: The bedroom is a guest bedroom in our house which is a charming, English inspired home located in the quiet and prestigious Fairy Hills area of Ivanhoe, North East of the city.  It is easy to reach the city from here.  You can do your exploring and sightseeing in the city and then return to a quiet and tranquil environment.  The house is set in a garden with trees, shrubs, and herbs. The bedroom has a ceiling fan and a modern en suite bathroom.  Quality linen and towels are used.  The house has modern hydronic heating throughout with a heating unit in the bedroom and a heated towel rail in the en suite.  Wifi is also available in all rooms. There is free car parking in the street. A light breakfast of fruit juice, cereal, toast, tea/coffee is included in the price. You are welcome to use the Lounge-Dining Room to relax in.   Ron and I generally use the Family Room in the evenings. Please note smoking is not allowed inside or out. If you smoke, we ask that you don't book.

neighborhood_overview: The immediate neighbourhood is very peaceful, with Upper Heidelberg Road and Ivanhoe strip shopping area a short walk or drive away with a large variety of boutique shops, restaurants and coffee shops.  The house is less than 10 minute walk along The Boulevard to Wilson's Reserve with walking trails and access to the Main Yarra bike trail, a beautiful walk/cycle track along the Yarra River into the city.  There is a public golf course at Ivanhoe and boat hire at the Fairfield Boat House both about 7 minutes drive away. It is also lovely just to walk around the streets of this area.
notes: Washing of clothes:   There is a wash trough in the laundry for hand washing of clothes.   You can use the washing machine and clothes dryer, for a small charge.   Please do not wash your clothes in the ensuite bathroom nor hang them out there.   There is a clothes airer and clothes line available for drying.
transit: It is just a 10 minute walk to Darebin Railway station or 15 minute walk to Ivanhoe Station (both Zone 1 and on the Hurstbridge Line) and a quick 15-20 minute journey to central Melbourne.
access: You are welcome to use the Lounge Room to relax in.   Ron and I generally use the Family Room in the evenings. You are also welcome to use the outside patio and garden. Use of the washing machine is available on request for a small fee.
interaction: Ron and I will be in residence when this room is rented.   When we are away travelling we do rent the entire house.  See listing under Comfortable Elegance in Ivanhoe.
house_rules: No smoking No high heels please, as they mark the polished wood floors. Please be considerate with perfumes and aftershave as I have allergies.
host_about: Susanne and Ron Clarkson are a retired couple from Melbourne Australia who enjoy travel overseas and caravanning around Australia.  Ron did Civil Engineering and Susanne did Social Research.

neighborhood_overview: Your 'lil cottage is in a premium  area of Melbourne. We are surrounded by lovely, caring neighbors who are there in the background, if you should ever need them.
notes: Free city tourists walks by volunteers, free city transport, tourist buses and events throughout the year.  Melbourne is fairly flat, so you will notice bicycles for hire all around the place. There's always stuff to do in Melbourne. Festivals, farmers markets, day trips to the country, cultural events, live entertainment and plenty happening around public holidays of which we have many.
transit: Trains and buses are 7 minutes stroll away.  Shops, fabulous cafe's, bars, 2 nice new large supermarkets are 10 minutes away.  Just at the end of the shops in Church Street is the beach. From the beach, you'll find a fabulous bike or walking track into the city along the beach, a very pretty scenic journey. A very nice thing to do this Summer in Melbourne.
access: Please check in with me before arrival for final arrangements regarding access.  In any case, I'll always be in contact with you before you arrive so it all happens nice and smoothly.
interaction: I'll be here to help make your stay as enjoyable as possible.  Basically, though, I'll just be doing my own thing around the house, unobtrusively or I just go with the flow.
house_rules: No smoking, no drugs. It's a very clean living environment here. ....all the normal things. Don't kick the dog or let him out of the house.  If he comes into your room, just shoo him out.  He's normally a very good boy. About me? I'm normally good too. But I'm allowed out of the house ha ha. Obviously, don't wreck the place please and leave everything as you found it!  You are welcome to use the kettle for tea making, the fridge, dishwasher and washing (website hidden) facilities, by special arrangement. Permanent stayers (30 days plus) obviously have use of all amenities. Normal noise reduction so neighbors don't arc up. The floors have just been polished, so "shoes off" policy in the house at the moment till the novelty dies down. I look forward to meeting you! I will ask you for full ID BEFORE moving in but also, please bring your ID with you;  Your drivers license, passport, credit card, or current council rates notice will b fine!  Thank you and I look forward to meeting you!
host_about:
Welcome to Brighton!
You'll find this place warm and welcoming. 
My little bow wow friend is a bit exuberant when he first meets people but, in a minute, he calms down and quietly just enjoys having you around.

If there's anything I can do to make your stay simply perfect, just ask!

I'm an Accountant with an IT bent.
Likes: Laughter, travel, positive people, movies, business books, gastronomy, sunshine, beautiful houses and gardens, inspirational people
Dislikes: Negativity, just HATE it, despise it, it's deplorable, terrible, makes me ill.. Tee hee.
Favorite Movies: Gran Torino, The Selfish Giant, Midnight in Paris, The Shawshank Redemption, The Kings Speech, Its a Wonderful Life.
Favourite Food: Japanese, Vietnamese...weeeelll love it all... If u must know.
Favourite people: Donald Trump, Bette Midler, Bill Gates n Brad Pitt can still ask me out if he's free ... or not.
Favourite Book of the moment: Family, Village, Tribe (The Flight Centre Story)

name: Modern Bayside Studio Apartment
summary: Self contained modern apartment with its own entrance, own bathroom and own outdoor deck.  Includes microwave, kettle, toaster and fridge.  5 mins walk to shops, 12 mins walk to railway station, 15 mins walk to beach.
space: We offer a self-contained modern apartment within the boundaries of our house. The apartment consists of a studio room with a double bed, table and two chairs, tv, a kitchenette (microwave, fridge, toaster, kettle - electric hob/BBQ also available on request), a bathroom with shower, toilet and basin and an outdoor deck with a table and chairs for your use. It has its own private entrance, so you may come and go as you please. Mordialloc is a pleasant beachside suburb about 45 mins from the centre of Melbourne. We live in a very quiet street, and our garden is visited by beautiful parrots and other wildlife. We are a few minutes walk from shops, buses and a swimming pool, and about a 12 minute walk from the railway station and centre of Mordialloc. The beach is about a 20 minute walk. The apartment is completely self-contained and private, and also attached to the house, so you can be as private or as sociable as you wish.  We also offer at no extra fee - - apartment cleaned and linen

name: Beautiful Fitzroy Getaway
summary: I have a beautiful Edwardian house located in vibrant Fitzroy at the top of Napier Street a short 1 minute walk to iconic Gertrude Street.  Located between Brunswick and Smith Street, everything you need to enjoy a fabulous stay in Melbourne is right on your doorstep, great cafés, galleries, bars, live music, boutiques, restaurants, book shops as well as outstanding shopping options.
space: The living area is a beautiful extension at the back of the house with a pitched ceiling and uninterrupted view of the small rear decked garden with a seating area which is perfect to relax in on those fabulous balmy Melbourne nights or to get a little fresh air and listen to the birds in the morning over your cup of coffee and muesli.  There are two bedrooms available in the house, the master bedroom is fully furnished with a king sized bed, lovely open fireplace and original sash windows. The second bedroom is fully furnished with a queen sized bed, chest of drawers and original sash windows.   Both rooms are really comfortable and cosy.  The street is very quiet and with the curtains drawn it’s impossible to know that it’s daylight outside so sleeping in is very easy, after a night out enjoying all Melbourne has to offer!  All sheets, blankets and bedding are provided as well as towels.   The bathroom has a bath with a shower over and the water is lovely and hot.  The bathroom is we
description: I have a beautiful Edwardian house located in vibrant Fitzroy at the top of Napier Street a short 1 minute walk to iconic Gertrude Street.  Located between Brunswick and Smith Street, everything you need to enjoy a fabulous stay in Melbourne is right on your doorstep, great cafés, galleries, bars, live music, boutiques, restaurants, book shops as well as outstanding shopping options. The living area is a beautiful extension at the back of the house with a pitched ceiling and uninterrupted view of the small rear decked garden with a seating area which is perfect to relax in on those fabulous balmy Melbourne nights or to get a little fresh air and listen to the birds in the morning over your cup of coffee and muesli.  There are two bedrooms available in the house, the master bedroom is fully furnished with a king sized bed, lovely open fireplace and original sash windows. The second bedroom is fully furnished with a queen sized bed, chest of drawers and original sash windows.   Both room
neighborhood_overview: Fitzroy has an amazing buzz and there is always something happening so it’s difficult to leave the area but if you do want to venture further afield virtually everything is a tram ride, cycle or walk away.  The Melbourne Museum and IMAX theatre is a short stroll down the road and the CBD is a 10 walk away through the beautiful Carlton Gardens. Victoria markets, Carlton, St Kilda, South Melbourne and pretty much everything else you may want to check out is a short tram ride away.  The house manual has a number of suggestions for local restaurants, things to do and maps.
notes: I always try to accommodate reasonable special requests so if there is anything else you need to make your stay even better please let me know and I will do what I can to accommodate you. NB:  please note that the cats are no longer living at the property, so if you read in the reviews that there are cats, they aren't here any more.
transit: The #86-tram stop is just a few meters away but you could easily walk into the city in about 10-15 minutes. There is fantastic public transport (trams every 10 minutes) and Melbourne Olympic Park is a 10 minute walk away so the MCG, Rod Laver and AAMI park are virtually on your doorstep which is perfect for the sports or entertainment fan.  Fitzroy has a great outdoor heated swimming pool and tennis courts, gyms and all sorts of other sporting facilities nearby.  It’s really easy to get here, you can catch the sky bus from the airport to Southern Cross station then from there you can catch Tram 86 along Gertrude St or alternatively you can catch an Uber or taxi from the airport and be here in about half an hour depending on the traffic.  Parking is available on the street out the front, see the signs for restrictions.
access: The whole house and garden.  There are a couple of cupboards where I store personal items that aren't accessible for guests as well as a clearly marked cupboard in the kitchen and the linen cupboard which is marked private.  All other areas of the house are available for guests to use.
interaction: Guests are welcome to get in touch during their stay but as I travel overseas I can't guarantee I'll be in the country so the best way to contact me is via (Hidden by Airbnb) or the Air BnB messaging system.   I always let guests know if I'm overseas in which case I will also provide a local contact in case of emergencies.
house_rules: No smoking in the house, there is a verandah at the front and garden at the back and you can smoke there although I do ask that you don't throw your cigarette butts in the garden but dispose of them thoughtfully in the bin.  No parties, having a couple of friends over for dinner or drinks is fine. The house has two bedrooms that sleep a total of 4 people in two beds.  The sofa cannot be used as an extra bed and extra bedding isn't available for this purpose.  Thank you for your understanding.
host_about:
When I'm at home in Melbourne I love to drink coffee and try out all the wonderful food Melbourne has to offer at the vast number of fabulous cafes and restaurants.  There are so many options!  

I also love movies, reading, the theatre and I also take every opportunity available to travel. For now Melbourne is my home but after living overseas for a number of years I still love to get out and see new parts of the world as much as possible. 

I look forward to meeting you soon.

Stop 16 is at the door on Abbotsford Street- you can walk to the city in 15-20 mins also.  Your room has a queen bed, built-in wardrobe and private en-suite shower, free WIFI. Apple TV/Netflix. Woolworths- 2 min walk. Car parking is available if required. Very close to hospitals, universities and CBD.  I have a new kitten so must love cats

Free Wifi through-out the house.  TV with Apple TV, Free Netflix & DVD player in the room. Best suited for single guest.

Apartment is 2 story, 2 bedrooms 2.5 bathrooms and offers fully -equipped kitchen
neighborhood_overview: Located in North Melbourne which is close to CBD, Vic Markets, Hospitals and Uni's Melbourne CBD is only a short tram ride or a nice leisurely walk away.  Tram stop is directly outside the block.   Close to shops and cafes of both North Melbourne and Kensington.  Groovy Errol Street cafe and shops are nearby, there is supermarket in walking distance and plenty more a tram ride away.  Kensington is also in walking distance.  Bike paths are nearby if you like riding and I have a bike that can be borrowed.  Royal Park, the biggest park in Melbourne is at the end of the road that also houses Melbourne Zoo.
notes: Entrance is via stairs as I live not the 1st floor. To get to the apartment it is up a flight of stairs.  Check-in is 1pm, please contact me if you need early or late checkin/outs - however if you are arriving on the same day a guest is checking in or leaving on a late flight when another guest is arriving, you may have to leave your luggage in the lounge room to allow cleaner to access to the room for the next guest. If you have an early morning arrival flight and want access to the room prior to 11am then you will need to book the night before you arrive to ensure you don't disturb checking out guests. Smoking is strictly in the outdoor area.
transit: Transport option at the front door.   Located 20 min walk from the city, or a 10-15 min tram ride to Melbourne CBD. Tramstop No. 57 Tram stops directly across the road and can take you to the CBD, Victoria Markets & RMIT  in only a few stops or to Flemington racecourse and Highpoint Shopping Centre in the other direction. The 59 tram is a 5 min walk or tram which takes you to Airport West Shopping Centre or to the hospitals and uni's then CBD.  There are also 3 train stations in walking distance Mccauley Station is the closest 5 min walk or bus, North Melbourne is a 10 min walk and Kensington Station a 10 min bus or walk.  The 402 bus takes you to Victoria Pde East Melbourne via Melbourne Uni and Carlton or to Footscray Station via Kensington Station in the other direction.    10 minute walk or tram to RMIT, Royal Melbourne hospitals and the Zoo. Walking distance to Errol St. - full of cafes, restaurants, comedy store and supermarket. From the airport you can catch a taxi for $40-50 ap
access: Apartment is 2 story, 2 bedrooms 2.5 bathrooms and offers fully -equipped kitchen with dishwasher, laundry with washing machine and dryer.  This room has it's own private bathroom with shower however toilet is separate and shared between the 2 rooms, it has locks.  Dining & lounge with outdoor area for guest use.   Suitable for single guest.  It's my house so it's lived in and has my things around it but it's always cleaned for each new guest.  Just don't expect the house to be a 5 star hotel - that's why it's cheap for an inner-city apartment with own bathroom.  The bedroom and private bathroom is only used for Airbnb guests so it's alway clean and has nothing in it but the furniture for your use.  Free underground secure parking is also available on request ($50 security key deposit refunded on return)
interaction: I live in the other room and am happy to offer advice and help but am also happy to let you do your own thing if you need privacy.    (good option if you want to make sure you are living with a local although sometimes, not often, mostly over Christmas,  I go away and rent my own room out but I let guests know in advance.) I enjoy meeting new people and will do my best to make sure my guests are looked after and enjoy their stay in Melbourne. But I'm also a quiet person who enjoys solitude every now and then so I will give you space and vica verca.
house_rules: If you book the room for 1 person, please don't show up and ask if you can have an extra guest - You must book for 2 prior to arrival.  Exceptions will be made for long term bookings only if you ask in advance and your guest is short term.  I have no control over Airbnb fees, I believe they are part of the service that make staying in peoples homes so readily available at such great costs, they ensure everyone is insured and comfortable and safe. I won't do direct bookings. Please don't ask. Smoking is permitted in outdoor areas only. There is a courtyard outside the door with chairs and tables for smoking.  Strictly NO smoking indoors. Please ensure that the heater is turned off if not at home as it is very expensive to run. Excess use will incur an additional fee.  The common areas need to be kept tidy and you are responsible for wiping down the kitchen and table after use.
host_about: Love to travelling to great locations, enveloping new cultures and experiences. I'm a city girl, which is why I live so close to Melbourne CBD and although i'm originally from Sydney, I love all that Melbourne offers with my love of great food and coffee and friendships.  Melbourne has become my home and I love that I can offer accommodation to visitors from around the world to experience the best of Melbourne easily.

Hi There,

Thanks for your enquiry.   We're unprecedentedly busy at present.

Our collection of homes/apartments:  https://www.airbnb.com.au/users/3721646/listings

- start date (any flexibility?): 
- duration of stay:
- how many guests:

We have a collection of 44 properties, they are 1, 2 and 3 bedroom apartments, townhouses and terraces in inner Melbourne areas which are close or right next to the CBD. They are premium 'value chic" style standard but at budget price points to ensure top value for money

we specialise in 14nights+ and 1, 2 ,3+ months if you so require.
But we can offer 3 nights + short stays at all Southbank Premium 2 and 3bedrooms and at all locations under 7nights before arrival for last minute specials. 

INNER MELBOURNE LOCATIONS such as:

SOUTH YARRA  | ST KILDA / SOUTH BANK / EAST MELBOURNE / RICHMOND / SOUTH MELBOURNE / FITZROY / ELWOOD / PORT MELBOURNE

But please check specific listing’s Amenities section

As short stay apartments, our rates are built on twin share (ie. 1 bedroom: 2 guests, 2 bedrooms: 4 guests and so on.

Rates start from:

kind regards,

Dianne and Alex

We are happy to share the books, DVD's and magazines in the apartment and book swapping is more than acceptable but please remember that the guests that will follow you may also enjoy the movies on offer. If anything is broken or needs replacing please let us know. These things happen and we can only get it fixed if you keep us informed. And, of course please remember this is a no-smoking venue.
host_about:
Hi,
An English girl abroad I first visited Australia in 2008.  My then 4 year old daughter and I toured the East coast in a camper van and completely fell in love with this gloriously laid-back country. Melbourne became our home over 6 years ago and  I have to say, I love this place.
I love the beach, I love the creativity you find within every nook and cranny of this city, I love the coffee, the cheap eats and cafes, the fancy restaurants and global cuisines. I love the markets, the lost afternoons at the park with the kids, I love the stunning views offered by a walk around the famous Albert Park lake, the glorious summer days and the rugged up winters but most of all I love sharing it, enjoying Melbourne with family, friends, sharing her secrets with visitors.
As your host I am more than happy to offer as much help and advice as I can to help you get the best from your time here in St Kilda and Melbourne.  I hope that our studio provides everything you may need during your stay and I trust that you will call if there is anything further we can do.

neighborhood_overview: Melbourne is a vast, diverse, cultural city but if you don’t feel like roaming too far Honey Apartments have heaps of cool adventures within a 200m radius. Right out the front door is tree lined Queen Street, featuring majestic gothic and art deco architecture. Want to shop? Turn left for the indie experience at All Star Comics. Feeling hungry? Take your pick, Japanese at Hako, Middle East fusion at MaHa, Italian at Saluministi. Feeling thirsty? Get your coffee hit at Toby’s Estate and hang with the hipsters but if your looking for a beer head downstairs to Bartronica and play pinball or around the corner to Robot for a super cool Japanese vibe. And this is only the tip of the iceberg of what is waiting for you right out the front door!
notes: Kid Friendly Honey Apartments are single level dwelling located on the 3rd floor, accessible via 2 lifts. Portacot and highchair are available on request at no extra charge and all beds are easily accessible for children of all ages. There is a bath in the bathroom and a dinning room table to serve family dinners. There is no outside area but a kid’s playground is only 2 blocks away and the Aquarium is located just around the corner. There is no parking provided with the accommodation but there are several commercial car parks less than 200 metres away.
transit: The location is perfect with all the following attractions a very short walk or tram ride away… WALKING • National Gallery of Victoria • Victorian Arts Centre • Queen Victoria market • St Pauls Cathedral • Block Arcade • Forum Theatre • Yarra River • Southbank • Crown Casino • Aquarium • ANZ Gothic bank • China Town • Collins Street • Parliament House • Bourke Street Mall • Flinders Street station • Federation Square • Southern Cross Station Direct tram ride or more than 15-minute walk • MCG  • Tennis Centre • Etihad Stadium • Botanical Garden’s NB Trams, trains, taxi rank, and busses are less than a block away
access: You will have the entire apartment to yourself.
interaction: I meet and greet all guests on arrival to hand over the keys, introduce you to my apartment and answer any questions you may wish to ask from how does the washing machine work to advise on my favourite restaurants. I am always accessible via phone, email or sms if you have any questions during your stay.

TELEPHONES  It is not possible to have the phone connected during your stay.  FUNCTIONS  Our accommodation is for residential purposes only. Functions or parties are strictly prohibited! name: Single room for female travellers
summary: Cosy room in a 3 bedroom Victorian house 8km from city centre (about 30 min bus trip away)  The room has a single bed, desk and wardrobe, a beautiful ornamental fireplace and lots of character.  The house has a lovely large living/kitchen area opening out to a small courtyard.
space: The home has lovely wooden floors throughout and the back room is huge with lots of natural light.  I have travelled quite a bit and have mementoes from my travels throughout the home.  The bathroom has a beautiful clawfoot bath which I highly recommend if you are here on a cooler day. Your room has a single bed, bedside table, built in wardrobe, a desk and chair.  There's a heater and electric blanket for those cold nights, a dressing gown and a universal adaptor.  If there's anything else you need I'm sure I can help you out. The bathroom has a supply of shampoo, conditioner, soap, toothpaste and a few airline toothbrushes if you need or forget anything!  You'll also get a towel and washcloth/face washer.

neighborhood_overview: Footscray is a multicultural suburb of Melbourne with loads of cheap and yummy restaurants and markets.
notes: I have two very sweet dogs, Charlie and Tess.  They are both very friendly and will definitely want to say hello and Charlie would love cuddles!   The house is an older home with some interesting quirks.  Everything works, but some things require a bit of patience and instruction which I will of course show you. I do my best to minimise my impact on the environment.  I aspire to a zero waste lifestyle so this means I refuse as much waste as possible and recycle, reuse and compost everything else.  I'd love it if you could support me in this while you're in my home.  I will show you all the different bins and if you're unsure just ask.  I also ask that people are conscious of their water and electricity use, but at the same time definitely want you to be comfortable.
transit: There's a bus at the end of the street and a train not much further.  Both go directly to the city via the heart of Footscray.  It takes about 30 mins to reach the city by bus.   There's a small supermarket 1km away and an Aldi supermarket also about 1km away.  Footscray also has 2 great fresh food markets which are cheap and not too far away.  The centre of Footscray is about 15 mins walk from my house or you can catch the bus.  There is a large shopping mall, Highpoint, 2.5km away which you can reach by Tram. I also have a bike that you're welcome to use.  It's a little old, but perfect for a trip to the shop or to get to the station.   I have a Myki card which I am happy to lend travellers.  Myki cards are needed for all public transport.  (you will need to top up or give me money to do so) If you are arriving to melbourne by plane, a taxi from the airport costs around $50 or alternatively you can catch the Skybus into the city and then get a train or bus to my home.
access: You have access to all the main living areas and are welcome to cook as long as you tidy up after yourself. I make fresh bread regularly which you are welcome to help yourself to at breakfast time.
interaction: I'm happy to have as much or as little contact as you want.  I can chat to you about things you might like to see and do in Melbourne.  I also have a few guidebooks to help you out.
house_rules: Treat my me, my home and my dog with respect and we'll get along fine.   No guests without checking first and definitely no parties!   Definitely no smoking inside. Guests who don't return keys on check out will need to cover the cost of the lock being changed. Please leave all communal areas neat and clean at all times and leave your room as you found it when you arrived.   Guests need to ensure house is secure when they leave including checking their window is closed and locked. I ask that guests be considerate of noise when others are sleeping. (No phone calls, music or tv in bedroom if others are sleeping) Check in 2-10pm, check out before 11am.
host_about: I am a 42 year old  who has lived in Melbourne my whole life.  I love to travel, but also love to come home as I love Melbourne and will never call anywhere else home.  I love reading and photography and of course travel.  I loved opening my home through Airbnb and now amusing it for my own travels.

name: Melbourne City Warehouse Loft
summary: A New York Style loft in the centre of Melbourne, a city renowned for its food, culture and shopping - what's not to like?! Spacious with high ceilings, polished floors and a brilliant kitchen. There are two sleeping areas with queen beds which are sound proofed, one of them is separated by heavy curtains so it's good for friends or families.
space: Summary: Our 2 bedroom loft is off Flinders Lane in the heart of Melbourne, a city renowned for its food, culture and shopping. The loft is huge and spacious with high ceilings, polished floors and heating. There's a brilliant kitchen but you might be more excited about the restaurants below.  The Space: Our loft is on the 4th floor of a 100 year old heritage building in the middle of Melbourne. It's huge with 12 foot ceilings and polished boards. There are 2 main sleeping areas, each of which have a queen bed, and 2 single beds which can be made up in the lounge room, but these are only suitable for children. There are 2 bathrooms, one with a shower and one with a bath. The loft is in central Melbourne, with trams and trains a minutes walk away. There's no parking with the loft but lots of parking stations around the area if you bring your own car. You can also sign up to something like flexicar ( a few weeks before your trip) if you want to use a car in the city. If you want to buy f

There are 2 bathrooms, one with a sho
neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is the city of Melbourne, post code 3000. There is EVERYTHING you need within the few blocks surrounding the loft. In the next block is the Nicholas building, chock full of quirky vintage shops, specialised button and japanese fabric shops and artists studios and galleries. Its a city that never sleeps and if you go out to the theatre/ cinema/ sports venue/ conference centres which are all within walking distance, you'll be sure to find sustenance on the way there and back no matter the time! Did I mention the Yarra river which is a block away? Or the Botanical Gardens or the Museum of Immigration? All just a block or so away - you won't have time to see and do everything the neighbourhood has to offer - looking forward to seeing you back again!
notes: It's a quirky environment with lots of character, not a hotel, so if you are the sort of person where everything has to be perfect, maybe its not for you! But if you like personality combined with comfort then we think we have it just right.
transit: I love trams - the best way to travel :-) Melbourne has what they call the Myki card, which you can buy for $5 for the card from any 7/11 shop and then top it up. Just hop on a tram and swipe your card and you are away. You can download a phone app called Tramtracker which will show you the tram routes and when the next tram will arrive. There are also suburban trains a block away or regional trains about 4 blocks away. If you fancy a ride on a boat there are ferries to Williamstown down at the Yarra. If you are really organised you can join Melbourne Bike Share which is a new form of public transport, designed for short trips across the city. Simply purchase a subscription that suits you, take a bike when you need it and then return it to one of the 50 bike stations throughout the city. (website (Website hidden by Airbnb) or there are similar car schemes which allow you to use a car for a couple of hours or a day, one is (website (Website hidden by Airbnb) which has a couple of cars p
access: Bligh Place is a small, friendly lane, off Flinders Lane. It has a couple of cafes in it and our building entrance is opposite Bistro du Monde. We are in the heart of the city, so there can be a little noise at night but the loft has been designed to minimise the street noise. The loft is accessed by a lift, there are about 6 steps when you first walk through the gate and after that it's flat. It's a great secure location as your key controls access to the floor.  Once you enter the loft you will find a large open plan kitchen and dining area with the laundry and second bathroom just around the corner. Bedrooms are further down, with the living area at the front. Large glass doors can provide privacy between each area.
interaction: Carmen will be your point of contact when you arrive and leave and she will be able to help you out if you have any questions. There is also a guide to the loft that you will find when you get there and that has all the information you will need - feel free to add any info to it if you discover a brilliant place to eat that we haven't discovered ourselves! You can also call us if you have any questions
house_rules: Please no smoking or animals, unless they are guide dogs of course. It's an old building with wooden floors and we like the people downstairs so maybe take the stilettos off when you get there? Definitely no parties of any sort though, sorry.
host_location: Coffs Harbour, New South Wales, Australia
host_about: My husband Wayne and I live in Coffs Harbour about half way between Sydney and Brisbane on the east coast of Australia where we have a software company. We also have a base in Melbourne where we do quite a lot of work. We love to travel, food, coffee, people and different experiences from our home town which is  a coastal paradise heavy on beaches, climate and lifestyle but a little short on heritage and everything associated with it which we crave when we travel, but spending time in Melbourne allows us the best of both worlds!

name: Bright apartment in vibrant Fitzroy
summary: A beautiful sunny space in the heart of Fitzroy with everything you need for a comfortable stay. Ideal for a solo traveller or couple who want to experience Melbourne like  locals.
space: This beautiful studio apartment has been recently renovated and is ideally located in Fitzroy within walking distance to Melbourne CBD. It is ideal for a single person or a couple.  The apartment is on the first floor of a small block of units (18 in total) surrounded by greenery. Our studio apartment (approximately 32m2) is tastefully decorated and has a large window overlooking Napier Street which gets lovely morning light.

neighborhood_overview: Fitzroy is one of the most exciting and vibrant neighbourhoods in Melbourne. Our apartment is located just off Gertrude Street, between Brunswick Street and Smith Street, all which offer some of the most interesting cafes, restaurants, bars, galleries and shops in town.
notes: There is no TV in the apartment, but rest assured there is plenty to do! If you have any questions please send us a message and we'd be more than happy to help.
transit: Getting around is easy with the 86 tram stop just 30 meters from our door, taking you directly to the city centre or towards Northcote in the other direction. You can also hire bikes close by or walk to the city in 10 - 15 minutes.
access: Guests will have access to a fully equipped kitchen, comfortable queen size bed, bathroom facilities and wireless internet. The apartment has ample storage for bags with hanging space and large drawers for clothes. Fresh towels and linen are of course provided and are included in the price. Guests have access to a communal, coin operated laundry on the same floor of the building and there is secure parking for one car if required.
interaction: Once we give you the keys the apartment is all yours to enjoy. It is very private and a wonderful retreat after a busy day of exploring the city. We are always happy to be contacted if you need advice or help throughout your stay.
house_rules: We ask you to please not smoke inside the apartment and to respect our neighbours by keeping noise to a minimum after 10pm.
host_about:

name: Elegant Apartment in Quiet Street
summary: A quiet apartment in the leafiest street of East Melbourne right near Fitzroy Gardens, the MCG and a 10 min walk to the city and the cafes and shopping of Gertrude St and Smith St, Fitzroy and Bridge Rd, Richmond. Easy access to trams and trains, or to Melbourne's Bike Share system.
space: A dance artist's apartment on the ground floor and in a great location. Perfect for one person or a couple. In my home I use only bio-degradable cleaning products, including laundry detergent, quality soaps and shampoos. For people sensitive to strong cleaning products this makes everyday life more comfortable and safe to live in.  As an original 1960's apartment it is graced with spacious rooms and quality fittings throughout. The building is well maintained and the surrounding gardens provide a quiet environment for all residents.

neighborhood_overview: East Melbourne is a green and leafy suburb right next to Melbourne's CBD, and this apartment takes advantage of both these aspects. It is ten minutes walk to the Paris end of Collins Street through the lovely Fitzroy and Treasury Gardens.  For an an intimate evening or long lunch try the City Wine Shop in Spring St, Self-Preservation in Bourke St or take a romantic walk to Gertrude St's  Enoteca Bar. Enjoy a stroll down Gertrude St -  famous for its fashion, food and design. You can also walk around the corner to Wellington Parade and enjoy breakfast at a variety of cafes. Great for sporting events and concerts, the apartment is a few minutes walk from the MCG,  Rod Laver Arena, AAMI Stadium and the Tennis Centre. Fitzroy Gardens are one block away for picnics and a walk through to the CBD. Bridge Rd, Richmond shopping is also close by.  Federation Square, the National Gallery of Victoria, the State Theatre and the Concert Hall are all twenty minutes walk or an easy tram or taxi ride.
notes: East Melbourne Library is almost next door and offers wonderful facilities. The benches outside also offer a great place to sit, read and observe. In the summer the benches become a meeting place for people to meet and play backgammon and chess. Take a cup of tea or a glass of wine and enjoy the summer evenings!
transit: Public transport is frequent and easy to access. There are trams and trains within a few minutes walk of the apartment - one block away. The closest station is Jolimont Station which connects with Hurstbridge and Mernda lines.   Get a Myki card and enjoy Melbourne. Or grab a bike from Melbourne's Bike Share system - it's a cheap and easy way to travel and you can explore the cycleways along the Yarra.
access: The bedroom has a queen-sized bed with wardrobe and drawer space.  I provide good quality cotton linen,  cotton and wool blankets as well as a variety of duvets. Melbourne's weather is variable and these options assure good sleep. The kitchen is perfect for home catering and includes a fridge, toaster and kettle. I also provide basic groceries for your use.  The bathroom contains shower-over-bath and is supplied with fresh towels and toiletries and includes a washing machine – clothes-lines are at the rear of the building. The apartments have a beautiful courtyard with seating where you can enjoy a coffee or a quiet reflective time with a book or your electronic device.
interaction: Entrance to the property is via coded key-boxes. I am available for questions by phone and can deal with problems if required.
house_rules: No shoes in the apartment. Please wear barefeet, socks or inside slippers. No pets. Please be respectful of others as this is a quiet residential block of apartments.
host_about:
I am a Melbourne based dance artist and travel Australia teaching and performing.
My interests include dance, performance, friendship and reading.

neighborhood_overview: Olinda is a township on top of the Dandenong Ranges. It is a temperate rainforest with lots of tall trees, birds and beautiful gardens tourist shops and cafes and restaurants. It is about 50 km from the center of Melbourne and about 5 degrees colder the whole year.  You will love Olinda's quaint little shops and touristy township - just a minute's walk from my place. Also, forests and public gardens and bus stop are just a short walk away too.
notes: Please observe house rules of no parties or events. Please supervise your children, please be respectful of the furniture, the floors, me and the neighbours, please understand you are a guest in my home. Please be aware of Global warming and Greenhouse emissions by wearing appropriate clothing for the weather conditions. Clothing is simply recycling body heat ;-) There are 17 steps in the staircase. You can use my kitchen upon request. I would love to assist you in finding the right restaurant or attractions or anything else you might require.
transit: Public transport is available from the city by train and then bus. The bus stop is 100 metres from my B & B.

This is the traditional B & B.
interaction: I am at your service.

Please keep the noise down after 11pm, no parties please. Being friendly and approachable is good. Visitors are welcome if you would kindly ask permission first.

name: Adorable Chalet Tucked Away in Bohemian St Kilda
summary: Have breakfast in a lush plant-filled garden that has a convincing countryside feel—except this charming chalet is in bustling St Kilda. Sunlight shines through lovely stained glass windows. A spiral staircase leads to a romantic sleeping loft.
space: The chalet is light filled and has a north facing courtyard and wrap-around verandah making it perfect for sun bathing and outdoor meals.   Open plan living with an upstairs bedroom, a huge ceiling fan and air-conditioning/heating perfect for some time out.  The open design with double doors brings the outside in and makes for a lovely experience. PROPERTY FEATURES: * Romantic, secluded, light and airy chalet - a unique property in the heart of St Kilda.  * Gorgeous outdoor area for sunbathing, cooking and eating * Lush garden  * Comfortable & high-quality queen-size mattress * Luxurious leather sofa, high quality German made, which folds out into a sturdy and comfortable double bed * Natural Light abounds - more happiness! * Open Plan Kitchen/Lounge/Dining * Period style bathroom with unlimited hot water * Safe and Secure and Private location with electronic security entrance * Street Parking available  (Please send me a request for the permit if required) * Clean, Clean, Clean - Guar
description: Have breakfast in a lush plant-filled garden that has a convincing countryside feel—except this charming chalet is in bustling St Kilda. Sunlight shines through lovely stained glass windows. A spiral staircase leads to a romantic sleeping loft.
neighborhood_overview: The chalet is tucked away from the streetscape, sitting behind the main house.  It’s near great coffee shops, restaurants, public transport and the beach. Please note that St Kilda has a long bohemian history, so you will see ladies of the night.
notes: Most people who've stayed in the chalet love it - it really is a special place. However, please note that St Kilda is 'a colourful' neighbourhood, and has a long Bohemian history so you will see 'ladies of the night'. There are possums living in the trees near the chalet.  You'll see them come out at night and eat fruits and vegetation.  Possums are cute and furry marsupials but they easily frighten. They are not dangerous but please do not attempt to pat them or pick them up; they might use their sharp claws to break free. You might hear them jump on the roof as they clamber about the treetops.
transit: WALKER'S PARADISE: Everything you need is within easy walking distance, including mega-supermarkets, hipster cafes, artisan bakeries, local galleries, live-music venues, fabulous hairdressers, and public transport, not to mention the novel Victorian-era Restaurant-Tram.  There's even an internationally renowned Italian cheese-maker down the street! PUBLIC TRANSPORT: Public transport is a breeze. The 96 tram stop is only a few minutes walk away on Acland Street and will take you into Melbourne's city centre within 20-25 minutes on a good run! St Kilda is surrounded by beautiful bay-side areas including Albert Park, South Yarra, Prahran and Port Melbourne so there's a vast range of shopping, dining and recreational opportunities on offer. St Kilda is a vibrant and wonderful location in the most livable city in the world. DRIVING: Drivers are located close to major arterials which means you'll be on the freeway in no time, whether it's Phillip Island, the Great Ocean Road, the Dandenongs,
access: Guests rent the entire property, including the garden area. Pets are strictly not allowed
interaction: I do not live in the chalet, but I'm close by if any help is required.  My son Jan ('Yan') lives in the next street so he'll often drop by when guests need help.

I would like all future guests to be able to enjoy the chalet and its furniture without dog hair on blankets, candle wax and candle burns, etc.  NOISE: Please treat others in the same way you'd like to be treated. I love spending time with my children and grand-children,  gardening, and travelling with my husband Stipe.  We really enjoy meeting interesting and kind people, especially travelers who are keen to explore this beautiful place.  We also really like a nice glass or two of good Australian red wine!

host_about:
Mark and Mike an Australian couple who married in New York, have lived in Melbourne since 1986. With both our families living overseas, travelling is just what you do. You'll often find us planning or thinking about where to stop off on the next trip and we try to have the next destination identified before finishing the current trip.

We both got the AIRBNB bug from our own hosted experiences in Prague, Paris and Amsterdam and started hosting over 10 years ago. Passionate about Melbourne it gives us a great buzz to be able to share our city and knowledge with visitors and hope that we can provide a great base for your Melbourne stay.

Mark has recently retired from teaching music in a college and Mike is a manager in the vocational education sector.  Mark is originally from New Zealand and is where we both met in 1984 with Mike hailing originally from London in the UK.

name: Paradise in the Heart of St Kilda
summary: Sleeping 6 with 2.5 bathrooms (en suite and main bathroom) in a stunningly renovated original St Kilda mansion. Beats a hotel any night. Be in the thick of it but sheltered by a private garden. Minutes to trams, restaurants and the beach.  Live like a local in luxury. Beats a hotel in price and comfort any day.
space: Stay in a 130 year old gorgeously renovated servants quarters 1 block from Fitzroy St. Set behind serene tranquil gardens this beautiful property evokes the by gone era of St Kilda as a premier beach side holiday location. 16 ft ceilings, original lead light windows, private court yards for coffee in the sun yet only a 1 minute walk to the best restaurants and night life St Kilda has to offer. Two blocks to the beach  and 10 minutes to Albert Park Lake. Your room is a beautiful double room with stunning lead light windows. Take a long soak in the full size claw foot bath after a day exploring Melbourne. Trams at the end of the street. You have access to a gourmet kitchen and gorgeous lounge and dining room. Each bedroom has its own bathroom and there is a double fold out couch in the lounge. Your host Sue is a Melbourne and St Kilda local who is happy to share her inside knowledge about the best places to see, eat and experience.

name: St Kilda oasis -  Fab retro - close to it all!
summary: A spacious one bedroom 1950s apartment only a short walk to Melbourne's St Kilda precinct and a quick tram ride to Chapel St shopping and the city.
space: Our spacious one bedroom 1950s apartment is in a perfect location to enjoy the highlights of Melbourne's St Kilda precinct. It's only a short stroll through the beautiful St Kilda Gardens to St Kilda's famous Acland St where you can catch the light rail into the city. Or head the other way and in a few minutes find yourself in Balaclava - a neighbourhood with a cafe scene that is fast becoming a favourite not so hidden alternative for local residents. From here you can take the train and in less than 15 minutes be in the heart of Melbourne and it's cultural precinct at Federation Square and Southbank. We are also only about a 10 minutes walk to the beach. We lived in our apartment for many years before moving overseas and  now spend very little time in Melbourne. It's a pleasure to offer it to guests who will appreciate the efforts we have made to maintain its original 1950s character although with modern comforts such as gas heating in the living area and underfloor heating in the bat

name: Sunny spacious Northcote home.
summary: Light-filled two storey townhouse with courtyard gardens in leafy Northcote. Two bedrooms plus study (which can be a third bedroom). Close to train station, bus stop and trams; 5 minutes walk to Merri Creek and Yarra Bend parklands; 10 mins walk to the cafes and bars of vibrant High St.
space: Warm sunny Northcote home, five minutes walk from Dennis station (15 minute trip to the CBD). Close to the cafes, bars, fashion shops, cinema and music venues of High St, from where the no 86 tram will take you straight into town. Not far from the Northcote, Collingwood and Fitzroy swimming pools and the Fairfield Boathouse with its rowboats-for-hire on Melbourne's famous Yarra River.  Sometimes whole house is available, other times one bedroom.  The house: two storey two bedroom house with a huge living room lined with bookshelves (and a baby grand piano), and two courtyard gardens for al fresco dining.  Large sunny kitchen/dining room.  There are two bathrooms upstairs plus an additional toilet downstairs. Pets must be negotiated with owner, but there is a dog door out to back garden. The three bedrooms are  light-filled carpeted second-floor rooms with built-in robes and floor-to-ceiling windows. neighborhood_overview: Northcote is close to the city but also close to the bushland and walking tracks of the Merri Creek and the Yarra River. Eucalypt-lined streets, cafes with excellent coffee, quirky retail strips with everything from vintage clothes and organic groceries to heritage cinemas and funky music venues.
notes: The train trip into the CBD is only 15 minutes from Dennis Station - perfect for getting to the Melbourne Film Festival and other city entertainments. It is only a ten minute walk to the Westgarth Cinema in High St.

host_about: I've been a journalist and broadcaster for twenty-five years and moved into part-time university teaching fifteen years ago. I'm still working as a freelance writer and radio presenter, and making music, and i completed a PhD in Creative Writing in 2015. My first book, a memoir called 'Shy', was published in 2014. I've travelled quite a bit in Europe, Scandinavia and Asia (and Australia).
