name: Relaxing villa, close to town.
summary: This light spacious double room has all the advantages of peaceful suburban life within easy reach of the Melbourne CBD. Start your day with an espresso in the sunny back yard, there is Fetch TV  and unlimited wifi along with fresh eggs from my chickens.
space: You will sleep in a large comfortable double bedroom. The unit is a stand alone building in a very quiet neighborhood. There is a shared kitchen and you will have space in the fridge and shelves for your stuff. There is a pleasant back yard for relaxing in. I have 3 chickens and you are welcome to have their eggs when they are available.
description: This light spacious double room has all the advantages of peaceful suburban life within easy reach of the Melbourne CBD. Start your day with an espresso in the sunny back yard, there is Fetch TV  and unlimited wifi along with fresh eggs from my chickens. You will sleep in a large comfortable double bedroom. The unit is a stand alone building in a very quiet neighborhood. There is a shared kitchen and you will have space in the fridge and shelves for your stuff. There is a pleasant back yard for relaxing in. I have 3 chickens and you are welcome to have their eggs when they are available. You have access to all shared spaces and the garden area. Off street parking available if required. I like to welcome guests and make them feel at home. Very happy to share the occasional meal or coffee, I do work quite long hours so my hours can be irregular. Happy to be guided by your wishes. The best thing about my neighborhood is the fact that it is quiet while still close to amenities and the bay.
neighborhood_overview: The best thing about my neighborhood is the fact that it is quiet while still close to amenities and the bay. There are some excellent cafes nearby and a good variety of shops for all your requirements.
notes: I'm fairly green in my approach to life. My house is energy efficient and I take pleasure in organic gardening. I would love to share those values with my guests... (without being the enviro-police). I have 3 free range hens in the garden and I am happy to share eggs with you.
transit: Arriving from the airport I suggest you catch one of the Skybus services to the Southern Cross station, then catch the Frankston Line train to Ormond Station, I am happy to pick you up in my car on the first arrival and drive you to my place. The Metro station is very close (8 minutes walk) with regular trains to the city and to Frankston and there is a bus stop right across the street from the house that goes to Chadstone shopping center and other destinations. UPDATE- currently busses replace trains for the last section of the trip from the city. I can arrange pick up from and drop off to Caulfield station with your luggage. Journey times to the city will be slightly longer.
access: You have access to all shared spaces and the garden area. Off street parking available if required.
interaction: I like to welcome guests and make them feel at home. Very happy to share the occasional meal or coffee, I do work quite long hours so my hours can be irregular. Happy to be guided by your wishes.
house_rules: While you are welcome to come and go as you please. I would appreciate quiet between the hours of 11.00pm and 7.00am.  It is a smoke free home, if you smoke I request that you do so outside.  If any issues arise for you while staying with me I would like to think you can approach me for assistance and resolution. If you leave the place as you find it I think that would cover it.
host_about: When I bought this unit I thought I would like to welcome Airbnb people here. I spent most of the 1990s living in London and mixing with people from many parts of the world, I would like to recreate some of that mood. I am a milliner and I value the creative life, since living here I have found a passion for organic gardening too. I can imagine sharing my city with Airbnb guests, telling you the places the locals go. I hope that when you come here you will find a base for exploring and a place to feel safe and 'at home'. I have a hundred words of Italian, French and German.

neighborhood_overview: Westgarth is a charming locality situated at the southernmost point of Northcote. Within walking distance of High Street and a range of bohemian cafes, bars and fashion boutiques, it’s the perfect location for the curious traveller. And if you're more of an outdoor type, the stunning Merri Creek Reserve is right on our doorstep and is ideal for exploring the greener parts of the city on foot, bicycle or scooter!
notes: Spare bicycle available for use - it’s an easy 30 minute bike ride into the city, or explore the nearby reserves and waterways!
transit: The location of the townhouse makes it very easy to explore Melbourne, particularly the northern parts of the city. Clifton Hill Metro Train Station (with frequent train services to the City) is a 10 minute walk, and the famed No.86 tram service is a stone's throw away. If you're driving, you'll be able to park on the street in front of the property.

AT THE COTTAGE, you will rest in simple, handmade spaces.  The accommodation, newly built and freshly painted, offers clean spaces, natural fibres, soft carpets for bare feet and peace. interaction: Either Peter or myself will stop by each day to check in if there's anything you need via the note  box. We honour your privacy so how much you see us  varies according to your needs.

host_about:
5 things I don't want to live without?
Love, Children, Beauty, Creativity, Stillness.

I'd like to begin by acknowledging the traditional custodians of country - the Boon Wurrung clan of the Kulin nation, people who have held and walked this land for thousands of years. We are the beneficiary of their ceremonies.
 
Thank you, now a bit about me...I've lived and worked in Asia as a fine artist and am planning to travel to France and Italy with my daughter in September on a spiritual pilgrimage through labyrinths. Yay!

My fave books are The Alchemist and Ashes and Snow. Fave movies include The Intouchables, The Big Blue, Under a Tuscan Sun. I'm rather a ridiculous fan of HP, Sherlock and Miss M (much to my families displeasure..."oh not again Mum...".

As a traveller I tend to be a pilgrim more than a tourist - however much I try. I just like to connect, put down roots, feel the pace of the place rather than run from one monument to the next clicking madly.

I'd love to travel on the Orient Express - 1st class of course. Train travel seems so civilised when one has one's own compartment! Far kinder than the crick in my neck from that last overnight flight back from India.

I travel for work (shall I call it that?) fine art exhibiting and now presenting on the labyrinth at conferences. It takes effort but it has my soul sing!

On that front, I have a deadline from my publisher to complete A HANDMADE LIFE - how to transition from a 'cookie cutter' life to a created, handmade life and be a soul happy mama.

I'm not an intrusive person. I don't want to be your instant best pal but if you stay with us (and we have a stream of house guests from all over the world between Pete and myself), my intention is that people feel cared for whilst they're in our space. 

I aim to create spaces that support people being able to rest, relax and leave enriched. The strike rate's pretty good so far...but hey, it's not hard when you're connecting with beautiful people!
cheers, 
Tina

space: For a truly unique experience of Melbourne and its cultural life, this Victorian Cottage in central Fitzroy is ideal.  It is nestled behind an art studio & puppet theatre and surrounded by eclectic cafes, bars, shops and galleries.   The living room is cozy,  with an open fireplace, unlimited Wifi connection, record player, gramophone, and a DVD player. The kitchen is fully equipped and stocked with herbs, spices, legumes and condiments for people who love to cook, although Fitzroy is home so many wonderful and reasonably priced restaurants that you might not feel like cooking. We provide you with breakfast at no additional cost.   The bathroom has a bath and a reliable hot water service and is reached via a pathway in a small colourful courtyard with an outside seating área. In the courtyard there is a gas BBQ and seating, lovely for relaxing and cooking dinner over a beer or wine on balmy summer evenings. neighborhood_overview: Fitzroy is the bohemian heart of Melbourne replete with options to colour your time in Melbourne.  With Gertrude, Brunswick and Smith streets on our doorstep, you will be able to explore the many speciality boutiques, book and record shops and vibrant cafes,  bars and eateries which make this zone so desirable.      Within a couple minutes walk, you can choose between many options to hear live music, catch an opening at a local gallery or artist run space, lay down in a park with a picnic (please ask for rug and picnic basket) or give the possums a night-time feed (fruit only).       There is a sociable community swimming pool, many gyms and yoga studios, public library, tennis courts, playgrounds and various supermarkets also within a couple of minutes walk.       Within a 10 minute walk you can immerse yourself in Melbourne's theatre scene at La Mama or La Mama Courthouse, or enjoy arthouse films at Cinema Nova.
notes: We are currently away, so a friend of ours, Nick, is minding our home and looking after guests needs.
transit: The number 11 (West Preston/St Kilda) tram is literally on our doorstep, and our home is within 2 minutes walk of tram routes: 86, 96 and 109.  The Central Business District is a short walk away.
access: Guests are expected to make themselves at home in the whole house excluding the other bedrooms.   They are welcome to play records but we ask that they return them to their sleeves after use.  Books may be borrowed after asking permission, but please do not take them out of our house, and return them to the same spot from where you borrowed them.
interaction: We let our guests dictate their level of interaction.  They are free to come and go when they please and are encouraged to help themselves to breakfast in their own time and use the kitchen to cook their own meals if necessary.  If a guest should feel like a chat or need any helpful hints about how to organise their time in Melbourne or where to seek out specialist interests, we are always available to help.
house_rules: Please wash cooking  and eating utensils after their use and if you use the BBQ, please do likewise.   We do not allow parties and ask that you respect our neighbours.
host_about: We are a family of four, from Australia and Argentina.  We are both visual artists and together run a studio shop front which in addition to visual art encompasses pre cinema, puppetry and theatre.  We have two sons, one two year old and another 6 month old.  We have travelled and lived abroad  for many years and so are sensitive to the needs of travellers and happy to help in any way we can.  At home we usually speak Spanish but can easily switch to English should your language be English.

Designed with your enjoyment and relaxation in mind, the superfluity of the set up allows guests to make a weekend away feel like a private retreat personally planned to provide a space to recharge, romance and revitalise the busy urban mind and body. Why not absorb all Emerald has to offer by walking up to Puffing Billy station and experiencing The Dandenongs from a truly unique view. *Price Includes Breakfast for two * Proposal Packages  available on request, contact host to find out more.

neighborhood_overview: For an exciting concoction of glamour and grunge, Prahran is lively place to go see and be seen. This inner-city neighbourhood is one of Melbourne's most trendy areas with its high end shopping outlets, amazing gourmet delights and vivacious nightlife. You'll spot avid fashionistas and social butterflies hitting the pavements of Prahran looking for the best boutique stores, bars and cafes. Chapel Street is a mecca for those looking for a bit (or a lot!) of retail therapy with shops filled with designer collections of upscale fashion and homeware to update your decor.

host_about:
Founded in 2006, the Boutique Stays Accommodation Group is an accredited tourism business providing quality houses and apartments to singles, couples and families in Melbourne. Distinguished by a commitment to high property standards, impeccable presentation and personalised customer care provided by a team located in the bayside suburb of Port Melbourne. 

A bespoke collection of 60 homes in Melbourne’s most iconic and popular neighbourhoods are handpicked to make guests feel at home with peace of mind that a dedicated, professional customer service team are ready to support each and every guest seven days per week.  A range of one, two, three and four bedroom homes are available in a choice of twenty suburbs in Melbourne for guests visiting family and friends, holiday makers travelling with or without pets and business travellers.

The Boutique Stays Accommodation Group has welcomed over 4,000 guests and 150 pets into our homes in the past year and look forward to welcoming you for your first or return visit.

neighborhood_overview: All of Melbourne's delights are right on your doorstep! Get a coffee from the cafe's on the laneway, you can stroll up to the famous and eclectic 'Hardware lane' for a plethora of awesome cafes, restaurants and bars. Cross Elizabeth and Collins Street to reach Flinders Lane and the cafe hotspot 'Degraves street'! You could not get a better location for exploring Melbourne on foot day or night! Situated at the start of Hardware Lane, but on the quiet end, the apartment is a hop, skip and jump from Bourke Street Mall and everything you want to see in Melbourne! You can take a tram anywhere in the city and enjoy the ease of night time dinning.  NEARBY TOURIST ATTRACTIONS: (Within 5-10 mins walk)  ✅ Queen Victoria Market ✅ Flagstaff Gardens ✅ Chinatown Melbourne ✅ Carlton Gardens  ✅ Melbourne Museum  ✅ Melbourne Town Hall ✅ Old Melbourne Gaol ✅ Flinders Street ✅ St. Patrick's Cathedral  ✅ Federation Square CAFES, BARS & RESTAURANTS: ✅ Red Spice Road (Modern Asian food with stylish decor) ✅
notes: KEY COLLECTION: From our office on 601 Little Collins St, across the street from Souther Cross Station We require all our guests to fill out an encrypted ID verification form either in person when you check in, or online if you're self checking in.
transit: Melbourne is one of the best cities to stay in and has so much to explore by foot or tram! The apartment is very close to all forms of public transport (trams, trains), and walking distance to supermarkets, shopping, cafes, bars and restaurants. It's 1 - 2 minutes walk to Bourke Street Mall, Hardware Lane, Little Collins Street, Centre Place, Degraves St, Flinders Street station, Victoria markets and awesome Flinders Lane!  TRAMS: The 86 | 96 trams run right along Bourke St and can be used to go down to St Kilda or up north to Brunswick & Fitzroy.  TRAINS: The apartment is super central and you have lots of options for trains such as Melbourne Central, Flinders Station, Flagstaff and Souther Cross Station.
access: The entire apartment is yours to enjoy, please feel right at home!
interaction: The Beyond a Room team are available in Melbourne whenever you need assistance.
house_rules: - Pets are not allowed (sorry!)  - No parties. You can have a couple friends over, but please save your energy for your night out and DON'T have a party! The neighbors will know :)  - Having a party will forfeit your entire bond. - When checking out, please leave the home in a clean and tidy manner. You don’t need to mop and vacuum but please remember to put things back where you found them. - Keep noise down between 10pm and 8am (City Council rule) and be respectful of our neighbors. - If there is a medical emergency, fire or matters requiring police assistance, please contact 000. For other matters, phone Beyond a Room. - It is your responsibility to lock up when you are not home and to turn off the coolers, fans, lights, heaters and TV. Plus, saving the environment makes you cool. - We do not accept responsibility for loss of property. However, if you realise you have left something in the apartment after check-out please phone and we will do our best to have it returned to you. - U

I'm Leyla and I live in Melbourne Australia but travel a lot for work, which allows me to rent out my apartments. I am a designer focusing on social and environmental sustainability and each of my apartments is a labor of love, where I carefully renovate and decorate with athletics and sustainability in mind.  

I'm really into art / design / creativity / music / culture / food / wine / travelling /  sustainability. Oh did I say food and wine?! 

I  love Melbourne and take great pride in showing other people just how cool this city is!

neighborhood_overview: South Yarra is approx 3 kms from the centre of the city.  Leafy and hilly, it is one of the most attractive suburbs of Melbourne. It is bordered by the Yarra River, the Botanical Gardens & Chapel St & Toorak Rd shopping precincts.  Lawson Grove is a cul de sac 200 meters back from the Yarra River, and all the buildings in Lawson Grove were built in the 1930s by the same architect Howard Lawson.

name: Seddon/Yarraville: stay in our lovely period home
summary: Our house in the heart of Seddon is cool in summer, but cosy in winter with many great nooks to hang out with a good book or sharing a wine or watch latest movies or documentaries on Netflix. Two large double bedrooms and great comfy queen beds, you will enjoy a good night sleep.  We're close Seddon Station and Seddon & Yarraville for great cafes, bars and restaurants.  Modern, renovated with private courtyard & traditional front veranda, 6km from CBD of Melbourne.  Min stay two weeks.
space: It's located in the heart of Seddon and walking distance to Seddon, Yarraville's great food, wine & beer culture with cafés, bars, restaurants very close by.  A ten minute walk to the Yarraville village provides access to local supermarkets, delicatessens, local butchers and produce.  A real feature for all visitors is the magnificent Art Deco Sun Theatre that is an experience in itself.    Two local train stations will have you in the CBD of Melbourne in 15 minutes. Melbourne city is famous for its architecture, gardens and renowned for major sporting events, the arts, theatre and live music scene. Central China Town is exciting and great food available.  If you're the energetic type, our mountain bike will take you into the city in no time and this trail connects you to a network of bike trails Melbourne is renowned for. A taxi fair into Melbourne's CBD will cost around $25 and plenty of cabs available.  Two mountain bikes available to connect you Melbourne's bicycle network.

Heating/cooling with cable TV and wifi available MYKI cards complimentary to guests upon arrival to use the public transport network.  Two mountain bike available to get about easily and enjoy the trails along the Maribyrnong & Yarra rivers in heart of Melbourne.
interaction: Bruce & myself are friendly guys but we understand people's privacy.  You can have as much or as little interaction as you'd like.  I'm available on my mobile or via email to answer any questions of course.
house_rules: The usual house rule of any place. You the traveller are most welcome in our home and we would expect the same rules as if staying as your guests in your home. Minimum 7 days
host_about:
Ideal for gay or straight singles or couples and parents needing a separate stay when visiting the grandkids! 

Overnight stays or longer term guests hosted by long time Melbournian guys happy to share some insight to this great city and make your stay a memorable one!

Self-contained, private-entrance accommodation with your own bathroom and kitchenette.
Your room features reverse cycled quiet air conditioning, HD-TV, CD, NETFLIX and a sunny verandah to sit and enjoy the view of the trees-lined street. 
Wi Fi available on request & public transport card & map. 

Just a short train ride to Melbourne CBD and tourist attractions and a short walk to The Sun (Art Deco) Theatre and restaurants, cafes, pubs and bars. Our home is well within distance of our city's famous food & wine culture, local markets, great beaches and airport transfers. 

Mountain bikes available to hire to explore the many of Melbourne's tracks & trails.  
 
The Milk Bar has its own private entrance separate to our residence which is an old Victorian weatherboard home full of character situated in a tree lined private cul-de-sac close to everything Melbourne has to offer the traveller. 

Long-stay guests please inquire. Some meals available on request.

name: Country Style 2 bedroom House - Off Street Parking
summary: This perfectly positioned, large 2 bedroom house is walking distance to vibrant Martin St village, Gardenvale Park and Gardenvale Station. Located in a quiet street but close to Brighton, Elsternwick, Elwood and Caulfield. Easy access to cafes, restaurants, shopping, public transport, (Railway station and Buses) parks, beaches and Movie theatres. Cycle and walking paths lead you to iconic St Kilda and Elwood Beaches. We are only 15 minutes by train to Melbourne CBD.
space: This renovated 1920’s Art Deco inspired family style house is in an excellent location and perfect for families and travellers visiting the area. Sparkly clean, cosy and comfortable 2 bedroom single level house complete with secluded outdoor area and native gardens. Your own Off Street Free Parking conveniently located in your own driveway. No internal stairs to climb or lifts to navigate. The house has 2 Bedrooms, one with a Queen bed the other with 2 single beds. All Linen and towels are supplied even Beach Towels. A relaxing Lounge room with TV and Stereo. Plus a separate large light filled Study with a selection of books and kids games and toys.  A fully equipped kitchen and separate  laundry with washing machine and dryer. An extra toilet is located in the laundry for your convenience. neighborhood_overview: This 1920's Holiday House is located in Gardenvale Melbourne's smallest and cutest suburb! Just a short stroll will take you to an amazing selection of shops in Martin Street Village Brighton. An easy walk to catch the train from Gardenvale Station to Melbourne CBD There are many great cafes, fish and chips, bakeries, restaurants, boutique shopping, a very good Op Shop, supermarket, news agency and butcher. Also you can pick up fresh fruit and vegetables at a local grocer.  'Omar and the Marvellous Coffee Bird' cafe is located on our street corner so you can pop down for breakfast and fabulous coffee to kick start your day.
notes: We think our location is fantastic but please choose the best location for you as once you arrive we can’t move the property to your preferred location. Please book because you want to stay HERE! Unfortunately we don't provide cleaning During your stay. We would like you to treat our house with respect and kindness.  We are a house that is exceptionally clean, comfortable and in what we think is a great location. Come and stay with us and feel 'at home' in Gardenvale.
transit: You can walk or catch public transport-we are that conveniently located. HIRE CAR: Once you are here you can hire a Budget,Avis,Europcar or Thrifty rental car. They are all located just around the corner! PUBLIC TRANSPORT: will connect you to: Brighton, Elwood, St Kilda, Monash University, Elsternwick, Moorabbin and Caulfield. Trains direct to the city on the Sandringham line will connect you with regional Victorian locations. Airport Bus stops minutes away. (Frankston and Peninsula Airport Shuttle)FAPAS
access: The whole house is for your use including On-site (off-street) parking Please park your vehicle in the Driveway  - you can park on the street but it is only 2hr parking.
interaction: Check in is preferred after 3pm - but if you are arriving earlier, please ask, we can perhaps assist if you want to drop off your bags OR if there are no guests checking out on that day I am more than happy to check you in earlier.  Please let me know your expected time of arrival as you will be met at the property, given your keys and shown around the house.  We are available to make your stay as comfortable and as easy as possible. So please do not hesitate to contact us for local information or assistance at any time prior to or during your visit.  We really hope you enjoy your stay, if you did we would love your review! If there are any issues, please contact me directly.
house_rules: Please leave the house clean and tidy before you depart. No parties, events or large gatherings allowed. No Pets/Animals allowed
host_about: My name is Katie and I just love cosmopolitan Melbourne! My favorite travel destinations are Sri Lanka, Vietnam, Fiji and anywhere country for a road trip. I prefer places that are clean and comfortable but not 'sterile'. Places where you can fit the family in, located close to public transport but not too close, close to cafes and restaurants and site seeing. This is probably why I set up 2 holiday houses myself to share these things with you. Check out Gardenvale Cottages and you'll see.

host_about:
I have owned two other service businesses since 1998. I started StayCentral with one apartment in 2005, and now manage multiple properties in many different locations in inner Melbourne.

Like many of my guests, I love to travel; both overseas to places like the Mulu Caves in Borneo, ancient cities (in many old countries), Antarctica & Alaska, Torres del Paine, and colourful markets in amazing places like Pha Long in Vietnam, Jaisalmer in India, & La Paz in Bolivia. I also love short domestic trips for weekends away just to relax. It means I get to be on the other side of the counter, and experience how other people look after their guests: and I take their good ideas back with me. 

(My manager, Max, has also travelled from afar to be here by the way, and he can also speak with our guests in Russian and Ukranian).

I even worked as a part-time tourist guide in Melbourne for a couple of years, and really enjoyed the interactions with the tourists off the huge cruise liners that appear in Melbourne each spring and summer. I have tried to extend this experience into my accommodation business here at home, where I really love assisting people with their stays. You only need to read the 800 plus reviews on Airbnb, Trip advisor, Goo gle, and on my own StayCentral website to realise how much our guests enjoy our apartments, and the way we look after them. 

I do love living in Melbourne. It enjoys a unique place in Australia. It is often described as the cultural, business, shopping and sporting capital of the country. The restaurants and cafes in Melbourne are amongst the best in the world. I love living in an urban village amongst these, and all the other everyday shops; and jumping on a tram and avoiding the hassles of traffic. It is a city of great opportunity, experiences, events and lifestyle that can be enjoyed by locals and visitors alike; and I really enjoy facilitating our guests' stays here.

I do hope I have the opportunity to help you get to know Melbourne and grow to love it as I have.

house_rules: House Rules To maintain a good standard for our guests we require certain conditions to be complied with. We appreciate most will respect our property but the occasional abuse requires that we state the following conditions: •	You are responsible for leaving the property in the state in which you found it on arrival. All breakages or losses must be reported immediately to the owner. Whilst we will not pursue reimbursement for minor accidental damage or normal wear and tear, the total cost of making good any other damage or loss to the property, garden or contents will be taken out of your security deposit. Please note this includes the removal of consumable items from the property, which are provided for guest use whilst in-house and are not intended as individual use presentations (examples include laundry powder, dishwashing liquid, toiletries provided in dispensers etc). •	Number of Guests should not exceed the number stated on the Confirmation Notice or subsequently agreed in writi
host_about:
Hi There,

I'm Jonathan, I'm in my mid 40's, sometimes older sometimes younger and I love to travel. 

In terms of a home I love a comfy couch, I love a deep bath and I love full blockout curtains. 

5 things I can't live without?

Books, I love a good book.
Good food. I love sharing a great meal with others.
Long sleep in's on Sundays or any day really.
Water. I love swimming in the ocean or rivers. Lets keep them clean.
Music. Anything from opera to house.

As your host, I will be on call to make your stay as comfortable as possible. If anything goes wrong during your stay, say the washing machine won't start or something, I will have it sorted immediately. I've had guest stay at my place for 3 month and then extend up to 16 months. I've had guests who moved out and then told me if they could stay forever they would be very happy. 

As someone who has travelled a lot with work and stayed in hotels motels and apartments both long and short term, I set out to create a space that was a real home away from home. Somewhere where you can feel safe, warm and cosy and enjoy a good home cooked meal. It was all about atmosphere. A deep bath to relax in, comfy couches to put your feet up on, a big TV to tune out to and stunning view whilst enjoying your breakfast. In winter turn on the gas log fireplace and enjoy a glass of wine. Head out to one of the many great eating establishments on Chapel St, Fitzroy St or take a tram to the city. the tram stop is a 2 minute walk away.

Everyone who has stayed at Charnwood has enjoyed their stay. I'm sure you will too. Great location, affordably priced and in a very convenient but quiet street.

name: Stylish Self Contained Bunkhouse
summary: Escape to our country retreat with a bunch of friends or family. So much fun to be had in this peaceful spot - whether you stay in house or explore the local delights, which are a drawcard for people from all over the world. We look forward to indulging you with our hospitality in our little bit of heaven!
space: Our bunkhouse is the perfect setup for a group of friends or a family looking for a good value country getaway. It can accommodate a total of ten guests in two separate bedrooms - one bedroom has two single beds (which can be converted to a double) and the other bedroom has 4 bunks, allowing for 8 people. Each bedroom has an entrance doorway to the well appointed, communal bathroom. You can look after all your needs in house with a fully equipped kitchen suitable to cook anything up to and including a Christmas dinner! The lounge area has a 42" flat screen TV, DVD player and stereo if you just want to relax. Surrounded by beautiful Paulownia trees the bunkhouse is well protected from the sun in summer and warmed by effective heating in the cooler months. There is an under cover outdoor sitting area with BBQ and heater which is a popular spot to read or watch the passing horsey goings on from.  Being a working equestrian property, there is the opportunity to have a riding lesson or two

This beautiful, fully equipped terrace house offers a brilliant base to explore Melbourne!

neighborhood_overview: North Fitzroy and the surrounding area is full of things to do and investigate. Edinburgh gardens is a hive of activity and a great place for a picnic. The Merri Creek will take you to the Abbotsford convent where you can visit the children’s farm and Melbourne farmers market. Cafes, Bakeries and restaurants are some of the best Melbourne has to offer.
notes: NA
transit: There are two main tram lines into the city on either side of Rae st (11 on Brunswick st & the 96 on Nicholson st). There's a train station a short walk away which runs to the city via Collingwood and Richmond. Or you can walk to the city in 20 minutes, up eclectic and cafe filled Brunswick st, or through the beautiful Carlton gardens and Melbourne Museum.

neighborhood_overview: We are in a very quiet neighborhood but still close to everything. You'll be able to walk to Puffing Billy and the main street of Belgrave. We have quite an array of good restaurants and cafes nearby.  Drive only 5 mins to Trees Adventure Park or Burnham Bakery ... and on to Sassafras and Olinda.  60 mins from Melbourne city. 40 mins to Healesville Sanctuary and the Yarra Valley. And only 90 mins drive to Phillip Island.
notes: NA
transit: Belgrave Station is conveniently a 10 minute walk away and it's 60 minutes by train into the city of Melbourne. Buses to all areas are at the station too.  There's safe street parking right outside our gate. 1 1/2 hour drive from Melbourne Airport. Or, take the bus from the airport to Southern Cross Station and get on the Belgrave line train to the end of the line.
access: There's a shared laundry right outside your door. Small charge for use will apply. Guests are welcome to walk around the garden and pick any fruit or vegetable in season.
interaction: We normally greet our guests on arrival and are happy to interact with you as little or as often as you like. It's up to you.
house_rules: Just respect our property as your own. No smoking inside.
host_about:
I love Melbourne!! And happily run a B&B now after being in the fashion industry for years. Love meeting people from all over the world and hearing about their lives and travels. Personal travel can be difficult sometimes but we manage to get away a couple of times a year. I lived in the US for 23 yrs so I travel there a lot to visit friends and family.

neighborhood_overview: Here is the closest State Park to Melbourne, Warrandyte is a haven for picnickers, bushwalkers, canoeists, cyclysts, and our unique precious wildlife.  Offering a large variety of walks.  The first gold strike in Australia was made here in Warrandyte, and there are still many who pan the creeks in search of it.   One of the oldest bakeries still exist, established in the 1880's, it still bakes using a wood fired oven come try a wood fire Pie.  Warrandyte has many coffee shops and restaurants, take away food and a supermarket.  There is a local market down by the river banks, which includes local produce, held 1st Saturday every month.   Warrandyte has alway been renowned as an artists community, from famous painters to potters, and this culture still thrives today.  There are also many quaint shops scattered through the township that are a pleasure to visit.
notes: NA
transit: Having a car is the best way to view and explore Warrandyte.  Bus stop across the road.  5.1 km to Train approx. 15 mins drive away.

neighborhood_overview: Being in the picturesque heart of the city with the beautiful Carlton Gardens to greet you every morning as you exit the building. It's literally whisper quite to hear birds tweeting in the morning as the apt is located to the rear of the block. I walk to Brunetti's in Carlton for breakfast & a coffee then stroll leisurely to the Victoria Markets for my fresh groceries. If hot, the Baths are 5 mins away too.  At lunch time I go to Soba and Sake for fresh handmade Soba or the famous Pelligrini's for an Italian dish. After that I get a macaroon at La Belle Miette in Collins Street then walk it off to Melbourne Central or QV for other dept store items. I pop into the State Library on Spencer street or get the free red tram to Docklands for other homewares or clothing. The free tram also takes me back to the apartment where I may prepare dinner then catch a comedy show down Hardware lane (email hidden) theatre show.
notes: This apartment is perfect for long stay guests of 28 days or more who are in Melbourne for business and lecturers for / at RMIT, visiting family and friends or longer stay tourist visiting this fabulous city.     Fully equipped apartment where all you need to bring is your clothing luggage.  Walking distance to practically everything.
transit: All Public transport is within less than 5 mins walk.  Free red Tram The trams to venture anywhere they go - being in the centre of the city all trams start or end there.  Bus stop is a few metres away.  Tourist & Double decker bus is a few metres away.  Closest railway station is Parliament Station about 5 mins walk.
access: The complete and entire self-contained studio apartment as per the description.  Including private bathroom powder room and kitchen.  Access to full laundry room with washing machines and dryer facilities are available to use within the complex on level 2.

Dishes washed and returned, appliances & furniture wiped clean, Bed to be stripped down including the sheets, pillow cases & quilt cover & placed in the black laundry basket located in the powder room &  rubbish removed please. All furniture is not to be moved/dragged from its original position. All damages and loss must be paid for.  Please report prior to checking out. Keys to be returned to the letterbox safe & locked. Towels not supplied.

host_about:
Hi, I am from Melbourne, Australia.

I am a lawyer and always seem to be travelling so I've put my home on AirBnb and now I am often staying at other people's AirBnb homes. It's great. I've enjoyed a lot of hospitality around the world and I like to reciprocate by offering a beautiful space for my guests. 

I am a clean living non-smoker. I do Ashtanga yoga most mornings and like to maintain a healthy lifestyle. I keep a clean home and try to fill it with love and positivity as well as some nice artwork.

Some of my favourite countries include Turkey, Portugal, Thailand, Spain, Ecuador, Panama, Brazil and the list goes on.

I speak a little Spanish and I am always trying to learn more. Hasta pronto!

neighborhood_overview: Ripponlea is a gorgeous, green, boutique suburb right next to all the must see suburbs visitors to Melbourne must see like St Kilda, Elwood, South Yarra and Prahran.  Everything is very close including public transport and guests are able to walk to gorgeous parks, cafes, shops, restaurants and bars.
notes: St Kilda Botanical Gardens are within walk distance and from there, you can walk to Acland Street and take a tram around The Esplanade and right through to Fitzroy Street.  You can get off along The Esplanade and check out St Kilda foreshore where you can walk out on to the pier and check out the penguins! Surrounded by fantastic bars, restaurants and St Kilda's amazing night life.  Everything is either at your door or one or two train or tram stops away.
transit: Ripponlea train station (on the Sandringham line) is 7 stops from the city and 300 metres door to door.  It takes 15 minutes before you're in the heart of the city at Flinders Street Station.  The tram also runs along Brighton Road which is 150 metres from your door step and takes you in to St Kilda, right along St Kilda Road and in to the heart of the city.

host_about:
I'm a friendly, positive, caring, open person who's hardworking, but relaxed and down to earth. I'm open to new experiences and meeting new people and doing new things.  I absolutely LOVE music and try to get to as many gigs when the piggy bank allows it. 

Love hanging out with my dog, Leni, friends and family.  Really enjoy going out for brekky, walking along the beach and around Melbourne's beautiful parks and gardens and getting back to nature and chilling out.  

I've travelled a bit through Europe, Asia, America, UK, Canada, India and have driven around Australia so if you need any tips or hints, I can help :)  

I love doing Airbnb as I get to meet fabulous new people and get to see how much they too love one of my favourite cities - Melbourne!

space: Location Hawthorn is a green and leafy suburb, just ten minutes from the CBD by train. Swinburne University is located here. Adjacent to Swinburne Uni, Glenferrie Rd is a well known strip of restaurants, cafes and shops.  The next suburb over is Richmond, where the MCG (Australian Football Rules Stadium) and Rod Laver Arena (Australian Open Tennis) are located. The Yarra River also runs through Hawthorn with nice bike paths, walking tracks and parks. The apartment is old but clean and comfortable. Nice and light as it is on the third floor. Your bedroom has a queen bed, built in robe, mirror, heater, fan, bedside table, lamp and a desk. Fresh linen and towels provided every 7-8 days. The bathroom is basic, with shower and washing machine which you are welcome to use. Plenty of hot water, good water pressure and lock on door. The living room is nice and bright. Access to a computer if you need it, access to WiFi, access to TV. The kitchen is small and old but does the job. You are welco

transit: To get back and forth from the CBD from our place is about 10 mins by train, the train station is in our street. Hawthorn is four stops from the CBD.  To get here from the airport, you catch the SkyBus ($18) to Southern Cross train station, about 20 mins, and then a train to Hawthorn station (myki card $6 + $4.40 for the trip), about 10 mins. A taxi is about $75 from the airport one way.
access: Shared bathroom, living room and kitchen. WiFi internet access, washing machine, kitchen facilities. Parking permit available for street parking.
interaction: Matt and I work 9am-5pm weekdays. We are happy to answer any of your questions about Melbourne or recommend things to do. We enjoy being airbnb hosts and meeting new people. We are happy to have a chat or leave you to do your own thing.
house_rules: 1. We require the bathroom for half an hour in the morning from 7:30-8:00 am approximately to get ready for work. 2. No smoking inside 3. We require the booking to be made by the person staying.  4. The room is for two people only.
host_about: I live in Melbourne with my partner Matt. We both work full time, I am in marketing and Matt is in property valuation. We love to travel and have been to a few countries between us. We also enjoy running and doing a bit of Parkrun tourism.

space: Brighton is a seaside suburb situated about 8 kilometers south of the centre of Melbourne. A sunny front room only with a queen size bed and comfortable chairs and table, ample cupboards, television and Wi-Fi; as well, a bar fridge and bedside reading lamp; cooling (ceiling fan) and heating. name: Baringa Villa "a touch of Tuscany"
summary: NA
space: Baringa Villa is a beautiful bed and breakfast offering a touch of Tuscany tucked away in the foothills of the Dandenongs Ranges in Victoria Australia. This unique accommodation offers a superior level of luxury and comfort complete with all the modern conveniences and is perfectly positioned for those looking for both short or long term stays.  This lovely Villa is a touch of Tuscany.   It has 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, a fully appointed galley kitchen, lounge, dining area and laundry facilities. Accommodates up to 6 guests. Close to public transport, local shops, restaurants and some superb attractions.

house_rules: We do have guests that get ready for wedding day as we have nearby wedding venues.   When they communicate with us we usually allow them to have small celebrations before their big day.   If they have a pet, they communicate with us truthfully as to the pet, its size and habits.
host_about:
Hi my name is Carmel.  I am married to Mario.

We both enjoy gardening and creating and growing our own produce when we can.
We both love people and sharing our wisdom & knowledge.  I am a professional Life Coach and Bars Facilitator and have been assisting and guiding people for many year.  
I enjoy the beach  both summer and winter.  At every opportunity especially in the cooler months, both Mario and I enjoy going to Peninsula Hot Springs in Rye.
I love experiencing other cultures and listening to different accents.
We have been to India many times as it feeds my soul and in turn bring that back to infuses others.  We also assist an orphanage in Mysore.

We love to travel, especially Italy as Mario has family living in Tuscany.  And we both speak italian.

I love a great film, especially if based on or inspired by true life happenings.  Mario also loves, loves action films.

We both love good quality food, simply cooked.   One of our favourite ingredient is a really good olive oil.

As for Baringa Villa.
When friends or guest stay they all comment on the tranquility of the place and how they could just sit, linger, and enjoy the peace and calm.
Given that our home is now bigger than we required!   And that we were able to easily create the private space,  Baringa Villa was born.

We really look forwards to your stay with us!

name: Modern 1BR City Apartment WiFi, pool, gym, parking
summary: This beautifully appointed, light and bright 1 bedroom apartment on St Kilda Road is the perfect spot to start and end a day during your stay in Melbourne, whether it be for holiday or business travel.
space: The apartment is located on the 4th floor in one of St Kilda Road’s most reputable apartment high rises. It has a fully equipped kitchen and an inbuilt European laundry, making longer terms stays feel like home. Enjoy free Wifi from the comfort of the leather couch or while you lounge beside the oversize windows that shower the combined lounge room living area with warm morning sunlight. The double windowed bedroom contains a built-in wardrobe with ample space for two travellers and a double size bed with all sheets and towels included. An indoor heated pool and gym is available exclusively to building residents and there is an onsite building manager during business hours. The apartment and building are strictly NO SMOKING.

The apartment building is a secure building which requires swip
neighborhood_overview: Melbourne is a creative and exciting city with unexpected surprises to be discovered in every basement, rooftop and laneway. For Melbournian’s it’s not about the tourist icons, we LOVE our city and we are passionate about making every part of it magical. We are obsessed with coffee, passionate about our foodie culture and are sports fanatics. We have super friendly and welcoming manner. It is a city of 4 Mill people but we joke that in Melbourne the 6 degrees of separation has reduced to 3. It has an amazing local, almost village feel about it. The city is a melting pot of cultures, offering a spread of the world's greatest cuisine.
notes: This building is mostly occupied by permanent residents and as such your stay will need to conform with reasonable expectations when it comes to noise and the respect you must show to the apartment, the common areas and other building residents. Sorry, there are no pets allowed.  The apartment and building are strictly NO SMOKING.
transit: St Kilda Road is Melbourne city’s tree lined main arterial gateway connecting the city’s CBD with St Kilda town, St Kilda beach and the iconic culinary and fashion destination that is Chapel Street. The apartment is a short stroll away from the Botanic Gardens, the National Gallery of Victoria and Albert Park (the Grand Prix track). The apartment is minutes from the hospital and several conference centres as well as being a short tram ride form the CBD for those whose stay is for business purposes. There is a tram stop immediately in front of the apartment building. The tram system can take you anywhere you’d want to go around Melbourne and its inner suburbs.
access: The apartment building is a secure building which requires swipe card access. Your swipe card also grants you access to the gym and swimming pool. All parts of the building are monitored by security cameras and the apartment itself has a dead bolt lock system making it extremely safe.
interaction: Either I (the owner) or a friend or family member will meet you at the apartment to hand over keys. I am available via phone 24/7 to assist with any questions or issues you may have.
house_rules: My apartment is my  pride and joy so I'd love it if you treated it like you would expect a guest to treat your home.  Specifically:  - STRICTLY NO SMOKING IN THE APARTMENT OR BUILDING  - Please be respectful of other residents in the building. Keep noise down to a reasonable level during the day and to a low level in the evenings. -no parties -Recycling needs to be taken to ground floor. There is garbage shoot on the  4th floor for everything else.  -Please make sure you clean the dryer filter after every use so it doesn't overheats. The filler is inside the door. - Please have your lights on while in the car park for safety reasons - There are a couple of shoe cabinets within the apartment near the doorway. The shoe cabinet nearest the door is marked "Do Not Use". This cabinet is broken so per the sign, please do not use -I would be very grateful if you would water the plants once a week during your stay.  * The building manager requires that all guests undergo a quick induction so gu
host_about:
36 year old Australian female. Love travelling! I have been to over 40 countries and aim to visit at least one new place each year. Airbnb has changed the way I travel. I have stayed at a couple of amazing places in the US and Europe and now I can't imagine doing it any other way. 

I have moved to Sydney to further my career in Travel Marketing & Digital and as a result have put my own Melbourne apartment on Airbnb.

name: Studio at VALLEY FARM VINEYARD!
summary: Valley Farm's stylish one bedroom villa has Alpacas at your windows while overlooking the vineyard. The property is set within a quiet secluded valley only 5 minutes drive away from the Yarra Valley's famous food and wine epicentre. Adult only and no pets, sorry.
space: Accommodation is in a refurbished satellite tracking station which was used to broadcast the 1984 Olympic Games. Massive windows provide vineyard and mountain views.  The studio cottage caters for 2 guests. Also on the property a 2 bedroom apartment can accommodate up to 4 adults and a 3 bedroom apartment can take up to 6 adults. Regretfully we do not cater for children under the age of 12 years. Note, sometimes the Alpacas may be in a nearby paddock rather than at the window (we do need to let the grass regrow)
description: Valley Farm's stylish one bedroom villa has Alpacas at your windows while overlooking the vineyard. The property is set within a quiet secluded valley only 5 minutes drive away from the Yarra Valley's famous food and wine epicentre. Adult only and no pets, sorry. Regretfully we do not cater for children under the age of 12 years. Note, sometimes the Alpacas may be in a nearby paddock rather than at the window (we do need to let the grass regrow) Guests are free to explore the property and interact with Alpacas and cattle in the paddocks. Prolific native birds and wildlife, mainly kangaroos and wombats. Fantastic views over vineyard and mountains beyond. Whethe
neighborhood_overview: The Yarra Valley, just over an hour's travel by car from Melbourne is synonymous with food and wine! ... and we are in the middle of it! Great coffee, restaurants and wineries are only minutes away, yet Valley Farm offers quiet seclusion, wildlife and walks for those that want to get away from it all. World famous Healesville Sanctuary is close by and we are surrounded by the Yarra Ranges National Park.
notes: Please be aware of wombats crossing our driveway if arriving at night.
transit: We are located 3 km from the Healesville township. Public buses travel daily from Melbourne. Rail service runs from Melbourne to Lilydale (about 28 kms away). Taxis available.
access: Guests are free to explore the property and interact with Alpacas and cattle in the paddocks. Prolific native birds and wildlife, mainly kangaroos and wombats. Fantastic views over vineyard and mountains beyond. Whether it's a stroll from your accommodation through the vineyard or wilderness trek through the National Park there are walks to suit anyone.
interaction: Guests can choose to either chill out in the privacy of their apartment or chat to the owners who live well away but on the 35 acre property. There is always some thing happening with seasonal work in the 22 year old vineyard. Our wine brand, Trellis comprises the following varietals; Pinot Noir, Chardonnay and Syrah. All wines consistently score between 90-96 points in the Halliday Wine Companion which benchmarks all Australian wines.
house_rules: NA
host_about:
Locals from the beautiful Yarra Valley.. whether it's wine, food or nature walks we'll show you the best the Yarra has to offer using Valley Farm as your base.
We're passionate about all things wine and agritourism and keen to meet travellers from all over the globe.

name: Amongst the Poets, central Elwood.
summary: Ground floor, secure apartment in a quiet, leafy part of Southey St. Well equipped kitchen. The bathroom is a little tired. Easy walk to tram, Tennyson St, Ackland St. Private decked courtyard, like an extra room in summer. Great afternoon light in Winter. Undercover car park. Limited Foxtel. New super comfy pillow top master bed!
space: Quiet, leafy, cosy, sunny and accessible. It's cheerful and usually one of the cheapest Airbnb's in Elwood/StKilda.  Unlimited internet.  Fitted out kitchen with food processor , basic cooking, cutlery and crockery. Fridge, microwave. There’s a washing machine under the kitchen bench. name: Henrietta, the Lygon St studio
summary: There are several types of people in this world and some of them are apartments. Henrietta is no different, she was born when coffee was black and damper was dinner. Fortunately coffee and cuisine have come a long way and Henrietta will indulge you.
space: Henrietta is a beautifully clever and spacious old girl, nested in the heart of Carlton, on the northern fringe of Melbourne’s Hoddle grid. Resting on a quiet laneway nearby Argyle Square, she enjoys the mouthwatering Italian delights of Lygon Street and its entertainment artery to the city. She wanders the nearby park sipping coffee from top baristas, venturing to Nova Cinema for an art house classic or just gets lost in the Trades Hall. She is ideal for couples with a kid or travelling dous and trios who need a central spot to spend the night. She is cosy and warm with plenty of natural light filling her up in the evening. If you’re looking for a central location, self-contained and surrounded by good food and entertainment, Henrietta is the girl for you.

access: She has a kitchenette where you can prepare basic meals, a desk and chair for you to eat, work or play and a bathroom for well, you know. Everything in the apartment is yours to use including the cupboards!
interaction: You will have the apartment all to yourself, there will be someone there to let you in and show you around. If you've got any questions or want some more info, feel free to get in touch!
house_rules: - No smoking. - Pets are not allowed. - No parties. You can have friends over, but please save your energy for your night out - Having a party will forfeit your entire bond. - When checking out, please leave the apartment in a clean and tidy manner. You don’t need to mop and vacuum but please remember this is someone’s home and to put things back where you found them. - Keep noise down between 10pm and 8am (City Council rule) and be respectful of our neighbours. - If there is a medical emergency, fire or matters requiring police assistance, please contact 000. For other matters, phone me. - It is your responsibility to lock up when you are not home and to turn off the fans, lights, heaters and TV. Plus, saving the environment makes you cool. - I do not accept responsibility for loss of property. However, if you realise you have left something in the apartment after check-out please phone and I will do my best to have it returned to you.
host_about:
I'm Linton, I own and run a short-stay management company, Beyond a Room, here in Melbourne. If you book with me you'll be communicating with both myself and my team.

I’m an entrepreneur, architecture graduate, photographer, cyclist (NOT the lycra kind), volunteer, adventurer and problem solver.

During my studies I worked at various cafes and architecture offices to save up for shoestring trips around the world. My grandma once told me I had ‘champagne taste but a beer budget’ and it’s a motto I’ve enjoyed applying to different parts of my life to get the more out of less and find enjoyment in the little things.

I love discovering authentic experiences when I travel and I love being able to share the opportunity with others, to live like a local when they travel too.

Some of my most memorable trips have been couch-surfin across Russia while taking the Trans Siberian, living in Helsinki and learning to hand build furniture, riding a vintage steel bicycle through France to race in L’Eroica and buying a car on craigzlist in Los Angeles and driving across the south, east and north coasts to arrive in Vancouver.

My listings are all managed by Beyond a Room. My aim is to give guests a unique and local perspective on the location and share my knowledge and experience of this wonderful city with travellers so that they feel at home. Search Beyond a Room to find out more about how we can help manage your airbnb.

I keep all my calendars up to date so if it’s available in the calendar, you can usually just go ahead and book instantly.

notes: This apartment is a TV free environment - yup there is no TV in the house! With all the things to see and all the things to do around the city I personally do not have time (nor have any interest) to watch TV and I would recommend you try and do the same during your stay!  May I suggest a nice bottle of wine on the terrace enjoying the city view instead? That would make a much more memorable experience.  Also please note: the apartment is set on top of a hotel building which also offers many rooms and suites in different shapes and sizes. Although this apartment is unique in its position, aspect, decor, view and use of outdoor space, if you are only concerned with location during your stay then you could have a look at the lower levels of the hotel building to see what other options are there.
transit: The apartment is surrounded by public transport options with 2 tram stops within 1 minute of the building entrance and major train stations within 5-10 minutes walking.  Enjoy the free tram zone all around the cbd from right outside the door!
access: All areas of the apartment (living room + kitchen, bedroom, bathroom and outdoor terrace) + gym, pool and sauna in the building.
interaction: When in Melbourne I am happy to suggest and share many of the 'secrets' that this city tightly holds away from the tourist eye. I work and spend a lot of time around the CBD so always very happy to help with any requests.
house_rules: No parties and no excessive noise. Please keep everything clean and tidy and leave the apartment in order.
host_about:
Creative director living in Melbourne and often found overseas and interstate. I love life in Melbourne's CBD and everything it has to offer: the laneways, the restaurants and bars, the ambiance and of course the people. The city base on offer is set in a humble rooftop apartment that reflects everything I love about urban life. No matter what I may have been through during my hard working days or weeks, a few minutes on my terrace soaking the city around me gets me right back to normal. 
After a recent visit to New York City I have decided to open and share my city base with like-minded travelers who may be looking for a unique, hidden city apartment that represents a lot more than just a roof over their heads. I hope you enjoy this humble Melbourne Pied-à-terre during your stay!

name: Mawarra Manor - Heritage listed mansion and garden
summary: Mawarra is a 3ac luxury estate and is heritage listed. The gardens, designed and constructed by Edna Walling offer numerous "outdoor rooms" whilst the Manor has that wood-panelled old world feel with a country kitchen, billiards room and amazing avocado-shaped indoor pool with sauna.
space: Mawarra Manor, heritage listed and built in 1932, is set on 3 acres and sleeps 8 in 4 exquisite bedrooms. The garden is recognised as the most famous surviving example by renowned garden designer Edna Walling. Whilst both house and garden have undergone extensive restoration their historic significance has always remained at the forefront of thinking. The manor incorporates all traditional formal and informal rooms that one would expect in a home of this era. Extensive wood panelling, wall to wall carpets, gas central heating, evaporative cooling and tasteful lighting provide a luxurious ambience. The upper level comprises an entry hall, large bow-shaped formal lounge with open fire place, enormous semi-enclosed balcony billiards room overlooking the central staircase and garden, country kitchen with Miele appliances including 2 dishwashers, built-in refrigerator and built-in coffee machine, electric oven, gas hob, microwave and separate gas AGA oven and hotplates. neighborhood_overview: This is a unique and quiet neighbourhood that has a lovely strip of shops with lots of cafes, various restaurants (Indian, Thai, Mexican, Pizza, BBQ Chicken and Fish & Chip Shop) close by. Lovely boutiques, hairdressing and gift shops. The beach has a walking track that takes you along the Bay, with great scenery. Westfield Shopping Centre, Cheltenham (Southland) has Cinemas, Myers, David Jones and many more fabulous shops.  8 minutes by car. The Mornington Peninsula and Red Hill wineries are approximately a 1/2 to 3/4 hour drive away. The Peninsula Hot Springs approx. 40 minutes drive away.  HOW TO GET TO MY HOME IN PARKDALE: Melbourne Airport - Catch the Red Airport Bus to Southern Cross Station in the City which will take about 20 minutes.  Then catch a Frankston Line Train to Parkdale - 35 minutes from Station. YOU WILL NEED TO PURCHASE A MYKI CARD TO USE FOR TRAIN TRAVEL (This is also used for any Metropolitan Bus or Tram travel during your stay). Airport to my home should take ab
notes: Wi-fi available for Free. Free use of washing machine/washing powder is also available, if required, for those on a longer stay. Use of Refrigerator for storing food and drinks if you wish. Rachel
transit: The closest Bus stop is only a 2 minute walk away on Beach Rd.  This can take you to Chadstone Shopping Centre, which is the largest shopping precinct in the Southern hemisphere. The Train Station is only an 8 minute walk away.  This will take you to the City of Melbourne in 35 minutes. If arriving by Aeroplane guests can catch a Red Frankston/Peninsular Skybus located just meters away from the baggage pick-up area.  This bus leaves the Airport every hour.   THE LAST BUS LEAVES AT 6.55 PM. Tickets can be bought from the booth outside to travel along Nepean Highway.  This is approx $38.00 from Airport to Parkdale Motor Inn,  I can pick you up from this drop off point as it is only a 3 minute drive from my home. Total travel time from Airport to Parkdale allowing for stop-offs for passengers on the way is approx. 1 hr 15 minutes.

I have a Beautiful Ragdoll appropriately named Bella (Beautiful).  She loves company and will follow you around as she loves company and a pat. As I am an Entertainer/Singer, I enjoy going out to listen to Live music so you can tag along with me if you wish.

I love eating Italian, Mexican, Thai and Vietnamese foods.
I enjoy travelling and cruising, especially Italy and Greek Islands.
(PS:  Minimum 2 Night Stay - Singles only preferred)

A hot spot for fashionistas and those who love their fine food, the area boasts fantastic local and international designers, great cafes and restaurants. Downstairs - in the building you have  Adriano Zumbo's flagship Melbourne store (the famous dessert chef from Sydney), and Two Birds One Stone (the sister cafe to Three Bags Full, one of the most iconic cafes in Fitzroy), and a hotspot for brunches and awesome breakfasts. neighborhood_overview: A hop from the City, a skip from the Carlton Gardens and a jump from quirky Brunswick street. We are nestled on a quiet street in the heart of Fitzroy's (and Melbourne's) finest.  Cosmopolitan Fitzroy is the inner city abode of Melbourne's most fashion, food and drink conscious. If it's cool, it must be in Fitzroy - that mantra applies to everything from bars and cafes to clothing and hairdressing salons. Little wonder then at the multitude of photoshoots that occur on the back streets and the main ones of Fitzroy.  Once a bohemian hideaway, Fitzroy is now the home of eclectic doctors, university professors and corporates many with young families. With a multitude of parks and playgrounds it is a destination for the young and the young at heart.

There are also many world famous cocktail bars on Brunswick St. 10 minutes away is Smith St and also Lygon st famous for modern eateries and Italian cuisine respectively. The options of activities is endless. A car is not required to get around the local area as everywhere is accessible via walking or public transport.

name: Cosy home in vibrant Collingwood
summary: Our quaint little 2 br house is an inner city sanctuary. Walking distance to the amazing Smith, Brunswick & Gertrude Streets; bars, pubs, cafes, restaurants, boutiques, galleries. It's an ideal base from which to discover Melbourne's best.
space: A combination of modern danish and quaint cottage design, filled with contemporary Australian art works, there's plenty of space for two guests to relax and unwind.  The second bedroom is child's room,  so our home is ideal if you're looking for a place to stay with your kids. Should you wish to stay in and cook, our kitchen is very well equipped. Otherwise, you're only a hop, skip and a jump from some of Melbourne's most famous cafes, pubs and restaurants (Saint Crispins, Red Sparrow Pizza, The Gasometer, The Builders Arms, The Craft & Co. etc.) plus some hidden gems, like our personal favourite, Cibi cafe. Everything you could possibly need is within a 1km radius!

name: Charming Granny Flat in Coburg
summary: Quiet and charming Granny flat set in a beautiful garden.  The air conditioned bedroom comfortably accommodates two people, and has a private bathroom, a private kitchen, and separate access.  Conveniently located, a quick tram ride takes you straight to the heart of Melbourne, with trains and buses a short walk away. A generous discount is offered for weekly or monthly stays.
space: Light and airy room (air conditioned) set in a beautiful garden, with queen sized bed, wardrobe, a small table for work or leisure, and a wall-mounted T.V. for relaxing! Comfortably fits 2 guests. Attached to it is a fully fledged new kitchen and separate bathroom both just gone through total renovation.
description: Quiet and charming Granny flat set in a beautiful garden.  The air conditioned bedroom comfortably accommodates two people, and has a private bathroom, a private kitchen, and separate access.  Conveniently located, a quick tram ride takes you straight to the heart of Melbourne, with trains and buses a short walk away. A generous discount is offered for weekly or monthly stays. Light and airy room (air conditioned) set in a beautiful garden, with queen sized bed, wardrobe, a small table for work or leisure, and a wall-mounted T.V. for relaxing! Comfortably fits 2 guests. neighborhood_overview: Coburg is a wonderful neighbourhood, friendly, leafy and quiet - close to the city and to fabulous Melbourne suburbs such as Fitzroy and Brunswick! The Merri Creek, 5 minutes walk from the house, offers some beautiful and relaxing walks.
notes: There is all-day free parking available out the front of the house.
transit: A tram to the city (and beach!) via the wonderful Lygon Street is a 2-minute walk from the house, and will take about 25 minutes to the CBD - or, if you prefer the train lines, there are direct-city services leaving at 20 minutes intervals at a 10 minute walk from the house. Buses linking East-West are close by. Melbourne University and RMIT are a short tram trip away.  For those interested in the Tennis Open Australia, a tram direct to the games leaves from outside the street!
access: Guests will have access to a private kitchen and a private bathroom. Feel free to enjoy our garden - shared with the colourful parrots and lorikeets who love our fruit trees - and easy access to the guest room from the street via a side-garden gate.
interaction: Feel free to ask for advice or help - we're friendly and speak English, French, and German.

neighborhood_overview: Armadale is Melbourne's best inner east suburb- hosting an eclectic mix of both period and modern architecture. High street once being the top fashion capital -has many top designers with a collection of various boutiques, bridal wear, and persian rugs to view, Some famous bakeries ; Philippas, which is home to some of the best cakes and fare in Melbourne,  or Glicks the famous bagel shop in Glenferrie rd -an abundance of cafes, -with a huge array of every culture represented on famous Glenferrie rd. the house is set back from the street so you can relax away from the business of the surrounding streets- especially with parks and gardens very nearby, as well as a library and gym.there is ample car parking outside.
notes: Close for everything, restaurants,gyms, swimming pools, library, Glenferrie rd, all public transport,  leafy trendy,supporting great variety of coffee shops, hairdressers, shopping and specialty bakeries. Check-in is usually after 4 pm  but if timing is good can renegotiate -same for check-out by 10 am, but if wanting to leave bags here for the day is quite ok- just let me know. We wear slippers inside and re-cycle our rubbish per council regs; In an energy efficient  home we use central heating and our wall air-con- so no blower heaters here as per council recommendations. many thanks fay
transit: All forms of transport nearby- train, tram, bus, tram, walking distance to all amenities. Trams run along; High/Wattletree/Glenferrie rds and a bus along kooyong road -so nothing is very far away. it is a very safe area to walk in ,both day and night, and has not only top designer shops but  many hairdressers, make-up and beauty shops, as well as vintage and toy shops, with top end perfumery and antique shops still abound the  area. 5 mins walk to bus tram and 10 mins to Armadale station. Glenferrie road is 10 mins away with all restaurant , cafes, well serviced with all needs met.
access: All rooms- except mine and study - of course-, kitchen, bathroom (with bathtub)- washing machine(weekly- on a shared load ), backyard,  flatscreen -tv, lounge, cooking, and excellent reliable wi-fi. Features include; 4 b/rooms. comfortable lounge, comfortable decor, clean and polished floor boards in hall kitchen, family room, this is an energy conscious home- so  high ceilings with period features,central heating in winter,air-con summer,( only my heating and air con to be used) clean modern, linen and bedding with towels, fully equipped kitchen all for use, coffee, tea, plunger, hairdryer,large bathroom,  ironing board,/iron, washing line, drying racks outside, washing machine (no dryer please) meals with island bench and comfy chairs, kitchen table with 6-8 chairs Garden area with chairs, power adapters, helpful maps, and tour guide books, best restaurants and shops nearby a train station nearby for  Myki  if needed, Also there is ample off street parking if needed as well.-
interaction: I will greet you and am available to answer any queries you may have during your stay. i love chatting and meeting new people from here and all over the world and enjoy sharing the special places in my neighbourhood  with guests. I'm in and out constantly but always happy to help;and as much contact as the guest prefers ; Friendly, respectful ,private and  helpful. i'm busy off and on so am usually doing my own thing. I enjoy  open communication - but let me know of your needs -as little or as much contact as you prefer. Enjoy yourself here.- is my motto. cheers Fay
house_rules: I have very few rules and I am more than happy to accommodate on any of them, but please give me notice and be communicative and be respectful. it is my home and i do live here as well. The only problems that have ever arose is when people have mistaken me for a maid in a hotel! It is a home-  so trust and happiness and respect are great for all to enjoy their time together in our home. Welcome! No smoking indoors. No sleepover guests.  Breakfast can be made available on request. I'd like to know your details such as gender / age / student / occupation / languages / marital status / reason for travel / length of stay as we have others here of various ages and feel the more we know early the better for all. Please show me a phot-(headshot) as you see of me when making your booking as it is easier for all and a photocopy of your passport / some ID.upon arrival Please confer with me when you wish to use the washing machine - as i switch it on- and a few other bits will go on- as only x1 p
host_about:
I'm a primary school teacher with grown up children who are living away from home. 

I love the outdoors, movies and cooking and meeting new people. I am relaxed and easy going. I like to go for walks at one of the nearby leafy parks and go for coffee.

Armadale is a great neighborhood, close to to transport and amenities. Also full of trendy shops and gyms/tennis courts and a library.

I look forward to meeting you. Welcome to Melbourne, I hope you have a great stay.

Cheers
Fay

name: Private room close to Melbourne
summary: Spacious and very private ground floor apartment in the heart of Epping (19 Km to North from CBD). Short walk to shops, cafes, pubs and bars, Green brook shopping center, Epping Plaza, Epping railway station, NMIT Epping campus, Northern hospital etc.
space: Easy access to the city on public transport. Just 3 min walk to catch the bus to anywhere or 10min walk to the train to city or South Morang. Every 20 minutes there is a train to city during the day. In peak hours there are more trains.  The apartment has a bedroom with single bed. Neat modern bathroom, living room & kitchen. Includes, air conditioning and heating. Tea and coffee facilities available. Microwave, crockery and cutlery, bed linen and towels supplied. Living room has a large couch to relax. The apartment is annexed behind the house, where owner living in. The host is available to meet you, providing advice about public transport and the best restaurants. The apartment is, however, completely separate from host's living areas, so you don't have to communicate unless you need to.  Fantastic exciting area with so much going on, but the apartment is quiet and peaceful, so it's a perfect retreat!

neighborhood_overview: Experience St Kilda! Walk to cool cafes, great local shopping, in Carlisle street, Balaclava. There are beautiful parks & Art-Deco cinema close by, historic homes & neighborhoods, and close to all public transport options - train, tram and bus to all areas of Melbourne. Minutes from famous St Kilda beach, and very close to Prahran, Windsor and South Yarra. Or imagine waking up on Saturday morning and strolling around the corner to the new Hank Marvin street food & produce market - it's super fun and delicious, set in lovely Alma Park. The Arts precincts of St Kilda, and Prahran/Windsor are just a few minutes away, and the Melbourne Arts Precinct (NGV, Arts Centre & Fed Square) is a short, 12 min train ride away.  Another few minutes walk will get you to famous Chapel street, where you can find every kind of fashion store, plus a huge variety of other shopping. It's also a cafe heaven, full of street culture, and revs up in the evenings as a lively nightlife destination.
notes: NA
transit: Tram - 2 routes within 5-8 minute walk. Train - 8 minute walk to station. Bus - 1 minute walk. Train to Melbourne CBD 15 min. Easy access to Monash University Caulfield Campus, Melbourne Polytechnic (Prahran campus)
access: You have your own entry, and a front porch/garden - great spot for brekky, or a relaxing drink after a day of exploring. Fancy a quiet night in? Pick up some supplies and prepare your meals in the kitchen. Need to catch up on some washing? No problem - laundry facilities are available for you to use!  Bathroom is shared.
interaction: This is a family home - the guest room is at the opposite end of the house from the living area. So you have privacy... But if you want to hang out with us sometimes, that's great too! I'm proud of the quality experience that I provide for my guests, as a St. Kilda & Melbourne host!
house_rules: Smoke free home - No Smoking. No partying. Registered Air BnB Guests only. Use of kitchen: Guests are very welcome to use the kitchen For preparing and/or cooking light meals, prior to 8pm. One load of washing (laundry) per week. Additional wash loads for $5 per load. Quiet time after 10.30pm.
host_about:
I know Melbourne like the back of my hand! (Well, almost..) Being an inner-city creative type - working in the Arts & Media - certainly means I know all the usual haunts, plus many more! I love to show visitors around Melbourne,
then set them on the road to their own discoveries of this amazing city.
The house is fun, cool, clean & creative & super-convenient!

name: Inner-city stylish Brunswick apartment
summary: Character-filled Brunswick apartment with one bedroom, huge balcony with garden, separate bathroom, vintage piano and books aplenty. A perfect base for your culture-filled trip. Inner-city Melbourne at its best. You'll be mere steps away from a public green space, bustling and multi-cultural Sydney Road and a tram stop to take you into the heart of the city. A quick walk to the train station.
space: Large top-floor, secure apartment in the heart of Brunswick (inner-city Melbourne) with extraordinary west-facing balcony (4m x 4m) for you to enjoy a morning coffee or yoga and beautiful evening sunsets.   So many places are sparse and sterile, this is the opposite. Styled with tasteful artwork and design features; a curated selection of books; a vintage piano; and located right in the thick of the city's inner north, this abode will literally feel like your home away from home.  The apartment is an unusually large space for a one bedroom pad. It is light-filled with floor to ceiling windows; wooden floating floorboards; a little office nook where you can set up your laptop and catch up on emails; separate dining table; lounge area and fully-equipped kitchen.   The bedroom has a (seriously good!) queen-sized bed and loads of storage space and there is a separate bathroom with shower (toiletries supplied).
