A quick walk to the train station. Large top-floor, secure apartment in the heart of Brunswick (inner-city Melbourne) with extraordinary west-facing balcony (4m x 4m) for you to enjoy a morning coffee or yoga and beautiful evening sunsets.   So many places are sparse and sterile, this is the opposite. Styled with tasteful artwork and design features; a curated selection of books; a vintage piano; and located right in the thick of the city's inner north, this abode will literally feel like your home away from home.  The apartment is an unusually large space for a one bedroom pad. It is light-filled with floor to ceiling windows; woo
neighborhood_overview: Brunswick is one of Melbourne's most diverse inner-city neighbourhoods with everything from ethnic grocers to indie pubs to vintage shops all living in harmony. A wonderful indie, culture-filled suburb.

name: Modern & Compact 1930s Art Deco 1BR Apartment
summary: If you're looking for a self contained place that's close to Melbourne city and all it offers, look no further! This ground floor apartment is in a recently renovated, highly sought after, exclusive and iconic 1930s Art Deco building, set in the middle of an enclosed, "city oasis" garden. Rooftop access with stunning views of Melbourne and the Yarra River, this flat has it all! Weekly and monthly bookings are discounted.
space: I lived here for a decade and I adore it - and I can't wait for you to stay here and discover why...  Tucked away in a historical 1930s Art Deco apartment block along the Yarra River in the exclusive inner-city suburb of South Yarra, this small designer ground-floor apartment with a "Juliet" balcony, as a neighbour calls it, overlooks a gorgeous garden "oasis" and contains one large bedroom; a living/dining room; a bathroom with a nice, deep bath/shower combo and vintage tiles; and a small but well equipped, functional kitchen. Bright, stylish, eclectic, cosy, a little bohemian and very comfortable - it's perfect for short or long stays!

Bright, stylish, eclectic, cosy, a little
neighborhood_overview: People generally love South Yarra for the trendy shopping, dining, coffee and clubbing along Chapel Street and Toorak Road. But I love it for its central location, which makes all of Melbourne and what it has to offer so incredibly easy to access. Melbourne city is virtually knocking on your door, so if you want some culture, you really don't have to go far to find it! Melbourne's sporting precinct, famous for our Melbourne Cricket Ground (MCG) which hosts the cricket, Aussie Rules football and concerts; and of course the neighbouring tennis grounds that host the Australian Open. All this is within an easy stroll - you can catch a game or even a concert there just about every night of the week. And if the wind is blowing in the right direction, you can hear the roar of the crowd at a game or the music from a stadium concert at the MCG! Richmond's fashion wholesalers on Bridge Road, beachy-bohemian St Kilda or the very hip bar, live band and art precinct of Collingwood and Fitzroy are j
notes: This is an old building, so don't expect modern luxuries - both the building and the apartment have their quirks.  However the building has a rich and colourful history and atmosphere that's very palpable, having lovingly housed some formidable Melbourne Bohemians over the last 75 years, including John Ellis Bains, the blind Jazz musician and his wife, Betty Pounder, a famous choreographer who worked at Her Majesty's Theatre in Melbourne, among many other Bohemians and colourful characters over the decades (me included?!). Fans of Nick Cave and the Bad Seeds will enjoy knowing that they're staying in the flat where 'Deanna' once lived... Oh, if the walls could talk! Also please note that to access the apartment and other features of the building, there are stairs, so wheelchair access is tricky.
transit: Public transport is so easy to access from here, with two bus routes right outside the door and your choice of Richmond and South Yarra train stations, both approximately 500m away, as well as the number 8 tram along Toorak Rd; the 70/75 tram on Swan Street or the 78/79 tram along Church or Chapel Street. Just make sure to pop into a convenience store to buy a Myki public transport card! If you feel like exercise, stroll, jog or cycle into the city or towards the leafy Eastern suburbs along the Yarra River track, or rent a bike at one of two Melbourne Bike Share stations nearby. If this is all a bit confusing, don't worry! I've written it all out, printed maps and tram & bus timetables for you to take in at your own pace.
access: -This cul-de-sac property is secure and can only be accessed via two gates. One gate has an intercom, but the security key* can open both.   -Wifi access throughout the apartment.  -Rooftop access* with beautiful 360 degree views of Melbourne city & surrounds - you can see as far as the Dandenong Ranges to the east on a clear day. -Communal, coin-operated laundry* with dryers, indoor and outdoor clothes lines. -Street parking. Visitor parking permit available for one car only. Please note that to access the apartment and other features of the building, there are stairs, so wheelchair access is tricky. *Security key required - the security key is expensive and difficult to duplicate, so I ask that you pay a security deposit which is inclusive of the cost of replacing the key. See pricing.
interaction: I will not be present during your stay, however where possible I will meet you to give you the keys and show you around the place and gladly answer any questions. I'll be contactable throughout your stay should you have any further questions or any problems; and I'm more than happy to share any local information and tips - just ask!
house_rules: -Smoking is allowed, provided that it is done outside, on the balcony ONLY. -Pets are allowed, but be aware that other residents also have pets (cats and dogs mainly). If bringing a dog, feel free to let it play in the garden, however please clean up after it as you would in a park. PLEASE ADVISE me if bringing a pet. -Please be considerate of other neighbours with regards to noise in the evening, especially after 11pm. -STRICTLY NO PARTIES in the apartment or on the rooftop! Body Corporate is very strict on enforcing this rule (and all rules listed) and monitors their adherence closely. -NO HIGH HEELS to be worn on rooftop as they damage the fragile floor membrane (and their sound resonates down through the apartments below). -For security reasons, always keep gates, laundry and rooftop closed. ALWAYS lock balcony and front doors behind you.  -For security reasons, do not disclose intercom gate code to anyone.
host_about:
Born in South Africa, raised in Italy and shaped by spending the majority of my life in Australia, you could definitely say that travel is in my blood.

I'm a dreamer; freelance videographer and photographer (my dream is to make feature length films) and I love to travel and trying different foods and learning about different cultures and languages. I am fascinated with archaeology and ancient cultures and I'm probably at my happiest exploring ancient ruins. I sing, play guitar and bass and I can keep a simple beat on the drums. I'm a cinephile with a passion for Australian schlock, or 'Ozploitation' films. Oh, and I love animals!

Currently my travel wish list includes: Norway, Peru, Mexico, Japan; more of Holland, Germany, Greece and Italy again of course; Turkey, Morocco, Egypt, Jordan, Portugal.

.. 

I speak fluent English and Italian.
I've enjoyed hosting via AirBnB (currently on hold) as well as being a clean and respectful (sometimes helpful) guest!

name: Art Deco Studio Apartment
summary: Set in lush garden grounds, this heritage 1930's art deco studio apartment has been recently renovated, making it a very comfortable stay for a couple. Centrally located in fashionable Fitzroy, it is a short walk from the city and the rest!
space: This apartment complex, designed by renowned Melbourne architect Best Overend in 1936, is on the Victorian Heritage Register as a building of great architectural significance.  The interior renovation of this particular apartment has recently received multiple awards and media recognition for its sensitive and clever design.

neighborhood_overview: This apartment is fantastically located in fashionable, bustling Fitzroy, just 10 minutes walk or a short tram ride from the city centre. It is directly opposite the heritage listed Carlton Gardens with such architectural icons as the Old Exhibition Building and the Melbourne Museum just across the road.  Just two minutes walk away are two of Melbourne's prime retail / fashion / dining / drinking streets: Brunswick Street and Gertrude Street. Location doesn't get much better than this!

name: South Yarra -  Amazing City Views
summary: Modern 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment located in the heart of South Yarra. With uninterrupted views across Melbourne's skyline this apartment is walking distance to Melbourne's key sporting venues and has easy access to public transport, restaurants and great shopping.
space: Located close to the corner of South Yarra’s iconic Chapel St and Toorak Road, and South Yarra Station, this spaciously modern apartment enjoys spectacular views of Melbourne. These take in St. Kilda, Port Phillip Bay, across the Botanical Gardens and around to the full city-scape of Melbourne’s CBD with Rod Laver Arena, AAMI Park and MCG in the foreground. This is the best view of the City of Melbourne! It is conveniently located within walking distance to some of Melbourne’s best shops and restaurants. Key venues such as the MCG, AAMI stadium, Rod Laver Arena, the Botanical Gardens and the Yarra are all less than a 15 minute walk away. Alternatively, South Yarra station and trams are only at the end of the road. The apartment is tastefully furnished and offers accommodation for up to 6 people. name: NY style rooftop apartment
summary: Location, Location, Location.  Beach, City, Cafes and Bars.  The apartment is a St Kilda NY style roof top apartment with its own private garden.   Clean, simple and comfortable accommodation for 2 people from which to enjoy wonderful Melbourne.  LEAVE YOUR CAR IN THE UNDERGROUND CARPARK AND WALK TO THE BEACH. No additional cleaning fee or carparking fee in the daily rate
space: Our apartment interior is clean, comfortable and functional. What it lacks in the latest fit out is more than compensated by its location in one of Melbourne's most dynamic city fringe suburbs. Although only one bedroom the rooms are generous and light. Then there is our very own garden in the sky. The outdoor area is as big as the apartment, with lush planters and a deck area where on warm days we have breakfast.  We are animal lovers and always travel with our small dog Bronte, so if you need a pet friendly apartment this is the ideal space for well behaved fur babies.

neighborhood_overview: St Kilda has it all.  It’s a suburb that shouts life and diversity and is enjoyed by the locals, attracts Melbournians for the beach and entertainment and is a must see for first timers to our fair city.   •	The beach is a 5 minute walk down Fitzroy St •	St Kilda salt water baths •	St Kilda Sunday market •	Every imaginable culinary option  	Circa (at the Prince) 	Milk the Cow 	The George 	Fitzrovia 	Stoke House •	5 minute walk to Ackland St  •	Albert Park Lake •	MSAC – Melb Swim and Aquatic Centre •	A tram to CBD via the light rail or alternatively along St Kilda Rd We are across the road from the bus that goes directly between the airport and St Kilda.   Also across the road is a Woolworths supermarket.
notes: The outdoor secure garden is a great place for small fur babies to enjoy
transit: The number 96 tram is a great way to get around.  The stop is just across the road.   Alternatively the Skybus from the airport also has a stop across the road. If you are heading into the city you will skirt along the edge of Albert Park Lake and South Melbourne (great food and shopping) turn left at Southbank and the Casino to Bourke St, Myer and David Jones.   This tram will take you up to Melbourne Uni and Carlton if you want to explore further afield
access: This is our home so it is pretty well set up.  The kitchen has gas hotplates and stove, a large fridge and dishwasher. You are welcome to use our tea, coffee and condiments to supplement a meal.  The bathroom is compact but includes a nice sized bath.  Bed linen and towels are provided.  In built heating and air-conditioning.  Communal washing machine and dryer
interaction: The apartment will be vacant when you visit so you will have the place to yourself.  We have provided a list of our favourite restaurants - ranging from a delicious breakfast at Miss Jacksons, fabulous treats and coffee at the French bakery next door or a drink at The George
house_rules: Banff apartments has a nice mix of people and everyone respects one another's privacy.  Although the rooftop garden is a lovely place to have a few friends over for a drink this is not a party venue.   It is however a puuuurfect home for you and your fur baby.
host_about:
Chris and I love living in St Kilda as there is so much variety packed into one suburb.  

We enjoy running along the beach or attending Park Run on a Saturday morning around Albert Park lake - how could we not enjoy that. 

There are new restaurants and galleries to discover in St Kilda and Melbourne is a fantastic place to visit. 

We hope to hear from you

neighborhood_overview: Hawthorn East is delightful. A great place to walk around the streets & local parks. Views of the city are great & it is very friendly. Combine this with local cafes, wine bars & restaurants all within walking distance. The walkable access to the Rivoli Theatre, Shops at either Tooronga Village & Camberwell Junction & to public transport do make it a joy to live here.
notes: NOISE: A new house is being built next door with builders starting from 7am most morning so there will be noise regretfully.!!  We are ONLY offering the kitchen for breakfast which we provide UNLESS BY PRIOR DISCUSSION.  There is a walk in Pantry with fridge which is ideal for making snacks etc. WE ARE OFFERING LITTLE TO NO COOKING FACILITIES.   LET'S FIRSTLY DISCUSS WHAT YOU HAVE IN MIND  PRIOR TO YOU BOOKING. (however strictly no pork, bacon ham, shellfish, prawns etc.)   Email or ring to discuss FIRST !!  Strict no smoking policy. Unless outside in the garden.  We ask you to treat our home as you would your own home.
transit: Unbelievable good access. 10 minute walk max to trams to city or to get to Camberwell Train station. Easy to get to Tennis Centre, shopping Centres, city & local theatres. We also have 2 train lines at Camberwell & 1 line at Tooronga a 20 minute walk.  There are also fabulous bike paths nearby that go to the city & out East.
access: You have the use of the bedroom and a shared open plan family / dining room and courtyard. We do have another double bedroom available which is upstairs with a family sized bathroom for your EXCLUSIVE use just across the hall. This can sleep 1 or 2 people - Price on application or via it's Airbnb listing. NB: THIS ROOM IS AT AN ADDITIONAL COST. In summer you may also use the swimming pool & relax in the courtyard. Free Parking is on the street & we have a parking Permit for you when required. We are ONLY offering the kitchen for breakfast which we provide unless by prior agreement/discussion.  Depending on how long you are staying we are happy to discuss the option of cooking however strictly no pork, bacon ham or shellfish, prawns etc.  Email or RING TO DISCUSS FIRST!! Some guests have requested, a cooked evening meal arrangement, ideal for people staying on business or for longer stays. Happy to discuss. Strict no smoking policy. Unless outside in the garden.
interaction: Over to you. So far we have enjoyed a glass of wine or cup of tea with many of our Airbnb guests & exchanged travel stories. Although we are both extensive travellers & stay in AirBnB overseas, this hosting is newish to us & we look forward to sharing our experiences of where to go, eat & shop locally & in Melbourne.
house_rules: If you are sharing the bedroom and there are two of you then you have the downstairs en-suite bedroom priced as stated. If there are 2 of you and you require 2 separate bedrooms then you will need to book the other bedroom separately. (additional cost).  If there are 3 or 4 of you then add additional guests when you make this booking. THERE ARE STAIRS TO CLIMB ONLY FOR THE UPSTAIRS BEDROOM. Typically the kitchen is unavailable HOWEVER we do provide a continental breakfast and great coffees / tea. We  potentially can make the kitchen available ONLY after we discuss your needs. (however strictly no pork, bacon ham etc. ) EMAIL OR RING PRIOR TO BOOKING TO DISCUSS !!   Strict no smoking policy. Unless outside in the garden. - Kitchen use is ONLY by PRE AGREED arrangement.
host_about:
Former Aucklander living & married for 34 years in Melbourne to a born & bred local Hawthorn girl. We are in our own fashion accessories business together & always seem to be planning a trip somewhere. 

We love checking out the roads less traveled soaking up the culture of other countries along with meeting new people. combine this with good food, wine & laughter & we have our ideal holiday break. 

Hopefully we can bring this to you if you wish during your stay with us.

summary: Our sun-drenched, beachside apartment provides the perfect getaway directly opposite St Kilda Beach. Just 5-min-walk from vibrant cafes, live music, yoga studios, deli's, shopping & public transport - it's the perfect place to chill out & call home.

Each day watch the sunset dip into the ocean from the dining table & balcony or literally walk out the front door, across the road and sit on the sand as the sun dips into the sea. As it's our home, we are normally around in the evenings and weekends, however tend to be out and about during the days. neighborhood_overview: What's not to love about St Kilda? The beach, the sun setting into the ocean every evening, the menagerie of cultures, cuisines and lifestyles intermingled with vibrant eclectic cafes and the CBD just minutes from your doorstep... The St Kilda Botanical Gardens are a gorgeous place to chillax after grabbing a coffee from Kotch Lane (best coffee in St Kilda, after Beaver's Tail which is just around the cnr)... The St Kilda tram line goes direct to Fitzroy which would have the best nightlife and bars in Melbourne - not to mention the food! From cheap eats and hole-in-the-wall diners to a-la-carte... There's always something to eat, see, experience and do...
notes: We prefer non-smokers only.
transit: The CBD, Fitzroy and Airport-Connect tram are literally 5 minutes from the building so getting around is really easy. A lot of vineyard tour buses pick up direct from St Kilda - as do most tour orientated services. Gettting here from the airport is easy - just take the Red Airport Sky Bus to Southern Cross Train Station and then walk out to Spencer St and catch the 96 tram to St Kilda - and get off at the end of the line (it's a 5 min walk from there)... You will need to buy a "Myki" to travel on pubilc transport in Melbourne ($6 per card and then you need to put money onto the card using the same vending machine it in order to use it)
access: You will have access to a private bedroom, shared bathroom, shared balcony, and shared kitchen, dining and lounge areas. Public transport, supermarkets, live theatre, restaurants, live music, bars, yoga studios, farmers markets, vibrant shopping strips, Luna Park, St Kilda Pier and the CBD are all literally on your doorstep - so rain, hail or shine there is always plenty to do. Vineyards are about a 1.5hr drive away, and there are plenty of day tours that collect direct from St Kilda.
interaction: As it's our home, we are normally around in the evenings and weekends, however tend to be out and about during the days. We're both always open for a wine and chat, however are respectful of our guests and happy to give you the space you need.

We're both always open for a wine and chat, however are respectful of our guests and happy to give you the space you need. As this is our home we simply ask that you treat it with respect and leave the areas as you found them. We prefer non-smoking guests only and are happy for small intimate dinner parties but absolutely no smoking or raging parties allowed.
host_about:
Hi there! I'm an easy going, professional Melbournian who loves nothing more than a glass of fine wine, a plate of good food and chilling at the beach after climbing mountains in the rainforest... Having grown up on a dairy farm I am pretty down-to-earth and relaxed about life, loving sun, sand, surf and trees.

For the past 4 years, I have lived by myself and enjoy keeping my home clean and tidy...  I'm into casual dinner parties rather than raging all-nighters and am more likely to have organic sesame snaps than timtams in my fridge :) 

As a guest I will treat your home as if it were my own, water your plants, feed your cat and enjoy a conversation if you're willing to have one... My ideal holiday is lying by the surf with my head in a book, wandering down random laneways and cooking up a storm with my goodies from the market. 

I'm looking for gorgeous tucked away hidden treasures with rambling gardens and mismatched artwork rather than polished overprice 'luxury' houses... Life is what you make of it... and travel is food for the soul... Enjoy your day... and hopefully I get to meet you soon!

neighborhood_overview: I love Melbourne CBD, and the Apartment location in Little Bourke Street has a Walk Score of 99 out of 100. This location is a Walker's Paradise so daily errands / sightseeing do not require a car. Right in the heart of the city and in the legal distict, just a couple of blocks from the hustle and bustle of the middle of the city it is safe and well lit.   But like all areas care needs to be taken when walking at night be aware of your surroundings.
notes: Bookings:   My place is open-plan shared space living, so is generally suited to shorter stays of up to a week. If you'd like to make a booking please have a clear photo and description of yourself on your profile and please make an inquiry and let me know a bit about you before you make a booking. Being right in the heart of a lively city there is the usual city noise, I do have double glazing installed on the windows.   I work in events and go out a couple of nights per week depending on what's on, there is always something happening in Melbourne! I have two cats who live on the property, those who are allergic or afraid of cats should not book with me.  There is no way to lock them out of your 'room'.
transit: FREE CBD Travel in the designated CBD Zone on ALL trams, or you can walk everywhere quite easily.   For trips further afield to St Kilda, Fitzroy, South Yarra I have MYKI cards you can top up and use.
access: • Double Sofa Bed in the lounge room on the first floor, you have the entire floor to yourself • Added comfort of 5cm thick  Soren memory foam Mattress Topper • Pillow Menu  • Your own toilet / powder room upstairs with sink and mirrors • Bedside drawers, and clothes rail for your use  if requested • Electric fan (if required it is a solid double brick building so stays quite temperate)  • Hotel Quality Bed linen and towels provided
interaction: ***Your Host***  • Professional, so I may not necessarily be there during weekday working hours, but I sometimes work from home. • I work on events so sometimes work late or on weekends or go away for the weekend • Friendly, passionate and well traveled, budget traveler have couch surfed for 6 years • Knowledgeable about Melbourne sights, nightlife, arts, theatre and foodie scene   • Is a good cook- you might be lucky enough for me to cook for you one night  • Due to my work commitments check in is at 6pm and check out at 11am.  I can sometimes be flexible but please take this into account when booking.
house_rules: - This is a strictly no smoking apartment and building, you can however smoke freely in the laneway or there is a courtyard at the back of the building. - This is my home, please treat it with respect but make yourself comfortable but also please if using the kitchen clean up after yourself. - I have two feline companions so if you are allergic to cats it is best to perhaps look elsewhere.  The cats reside elsewhere if I am renting the entire apartment.   - Only the guests named and registered in the original reservation are permitted to enter the building. - A second set of keys can be provided to parties of 2 or more. All keys must be returned at check-out; missing keys will result in forfeiture of the security deposit. - In this time of heavy crackdowns, downloading of copyrighted materials is not permitted. - Check-ins before 5 PM and check-outs after 11 AM are not always possible, and subject to the presence of other guests and the hosts' availability. Please inquire before bookin
host_about:
Hello World, I'm sharing my local knowledge with the world... one guest at a time.

I have traveled quite extensively every 2-3 years for usually 3-4 months at a time. The first time I traveled Overseas alone was when I was 16, to the US and Canada.  I lived in the UK for 2 1/2 years and again for 3 months last year and most of my traveling has been backpacking and used other sharing economy websites, staying on couches and letting out my couch.  I used AirBnB during my 3 week trip to New Zealand in 2013 and thought this is perfect for me living right in the heart of the city and working in Tourism and Events I can share my local knowledge with the world... one guest at a time.

I work in Events Management and have worked on such exciting events as the London Olympics 2012, The Commonwealth Games, The Australian Open and the Tim Burton Exhibition Opening at ACMI.

I love horse riding, travel, theatre, comedy shows, live bands and seeing and experiencing what the world has to offer.  I have traveled extensively but I am in love with Melbourne and its many faces.

I am a frugal traveler and love to share my tips and there is a lot to see and do in Melbourne that is free.  I currently work in the Tourism Industry so I know this place pretty well and living in the city well, it give life a completely different flavour, I love it.

Why AirBnB?
Simple as a keen traveler and loving my city I want to share it.  I live in a central location and I have had many friends across the world stay, some whom I have met on my travels, some who became friends after they stayed.

AirBnB will help me stay in my apartment, living in the city can be quite expensive so by utilsing AirBnB I can continue to live in the city I love.

AirBnB has helped me renovate upstairs, removing my carpet and replacing with floorboards.  Installing a custom blind of Melbourne's art centre and skyline, and most recently it contributed to an new kitchen! How awesome is that!

Next goal your stay is contributing to:  Renovating the laundry/powder room.

transit: Located just off Flemington Road, it is a 2 minute stroll to either the Train  (Flemington Bridge station) or the tram (Flemington Bridge Stop - Route 59, Stop 22).  Plenty of on street parking is available. Taxi's are easy to get and cost around $10-$15 to the CBD at night (Taxi 131 008).
access: Guests will have access to whole house. Use of kitchen, the master bedroom is upstairs and features an ensuite and hidden laundry and large private deck. There are 2 downstairs bedrooms, one is next to the bathroom and features a private garden that is beautifully lit at night.The other gets the morning sun and it’s a lovely spot to have a lie in.  PLEASE NOTE RE PARKING. 7 DAYS A WEEK: Unlimited free parking in Manningham St which is a 1 minute walk from house . WEEKDAYS & SAT UNTIL 12.30pm:2 hour free parking in the street directly out the front of the house.  SAT from 12.30pm & ALL DAY SUNDAY : Unlimited free parking in the street directly out the front of the house .
interaction: I am for the most part not around and so you have a key box to let your self in. I am at the end of the phone should you need anything at all.
house_rules: I ask my guests simply appreciate the house and enjoy it as much as I do. I would consider your dog if it doesn't drop hair and is a well behaved indoor dog. Lets have a chat about it before you book.
host_about: From Hopetoun and I love to walk my dog.

host_about:
I have owned two other service businesses since 1998. I started StayCentral with one apartment in 2005, and now manage multiple properties in many different locations in inner Melbourne.

Like many of my guests, I love to travel; both overseas to places like the Mulu Caves in Borneo, ancient cities (in many old countries), Antarctica & Alaska, Torres del Paine, and colourful markets in amazing places like Pha Long in Vietnam, Jaisalmer in India, & La Paz in Bolivia. I also love short domestic trips for weekends away just to relax. It means I get to be on the other side of the counter, and experience how other people look after their guests: and I take their good ideas back with me. 

(My manager, Max, has also travelled from afar to be here by the way, and he can also speak with our guests in Russian and Ukranian).

I even worked as a part-time tourist guide in Melbourne for a couple of years, and really enjoyed the interactions with the tourists off the huge cruise liners that appear in Melbourne each spring and summer. I have tried to extend this experience into my accommodation business here at home, where I really love assisting people with their stays. You only need to read the 800 plus reviews on Airbnb, Trip advisor, Goo gle, and on my own StayCentral website to realise how much our guests enjoy our apartments, and the way we look after them. 

I do love living in Melbourne. It enjoys a unique place in Australia. It is often described as the cultural, business, shopping and sporting capital of the country. The restaurants and cafes in Melbourne are amongst the best in the world. I love living in an urban village amongst these, and all the other everyday shops; and jumping on a tram and avoiding the hassles of traffic. It is a city of great opportunity, experiences, events and lifestyle that can be enjoyed by locals and visitors alike; and I really enjoy facilitating our guests' stays here.

I do hope I have the opportunity to help you get to know Melbourne and grow to love it as I have.

neighborhood_overview: Your Southbank serviced accommodation is so central;  On the Yarra River is the never-ending Southbank Promenade; famous for its world-class restaurants, shops and of course, Crown Casino. In addition, there are multiple food outlets, buskers and arts & crafts events. And the Melbourne Exhibition Centre (better known as Jeff Shed) is just across Clarendon Street, opposite the Casino. Just pass Southern Cross Station you will land yourself in Docklands; an amazing world of it's own. More importantly though, are the Melbourne icons; the Arts Precinct, some of Australia's best shopping all around you, (the Flinders Street shops and laneways, Collins St, Bourke St Mall and Melbourne Central), and some of the best and varied restaurants, cafes and bars in the world.

name: Giant 1 Bedroom Apartment in Magnificent Building
summary: Huge 80m² mezzanine apartment within the heritage Grand Hotel complex. A moment's walk to Southern Cross Station, Crown Casino, Convention Centre and all CBD attractions. Guests have full access to pool, gym, sauna, and courtyard with barbecues. There is a restaurant and bar in the building.
space: The main reason you book this apartment is the size. A typical 2 bedroom modern apartment in Melbourne is 40m². This one bedroom is double that. Huge living space, big bedroom with plenty of space around the king bed, big bathroom, separate kitchen and dining rooms. The living area has 6m high ceilings with full height windows all the way up. The Grand building is one of Melbourne's finest buildings. Built as the offices of the Railway Administration at the height of the boom period in 1893, it was converted into a 5 star hotel and apartment complex in 1996. In a modern apartment the walls are two layers of plasterboard and you can hear your neighbours breathing. In this building the walls are 3ft thick brick. The double glazed windows face north for the afternoon light. Fully airconditioned and heated.

space: This apartment is just 15 minutes walk to the Melbourne Showgrounds and Flemington Racecourse, and 20 minutes to the city by walk and train. It is in a lovely leafy suburb, and the area convenience, amenities and ambience adds to it's appeal. Public transport is a dream. There is a tram and train nearby. Take the 59 or 57 tram from the city (cnr Elizabeth St and Flinders St) and disembark at Stop 26 on Mount Alexander Road. Walk 5 minutes to the apartment.  Or take the train on the Craigieburn line from Southern Cross or Flinders St station in the city and disembark at Newmarket Station. Walk 10 minutes to the apartment. name: Private Cozy Room Funky Fitzroy
summary: I have a beautiful Edwardian house located in vibrant Fitzroy at the top of Napier Street a short 1 minute walk to iconic Gertrude Street. Located between Brunswick and Smith Street, everything you need to enjoy a fabulous stay in Melbourne is right on your doorstep, great cafés, galleries, bars, live music, boutiques, restaurants, book shops as well as outstanding shopping options.  If you want to book the whole house please refer to my other listing.
space: There are two bedrooms in the house the bedroom listed here is fully furnished with a queen sized bed, chest of drawers, built in cupboard and original sash windows.  It's a lovely room really comfortable and cosy. The street is very quiet and with the curtains drawn it’s impossible to know that it’s daylight outside so sleeping in is very easy, after a night out enjoying all Melbourne has to offer! All sheets, blankets and bedding are provided as well as towels. There is even an electric blanket for those cold Melbourne winter nights.  The living area is a beautiful extension at the back of the house with a pitched ceiling and uninterrupted view of the small rear decked garden with a seating area which is perfect to relax in on those fabulous balmy Melbourne nights or to get a little fresh air and listen to the birds in the morning over your cup of coffee and muesli.  The shared bathroom has a bath with a shower over and the water is lovely and hot. The bathroom is well equipped with
description: I have a beautiful Edwardian house located in vibrant Fitzroy at the top of Napier Street a short 1 minute walk to iconic Gertrude Street. Located between Brunswick and Smith Street, everything you need to enjoy a fabulous stay in Melbourne is right on your doorstep, great cafés, galleries, bars, live music, boutiques, restaurants, book shops as well as outstanding shopping options.  If you want to book the whole house please refer to my other listing. There are two bedrooms in the house the bedroom listed here is fully furnished with a queen sized bed, chest of drawers, built in cupboard and original sash windows.  It's a lovely room really comfortable and cosy. The street is very quiet and with the curtains drawn it’s impossible to know that it’s daylight outside so sleeping in is very easy, after a night out enjoying all Melbourne has to offer! All sheets, blankets and bedding are provided as well as towels. There is even an electric blanket for those cold Melbourne winter nights.
neighborhood_overview: Fitzroy has an amazing buzz and there is always something happening so it’s difficult to leave but if you do want to venture further afield virtually everything is a tram ride, cycle or walk away. The Melbourne Museum and IMAX theatre is a short stroll down the road and the CBD is a 10 walk away through the beautiful Carlton Gardens. Victoria markets, Carlton, St Kilda, South Melbourne and pretty much everything else you may want to check out is a short tram ride away.
notes: Two cats live on the property and come and go as they like.  If you are an animal lover they are friendly and will welcome a cuddle.
transit: The #86-tram stop is just a few meters away but you could easily walk into the city in about 10 minutes. There is fantastic public transport (trams every 10 minutes) and Melbourne Olympic Park is a 10 minute walk away so the MCG, Rod Laver and AAMI park are virtually on your doorstep which is perfect for the sports or entertainment fan. Fitzroy has a great outdoor heated swimming pool and tennis courts, gyms and all sorts of other sporting facilities nearby as well as the Australian Catholic University and the Melbourne Hospital Precinct.  It’s really easy to get here, you can catch the sky bus from the airport to Southern Cross station then from there you can catch Tram 86 along Gertrude St or alternatively you can catch an Uber or taxi from the airport and be here in about half an hour depending on the traffic.
access: The listing includes a private room with a Queen sized bed.  There is space to hang clothes as well as drawers available in the room.   The rest of the house is shared including the kitchen, bathroom, lounge/dining and outside areas.   This listing is for a maximum of 2 people, it's not possible for extra guests to be accommodated, if you do need more beds the whole house can be booked.
interaction: I live at the house but I travel a bit so I cannot guarantee that I'll be available personally while you stay.  If I am in town we will likely meet as I stay in the other room.   If I'm around I am happy to interact and socialise as much as guests want and is possible during their stay.
house_rules: No smoking in the house, there is a verandah at the front and garden at the back and you can smoke there although I do ask that you don't throw your cigarette butts in the garden but dispose of them thoughtfully in the bin.  Please be considerate of the cats, it's their home as well and they love guests so just be kind to them.
host_about:
When I'm at home in Melbourne I love to drink coffee and try out all the wonderful food Melbourne has to offer at the vast number of fabulous cafes and restaurants.  There are so many options!  

I also love movies, reading, the theatre and I also take every opportunity available to travel. For now Melbourne is my home but after living overseas for a number of years I still love to get out and see new parts of the world as much as possible. 

I look forward to meeting you soon.

neighborhood_overview: St Kilda is eclectic, vibrant, fun and full of interesting people right on our beautiful bay in Melbourne. In the hot weather you can enjoy the promenade and beaches by the water - a 5 minute walk from the Apartment.     We have Luna Park, great live music venues literally around the corner or down the road from our place.     You can find great food, drink and entertainment every day of the week and I will be super happy to help you maximise your experience of our wonderful Neighbourhood!
notes: Car Parking: Fee for car park is $25.  5 days and over is $7 per day  The car park is suitable for a small or medium sedan- a 4WD won't fit into the space. The clearance is 1.5m for your car.  Also check your car antenna before entering the car park, it may be too high and could scrape. Park your car as forward as it can go or the car above (car stackers) may clip yours if not parked properly. Cleaning Fee: For stays 2 to 3 nights  a cleaning fee of $30 will apply. This will be charged automatically along with the Airbnb fee. For stays 4 nights and over, an extra $30 cleaning will apply.  This can be paid for on arrival, cash.
transit: Getting around     If you're keen to head into the city you can easily jump on the 96 or 16 tram on Acland St and be there in 20 minutes. Coming in from the airport you have Taxi, Skybus + 96 Tram or FAPAS ( booked bus transfer directly to the corner of our road). We're easy to reach with lots of options.     The Melbourne transit system (trams, trains and buses) use the Myki system, have a search on how it all works or I'll explain it all when you arrive.     The Melbourne Bike Share system is a quick 5 minute walk from the apartment and it's pretty great for riding around the bay and into the city.

neighborhood_overview: The Neighbourhood Coburg (like any Inner Northern suburb in Melbourne) is a fantastic place to live and stay, and has really held onto a wonderful multi-cultural vibrancy - in our educated opinion, it's the side to be on!  You only need to read our reviews to see how much our guests love the neighbourhood and it's easy access to the city! Coburg is home to the lightest, fluffiest falafel in all of Australia at one of the many reasonably priced Middle Eastern food shops.  The Post Office Dining Hall/Cafe and Hotel (see pics at end of listing) is stylish, beautiful and just around the corner (a great place to have dinner, listen to some fantastic live music or sit in the awesome leafy beer garden with a pint.  There is a lovely cafe just around the corner called 'True North' which we love and it's quintessentially 'Melbourne'.  The 'Eastern Block' and 'East Timor' are 2 other great cafes nearby. There are new cafes popping up everywhere at the moment! The quirky Woodlands Hotel is also n
notes: One small thing to note is that the back house backs onto the train line and whilst guests don't see this as a problem we want to make sure you're aware that there is some noise as a result. We have slept before in the house and had no issue with this however some may find it distracting!
transit: Public transport is easily accessible from the house. The closest train station is Coburg, which is a 1-2 minute walk away near the shops. The closest tram stop is also a 1-2 minute walk away and located on the corner or Sydney Rd and Reynard (or Munro Street). There are also bus stops nearby.
access: Guests will have access to the front and rear house. The garage area in the rear house is not currently available for guest use. LAUNDRY / Located at rear of front house. Access to large commercial washing machine, portable clothes line with pegs and gas dryer. FOXTEL PLATINUM PACKAGE + CABLE INTERNET Access for both dwellings. PANTRY Stocked with a lot of baking basics for guest use during your stay. Please do not remove pantry items upon vacating the house. Guests will be provided with a pin code for both the FRONT and REAR property entry doors. We supply you with our contact numbers in the event you need to contact us at any time and are available 24/7. We are more than happy to help with any suggestions/information you may need during your stay in Melbourne and also provide lots of booklets/flyers and books which offer up to date and helpful suggestions.
interaction: We live close by, and are always contactable!
house_rules: The Yellow Door has a strict 'No Smoking' policy indoors. Any evidence of smoking indoors will result in the bond being withheld.  Please adhere to the check-in and check-out times as due to the popularity of the house we often have back to back bookings and require enough time to replenish, re-organise and clean the house. Early check-in and late check-outs may be possible depending on the calendar and will incur an additional cost. This house is strictly not to be used as a party house. Please do not book this house if this is your intention. Any evidence of it being used as such will result in immediate termination of the stay and the bond withheld. In staying at The Yellow Door, you agree to keep moderate noise/voice levels at all times, respect the neighbours and refrain from playing loud music at night. Please do not remove any shampoo, conditioner, body wash or hand soap from the property. We prefer to provide a superior product for our guests that creates less wastage, therefor
host_about:
We are an energetic and fun family of 8. Yes that's right - 8! I am a lab scientist and each one of us has an interesting and different profession and passion - whilst different in our work lives you'd struggle to find a more tight-knit and welcoming family! 

There's Sam, Samantha, George, Fred, Rim, Dani, Steph and myself and we are very proud to offer our property as luxurious guest accommodation. 

Between us we have travelled to over 20 countries, experienced many wonderful cultures and stayed in countless accommodation. We are passionate about hosting and providing an excellent level of care and attention. We hope you feel 'at home' at The Yellow Door during your stay!

name: Paradise Location 3BD in Southbank
summary: Our spacious, modern and dynamic 3BD apartment is placed in the heart of Melbourne's Southbank district. It is a quite residential complex, offering pool, gym, and space. Access to city, sports and arts venues, and the best restaurants and bars.
space: The apartment is perfect, everyone says that it feels like a home away from home.  Only minutes from Southgate River Promenade, Crown Casino, the Arts Centre, Botanical Gardens or the CBD, boasting great coffee, amazing breakfast, world class eateries, a river escapade, or the many arts and gardens.  Only 10 minute walk from Melbourne's sporting hub, the MCG, the Australian Open tennis centre, AAMI stadium (home of ARL rugby and A League soccer), and Etihad Stadium.  It is a short drive to the beaches, and the famous, ultra hip, cool strips of Chapel Street (Cool), Acland Street (Hip), Brunswick St (Alternative), and Lygon St (Italian). Tram stop is a minute way. Train: Melbourne's famous and central Flinders street station is across the river, 7 minute walk. Taxi's are always passing by on the main streets. Family first, everything second.

My motto is "Life is not a rehearsal".

Very genuine person, approachable, love having a laugh and always see the good in things.

As a host I go out of my way to ensure a great stay.

name: Innercity pad: the heart of the CBD
summary: Comfortable 1 bedroom apartment for an inner city Melbourne getaway. A close walk to trams, trains, Melbourne City Baths, Queen Vic Market, shopping, State Library, cinemas, galleries, Museum. The price is relatively cheap  as I live here part time.
space: 3 room apartment (separate bedroom, bathroom, kitchen-lounge area) with a double bed on the 9th floor of a modern apartment block on one of the main streets in the  Melbourne CBD. Just to avoid disappointment or confusion; this is NOT a motel room! I can't be clearer about this! ! I live in the apartment for some of the week and head to the country for the rest of the week; some of my belongings are in the apartment. The price, a little below the average for the area, indicates this. If you don't like this then you should pay some more somewhere else and/or get a motel. I am being frank here so as not to mislead or have you disappointed.  I always put clean sheets on the beds and I have fluffy guest towels.  There is often food in the fridge, groceries in the cupboards and clothes in the wardrobe. It has a 'lived in' feel and not a sterile motel feel. The apartment block is primarily student accommodation and has people from all over the world coming to stay and study in Melbourne. Thi

neighborhood_overview: This neighbourhod is right in the centre of the Lygon st restaurant district. Many different cuisines to try. Lots of great shopping in Lygon st too. The flat is a 4 block walk away from the state library (and my favourite coffee shop Mr Tulk) and the place reported to have the best coffee in Melbourne: Seven Seeds. Mmmmmm: delicious!
notes: I have a small selection of bathroom supplies such as soap, shampoo and conditioner, razor and toothbrush if you have lost or forgotten yours! Due to cleaning costs,  I am accepting a minimum of two days for each booking.
transit: The No 1 and No 15 tram routes, as well as many other tramlines run straight outside the door of the building (my flat is on the other side of the building so you get all the convenience with none of the noise). There are several GOGET car share pods within a one block walk and the Melbourne bikeshare set up is just over the other side of the park and is easy to access. (to access these just put GoGet Melbourne and Melbourne bikeshare into your browser for the details)
access: There is free WIFI. There is a shared BBQ area downstairs if you are interested in cooking at home. There is a shared laundry downstairs with washers and dryers available. ($10.00 to wash and dry a load)
interaction: I am not there! Happy to help by phone if there are any questions, though.
house_rules: If you can keep noise levels to a minimum to be courteous to neighbours that would be great. The building is non smoking. There are no pets. Please leave my home as you found it.
host_about:
I was born in the Geelong area and after many years in Alice Springs and Melbourne I have moved back to be a bit closer to the beach. The coast is gorgeous. I try to grow my own produce in my vege garden.  I am proud that I have invested in the house so it runs on solar power; the environment, and treading lightly on the planet where I can, is important to me. 
My work is mainly in Melbourne and travelling around the countryside so I have a flat in the city and spend my time between these two places.
I love the possibilities airbnb offers to make connections and create communities.
I hope that by doing this I am supporting people to be with themselves and each other in ways that help them understand each other better, to build bridges between communities and create more love on the planet.

neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is in close proximity to shops, restaurants and bars in Elsternwick, Brighton, Gardenvale, Glenhuntly, Malvern and Elwood. I'm only 3km from the beach, close to open space and easy to get around on various public transport options.
notes: If you wish to ride a bike, I have a hybrid bike that is available to ride and there are plenty of bike tracks around.
transit: At the end of my street is a tram line that can take you to Kew, City centre, St Kilda beach and Malvern. A block from my house is a bus that takes you to a number of locations including Chadstone shopping centre, Chapel Street, Prahran market, Victoria market and more. Tram route 64 - Melbourne university to Brighton East is just at the end of my street. Tram route 67 from Carnegie to Melbourne University crosses with the no.64 that can take you to Glenhuntly and on to Carnegie.  Sandringham train line is a 10 minute walk - Sandringham via Brighton Beach and into the city.  Bus route 219 takes you from Gardenvale ( a couple of streets away) through the city and on to Sunshine in the West.  Bus route 605 will go from Gardenvale to the city.  Bus route 625 will take you from Elsternwick, past the next street to my house and on past Oakleigh to Chadstone Shopping Centre.  Bus route 630 from Elwood (near St Kilda) via Gardenvale and then on to Ormond and Huntingdale.  There is also a bus

If you want to borrow a bike you can use it to ride to St Kilda, Brighton to view the bathing boxes or even just up to the supermarket.

house_rules: I keep a clean and tidy house in a nice quiet area and ask that my guests respect my house the way that I do. There is no smoking in the house. Also, if you have friends that you meet up with, I would appreciate it if you could meet up with them at a venue rather than at my house. I may have other guests staying as well and value everyone's privacy and security. Thanks
host_about:
Hi

I've been hosting on airbnb for over 4 years now and have held Superhost status since it was introduced. I host several properties and respond to ALL requests and mostly within an hour - unless your request is from another time zone but even then I will respond asap. 

I am an energetic person that loves meeting new people and even if I don't get to meet you, I am always contactable and willing to assist with your enquiry. 

I try to ensure my guests have the experience of a wonderful stay and make their trip to Melbourne (or Yarrawonga) a memorable one. I have travelled extensively myself and know how important it is to obtain information and assistance without too much bother. 

I have lived in Melbourne all my life and like to share my passion with others to make their stay memorable.

I have several types of accommodation available and provide greater discounts for longer stays so please take a look at the pricing options.  I like to provide all the comforts to my guests as I myself would like them provided if I were to stay.  

You will see that there aren't too many reviews on my spaces considering the number of years that I have been hosting but that's due to the fact that many come and stay for longer periods as I provide significant discounts for stays of a month or more. I also have several guests coming back for 3 or more visits.

Melbourne has been voted now the most liveable city in the world - several times over in case you haven't already heard :)

Come and stay and see for yourself.

neighborhood_overview: For our wonderful tourists, I welcome you all.  Be sure to flip your designer handbag so the label is most certainly on display (omg is Joe serious?)  and hit the shopping strips of Toorak and South Yarra, daring to dream at the real estate listings and peeking at the lives of privileged pioneers. (Pffft, who cares, you guys just wanna have fun I'm sure) Marvel at the works of art that are the haute couture window installations on Chapel Street and Toorak Road, though even the most exclusive boutiques struggle to rival the jewels in the window of Burch & Purchese Sweet Studio patisserie. (yep, I do carry on a bit I know) Shopping between meals: European designers and local heroes like Collette Dinnigan will happily make a dent in your wallet and ensure you look the part. Enjoy a terrace breakfast at Two Birds One Stone, the NEW and amazing ZUMBO for a cakes and macarons, for a coffee at Caffé e Cucina, Yum Cha at Ay Oriental Tea House or Lunch at MissChu before the shopping begins. Lon
notes: Cleaning Fee: For stays 2 to 3 nights  a cleaning fee of $30 will apply. This will be charged automatically along with the Airbnb fee. For stays 4 nights and over, an extra $30 cleaning will apply.  This can be paid for on arrival, cash.
transit: The train station is a 2 min walk away, tram stop the same!
access: Access to all facilities- Pool, social common areas. Off limits only if Body Corporate posts new rules or areas are under repair.
interaction: All you have to do is read the reviews!

name: Cozy Apartment in Central Business District
summary: Cozy up in this comfortable apartment. Pull up the orange chair by the bright, bay window and compile an itinerary for around Melbourne from one of the provided maps and visitor guides, or catch up on e-mails at the sleek desk near the bed.
space: LOCATION It’s all about location! Our charming, boutique apartment lies literally a few steps away from cafes, restaurants, shops, theatres, China-Town etc.   You can catch the free city tram network will take you from nearby St Patrick's Cathedral to St Paul's Cathedral, Federation Square, the Melbourne Museum, and Victorian State Library, the new Docklands area and the famous Melbourne Crown Entertainment Complex and Casino... It goes on and on, and a lot of these are within walking distance.  You are also close to the trams in Bourke Street or Spring Street and the underground railway station. St Vincent's Hospital is a 10 minute walk from the apartment so handy if you are visiting relatives or friends in the hospital. Shopping is so close by - just a couple of blocks away there are lots of arcades with interesting and individual shops, department stores, Bourke Street Mall, Melbourne Central Mall, QV Shopping Mall;  the list goes on, as Melbourne is the shopping capital of Australi

Can't live without great coffee - and the occasional glass of red!

name: Brilliant Location in Melbourne CBD
summary: Central, clean and welcoming. Join me in the heart of my favourite city. Just a short walk to many great Melbourne attractions, transport and food, enjoy sharing my bright and spacious apartment with the sole use of a bathroom and private bedroom. I am very flexible with check in & out times but you may need to meet me at my office in the city as I work during the day. Please let me know you check in time when booking and I will do my best to accommodate.
space: This apartment is so close to everything Melbourne has to offer. A five minute walk to Crown Casino, Southbank, the Yarra River, Melbourne Aquarium, just two blocks to Southern Cross Station (where the Airport Bus terminates) and Etihad Stadium, and a short walk or free tram ride to Docklands, (yummy) Degraves St, South Melbourne Market, DFO South Wharf (shopping!), Swanston St, Bourke St Mall (more shopping!), Flinders St Station, Federation Square, ACMI, Melbourne Arts Centre, the MCG, Rod Laver Arena, Hisense Arena and the Melbourne Park tennis centre (home of the Australian Open). Best of all there is a brilliant outlook over Southbank and the Yarra River which is lovely for breakfast in the sun or a drink at night to watch the Crown Casino fire show.

neighborhood_overview: Here, you are in the centre of Melbourne - right in the CBD. There are so many great things to do that are just a short walk away.  Some of my top tips for what to do during your stay are: - Check out South Melbourne Market - it is the cooler (and closer!) cousin to the Queen Victoria Market, hip homewares and tasty food - including the famous South Melbourne Market Dim Sims! - Hang out at cool Southbank bars and restaurants (covering all price ranges) and enjoy the lights over the Yarra River - Get a surprise from the Crown Casino flames every hour in the evening when they burn brightly and tower up into the sky (a great view of these from my balcony) - Go shopping on Bourke St (a short walk away) or find bargains at DFO South Wharf  - Stop by Degraves St for an excellent brunch or perfect coffee - Check out a sporting or music event at the MCG, Rod Laver Arena, Hisense Arena or Etihad Stadium - Be the first to find a cool laneway bar or nightspot that no one else knows about... yet!
notes: Note that occasionally I may have a friend visit (we'll make sure we are quiet if people are sleeping), I will do my best to let you know beforehand and if you have any concerns about this please do talk to me and I can try make accommodations.  If there is anything at all during your stay that is not to your satisfaction please let me know, I would rather help and fix it to make you comfortable than find out after your stay.
transit: My apartment is very close to many tram routes and all CBD trams are now free and within walking distance to the two major train stations Flinders St station and Southern Cross Station.  The apartment is a two block walk from where the airport bus (Skybus) terminates at Southern Cross station.  If you need any help, just ask! I can help you plan a route to get pretty much anywhere in Melbourne. In the carpark beneath the building there are two GoGet cars which can be used for short term rental, you can find out information about how to use and book them on their website (I haven't used GoGet personally, but I hear they can be a good alternative to hiring a car for your whole stay - and you don't have to pay parking!)
access: As I have my own en-suite you will have sole use of the main bathroom which includes laundry facilities and is located right next to the guest bedroom. The bedroom contains very large built in robes with some wire draws and hangers available.  I have high speed Wi-Fi which you are welcome to use and extensive kitchen, laundry facilities and appliances. The balcony offers a great view over Southbank, you are very welcome to use it, just be careful opening the door it is very heavy (double glazed for soundproofing) and I don't want you to hurt yourself.
interaction: Hi, my name is Katie, this apartment is my home and I treat it with great care and hope you will too. I work during weekdays and often go out at night so you will have the space to yourself but I do like to share the living area and kitchen when I am home (you may be lucky and catch me in a cake-baking mood).  I am very happy to offer suggestions on the best ways to experience Melbourne and what it has to offer, I have lived here my whole life and know some great secret places.
house_rules: No smoking or vaping (including on the balcony) or pets please. Please make sure you lock the door from the outside and check it by testing the handle when leaving the apartment. You can wear shoes in the apartment, but if you choose to take them off do not leave them in the hallway as it is a trip hazard when entering or exiting the apartment. Please put them in the bedroom or bathroom.
host_about:
I live in Melbourne and love living in the city and enjoying everything it has to offer, going to markets, brunch spots, cool bars and sporting events.
I am a professional person and work in IT but I travel when ever I can get a break from work, I have been to India, Bali, Tahiti, Thailand, Greece, USA, England, France, Monaco, Italy, Vatican City, Malaysia, Singapore, New Zealand - and I am always looking for suggestions for the next adventure!

name: Beautiful South Yarra Home
summary: South Yarra house on tree lined street. 5 mins walk to all public transport, two train stops away from the city centre, only minutes walk to Chapel St & all South Yarra has to offer. Close to both Fawkner Park & Botanical Gardens.
space: This is a fantastically kept 1960's house, in a private setting with beautiful garden surrounds. The house its self is our house that we live in, if its available to rent, it means we are on holidays!! Yah! So it is fully decked out with everything that you need...without being overly personal.  The house has two bedrooms, we currently have the second set up as our gym, so I haven't included images of the second bedroom. However it is pretty simple with a double bed and inbuilt robes (again pics can be provided to you if needed). If you do require more beds, we have a Eurobed or Queen foam mattress that can be set up in our studio area or our lounge is very deep and long and easily accommodates 1 person. We have everything that you need, in a lovely well thought out space.

neighborhood_overview: It is on a pretty tree lined street, moments walk from Fawkner Park and about 5 mins walk from the Botanical Gardens. Whilst private it is so close to all the action that beautiful South Yarra has to offer, moments away from Toorak Rd and Chaple St you will be surrounded by some of the best food, coffee, and bars that Melbourne has to offer. Not to mention shopping, if Melbourne has one big draw card, it's shopping and South Yarra is one of he most popular and famous places in Australia to get your retail therapy. Our street is a pretty quiet family orientated street, we ask that you be respectful of our neighbours.
notes: ***Our House is available strictly 18 May 2016 - 24 June 2016*** The house comes with a visitors parking permit for on street parking. (please look at street signs) Again this house is older, whilst it is very clean and well looked there are things that go along with and older house. But these will not effect your stay! It has fantastic heating to keep you warm and beautiful windows that let light into all rooms looking onto the garden making it lovely for a winter stay. The house does not have a clothes dryer, however the ducted heating is really good, and we have two clothes airers that we put over the vents that work realy well! Two burners don't work on the stove, but there is still two, so easy to cook.
transit: South Yarra is on of the most accessible suburbs in Melbourne, serviced by buses, trams and trains all moments walk from the front door. We leave our guests myki cards (travel cards) pre loaded with a few dollars to get you started. We also have bikes if you would like we can leave them out for you. If driving South Yarra is located only 2km from the city centre, with the beautiful Melbourne Botanical gardens dividing us.
access: We remove "our stuff" from the house, so you will have access to the clothing cupboards and draws. We provide all linen and towels that are for Airbnb use only, so no need to worry about old looking towels and sheets. The master bedroom has a brand new king size bed, so you will have wonderful sleep in a lovely cozy bed. Any cupboard that we need to leave stuff in will be clearly marked. We also have a shed in the back yard that will be off limits to guests, as will our carport, but neither of these are areas that will effect your stay. Please contact me if you have any questions about this. I am happy to go through and show you pics of the areas that are not usable. Apart from that mi casa su casa. We like our guests to feel at home and invite them to use our stuff. We have good internet along with Netflix and Stan on our smart TV and a PS4 that you are welcome to. We can also provide you with a TV in the master bedroom if you like.  There is a on street car parking pass that will be
interaction: Yes! I am available. Email will be the best way to contact me. There will probably be a time difference but I will do my best to answer all enquiries as promptly as possible. Alternatively my sister in law manages the property whilst we away (she will be there for check in) and she can manage any urgent enquiries you might have. By phone and email. These details will be provided to you on check in.
house_rules: - This is a no smoking house. I don't mind if you smoke outside, but please don't let it go inside the house.  - We ask that you turn the heating off when you are going out, because it is pretty expensive to run.  - Please be respectful of our neighbours - No parties - Please keep the house clean and tidy, on check out have everything put away and all dishes washed. - Please put bins out on bin day (instructions will be provided to you)
host_about:
Hey!
We are Jaime + Dylan

I am an Interior Designer with my own small studio, Dyl has his own business and is a great illustrator and makes and designs furniture.

My favorite thing to do after a long day is have a cup of tea and snuggle with my dog Raph..after the ninja turtle.

We love all food, eating out is always fun but just as happy to get produce and cook up at home.

We are pretty cruisy and when we are away try to immerse ourselves as much as possible into the culture that surrounds us....thats why we like to use this site, give us access to a more local life.

thanks :)

You don’t need to mop and vacuum but please remember to put things back where you found them. - Keep noise down between 10pm and 8am (City Council rule) and be respectful of our neighbours. - If there is a medical emergency, fire or matters requiring police assistance, please contact 000. For other matters, phone Beyond a Room. - It is your responsibility to lock up when you are not home and to turn off the coolers, fans, lights, heaters and TV. Plus, saving the environment makes you cool. - We do not accept responsibility for loss of property. However, if you realise you have left something in the apartment after check-out please phone and we will do our best to have it returned to you.
host_about:
I'm Linton, I own and run a short-stay management company, Beyond a Room, here in Melbourne. If you book with me you'll be communicating with both myself and my team.

I’m an entrepreneur, architecture graduate, photographer, cyclist (NOT the lycra kind), volunteer, adventurer and problem solver.

During my studies I worked at various cafes and architecture offices to save up for shoestring trips around the world. My grandma once told me I had ‘champagne taste but a beer budget’ and it’s a motto I’ve enjoyed applying to different parts of my life to get the more out of less and find enjoyment in the little things.

I love discovering authentic experiences when I travel and I love being able to share the opportunity with others, to live like a local when they travel too.

Some of my most memorable trips have been couch-surfin across Russia while taking the Trans Siberian, living in Helsinki and learning to hand build furniture, riding a vintage steel bicycle through France to race in L’Eroica and buying a car on craigzlist in Los Angeles and driving across the south, east and north coasts to arrive in Vancouver.

My listings are all managed by Beyond a Room. My aim is to give guests a unique and local perspective on the location and share my knowledge and experience of this wonderful city with travellers so that they feel at home. Search Beyond a Room to find out more about how we can help manage your airbnb.

I keep all my calendars up to date so if it’s available in the calendar, you can usually just go ahead and book instantly.

name: Queen Bea - Melbourne
summary: Queen Bea is a beautiful inner-city house located in the heart of Northcote, 6km north of the City of Melbourne. Owned and operated by a children’s book publisher, the house is decorated with original art and furnished with designer furniture. Perfect for families, lovers and business travellers.
space: QUEEN BEA The house is set between High Street and St Georges Road - close to trams, trains and the Merri Creek trail. It is a short walk to great coffee and top quality restaurants. Northcote is Melbourne’s vibrant arts hub and is brimming with galleries, bars, music venues and independent retail stores. The Westgarth cinema is a short tram ride away at the foot of Ruckers Hill, and CERES Environment Park is just across the river. For those who enjoy exercise there is a membership free gym close by, a nearby tennis court for hire and a golf course not far away. We’ll leave some hot tips, but there is plenty to explore and discover on your own. Queen Bea is the perfect place for families, friends, lovers and business travellers visiting Melbourne for both short and long stays. WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW Two bedrooms in total, the house comfortably sleeps four people and can accommodate one more on a foam mattress. name: The Sixth Hole
summary: Set on 3ha of garden and native bush, the Sixth Hole is a self contained, single bedroom, rustic log cabin featuring a huge stone fire place. It has wide verandahs with views of the golf course, bbq pavilion and croquet lawn. It also has a sofa bed.
space: The large stone fireplace makes this a great place in winter to enjoy a glass of wine with someone special, or some friends. In summer the wide verandahs and trees make it a well shaded oasis out of the hot sun. Sally makes olive oil and coconut oil soap, shampoo and body scrubs on the premises. If you would like to see her range of products, just ask. They   can also be purchased from her.

neighborhood_overview: Enjoy the natural setting (wallabys and koalas used to live in this area but now are rarely seen) abundant birdlife occasionally sugar gliders in the area of Langwarrin South, just 45 minutes from  Melbourne CBD, five minutes to shopping centres of Somerville, Langwarrin and Pearcedale and 15 minutes to the seaside thriving metropolis of Frankston. Langwarrin South is at the gateway to the beautiful Mornington Peninsula with its stunning beaches, world-class golf courses, wineries and restaurants.  Fishing and boating activities abound at nearby Tooradin, Warneet, Yaringa Boat Harbour and Hastings all about 15 minutes away. And the Langwarrin Flora and Fauna Reserve, Cruden Farm- the home of the late philanthropist Dame Elisabeth Murdoch- Mulberry Hill the former home of the late artist Sir Daryl Lindsay and Lady Joan Lindsay author of 'Picnic at Hanging Rock', and  the award winning Pearcedale Moonlit Sanctuary is five minutes away.
notes: We have a minimum two-night stay for our cottages.  Also, this is a large property and we are constantly trying to improve it. Sometimes this can mean tradespeople are here when we have guests, however if this is going to happen, we will advise guests in advance and we are happy to reschedule the tradesmen if necessary.  We are a pet friendly property, but if you plan to bring a pet please let us know at the tim of booking.  Also we please not that we charge per person for both adults and children. If the numbers increase the cost will also alter.
transit: Trains run regularly from Melbourne to Frankston. Every 20 minutes in peak hours and approximately hourly until midnight.  Buses run from Frankston to Pearcedale (the 776 buses) which stops at both ends of West Road. However we will usually try and pick you up from Frankston station if we can. This is by prior arrangement obviously. Taxis also operate from Frankston.
access: It is set in country gardens on a property of three hectares with native bush walks, bbq facilities, tennis court, solar-heated swimming pool and three-hole golf course. Ideal for a romantic getaway for two, or a small family group. By booking Kookaburra Cottage as well, The Sixth Hole is also lovely for groups like buck's or hen's weekends, gatherings of friends, or book clubs where you can enjoy the evening sitting around the fire in the log cabin with a glass of wine  and solve the world's problems. Or just enjoy the bird watching. The property is ideal for club getaways, family gatherings, birthday celebrations - the possibilities are endless.  We live on the property in a separate house. The area inside the circle of the driveway is private property.
interaction: We interact as is required. We like to greet guests to show them around (if they wish), provide anything they may need like golf clubs, or tennis racquets and balls,  and answer any questions. Other than that, we like to leave things to the guests. We may be involved in property maintenance and gardening as required, but generally when guests arrive our work ends.
house_rules: While we have always been very relaxed about the use of the property, we have had to stipulate rules due to a couple of unfortunate incidents.  These rules now are: Due respect must be paid to other residents on the property and our neighbours. The property is for the use of the booked in guests only. This means that no visitors may enter the property without prior approval of management.  There is no smoking in the cottages but ashtrays are provided on the picnic tables.  One bed is the sofa in the lounge room of the Sixth Hole that may be used as a double bed. While the property is not fenced on one side, pets are OK by prior arrangement so long as they stay outside the cottages and under the effective control of their owners. Golf can only be played on the golf course. If you are a novice, we can provide plastic golf balls to practice your stroke on. This may be done in front of the cottage. Please don't alter the pool umbrellas unless you know how they work. If in doubt just ask an
host_about: I am a writer and journalist and mother of four young adults. Gary my husband (also a journalist) look after the property, and manage the cottages between a busy life of visiting friends in Melbourne, seeing films and gardening. We love our property and hope you will enjoy it as much as we do.

neighborhood_overview: THE NEIGHBORHOOD  Chapel Street is arguably the best place for visitors to stay in Melbourne, as it's central and renowned for it's great shopping, restaurants, nightlife, entertainment, and more (please be aware it is a lively street and there can be noise on the weekends). Famous for having the best fashion in Australia ranging from local boutique designers to international top brands and quirky brick-a-brack stores like the renowned Chapel Street Bazaar, it's the place to be if you're looking for something unique and special. A long day of shopping or sightseeing can work up quite an appetite so whether you feel like a gourmet dinner at a trendy upscale restaurant or some quick and easy take out Chapel Street has it. There's no shortage of cafes and restaurants to suit all budgets right on our door step, so many to choose from that in five years we've still not tried them all but check out our guidebook for some of our favorites. After dinner there's plenty happening with countless
notes: We absolutely adore our apartment but please remember this is not a hotel and not a brand new penthouse, it is our home and this is reflected in the price, the Cullen Hotel next door has a similar size two bedroom suite for around $1,000 a night.   Check our House Rules before booking - NO PARTIES - by booking our apartment you agree that any violation of our rules will result in the loss of your deposit. YOUR HOSTS We have traveled all over the world and stayed in countless Airbnb properties so understand what each traveler needs is different. Our goal is to provide everything anyone might need or want.  If you have any questions during your stay please don't hesitate call us.
transit: If you do need to leave Chapel Street then getting around couldn't be easier with trams, trains and busses leaving from right outside your door. You can get to Flinders Street Station, Federation Square, or Southern Cross Station (in the CBD) in under 10 minutes or over to St Kilda Beach or the famous Brighton Beach boathouses in less than 15.  All the major sporting events such as the Grand Prix, the Australian Open, Spring Racing Carnival, AFL Football, and other major concerts and events held at the MCG or Etihad Stadium are easily accessible. We live here and sold our car, that's how convenient it is. PUBLIC TRANSPORT You will need to purchase a myki card to access the public transport system, you can buy these at the 7/11 a block from the apartment on Chapel Street (see guide book for exact location). You can top up cards at the  7/11  or at any major train station.   Trams, trains and busses leave from right outside your door and Prahran station is a 3 min walk away on Greville S

interaction: We will probably be away so we'll make other arrangements for a key to be made available if we can't be there in person.

Any parties will result in immediate forfeiture of security deposit and eviction, this has happened before so please save everyone the trouble and don't even try. 2. Quiet hours are between 8pm - 8am, please do not use the balcony or have music on during this time, any complaints from our neighbors will result in the forfeiture of your security deposit.  3. No more than 8 people are permitted in the apartment at any time including visitors.  4. Please be quiet and respectful of neighbors when coming home late at night, see above. 5.
