host_about:
We love bringing everyone together and giving all our guests an experience to last a lifetime.  Our goal is to make a positive impact on the world by connecting with people and encouraging others to do the same. 

Our business "Official Walking Tours" gives entertaining guided tours of famous sights in Los Angeles, New York, Hawaii, Melbourne, and more... we actually have the most popular Airbnb experiences in the whole world. 

We're also Superhosts renting out apartments in Los Angeles, New York, Waikiki, Melbourne, and Perth to countless satisfied guests including famous celebrities and even the founders of Airbnb... with over 3,200 five star reviews we must be doing something right. 

Currently we live between Los Angeles and Melbourne and use Airbnb wherever we travel, we love to explore the world so are constantly on the move.  Some of our favorite places include Barcelona, New York, Hawaii, Amsterdam, and of course LA and Melbourne.

If you have any questions or need assistance please send us a message as we're always happy to help.  Follow us on social media @officialwalkingtours 

We look forward to hearing from you.

Cheers!
Thomas & Jessie

Sorry, the apartment is not suitable for children or babies. The apartment is light filled and has great views to the north over all the Richmond rooftops.  Tastefully furnished & with new plantation shutters mean that it is much nicer than a boring hotel room.

neighborhood_overview: Richmond is one of Melbourne's most popular inner urban suburbs only 3km from the city. Everything is right at your doorstep in Lyndhurst St.  You could just about eat at a different restaurant every night of the year without leaving 3121! For breakfast try Friends of Mine at 506 Swan St or Top paddock at 658 Church St. Maybe try Baby for lunch at 631 Church St and then dinner at Bouzy Rouge at 471 Bridge Rd.  Catch the tram along Church St to get to Chapel St & on to St Kilda and shop till you drop in Bridge Rd. Richmond really does have it all and I am sure you will love it as much as we do.  It is very conveniently located for the tennis or concerts at Rod Laver. I would walk as it is only about 20 mins away or you can catch the 70 tram down Swan St. The Richmond Recreation Centre with its 50 mtr pool is only a 5 minute walk away in Gleadell st or this is Anytime Fitness just around the corner if you are a member.
notes: NA
transit: You are surrounded by convenient public transport. There is the tram in Bridge rd 250 metres away. The tram in Church St is 230 metres and the tram in Swan St or the East Richmond station are both 650 metres away. Getting to the apartment from the airport is very easy. You catch the sky bus to Southern Cross station & from there catch the number 48 or 75 tram which will drop you at the bottom of the street. There are 2 Myki cards in the apartment which you can top up to use on all public transport.
access: There is a kitchen, living room & bedroom with ensuite.  Lyndhurst St is in a quiet pocket of Richmond where it is not hard to park & there is a lock up garage onsite.  The kitchen is well fitted out with all cooking utensils and a microwave, cooktop (no oven) & fridge & includes essentials like salt & pepper & oil etc. We have a coffee plunger & coffee plus a selection of Twinings tea bags & biscuits.   There is a Queen size timber bed (made by my husband) comfortable mattress & all cotton bedding. We provide good quality pillows & a lightweight coverlet for the warmer nights. There is a good sized wardrobe with plenty of coat hangers.  There are towels in the bathroom, shampoo, conditioner & a hairdryer.  There is a 32inch flat screen TV & DVD player with lots of DVD's for you to watch, there are books & magazine and wireless internet included.    The property has a coin operated communal laundry plus a clothes line downstairs and there is an iron and ironing board in the apartment.
interaction: I am only ever a phone call away and I am also in Richmond if you ever need me but everything required for your stay is there for you when you open your keysafe at the front door.
house_rules: Please feel like you are borrowing a friends apartment which means that you can feel very relaxed & enjoy yourselves but are aware of the responsibilities.  The apartment is for quite singles or couples only. The most important thing is to be considerate of the neighbours at all times, particularly with noise at night.  Remember you are not staying in a hotel, so please tidy up, wash your dishes & put the rubbish out before you leave.  A maximum of two guests and sorry no children or babies. Don't forget to leave the Myki cards when you leave. This is a no smoking apartment.
host_about:
I have lived in Melbourne my whole life and think it is one of the greatest cities in the world as we have such fantastic restaurants, shopping and great neighbourhoods to explore.
I have been a host on Airbnb since November 2013 & absolutely love it. My husband & I are semi retired & we split our time between Richmond & the Mornington Peninsula. I started out with one small apartment we owned in Richmond & enjoyed hosting so much that we bought another one. We also rent out our home & the cottage which is on that property at Tyabb on the beautiful Morn Pen.
I love to travel  and usually choose to stay in apartments as I find it more relaxing than staying in a hotel. 
My favourite city in the world is New York!

neighborhood_overview: Middle Park is a suburb of Melbourne, situated between St Kilda and Albert Park and 4 km south of Melbourne's Central Business District.  Located between Port Phillip and Albert Park Lake, which is about halfway across the western side of the Albert Park Reserve (a state park), hence the name "Middle" Park. Middle Park, along with neighbouring Albert Park, contains some of the best preserved terrace house and Victorian architecture in Melbourne and is part of a strict heritage-conservation area. The fine old buildings and development restrictions in the area and new developments are generally sympathetic to the prevailing style, driving up real-estate prices dramatically, in marked contrast with neighbouring St Kilda. Exclusive shopping, coffee shops and restaurants are found in the main shopping street, Armstrong Street.

space: This gorgeous, recently renovated garden studio is self-contained. It is a separate building overlooking the garden, with a private entrance. It has a beautiful Tasmanian oak floor

name: Amazing 5-bedroom Melbourne Mansion
summary: Our huge 400sqm renovated 1887 house is a St Kilda (and Melbourne) surprise. 5 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, 3 living spaces, lush private garden, gourmet kitchen, stroll to Acland St, St Kilda beach, trams to the city. Great for groups, friends and family get-togethers.
space: Welcome to St Kilda and to our unique St Kilda mansion. Our five-bedroom house is truly beautiful and in a stunning location. The house is huge (over 400sqm) and is bright, light and airy with heaps of space for up to 10 people to enjoy. This is one of the best locations in St Kilda. You won't need a car (though we have off-street parking for two cars if you do drive). Acland Street is 2-3 minutes walk and the beach about 1km away, Fitzroy Street and Carlisle Street are an easy walk. The St Kilda Botanic Gardens are at our back door and trams to the city (no.96 and 16) within minutes. The house has everything you will need for a short or long term stay, making it perfect for families, groups, girlfriend getaways and corporate relocations. Naturally, there is WiFi and Netflix. Our guests have loved the house's size, the "wow" factor when entering for the first time and the surprisingly peaceful and luxuriously large rear garden. There is a floor plan in the photos. BEDROOMS & BATHROOMS

summary: Something for everyone - A location central to all the amazing Collingwood cafes, bars and shopping, close to the CBD, MCG and Fitzroy's Brunswick St. Our large, modern unit is very quiet. A relaxing place to return after enjoying vibrant Melbourne. Full kitchen, wifi, car space.
space: A 2 storey modern unit, tastefully furnished and the perfect base for exploring Melbourne. The unit is in a converted warehouse complex of 12 units and is off the street, so very quiet. Suits 2-6 people: 1 queen bed, 2 singles and a double fold out sofa in the open plan living room. The 2nd bedroom with single beds can be made into a single larger king bed on request.  Please note: Both bedrooms are loft/mezzanine style, with the main bedroom having a skylight opening to the kitchen below, and both bedrooms open at the ceiling to the stairwell. Fully equipped kitchen, BBQ, car space, fast wifi, heating, cooling (A/C), laundry with washer and dryer, ironing board and hair dryer. The unit is less than 5 mins walk to Smith St, which is full of restaurants and shopping. One of the most popular eating strips in Melbourne. Tram 86 runs along Smith St and is a short ride to the CBD. Trendy Brunswick St is 10 mins walk. For sports enthusiasts, the MCG is about 20-30 mins walk or you can walk 1

neighborhood_overview: Collingwood is an amazing suburb. Our apartment is a very quiet semi-suburban location, but still only 10 min walk from Smith St and the Tram. In Collingwood you will find lots of great bars, restaurants, galleries and interesting shops. It is only 20-40 mins from the airport and 20 mins via public transport to the city. But we think you really don't need to go beyond Collingwood and Fitzroy to have fantastic time. If you need recommendations on what to do, we have left a guide  in the apartment with some of our favourites, or give us a call and  we might have some fresh recommendations.
notes: Sofa bed linen will be made available for groups of 5 or 6, otherwise we assume it is not required. We are also happy to provide sofa bed linen to groups of 4 or less for an additional fee of $30, just mention this in your booking inquiry, and we can arrange a special offer to include this additional fee.
transit: There are multiple options for public transport - the 86 Tram on Smith St and Buses on  Johnston St  are 5 minutes walk away and will take you to the City in about 20 minutes. The Victoria Park train station is about 10 mins walk, and another 10 mins ride to the city. You are also located right in the fabulous suburb of Collingwood, and you are 10 mins walk from the equally cool Fitzroy.
access: The apartment is all yours and has everything you'll need. Check in is 2pm and check out is 10am, but this is negotiable. After your booking is confirmed, we will send you a detailed message a couple of weeks before your stay with information for your arrival. Unit includes • Free wifi internet • TV  • Books and magazines • Washing machine and dryer  • Iron and ironing board  • Vacuum, mop and cleaning supplies  • Dish rack and tea towels  • Bed linen (beds will be made for you - if you are using the sofa bed, we will leave the linen out for you)  • One towel per person  • Bathmat and hand towels • Hair dryer • Coffee, tea and sugar • Open pantry: lots of food left in the cupboards like oil, condiments, sauces, etc. • Parking is off the street • Unit manual and info on the surrounding area
interaction: All interactions will be done through the Airbnb website. We are also available on the phone at any time.
house_rules: * No pets * No smoking inside * If smoking outside please dispose of butts thoughtfully. * Please only park in the allocated space and don't block other residents driveways/garages. * Please minimise energy consumption by turning off lights, heating and AC when not home. * Lock the doors when not in the apartment. * Please be aware of other people living in the block and limit noise. * If staying longer than a week, we can put you in touch with our cleaner to arrange cleaning during your stay. * No parties * Call us if you have any problems!
host_about: We have had a great time using airbnb in Australia and overseas. Our unit in Collingwood is available for airbnb guests when our family are not staying. It is a great spot to live!

name: Designer 1br in Ripponlea / St Kilda East
summary: Our recently renovated, relaxed designer style apartment in Melbourne's beautiful Ripponlea is 15 minutes from the CBD and walking distance to Melbourne's best cafes, eateries and boutique shopping. Enjoy living the Melbourne lifestyle like a local.
space: The apartment itself has an incredibly is very user friendly, comfortable and relaxed.  The kitchen is set up with anything you may need and staple ingredients are on hand. The living and dining space is open and light, you can sit on the balcony and unwind after a long day touring the city. The bedroom is clean and simple, comfortable mattress with fresh crisp bedlinen and towels for a true hotel feel. The bathroom is equipped with all basic amenities including a large shower and washing machine. Enjoy relaxing on the sofa with tv and wifi at your disposal, cook a meal and wander down to the StKilda foreshore or for a drink at our local 150 metres down the street.

neighborhood_overview: The location is just perfect, surrounded by leafy trees and beautiful parks and gardens - the stunning Ripponlea House and Gardens that makes this suburb famous and is a 5 minute walk away. World top 20 listed Attica restaurant is just 300 metres down the street on Glen Eira Rd!  As well as a handful of great casual cafes and bars, local grocers and food specialty food suppliers a fish shops and other basic amenities.
notes: Maximum 2 adult guests. 1 double bed in guest bedroom. Children and babies can be accommodated in living room or guest bedroom with additional mattress or cot for $30 each per night
transit: The train station is 150metres from our front door and will have you in the city within 14 minutes and Richmond station within 10 minutes. Tram stops along Brighton Rd / St Kilda Rd is just a 3 minute walk away (a major road which takes you straight into the city as you pass vies of the Botanic Gardens and the Shrine of Remembrance)  There is free on street parking and was we are on a quieter end of a major shopping strip it takes no time to hit the road and make tracks to your next destination.
access: Guests will have access to the kitchen and can feel free to use staple ingredients.  Guests can enjoy using our dishwasher, electronic cooktop, oven, washing machine, tv, wifi, heaters and fan. Guests can invite a couple of guests over to visit, but there are to be strictly  - no parties,  - no smoking inside or on the balcony, - no additional guests staying over, - the place should be treated with respect and kept clean as we trust our guests to enjoy it and take care of it
interaction: We look forward to meeting our guests on the day of arrival and talking them through any queries they may have.  If we are not available we will leave a comprehensive instruction list with specific notes to guide you through your arrival and will follow up with a personal meet and greet at a suitable time. Also our friends at Hostmaker are looking after our home while we are away. They're an Airbnb management service team of Londoners who are Airbnb hosts themselves. We trust them to give you a warm welcome! Hostmaker will look after you. If you have any questions about your stay, please get in touch through the Airbnb platform.
house_rules: No smoking inside or in the balcony, at all.  No events or parties.  The guest bedroom to be used only, our master bedroom will be closed and we appreciate that it remain untouched.  We expect guests to treat our place like it is their own. Enjoy the comforts and benefits provided, and leave the place in the condition in which you found it.
host_about: Madeline & Jake - Young working professionals from Melbourne, Australia. Currently living & working in London, and travelling Europe whenever we get the chance. We love eating out with friends, cooking dinner parties, exploring new neighbourhoods, new & old art and design.

space: We have two large bedrooms with Queen beds and two bathrooms upstairs.  A third bedroom is set up as a study but has a single futon if you have an extra guest. Its a perfect place for two couples!!

neighborhood_overview: St Kilda is a complex and interesting neighborhood with a rich history and plenty to see and experience. The local food, art, architecture and all wonderfully diverse and original. And of course the beach is only a stones throw away, as is the historic kiosk and pier and the famous Sea (website hidden) Kilda is home to some of Melbourne's best shopping and favourite restaurants, bars and cafes, including: The George, Cicciolina, Tolarno's, Lau's Family Kitchen, Chinta, Circa @ The Prince, Mirka – Tolarno , Cafe  and bar Di Stasio, Newmarket Hotel, Mr Wolf and Dr Jekyll, Phamish, iLforniao, Woodfrog bakery. There are notable boutiques too offering original designs and an array of vintage, recycled clothes, home ware stores and bookshops are also located in St.Kilda.  Kite-Surfing on the bay and rollerblading, new skate park, Albert Park Lake and Melbourne Sports and Aquatic Centre are all close-by. Or bikes are available to ride or jog along the beautiful foreshore. There are extensive
notes: There is no lift situated in the building but the stairs aren't bad and the climb is worth it! Also there is to be NO smoking in the apartment at any time, inside or out. If you want to smoke, please do so downstairs in the car park.
transit: Located just 6km from Melbourne's CBD, St Kilda is a beautiful bay-side suburb with something for everyone. It is a walkers paradise, the public transport is also excellent and for you the tram and light-rail are just a minutes walk. With the beach being across the road, it's a great to be able to walk along the beautiful promenade to sample the fantastic food and admire the stunning sunsets. The apartment provides a quiet and spacious oasis, for both fun and relaxation. It is truly worth every penny to experience this amazing property in this first class location. Come and see for yourself.
access: The entire apartment is available with a car park. We can make some space available for guests to store their clothes etc
interaction: We will often be available for guests, this will depend upon the timing and guests wishes.
house_rules: Feel free to use basic provisions from the kitchen and bathroom. Please replace anything you use in large amounts. Please bring your own alcohol.  Our Cat, Lucy, is a quirky and lovable Burmese, if you are prepared for her to stay in the apartment with you and feed her and provide her with fresh water etc we offer you a $20 per day discount. She is easy to care for and loves a cuddle, she requires minimal effort.  We expect you to treat our home with care and respect.  We cannot allow pets.  No smoking please. No parties, No functions. Please relax and enjoy yourselves.
host_about: I love living in St Kilda, it reflects all that I am, a complex mixture of  contradictions in all things including; lifestyle choices, food, culture, spirituality and list goes on. Travel is one of the main things I love, as is being with close friends and family. Being an introvert, a secure and beautiful home base is a key to maintaining my sanity. I have travelled with my partner and sometimes with my teenage daughter, we love adventure- 2am on the NYC subway is not daunting. My work with autistic adults has taught me much about acceptance and respect. I am always learning and expanding my views on the world. Lucy (our cat) is a funny and interesting addition to my life and hopefully to yours too. I feel so blessed to live here.

Mature woman, friendly and outgoing, 
Well travelled.  Previously worked in welfare now enjoying being active without going out to work.
Interested in community, Probus member.
Hobbies include reading and travel.  
Enjoy apartment living and love all aspects of being close to everything, including eating out, activities, water views and new friendships.

Just around one corner is the bistro life of Carlton and The Melbourne Museum and the the University of Melbourne, and around the other are the Exhibition Gardens, the Central Business District, Chinatown, theatres and night life etc. The recent renovations and major building works at Medley Hall includes a lift to help shift between the fully renovated three levels of bedrooms (some doubles), a tv lounge room adjoined to a fully functional kitchen allowing you to cook your own food if you wish, and a modern and beautiful three story high glass atrium. The atrium ties the new with the old, a magnificent Victorian Italianate

name: Quiet room in the heart of Elwood
summary: Stay at this modern, light-filled room with polished floorboards, fully equipped kitchen, central bathroom, lounge/dining in Melbourne's popular inner-city suburb, leafy tree-lined streets in close proximity to St Kilda and the beach.
space: Welcome to Elwood! Enjoy your stay in this clean, quiet and modern furnished apartment. Your room offers a very comfortable queen sized bed, a desk, plenty of storage space and boosts lots of natural light. The apartment is located on the second floor (no lift) in a small block of only 7 apartments. Your room overlooks a backyard, away from any street noise, guarantying a good night's sleep. The kitchen is very functional and offers modern appliances incl. dishwasher.  This is the perfect place to stay and to explore the beauty of Melbourne's popular inner-bayside suburbs like St Kilda and Albert Park. Walk along the tree-lined streets to Elwood beach, St Kilda Botanical Gardens and Acland street, well known for great restaurants, bars and nightlife.

notes: Travelling from Melbourne airport has just become easier; Skybus is now operating between the airport and St Kilda. If my work commitments allow for time,  I'm happy to pick you up from Stop 2 (Carlisle St).  There is free on-street car parking available. Please note max 2 guests per booking. $25 p/night applies for additional guest (max 4 nights) A $25 cleaning fee applies for each booking.
transit: The nearest tram stop is only  a 5 minute walk away. Tram 67 goes along St Kilda Road and offers convenient access to Albert Park.  Ripponlea train station (Sandringham Line) is a 10 minutes walk away. It takes only 15 minutes to get to Melbourne CBD and provides easy access to Chapel Street, South Yarra and Richmond. A Myki card is available for you to use during your stay.
access: Lounge, kitchen and bathroom are shared areas. Both, bathroom and kitchen are provided with shelf and cupboard space to store your belongings/food. There is plenty of cups, cutlery, storage containers that you are welcome to use and a washing machine to do your laundry. Bath, Face and Beach Towels, linen, extra blanket are all provided as well as a hairdryer.
interaction: I'm happy to hear about your travels and will try to answer any questions you may have about the neighbourhood and getting around in Melbourne; at the same time I respect your privacy. My work as Personal Assistant and part-time Personal Trainer keeps me busy and out and about. When home you will see me in the kitchen preparing healthy meals or working online.
house_rules: No smoking inside, no pets, treat the place like your own. For long term stays (2weeks+) $35.00 p/week cleaning charge may applies.
host_about: Born and bred in northern Germany, I'm lucky calling Australia home. I enjoy living and working in beautiful Elwood, as much I like travelling, cooking, fitness and spending time with friends.  Hosting and meeting people via Airbnb has been a great experience. I look forward to welcome you at my place, whilst exploring or working in Melbourne.

name: Signal Box Short Stay
summary: Signal Box short stay is  a newly built comfortable space for couples. Two rooms are available with ensuites.  Great views are enjoyed from the bedroom  with either mountains and farmland or a private garden view. The Puffing Billy Train track passes Signal Box. Gembrook station is just 500 m walk, as are restaurants and coffee shops. The National Trail is 10m from the Signal Box. This allows shorter or longer walks or bike rides. Perfect single night stay for wedding or special event.
space: Signal Box has a spacious upstairs bedroom with Queen bed, ensuite and balcony. Downstairs is a large modern kitchen, dining and lounge with both gas and wood fire heating. An optional extra is the heated  indoor lap lane pool. Signal Box overlooks mountain views and farm lands. It is adjacent to the Puffing Billy train line and you can see the train from the property. Guests can expect Rest, Relaxation and Revival from this unique apartment. It has double glazed windows, rammed earth walls and an exposed quartz polished floor. While the apartment has modern appliances, guests may wish to eat at nearby restaurants; Forest Edge, Jinks Creek winery, Elevations, The General Food Store or Woodstock. These are all no more than 20 minutes drive. You can catch the Puffing Billy train from Belgrave. There is a frequent bus service to Belgrave train station. If you wish to be collected from the bus or Puffing Billy- just ask. Signal Box Retreat allows you to REST, RELAX, REVIVE.

neighborhood_overview: People love the Puffing Billy train; the views over mountains and fields; they love the big trees and the fresh air. Gembrook is just an hour out of the city so people love to experience the country so close to where they may live. The walking trail between Emerald Lake and Gembrook is suitable for bikes or walking. It is 10 m to walking trail from Signal Box. Walk or catch a bus one way and come back on the steam train.
notes: Signal Box is a unique building. Its designed on sustainability principles and people feel rested after experiencing the earth walled ambiance.
transit: Buses leave for Belgrave Station every half hour. Mainly people travel by car so they can visit other towns and wineries in the area. It is possible to come on the Puffing Billy train and Cherie will collect you from the station. It's a 400m walk.
access: Landscaped garden is for guest enjoyment; Puffing Billy station is 800 metres away. THe National Walking trail may be used by walkers and pushbikes. It is wheel chair friendly. The trail goes into Gembrook centre (400m) and to Cockatoo (6kms) and Emerald (14 kms)
interaction: Meet and Greet and sign in is required on receipt of the key. The Owner lives in a separately locking part of the house.
house_rules: Noise policy is strict; respect host, other guests and neighbours. Strictly no wedding party preparations. Guest couples only. Respect the property. It is an all new premises and planned for your enjoyment.
host_about: With a passion for sustainable building Signal Box Short Stay was constructed with a view to allowing others to experience the ambiance of earth. The building and the local area have much to offer in rest and recreation. There's walks in nearby forests; great wine making; restaurants and cafes. For me Gembrook is a gem!

name: Arty Flat on the Merri Creek
summary: An inner city flat in a bushland sanctuary is your perfect retreat. This arty apartment is surrounded by parklands and set directly on a bike/walking path overlooking the Merri creek. Cyclists & walkers will  love it. This cosy flat offers a treetop outlook over Merri Creek and park opposite. Perfect writers workplace. You are guaranteed a peaceful nights sleep as it tucked away from the traffic and surrounded by trees and birdsong!
space: Set in a mid-20th-century block this elevated ground-floor apartment has polished concrete floors, and a galley kitchen with microwave, fridge & stainless steel appliances. Also a cute coffee machine to make your own lattes or teas, and a condiments pantry available for your use in the kitchen.  Guests will enjoy the comfortable furnishings as well as, books to read, music to listen too and DVD's to watch. The TV has an in-built DVD player. My flat is pet-friendly for indoor cats and small dogs. If you are bringing a pet, tell me so I can further advise of the balcony and surrounds. Smoking is also allowed on the balcony. The flat is set away from the street so you will hear no traffic noise. It is in a communal block so neighbors can be heard at times.  The bedroom has a super comfy queen-sized bed giving a great night's sleep. Towels and linens are provided with the bed made ready for your stay. neighborhood_overview: The flat is nestled in the green belt of the Merri Creek yet close to the city the buzz of Brunswick! You are close to great bars and eateries on Lygon streets and even more on Sydney Road. Please see my guidebook for local recommendations.
notes: If the stay is over a week guests are welcome to changeover sheets and towels. You will be left extra sets for you to change over. Longer stays of over two weeks to a month will include a mid-stay house clean. If you have any special requests or questions do ask me.
transit: The flat is a short walk to the 96 tram on Nicholson Street - which takes you through North Carlton, North Fitzroy, Fitzroy, past the Melbourne Museum and onto Spring then Bourke streets and will take you all the way to St Kilda.  Or further along walk to Lygon Street for the no.1 and 8 trams which take you along Lygon street to Carlton, Melbourne Uni and the city.  Closest train station is Northcote off Arthurton Road about a 15 minute walk also. If you ride or walk along along the bike path you can have a great day out travelling around Melbourne's inner north, with the Abbotsford Convent well worth a visit about 20kms away. East Brunswick and North Fitzroy boast a variety of cafes and restaurants. There are recommendations of food places and shopping here in the listing and in the House Manual.
access: Guests have access to a car space on the block and parking is also easy in the street. You are a quick drive to Sydney Road cafes, shops and surrounds. Buses run from Blyth street and along Albion street to Essendon & Highpoint shopping centres and connect with the Upfield or Hurstbridge train lines. The shops and trams #96 to City via Bourke street and St Kilda travels along Nicholson Street and the #8 & #1 trams to South Yarra via the City travel along nearby Lygon street, are a 10 minute walk away. You are on the doorstep of the Merri Creek bike path and surrounding parklands which will take you to Coburg going north or North Fitzroy, Clifton Hill, Abbotsford, Collingwood travelling south, along the Capital City Trail. If you don't wish to move far you can wander up the bike path and have a bite at Ceres or buy produce from their market. Great cafès are up at the nearby corner of Blyth and Nicholson streets too.
interaction: I am often there to meet you, check you in and hand-over keys.  If I am away I have a concierge or if you need a late check-in I will give you key collect details. I am also available by phone and other messenger apps, contactable during your stay for any concerns or queries. Otherwise my concierge will be able to help you out. There is a House Manual re how to use things such as the TV/DVD includes a list of worthwhile places to eat and drink and local places of interest.
house_rules: Please note: you will be responsible for breakages, damage or theft of items and the deposit will be claimed against. Sadly I have endured a few really bad guests most recently hence this note.  You are staying in a dwelling where there are personal items/objects in this flat so please - treat the flat as you would your own home. Please understand using the coffee machine BEFORE use and the TV/DVD. You will be staying in a flat that is lived in so please take care of the personal effects. A house manual will be sent to you for further details on the flat/how things work etc. Please enjoy the flat and balcony but please limit noise for the other tenants. You can smoke on the balcony using the ashtray outside.  Please lock up the apartment (balcony locked window and both entry doors) and turn the heating off when you leave/exit.  But most importantly please have a good restful visit!  I hope you will enjoy your stay and many thanks for your booking. : )
host_about:
Melbourne-born creative who travels quite a bit for work and pleasure.
I've always lived in the inner city and love the lifestyle. I work in the arts/creative industries and so I know alot about what's going on in Melbourne!  I love entertaining and meeting new people. A confirmed coffee & art addict, bike rider, & avid 3RRR listener :)

name: Beautiful Artists home, Fitzroy
summary: This cottage nestled behind our shopfront art studio in the electric heart of Fitzroy, is a peaceful oasis which will delight lovers of Art, Books and Music.  It is a doormat away from cultural and hedonistic delights, and a short walk to the CBD.
space: For a truly unique experience of Melbourne and its cultural life, this Victorian Cottage in central Fitzroy is ideal.  It is nestled behind an art studio & puppet theatre and surrounded by eclectic cafes, bars, shops and galleries.   The living room is cozy,  with an open fireplace, unlimited Wifi connection, record player, gramophone, and a DVD player. The kitchen is fully equipped and stocked with herbs, spices, legumes and condiments for people who love to cook, although Fitzroy is home so many wonderful and reasonably priced restaurants that you might not feel like cooking. neighborhood_overview: Fitzroy is the bohemian heart of Melbourne replete with options to colour your time in Melbourne.  With Gertrude, Brunswick and Smith streets on our doorstep, you will be able to explore the many speciality boutiques, book and record shops and vibrant cafes,  bars and eateries which make this zone so desirable.      Within a couple minutes walk, you can choose between many options to hear live music, catch an opening at a local gallery or artist run space, lay down in a park with a picnic (please ask for rug and picnic basket) or give the possums a night-time feed (fruit only).       There is a sociable community swimming pool, many gyms and yoga studios, a public library, tennis courts, playgrounds and various supermarkets also within a couple of minutes walk.       Within a 10 minute walk you can immerse yourself in Melbourne's theatre scene at La Mama or La Mama Courthouse, or enjoy arthouse films at Cinema Nova.
notes: NA
transit: The number 11 (West Preston/St Kilda) tram is literally on our doorstep, and our home is within 2 minutes walk of tram routes: 86, 96 and 109.  The Central Business District is a short walk away.
access: Guests are expected to make themselves at home in the whole house excluding the other bedrooms.   They are welcome to play records but we ask that they return them to their sleeves after use.  Books may be borrowed after asking permission, but please do not take them out of our house, and return them to the same spot from where you borrowed them.
interaction: We let our guests dictate their level of interaction.  They are free to come and go when they please and are encouraged to help themselves to breakfast in their own time and use the kitchen to cook their own meals if necessary.  If a guest should feel like a chat or need any helpful hints about how to organise their time in Melbourne or where to seek out specialist interests, we are available to help.
house_rules: Guests are expected to wash cooking  and eating utensils after their use.  If you use the BBQ, please do likewise.  Please smoke outside.
host_about: We are a family of four, from Australia and Argentina.  We are both visual artists and together run a studio shop front which in addition to visual art encompasses pre cinema, puppetry and theatre.  We have two sons, one two year old and another 6 month old.  We have travelled and lived abroad  for many years and so are sensitive to the needs of travellers and happy to help in any way we can.  At home we usually speak Spanish but can easily switch to English should your language be English.

I am always there to check my guest in and give them a brief tour.  I have both a house manual and many guidebooks, maps and flyers of things to do during your stay in Melbourne.
house_rules: - This is a strictly no smoking apartment and building, you can however smoke freely in the laneway or there is a courtyard at the back of the building. - This is my home, please treat it with respect but make yourself comfortable but also please if using the kitchen clean up after yourself. - Only the guests named and registered in the original reservation are permitted to enter the building. - A second set of keys can be provided upon request. All keys must be returned at check-out; missing keys will result in forfeiture of the security deposit. - In this time of heavy crackdowns, downloading of copyrighted materials is not permitted. - Check-ins before 5 PM and check-outs after 11 AM are not always possible, and subject to the presence of other guests and the hosts' availability. Please inquire before booking if you need special accommodations in this regard. - I will request to view your passport or drivers licence when you check in.  - No parties and please be respectful of my nei
host_about:
Hello World, I'm sharing my local knowledge with the world... one guest at a time.

I have traveled quite extensively every 2-3 years for usually 3-4 months at a time. The first time I traveled Overseas alone was when I was 16, to the US and Canada.  I lived in the UK for 2 1/2 years and again for 3 months last year and most of my traveling has been backpacking and used other sharing economy websites, staying on couches and letting out my couch.  I used AirBnB during my 3 week trip to New Zealand in 2013 and thought this is perfect for me living right in the heart of the city and working in Tourism and Events I can share my local knowledge with the world... one guest at a time.

I work in Events Management and have worked on such exciting events as the London Olympics 2012, The Commonwealth Games, The Australian Open and the Tim Burton Exhibition Opening at ACMI.

I love horse riding, travel, theatre, comedy shows, live bands and seeing and experiencing what the world has to offer.  I have traveled extensively but I am in love with Melbourne and its many faces.

I am a frugal traveler and love to share my tips and there is a lot to see and do in Melbourne that is free.  I currently work in the Tourism Industry so I know this place pretty well and living in the city well, it give life a completely different flavour, I love it.

Why AirBnB?
Simple as a keen traveler and loving my city I want to share it.  I live in a central location and I have had many friends across the world stay, some whom I have met on my travels, some who became friends after they stayed.

AirBnB will help me stay in my apartment, living in the city can be quite expensive so by utilsing AirBnB I can continue to live in the city I love.

AirBnB has helped me renovate upstairs, removing my carpet and replacing with floorboards.  Installing a custom blind of Melbourne's art centre and skyline, and most recently it contributed to an new kitchen! How awesome is that!

Next goal your stay is contributing to:  Renovating the laundry/powder room.

neighborhood_overview: What's South Yarra like? Who wouldn't love staying in the center of Melbourne's best shopping, best restaurants, best night life and entertainment. From here you can walk to some of Melbourne's finest spots, the Yarra River, the Botanical Gardens, Fed Square,the city, Southbank and more. Dine on street, people watch, enjoy fashion, glamour and style all day, every day, all year round. Shopping’s the name of the game in South Yarra, where Chapel Street reigns supreme. The fashion strip contains all manner of high-end designer boutiques, chain-stores, hipster hang-outs, cinemas and gift shops. There’s also a seemingly unlimited array of cafes and restaurants to help revive weary shoppers by day, and bars and clubs to keep the buzz going at night. Naturally then, South Yarra attracts the young, hip and fashion conscious, at least on its main strip and the streets immediately surrounding. The residents are a mix of young professionals, families and empty nesters – all attracted to this sal

name: Beautiful apartment sweeping views
summary: Contemporary one bedroom apartment with magnificent views.  Quiet and secure within 10 minutes of the city, walking distant to local villages and Melbourne's best breakfasts.  Lie in a luxurious bed, watch the sunrise and enjoy stylish urban charm.
space: The apartment offers spectcular views across North Fitzroy to the Dandenong ranges.  It is modern, offering all the facilities for preparing meals and enjoying a quiet drink among friends.  Facilities include a Samsung LCD Smart TV, free telephone calls within Australia and free WiFi access.  There is a reverse cycle air-conditioning so that guests can enjoy the apartment no matter what the temperatures is on the outside as well as a washing machine and dishwasher. Another feature of the apartment is a piano which can be enjoyed by guests.

neighborhood_overview: North Fitzroy offers the visitor a wonderful experience as it serves great coffee, is within walking distance of the best cafes for breakfast in Melbourne (Pope Joan, St Ali, Hammer & Tong) for breakfast as well as neighbourhood wine bars and offers the guest a chance to explore multiple neighbourhoods with their own unique restaurants and shops.  It is also close to the beautiful Edinburgh Gardens and a short walk to Merri Creek and onto the Yarra River.  Getting to the MCG is easy via the No 112 Tram along St Georges Road followed by a nice walk through the Fitzroy Gardens. Etihad Stadium is a door to door experience as its located along the No 96 Tram route. The combination of an inner city neighbourhood with multiple amenities, proximity to open green spaces and a view that makes you feel a part of this great city, provides the guest with a memorable experience.
notes: NA
transit: Underground car parking is available free to guests of the apartment.  The No 96 tram runs along Nicholson Street and then along Bourke Street in the city and onto St Kilda Beach and  a stop is within 2 mins walk.  Alternatively the No. 86 tram runs along nearby St Georges Road /Brunswick Street which is a 5 minute walk away.
access: Guests have full use of the apartment.  Access to the apartment is restricted to guests through the use of a swab key which makes it a very safe environment.  There is also a communal BBQ for guests wanting to meet some of the locals.
interaction: All guests will be met upon arrival.  A key will be provided along with any advice required to make sure guests settle in and understand the facilities and what the neighbourhood has to offer.
house_rules: No smoking is permitted in the apartment. All rubbish is to be properly bagged and removed in the garbage chute which is located opposite the lifts on the 6th floor or in the recycling areas located in the basement carpark. The room is to be left tidy and clean. Guests must abide by all apartment complex rules, particularly keeping noise to a minimum after 10 pm.
host_about: I am an urban planner so I love exploring cities to understand what makes them unique. I also like to write creative fiction in my spare time which keeps me dreaming of other worlds.  You will be staying in my lovely home whilst I am living in the countryside so I hope that you enjoy the things I have collected on my travels over the years.   As I am a regular visitor to Melbourne I will be available to assist you with anything you may need.

neighborhood_overview: Richmond is a super-convenient suburb as it offers all the facilities you need, PLUS it is close to town and public transport.
notes: The kitchen has everything you will need or there are cafes and restaurants nearby if you prefer not to cook. Our house has aircon in each room as well as heating.  Every bedroom has extra linen and quilts should you need them.
transit: Trams are available on Swan st and Bridge road. Route maps are in the house.  Trams take about 20 min to get to the city. Myki cards - stored value tickets for all buses, trams, and trains - are sold at 7 -Eleven shops on Church st and Bridge rd.  Trains stop at Burnley station, and East Richmond. The busiest station is Richmond - see the guidebook.
access: Guests have use of all house facilities.  We have a wide hallway which pram-owners may find useful! Free Wi Fi! In terms of food, you can use any supplies you find in the cupboards or fridge.  We have supplied as many kitchen utensils we felt would be used but I am interested in any feedback on any thing that is missing, or any kitchen appliance you feel I should consider making available as well. There are a number of books in the house and other tourist leaflets. Feel free to use and read these and afterwards please leave the books in the house for the next guest. Our back terrace is lovely in winter or summer and our bbq is always clean with supplied with gas.
interaction: Interaction with guests depends on our work programme. However we would always try to be available to welcome guests, and to answer any questions or provide advice and information during the stay.
house_rules: This house is located in a quiet residential street, and as such is not suitable for large or noisy social gatherings - Parties are not permitted. Smoking and pets are also not permitted.   We welcome any calls to us if there are any issues during the stay.  Please let me know if there are any breakages, or something does not work, or you need extra linen. We can also arrange for a cleaning service during your stay if you require - at the same rate ($100). Please separate your rubbish. The bin under the sink is for general rubbish and the silver rubbish bin is for recyclables. Rubbish bins are located on the front veranda - yellow lid for recyclables, green for general waste.
host_about:
Hi 
I'm Julia. My partner and I live in Richmond with our daughter who attends a local school in Richmond. We live in Richmond and even support Richmond Football Club!

I work for a not-for-profit involved in raising funds for mental illness medical research.

I've travelled lots and lots and I love it. Some of my best trips were when I stayed in people's houses- they are just so much easier than hostels, backpackers, and hotels.

We love Richmond and all the local facilities, and we are very happy to share this with our guests.

name: Parking, privacy, comfort and warm welcome
summary: Our quiet upstairs guest room is a comfortable place to relax, a short walk to many great parks, cafes, restaurants and music venues. Park your car safely in front and use public transport or walk around the neighbourhood. The Yarra River bike paths are nearby and it's very quick to get to the city by train or bus. We provide tea and coffee making facilities in your room as well as in our kitchen but we don't allow cooking.
space: Our two storey, three bedroom townhouse is a comfortable place to relax with easy bus or train options to the city. The upstairs guest bedroom has a queen sized bed, plenty of wardrobe space and adjacent large private bathroom . The courtyard is a relaxing place to kick back with a coffee and a book. The street is quiet but the train is a 5 minute walk and a bus to the city passes the end of the street.  Ours is the perfect place to be close to the CBD, Northcote, Fairfield, Carlton and Fitzroy but far enough away to be able to really chill out and enjoy some space.  Station St Fairfield, a short walk away has many cafes and numerous restaurants including Greek, Vietnamese, Indian, Japanese and Thai.  Cyclists can choose many directions to take bike paths all over the city. We are happy to provide suggestions for cycling and resources to help plan your ride.

transit: Its a short walk to the train station and then a fifteen minute trip into the city. There is also a bus stop around the corner where you can catch a bus to either the city or across town.
access: Your bedroom is adjacent to the large upstairs bathroom which will be yours only. We are happy for you to share our living and dining room (if you have ready made meals you can eat them using our crockery etc but we don't allow cooking or eating in your bedroom).  You can park your car safely in the street.
interaction: We like to get to know our guests but assure them of respectful privacy, as we assume from them. All of our guests come and go with their own key at whatever hours suit their individual schedules and this works for us.
house_rules: Guests should be non-smokers both in our home and beyond. The kitchen is not available for cooking.
host_about:
My husband Allan and myself love to travel and meet locals when we do. In the last few years we have spent some months exploring Europe and Asia, as well as some fantastic road trips within Australia in our campervan. 
We love to share what we like about our neighbourhood and are passionate about the joys of living in Melbourne. 
We like it when prospective guests have a profile that tells us a little about themselves and in their booking enquiry, something about their stay. This helps us to  better anticipate our guests' needs and  prepare for them.
We enjoy cycling, kayaking, bush walking, theatre, cinema, cooking, reading and gardening.

neighborhood_overview: Brunswick is well known for its many events and attractions including the Brunswick Music Festival, Sydney Road Street party, Melbourne Zoo, multi-cultural cuisine, Brunswick market and the community environment park. Traditionally a working class area noted for it's large Italian and Greek communities and long a stronghold of left-wing politics in Melbourne, Brunswick is currently known for it's local bohemian culture, strong arts community and large student population, owing to it's proximity to the University of Melbourne and RMIT University, the latter of which's Brunswick campus is located within the suburb. Brunswick takes its name from George IV and the city of Brunswick, Germany. It is bordered to the south by the suburbs of Princes Hill and Parkville, to the east by Brunswick East, to to the north by Coburg and to the west by Brunswick West. Brunswick's main thoroughfare and commercial strip is Sydney Road, which runs north-south as the continuation of Royal Parade and which s
notes: Guests will be asked to acknowledge acceptance of StayCentral Terms & Conditions and House rules and may be asked to provide photo ID prior to, or on arrival. Pets are allowed in many of our apartments, as long as they are quiet, and do not damage or climb on the furnishings.
transit: Trams are just out the front, run every 6 minutes, and only take 10 mins to reach the CBD. Or you can travel north to Coburg and Preston. You can also walk to shops, cafes, restaurants etc in Sydney Road nearby, and some great restaurants nearby in Lygon St..

In the event that any additional persons stay at the property, an additional fee may be charged according to our usual rates and/or we reserve the right to terminate the booking without refund. •If pets are entering the property or staying at the property (only allowable for pet friendly properties), this must be disclosed at the time of booking, or we reserve the right to terminate
host_about:
I have owned two other service businesses since 1998. I started StayCentral with one apartment in 2005, and now manage multiple properties in many different locations in inner Melbourne.

Like many of my guests, I love to travel; both overseas to places like the Mulu Caves in Borneo, ancient cities (in many old countries), Antarctica & Alaska, Torres del Paine, and colourful markets in amazing places like Pha Long in Vietnam, Jaisalmer in India, & La Paz in Bolivia. I also love short domestic trips for weekends away just to relax. It means I get to be on the other side of the counter, and experience how other people look after their guests: and I take their good ideas back with me. 

(My manager, Max, has also travelled from afar to be here by the way, and he can also speak with our guests in Russian and Ukranian).

I even worked as a part-time tourist guide in Melbourne for a couple of years, and really enjoyed the interactions with the tourists off the huge cruise liners that appear in Melbourne each spring and summer. I have tried to extend this experience into my accommodation business here at home, where I really love assisting people with their stays. You only need to read the 800 plus reviews on Airbnb, Trip advisor, Goo gle, and on my own StayCentral website to realise how much our guests enjoy our apartments, and the way we look after them. 

I do love living in Melbourne. It enjoys a unique place in Australia. It is often described as the cultural, business, shopping and sporting capital of the country. The restaurants and cafes in Melbourne are amongst the best in the world. I love living in an urban village amongst these, and all the other everyday shops; and jumping on a tram and avoiding the hassles of traffic. It is a city of great opportunity, experiences, events and lifestyle that can be enjoyed by locals and visitors alike; and I really enjoy facilitating our guests' stays here.

I do hope I have the opportunity to help you get to know Melbourne and grow to love it as I have.

name: Comfortable light-filled home
summary: Our two bedroom, two lounge-room home is in a quiet tree-lined street, conveniently located to parks, bike trails and funky High Street. Just a stone's throw from public transport, we are close to all the action while enjoying a quiet neighbourhood and peaceful garden setting.
space: There's plenty of space with 2 bedrooms - one with a queen bed, the other with a double bed.  There are also two lounge-rooms.  The large main lounge-room has a northerly sunny  aspect and overlooks a leafy garden. The second lounge room  has a  tuned piano and 2nd TV. As a two bedroom house, it is best suited to 4 people. However, a fifth person can be accommodated on a mattress in one of the loungerooms, or in one of the bedrooms.  We can fit this with sheets, blankets and pillow.  During the period of your stay there will be a tenant living in the backyard studio.  Access to the studio is from the pathway down the side of the house to get to the back garden. The studio is an entirely separate area from the house and is screened from the house by use of a timber screen.  The garden, however, is a shared space.  Note:  The timber privacy screen is not shown in the listing for the house but can be seen in the studio listing. (See "studio apartment in garden setting")

neighborhood_overview: Northcote is a fantastic inner city suburb with lots of character. It has an exciting strip-shopping area in High Street dotted with bars, coffee shops and eateries. Our area is just a five minute walk to High Street, close to Westgarth Village and Northcote Hill. We are only three minutes walk from North Fitzroy and the Merri Creek which hosts the Merri Creek bike trail, meandering around the adjoining suburbs and then connecting to the Yarra Trail and on to the city.
notes: We have lived in our house for nearly 30 years.  We think its beautiful, but don't expect perfect!  You will find some scratches, smudges and chips on the surfaces but it will be clean, cheery and comfortable!
transit: Northcote is crisscrossed with lots of public transport including two tram lines, two train lines and numerous bus routes. Our nearest rail station is Merri station on the Mernds line. The train goes to the city via Clifton Hill Station, The no 112 tram route, at the end of our street, goes to the city via famous Brunswick Street. Our preferred method is by bike through the Edinburgh Gardens and Napier Street, Fitzroy.
access: Guests have access to all rooms except for a third locked bedroom which we will use as a storage area but will not need to access while you are staying in the house. There will be empty wardrobe space in both bedrooms for your use. Guests can help themselves to any food in the pantry or cupboards.
interaction: We can be contacted by email and will reply promptly.
house_rules: No smoking inside the house please - outside is fine.  No parties. We love our piano and request you do not put drinks on it.  There may be a small fluffy dog on the property but he will keep out of your way if that's your preference. Our air-conditioner is  in the back part of the house. We ask guests to be respectful with energy use, and operate the AC only when in the house, and never leave it running when the house is unoccupied.
host_about: We love living in Melbourne, home to good food, music and bike trails.  We love Northcote for its eclectic music scene and vibrant High Street.   We are both cyclists and enjoy taking advantage of the many wonderful bicycle paths in Melbourne, and most weekends we are out riding.  When we're not in Melbourne, we're finding new places to explore on our bikes.

neighborhood_overview: There are plenty of cafes, restaurants, everyday shops, great pubs and supermarket on your doorstep. Nearby, the never-ending walking and bike paths wrap around Port Phillip Bay and it's continuous beaches. To the right you will find Station Pier (where the Spirit of Tasmania and the huge cruise liners dock) and several great sea-side restaurants and hotels, and Beacon Cove. To the left you will find some of the most stunning seaside homes, both historic and trendy, along the walk to St Kilda Point.
notes: Guests will be asked to acknowledge acceptance of StayCentral Terms & Conditions and House rules, and may be asked to provide photo ID on arrival. The location is ideal. 5 minutes to the CBD, walking distance to the beach. Plenty of cafes and restaurants on the street below. The furniture is modern, stylish and comfortable. No expense has been spared in terms of attention to detail. host_about:
I have owned two other service businesses since 1998. I started StayCentral with one apartment in 2005, and now manage multiple properties in many different locations in inner Melbourne.

Like many of my guests, I love to travel; both overseas to places like the Mulu Caves in Borneo, ancient cities (in many old countries), Antarctica & Alaska, Torres del Paine, and colourful markets in amazing places like Pha Long in Vietnam, Jaisalmer in India, & La Paz in Bolivia. I also love short domestic trips for weekends away just to relax. It means I get to be on the other side of the counter, and experience how other people look after their guests: and I take their good ideas back with me. 

(My manager, Max, has also travelled from afar to be here by the way, and he can also speak with our guests in Russian and Ukranian).

I even worked as a part-time tourist guide in Melbourne for a couple of years, and really enjoyed the interactions with the tourists off the huge cruise liners that appear in Melbourne each spring and summer. I have tried to extend this experience into my accommodation business here at home, where I really love assisting people with their stays. You only need to read the 800 plus reviews on Airbnb, Trip advisor, Goo gle, and on my own StayCentral website to realise how much our guests enjoy our apartments, and the way we look after them. 

I do love living in Melbourne. It enjoys a unique place in Australia. It is often described as the cultural, business, shopping and sporting capital of the country. The restaurants and cafes in Melbourne are amongst the best in the world. I love living in an urban village amongst these, and all the other everyday shops; and jumping on a tram and avoiding the hassles of traffic. It is a city of great opportunity, experiences, events and lifestyle that can be enjoyed by locals and visitors alike; and I really enjoy facilitating our guests' stays here.

I do hope I have the opportunity to help you get to know Melbourne and grow to love it as I have.
